INSERT INTO `Directori` VALUES (16,13,0,'José ','Aguilera Avila','Professor','M2 118','','+34 935 811 673','jose.aguilera@uab.cat','<p>\n	Department of Biochemistry and Molecular Biology<br />\n	<em>Institut de Neuroci&egrave;ncies</em><br />\n	Faculty&nbsp; of Medicine (room M2-118 and director office M1/103)<br />\n	<em>Universitat Aut&ograve;noma de Barcelona (UAB)</em><br />\n	Bellaterra Campus 08193-Cerdanyola del Vall&eacute;s</p>\n','16DSC00858web.jpg','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	Jos&eacute; Aguilera started his scientific career as a PhD student in the laboratory of Professor Fran&ccedil;esc Gonz&aacute;lez-Sastre (Dpt. Biochemistry and Molecular Biology, <em>Universitat Aut&ograve;noma de Barcelona</em>; UAB) and received the PhD degree en 1984. After PhD, he completed his training in Neurochemistry at The Weizmann Institute of Science (WIS, Rehovot; Israel) under the supervision of Professor Ephraim Yavin (1988-1989) and at Food and Drug Administration (FDA, Bethesda, MA; USA) under the supervision of Professor William H. Habig (1999-2000). In both laboratories he developed the research concerning to Clostridial Neurotoxin Receptors and its Signal Transduction Mechanisms. He was awarded a staff position in the Department of Biochemistry and Molecular Biology of the UAB as Professor (1992), But run his own laboratory and his research projects from 1984 even as Research Assistant. His laboratory is part of a Group of the CIBERNED (Spanish Center for Translational Research in Neurodegenerative Diseases) and is part of the Biomedical Research Group in Neurodegeneration (SGR2014-0984). During all these years at UAB, He has also been engaged with academic activities, besides teaching at undergraduate and graduate levels, and he had directed dozen of doctoral thesis.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	It will like to remark his appointment as Director of the Department of Biochemistry and Molecular Biology (2002-2007) and as Director of the <em>Institut de Neuroci&egrave;ncies</em> (INc) of the UAB from 2009 until now. His is member of: <em>Claustro de la UAB</em>, <em>Comisi&oacute;n de Econom&iacute;a de la UAB</em>, Member of the <em>Junta de personal docente Investigador</em> (JPDI) <em>de la UAB, &hellip;</em></p>\n','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	He now studies the pharmacological potential of the most unexplored member of the family, tetanus toxin, and, especially, of the non-toxic C-terminal-fragment of its heavy chain (Hc-TeTx). He demonstrated that Hc-TeTx, due to its characteristics of binding, internalization and retroaxonal transport, can be used as a putative neuroprotector in neurodegenerative diseases. But he last invention relates to a cyclic peptide that inhibits the binding of&nbsp;clostridium neurotoxins to neurons, and therefore is useful in the prophylaxis and/or treatment of the diseases caused by these neurotoxins, this invention could represent the only specific treatment to tetanus and botulism.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PATENTS</strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n		Name: Peptide for use in the treatment of disease caused by Clostridium neurotoxins. Inventors / authors / obtainers: Thomas Scior, Ana Candalija, Jos&eacute; Aguilera. Patent holding body: Universitat Aut&ograve;noma de Barcelona (Spain) and Benem&eacute;rita Universidad Aut&oacute;noma de Puebla (M&eacute;xico). Date of receipt: 21<sup>th</sup> September <strong>2015</strong>. Application number EP15186045.9</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n		Name: Therapeutic use of the encoding sequence of the carboxy-terminal domain of the heavy chain of the tetanus toxin. Inventors / authors / obtainers: Jos&eacute; Aguilera, Mar&iacute;a Moreno Igoa, Ana Cristina Calvo Royo, Mar&iacute;a Jes&uacute;s Mu&ntilde;oz Gonzalvo, Pilar Zaragoza, Rosario Ostas Pinzolas.Patent holding body: Universitat Aut&ograve;noma de Barcelona and Universidad de Zaragoza Application number: 12/754,552. Priority country: United States of America and Europe. Date: 5<sup>th</sup> April <strong>2010.</strong> Transferred to Ferrer International, Janus Development and Bioesferium (ALS-TTC Biotech).</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n		Name: Empleo de un polip&eacute;ptido que comprende el dominio C-terminal de la cadena pesada de la toxina tet&aacute;nica en el tratamiento del parkinsonismo. Inventors / authors / obtainers: Jos&eacute; Aguilera. Patent holding body: Universitat Aut&ograve;noma de Barcelona. Application number: 200600312. Priority country: Spain. Date: 20<sup>th</sup> January <strong>2006</strong>.</li>\n</ul>\n','<p>\n	See all J. Aguilera publications at <a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830283/public/\" target=\"_blank\">PubMed</a>.</p>\n<p>\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>SELECTED PUBLICATIONS</strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		Patricio-Mart&iacute;nez A,&nbsp;Mendieta L,&nbsp;Mart&iacute;nez I,&nbsp;Aguilera&nbsp;J,&nbsp;Lim&oacute;n ID. <em>The recombinant C-terminal fragment of tetanus toxin protects against cholinotoxicity by intraseptal injection of &beta;-amyloid peptide (25-35) in rats.</em> Neuroscience.&nbsp;<strong>2016 </strong>Feb 19;315:18-30. doi: 10.1016/j.neuroscience.2015.11.066. Epub 2015 Dec 11.</li>\n	<li>\n		Candalija A, Cub&iacute; R,&nbsp;Ortega A, Aguilera J, and Gil C. <em>Trk receptors need neutral sphingomyelinase activity to promote cell viability. </em>FEBS Letters<strong>2014</strong>, 588: 167-174. (ISSN 0014-5793, Elsevier)</li>\n	<li>\n		Mart&iacute;nez D, Garc&iacute;a L, Aguilera J and Ortega A. <em>An acute Glutamate exposure induces long-term down regulation of GLAST/EAAT1 uptake activity in cultured Bermann glia cells. </em>Neurochemistry Research (In press <strong>2014</strong>).</li>\n	<li>\n		Balderas A., Guillem A.M., Mart&iacute;nez-Lozada Z., Hern&aacute;ndez-Kelly L.C., Aguilera J. and Ortega A. <em>GLAST/EAAT1 regulation in cultured Bergmann glia cells: Role of the NO/cGMP signalling pathway. </em>Neurochemistry International, In press<strong>2014</strong>(ISSN 0197-0186, Elsevier BV, Netherlands &ndash; Scopus 2009: 74/303)</li>\n	<li>\n		Cub&iacute; R, Matas L.A., Pou M. , Aguilera J. and C. Gil. <em>Differencial sensitivity to detergents of actin cytoskeleton from nerve endings. </em>Biochimica et Biophysica Acta (Biomembranes) 1828: 2385-2393,<strong>2013</strong>(ISSN 0005-2736, Elsevier)</li>\n	<li>\n		Cub&iacute; R, Candalija A, Matas L.A., Ortega A., Gil C. and J. Aguilera. <em>Tetanus toxin Hc fragment induces the formation of ceramide platforms and protects neuronal cells against oxidative stress. </em>Plot One 8 (6): e68055, <strong>2013</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n','<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0002-9906-8034\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"27\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/orcid.png\" width=\"27\" /></a></td>\n			<td>\n				&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=6507775989\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 29px; height: 29px;\" /></a></td>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"http://www.researchgate.net/profile/Jose_Aguilera3/publications\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"26\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/researchgate.jpg\" width=\"26\" /></a></td>\n			<td>\n				&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>\n				&nbsp;</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n'),(18,13,0,'Laura ','Aldavert Vera',NULL,'B5/049','Facultat de Psicologia','+34 935 812 543','laura.aldavert@uab.cat',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'<p>\n	See all L. Aldavert publication at <a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/49050461/public/\" target=\"_blank\">PubMed</a>.</p>\n',NULL),(20,10,0,'Beatriz ','Almolda Ardid',NULL,'M5 107','Facultat de Medicina','+34 935 811 826','beatriz.almolda@uab.cat',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(21,14,0,'Isabella ','Appiah','Research Assistant','M5 105','','+34 935 811 826','isabella.appiah@uab.cat','<p>\n	Laboratory of Histology<br />\n	<em>Institut de Neuroci&egrave;ncies</em><br />\n	Faculty&nbsp; of Medicine (room M1-108 and M5-107)<br />\n	<em> <em>Universitat Aut&ograve;noma de Barcelona (UAB)</em><br />\n	Bellaterra Campus 08193-Cerdanyola del Vall&eacute;s</em></p>\n','','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	2005 I obtained my Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree in Biology, University of Belgrade and 2011 I received&nbsp;my PhD in Biology at the Institute for Biological Research &ldquo;Sinisa Stankovic&rdquo;, University of Belgrade.&nbsp;Since 2008 I am working as a Research Assistant of Dr Bernardo Castellano&rsquo;s group at the <em>Institut de Neuroci&egrave;ncies</em> (INc) and 2015 I also became Research Assistant at the Core Histology Lab of INc.</p>\n','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	I have previously worked in the field of Pharmacology, within which I performed my PhD on the role of reactive oxygen species and mechanisms of ion channels in myometrial activity. Since 2008 I have been involved here at the Institute of Neuroscience (INc), as a Research Assistant in the group of Dr Bernardo Castellano. In the numerous projects studying the role of microglial cells in the control of the immune responses associated to different types of lesions in the central nervous system as well as in the development of neonates, I worked on establishing transgenic mice lines for these studies as well as performing stereotaxic surgeries, tissue sample preparation for microscopy, including, animal perfusions, tissue isolation, cryotomy, microtomy and immunohistochemical studies. Since 2015 I have also become Research Assistant at the Laboratory of Histology of the INc. Here I am giving support to INc&rsquo;s and external research community in all previously mentioned techniques as well as in Luminex multiplex protein bioassays.</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n','<p>\n	<strong><span style=\"color:#800000;\">Authorship</span></strong></p>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		I Appiah, A Nikolic-Kokic, Z Orescanin-Dusic, R Radojicic, S Milovanovic, M Spasic, and D Blagojevic., Reversible Oxidation of Myometrial Voltage-Gated Potassium Channels with Hydrogen Peroxide, Oxidative Medicine and Cellular Longevity, 2012: 7 (2012)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\n	<li>\n		I Appiah, S Milovanovic, R Radojicic, A Nikolic-Kokic, Z Orescanin-Dusic, M Slavic, S Trbojevic, R Skrbic, MB Spasic and D Blagojevic. Hydrogen peroxide affects contractile activity and anti-oxidant enzymes in rat uterus. British Journal of Pharmacology, 158, 1932-1941 (2009)</li>\n	<li>\n		Ore&scaron;čanin-Du&scaron;ić Z , Milovanović S, Radojičić R, Nikolić-Kokić A, Appiah I, Slavić M, Čutura N, Trbojević S, Spasić MB, Blagojević D. Effects of protamine sulphate on spontaneous and calcium-induced contractile activity in the rat uterus are potassium channels-mediated. Gen. Physiol. Biophys. Special Issue, 28, 143&ndash;148 (2009)</li>\n	<li>\n		Slavic M, Appiah I, Nikolic-Kokic A, Radojicic R, Jones DR, Spasic MB, Milovanovic S, Blagojevic D: The anti-oxidative defence system in the isolated rat uterus during spontaneous rhythmic activity. Acta Physiologica Hungarica, 93 (4), 335-339 (2006)</li>\n</ul>\n<p style=\"margin-left:36.0pt;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>Acknowledgments</strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		Villacampa N, Almolda B, Vilella A, Campbell I, Gonz&aacute;lez B, Castellano B. Astrocyte-targeted production of il-10 induces changes in microglial reactivity and reduces motor neuron death after facial nerve axotomy. Glia 00:0-0, doi:10.1002/glia.22807 (2015)</li>\n	<li>\n		Almolda, B., de Labra, C., Barrera, I., Gruart, A., Delgado-Garcia, J.M., Villacampa, N., Vilella, A., Hofer, M.J., Hidalgo, J., Campbell, I.L., Gonz&aacute;lez, B., Castellano, B., Alterations in microglial phenotype and hippoc