"https://es.linkedin.com/pub/isabella-appiah/8/471/126\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Linkedin.jpg\" style=\"width: 35px; height: 29px;\" /></a></td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n'),(22,13,0,'Antonio','Armario García',NULL,'C2 035','Facultat de Biociències','+34 935 811 840','antonio.armario@uab.cat',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'<p>\n	See all Antonio Armario publication at <a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830297/public/\" target=\"_blank\">PubMed.</a></p>\n',NULL),(25,14,0,'Núria ','Barba Bosch',NULL,'M1 108','Facultat de Medicina','+34 935 812 733','nuria.barba@uab.cat',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(28,13,0,'Carlos','Barcia González','Tenure Track Professorship','M2 107.1','','+34 935 814 116','carlos.barcia@uab.cat','<p>\n	Department of Biochemistry and Molecular Biology<br />\n	<em>Institut de Neuroci&egrave;ncies</em><br />\n	Faculty&nbsp; of Medicine (room M2-107.1)<br />\n	<em>Universitat Aut&ograve;noma de Barcelona (UAB)</em><br />\n	Bellaterra Campus 08193-Cerdanyola del Vall&eacute;s</p>\n','28retoc_barcia_tamanyok.jpg','<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>ROLES AND RESPONSIBILITIES</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	Ram&oacute;n Y Cajal Tenure Track Professor and Researcher<br />\n	Mentor of the Master&rsquo;s Degree in Neuroscience<br />\n	Advisor at the PhD Neuroscience Program<br />\n	Group Leader, <a href=\"http://inc.uab.cat/English/index.php#!/Carlos%20BARCIA%20GONZ%C3%81LEZ_664_1\"><span style=\"color:#000000;\"><strong>Neuro-immunity</strong></span></a> Research Group</p>\n','<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>RESEARCH INTERESTS</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	The investigation that we are currently developing is focused on the immune responses in the brain. Non-neuronal cells, such as glial cells and brain- infiltrated blood cells are critically involved in the local resolution of brain injuries, covering neurodegenerative diseases and many other insults, including brain tumors. Our research interest is to unravel, at the cellular level, the function of glia and lymphocytes within the inflamed brain, and, particularly, the communication and interactions that take place between immune cells and other target cells.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<br />\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>CURRENT WORK</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<ol>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n		<em>Parkinson&rsquo;s disease:</em> We aim to understand the interactions between microglial cells and dopaminergic neurons in experimental models of Parkinson&rsquo;s disease. The knowledge of these complex interfaces <em>in vivo</em> and <em>in vitro</em> will help to propose therapeutic anti-inflammatory strategies to avert or decelerate Parkinsonian degeneration.<br />\n		&nbsp;</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n		<em>Glioma: </em>Our goal is to explore in depth the microenvironments of human glioma samples (a collaborative project with the Neurosurgery Department of the General Hospital of Valencia), and analyze experimental models <em>in vivo</em> and <em>in vitro</em>, in order to understand the function of immune cells, microglia-macrophages and lymphocytes, to achieve tumor clearance. The outcome of this project will suggest novel strategies for immunotherapy.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n','<p>\n	See all Carlos Barcia&nbsp; publications at <a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830637/public/\" target=\"_blank\">PubMed</a>.</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>SELECTED PUBLICATIONS- Last 10 years</strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		Mitxitorena I, Saavedra E, Barcia C. Kupfer-type Immunological Synapses in vivo: Raison D&#39;&ecirc;tre of SMAC. Immunology &amp; Cell Biology. 2015. Immunol Cell Biol. 2015 ;93(1):51-56.</li>\n	<li>\n		Barcia C, Ros