;\"><strong>TEACHING</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	Degree: Medicine, Speech &amp; Language Therapy, Nursery</p>\n<p>\n	MS: Master in Neuroscience</p>\n','<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>RESEARCH INTERESTS</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong>Mechanisms of neurodegeneration vs endogenous neuroprotection after axonal injury or disease progression </strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	Using the motor neuron as the main neuronal model due to its ease accessibility in vivo, our particular interest is focus in getting an integrative view of molecular programs involved in several physiological and physiopathological processes. In particular, we are interesting in providing an integrative view to define the cellular and molecular mechanisms that account to motor neurons when degenerate, regenerate or suffering after synaptic disconnection, disease or by traumatic axotomy. Some particular molecular signaling cascades have been detailed analyzed, such as autophagy or the response to endoplasmic reticulum stress, as part of the endogenous neuroprotective program commonly triggered after axonal injury of motor neurons although often deficient. Finding out why these endogenous mechanisms of neuroprotection turn out underprovided is a major interest. We have recently performed an unbiased proteomic study coupled to a system biology analysis to decipher these mechanisms. We aim to provide insight and develop novel therapeutic strategies and biotherapies for motoneurodegenerative processes.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PATENTS</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<em>-NEW COMBINATION THERAPIES FOR TREATING NERVOUS SYSTEM DISEASES</em><br />\n	Mireia Coma, Patrick Aloy, Albert Pujol, Jos&eacute; Manuel Mas, CATALINA CASAS LOUZAO, Mireia Herrando-Grabulosa, Xavier Navarro, Jordi Naval<br />\n	Num. 61/754,186- February 2013</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	ANAXOMICS SL</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<em>-USE OF VALPROATE FOR REDUCING CHOP LEVELS, PARTICULARLY IN A MAMMAL HAVING SCI</em><br />\n	CATALINA CASAS LOUZAO, Clara Penas, Xavier Navarro, Enrique Verdu<br />\n	Num. EP08382062.1- October 2008</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	Universitat Aut&ograve;noma de Barcelona</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	-<em>UTILIZACI&Oacute;N DE VALPROATO PARA EL TRATAMIENTO DEL MIEDO Y LA FOBIA EN SUJETOS CON LA ENFERMEDAD DE ALZHEIMER</em><br />\n	Carlos Alberto Saura Antol&iacute;n, CATALINA CASAS LOUZAO, Lydia Gimenez Llort, Judith Espa&ntilde;a Agust&iacute;<br />\n	Num. 200703252- December 2007</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	Universitat Aut&ograve;noma de Barcelona</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<em>-ANIMAUX TRANSGENIQUES PRESENT DES TROUBLES MAJEURS LIES A LA MALADIE D&#39;ALZHEIMER&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\n	&nbsp; TRANSGENIC ANIMALS EXHIBITING MAJOR DISORDERS RELATED TO ALZHEIMER&#39;S DISEASE<br />\n	CATALINA CASAS LOUZAO, Patrick Benoit, Laurent Pradier, Jean-Michel Itier</em><br />\n	Num. FR20030011578- October 2003</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	AVENTIS- PHARMA</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n','<p>\n	See all Caty Casas&nbsp; publications at <a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830650/public/\" target=\"_blank\">PubMed.</a></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>RELEVANT AND RECENT LIST OF PUBLICATIONS</strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		Casas, C., Isus, L., Herrando-Grabulosa, M., Mancuso, F. M., Borr&aacute;s, E., Sabid&oacute;, E., For&eacute;s J., Aloy, P. (2015). Network-based proteomic approaches reveal the neurodegenerative, neuroprotective and pain-related mechanisms involved after retrograde axonal damage. Scientific Reports, <em>5</em>, 9185.</li>\n	<li>\n		Casas C, Manzano R, Vaz R, Osta R, Brites D. (2015) Synaptic Failure: Focus in an Integrative View of ALS. Br