ps and the periods as research assistant and technician of the INc&rsquo;s Histology core facility, I have gained extensive experience in the field of Nervous tissue obtaining, processing and demonstration of different markers by means of varied techniques.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	For more details you can check: <a href=\"http://inc.uab.cat/English/index.php#!/Histology_362_1\" target=\"_blank\">Core facilities-Histology</a></p>\n','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	As technician, Mar I have collaborated with the research of many groups of the INc, training of theMaster and PhD in Neuroscience students as well as participated in educational activities for schools.</p>\n','<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0001-8176-1976\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/orcid.png\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"http://www.researcherid.com/rid/C-9239-2011\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/RID.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=55393860200\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n			<td>\n				&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>\n				&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>\n				&nbsp;</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n'),(43,13,0,'Enrique','Claro Izaguirre',NULL,'M2 114','Facultat de Medicina','+34 935 814 150','enrique.claro@uab.cat',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'<p>\n	See all E. Claro publication at <a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830780/public/\" target=\"_blank\">PubMed</a>.</p>\n',NULL),(44,13,0,'Victòria','Clos Guillèn',NULL,'M4 104','','+34 935 811 963','victoria.clos@uab.cat',NULL,'44victoriaclos2.jpg',NULL,NULL,'<p>\n	See all V. Clos publication at <a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830631/public/\" target=\"_blank\">PubMed</a>.</p>\n',NULL),(46,13,0,'Margalida','Coll Andreu','Professor and researcher in Psychobiology- Coordinator Master in Neurosciences','B5 047','','+34 935 811 173','margalida.coll@uab.cat','<p>\n	Department of Psychobiology and Methodology of Health Science<br />\n	<em>Institut de Neuroci&egrave;ncies</em><br />\n	Faculty&nbsp; of Psychology (room B5-047)<br />\n	<em>Universitat Aut&ograve;noma de Barcelona (UAB)</em><br />\n	Bellaterra Campus 08193-Cerdanyola del Vall&eacute;s</p>\n','46MColl-fitxa2.jpg','<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>TEACHING TASKS</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	Degree in Psychology<br />\n	Master in Neuroscience<br />\n	Master in Disorders of Communication and Language</p>\n','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>RESEARCH INTERESTS</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	My research interests are focused on the neural bases of memory modulation in order to find treatments capable of improving memory processes in healthy animals, and reducing memory deficits in animals with brain damage.&nbsp; I have studied the role of thalamocortical and brainstem structures (thalamic reticular nucleus, pedunculopontine tegmental nucleus), and the hormone epinephrine, on memory modulation.&nbsp; In the last years I have focused my research on studying the efficacy of physical exercise and certain pharmacological treatments to reduce memory deficits in animals with traumatic brain injury (TBI).</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>CURRENT WORK</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	In human patients TBI usually leads to long-term sequels in a variety of domains, and there is also evidence that it increases susceptibility to neurodegenerative disorders, with the subsequent personal, social and economical burden. In this setting, I am currently working in a research group leaded by dr. Isabel Portell and focused on the study of the efficacy of physical exercise, either alone or combined with pharmacological treatments, to reduce the memory deficits in a rat model of TBI. Our research group is also interested in investigating whether the benefits of physical exercise on cognition are mediated by neuroprotective (reduction of neuronal death, myelin loss, etc), and neuroreparative (increased cell proliferation and neurogenesis, enhanced expression of plasticity-related molecules, etc) mechanisms. Additionally, the potential of physical exercise to prevent the increased susceptibility to neurodegenerative diseases associated to TBI is also being investigated. In the middle term it is expected that the achievement of these goals through animal research will aid in designing and implementing appropriate physical exercise treatment schedules that might alleviate some of the sequels of TBI in human patients.</p>\n','<p>\n	See all Margalida Coll Andreu publications at <a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/49032210/public/\" target=\"_blank\">PubMed</a>.</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>SELECTED PUBLICATIONS</strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		Jacotte-Simancas, A.; Costa-Miserachs, D.; Coll-Andreu, M.; Torras-Garcia, M:, Borlongan, C.V.; Portell-Cort&eacute;s, I. (2015) Effects of voluntary physical exercise, citicoline, and combined treatment on object recognition memory, neurogenesis, and neuroprotection after traumatic brain injury in rats. <em>Journal of Neurotrauma</em>, 15, 32(10):739-51.</li>\n	<li>\n		Amor&oacute;s-Aguilar L, Portell-Cort&eacute;s I, Costa-Miserachs D, Torras-Garcia M, Coll-Andreu M. Traumatic brain injury in late adolescent rats: effects on adulthood memory and anxiety. <em>Behavioral Neuroscience</em>. 2015, 129(2):149-59.</li>\n	<li>\n		Jacotte-Simancas, A.; Costa-Miserachs, D.; Torras-Garcia, M., Coll-Andreu, M.; Portell-Cort&eacute;s, I.. (2013). Effects of voluntary physical exercise and post-training epinephrine on acquisition in a spatial task in the Barnes maze. <em>Behavioural Brain Research, </em>247<em>, 178-181</em></li>\n	<li>\n		Jurado-Berbel, P.; Costa-Miserachs, D.; Torras-Garcia, M.; Coll-Andreu, M.; Portell-Cort&eacute;s, I. (2010). Standard object recognition memory and &ldquo;what&rdquo; and &ldquo;where&rdquo; components: Improvement by post-training epinephrine in highly habituated rats. <em>Behavioural Brain Research, <strong>207</strong>, 44-50.</em></li>\n	<li>\n		Garc&iacute;a-Capdevila, S.; Portell-Cort&eacute;s, I.; Torras-Garcia, M.; Coll-Andreu, M.; Costa-Miserachs, D. (2009). Effects of long-term voluntary exercise on learning and memory processes: dependency of the task and level of exercise. <em>Behavioural Brain Research, <strong>202</strong>, 162-170.</em></li>\n	<li>\n		Homs-Ormo, S.; Torras-Garcia, M.; Portell-Cort&eacute;s, I.; Edo-Izquierdo, S.; Morgado-Bernal, I.; Coll-Andreu, M. (2007). Effects of posttraining damage to the pedunculopontine tegmental nucleus on conditioned stimulus transfer in two-way active avoidance in rats. <em>Behavioral Neuroscience, <strong>121</strong>, 411-421.</em></li>\n	<li>\n		Andero, R.; Torras-Garc&iacute;a, M.; Quiroz-Padilla, M.F.; Costa-Miserachs, D.; Coll-Andreu, M. (2007). Electrical stimulation of the pedunculopontine tegmental nucleus in freely moving awake rats: time- and site-specific effects on two-way active avoidance. <em>Neurobiology of Learning and Memory, </em><strong>87</strong>: 510-521.</li>\n</ul>\n','<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"http://orcid.org. 0000-0003-4106-2606\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/orcid.png\" style=\"width: 26px; height: 26px;\" /></a></td>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"http://www.researcherid.com/rid/C-9119-2011\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/RID.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=6602648324\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 29px; height: 29px;\" /></a></td>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"http://www.researchgate.net/profile/Margalida_Coll-Andreu\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"27\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/researchgate.jpg\" width=\"27\" /></a></td>\n			<td>\n				&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>\n				&nbsp;</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n'),(48,14,0,'Gemma','Comes Orpinell',NULL,'C2 063','Facultat de Biociències','+34 935 811 664','gemma.comes@uab.cat',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(50,13,0,'David ','Costa Miserachs','Professor','B5 049','','+34 935 812 543','david.costa@uab.cat','<p>\n	Department of Psychobiology and Methodology of Health Science<br />\n	<em>Institut de Neuroci&egrave;ncies</em><br />\n	Faculty&nbsp; of Psychology (room B5-049)<br />\n	<em>Universitat Aut&ograve;noma de Barcelona (UAB)</em><br />\n	Bellaterra Campus 08193-Cerdanyola del Vall&eacute;s</p>\n','','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	David Costa-Miserachs received the Psychology degree in 1989 and the PhD in Psychology in 1993, both from the <em>Universitat Aut&ograve;noma de Barcelona (UAB)</em>. He completed his training at the University of Konstanz under the supervision of Professor J.D. Delius (1996) and got a tenured position in 1999 at the Department of Psychobiology and Methodology of Health Science at the UAB. In addition to his research and teaching role, he is actively involved in the dissemination of neuroscience.</p>\n','<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>RESEARCH INTERESTS</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	His research interests focus on the capacity of physical exercise to improve cognition in healthy subjects and to reduce cognitive deficits associated to brain injury.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>CURRENT WORK</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	His current work focuses on evaluating the temporal patterns of physical exercise that are able to reduce memory deficits, and the cellular and molecular mechanisms underlying the differential effects. The research group is also interested in studying whether TBI affects several biomarkers related to synaptic plasticity, neuroinflammation and neurodegenerative diseases, and to evaluate whether the observed effects might be reduced by physical exercise. He is also involved in a translational project aimed at the introduction of physical exercise as a treatment for cognitive rehabilitation in patients with traumatic brain injury.</p>\n','<p>\n	See all Costa-Miserachs, D publications at <a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/49049842/public/\" target=\"_blank\">PubMed.</a></p>\n<p>\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>SELECTED PUBLICATIONS</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"margin-left: 35.35pt; text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;Jacotte-Simancas, A.; Costa-Miserachs, D.; Coll-Andreu, M.; Torras-Garcia, M.; Borlongan, C.; Portell-Cort&eacute;s, I. (2015). Effects of voluntary physical exercise, citicoline, and combined treatment on object recognition memory, neurogenesis and neuroprotection after traumatic brain injury in rats. <em>Journal of Neurotrauma</em>, 32 (739-751).<br />\n	&bull;Amor&oacute;s-Aguilar, L.; Portell-Cort&eacute;s, I.; Costa-Miserachs, D.; Torras-Garcia, M.; &nbsp;Coll-Andreu, M. (2015). Traumatic Brain Injury in Late Adolescent Rats: Effects on Adulthood Memory and Anxiety. <em>Behavioral Neuroscience</em>, 129 (2), 149-159<br />\n	&bull;Jacotte-Simancas, A.; Costa-Miserachs, D.; Torras-Garcia, M., Coll-Andreu, M.; Portell-Cort&eacute;s, I. (2013). Effects of voluntary physical exercise and post-training epinephrine on acquisition in a spatial task in the Barnes maze. <em>Behavioural Brain Research, </em>247<em>, 178-181.</em><br />\n	&bull;Jurado-Berbel, P.; Costa-Miserachs, D.; Torras-Garcia, M.; Coll-Andreu, M.; Portell-Cort&eacute;s, I. (2010). Standard object recognition memory and &ldquo;what&rdquo; and &ldquo;where&rdquo; components: Improvement by post-training epinephrine in highly habituated rats. <em>Behavioural Brain Research, </em>207<em>, 44-50.</em><br />\n	&bull;Garc&iacute;a-Capdevila, S.; Portell-Cort&eacute;s, I.; Torras-Garcia, M.; Coll-Andreu, M.; Costa-Miserachs, D. (2009). Effects of long-term voluntary exercise on learning and memory processes: dependency of the task and level of exercise. <em>Behavioural Brain Research, </em>202<em>, 162-170.</em></p>\n','<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0001-5781-0774\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/orcid.png\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"http://www.researcherid.com/rid/E-1318-2011\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/RID.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.uri?authorId=6506703096\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"https://www.researchgate.net/profile/David_Costa-Miserachs\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/researchgate.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n			<td>\n				&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>\n				&nbsp;</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n'),(51,10,0,'James ','Dalton',NULL,'M3 206','Facultat de Medicina','+34 935 818 148','james.dalton@uab.cat',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(52,13,0,'Sònia ','Darbra Marges ',NULL,'B5 051','Facultat de Psicologia','+34 935 812 542','sonia.darbra@uab.cat',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(54,10,0,'Jaume ','Del Valle Macià','Postdoctoral Researcher','M4-114','Facultat de Medicina','+34 935 814 506','jaume.delvalle@uab.cat','<p>\n	Department of Cellular Biology, Physiology and Immunology<br />\n	<em>Institut de Neuroci&egrave;ncies</em><br />\n	Faculty of Medicine (room M4-114)<br />\n	<em>Universitat Aut&ograve;noma de Barcelona (UAB)</em><br />\n	Bellaterra Campus 08193-Cerdanyola del Vall&eacute;s</p>\n','54Joweb.jpg','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	Jaume&nbsp; del Valle is a Post-Doc in the Department of Cell Biology, Physiology and Immunology at Universitat Aut&ograve;noma de Barcelona. He finished his degree in Pharmacy at the university of Barcelona and obtained the PhD (2010) working with blood-brain barrier and Alzheimer&rsquo;s disease. After a short post-doc (2010-2012) in the same PhD working with neurodegeneration he moved to his current position in the Neuroplasticity and regeneration group to work with peripheral nerve regeneration and nerve interfaces for the control of neuroprostheses. With an H index of 13, he has contributed to more than 30 articles and to 2 book chapters.</p>\n','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	Working in the group of Neuroplasticity and Regeneration of the UAB (Universitat Aut&ograve;noma de Barcelona), my research focuses on different strategies to tackle peripheral nerve injuries. I am leading the program of nervous system interfaces by testing new electrodes and how they stimulate or record nerve activity, which is their selectivity and biocompatibility and providing feedback to improve their design to several European collaborators. Moreover, I am also interested in how to improve axon regeneration after peripheral nerve injury and different mechanisms to selectively promote subpopulations of nerve fibers.</p>\n','<p>\n	See all Jaume del Valle publications at <a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=del%20Valle%20J[auth]\" target=\"_blank\">PubMed</a>.</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>SELECTED PUBLICATIONS</strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		Cutrone, A., Del Valle, J., Santos, D., Badia, J., Filippeschi, C., Micera, S., Navarro, X., Bossi, S. A three-dimensional self-opening intraneural peripheral interface (SELINE). (2015) Journal of Neural Engineering, 12 (1)</li>\n	<li>\n		del Valle, J., Navarro, X. Interfaces with the peripheral nerve for the control of neuroprostheses. (2013) International Review of Neurobiology, 109, pp. 63-83.</li>\n	<li>\n		Torres-Esp&iacute;n, A., Santos, D., Gonz&aacute;lez-P&eacute;rez, F., del Valle, J., Navarro, X. Neurite-J: An Image-J plug-in for axonal growth analysis in organotypic cultures (2014) Journal of Neuroscience Methods, 236, pp. 26-39.</li>\n	<li>\n		Mancuso, R., Del Valle, J., Morell, M., Pall&aacute;s, M., Osta, R., Navarro, X. Lack of synergistic effect of resveratrol and sigma-1 receptor agonist (PRE-084) in SOD1G93A ALS mice: Overlapping effects or limited therapeutic opportunity? (2014) Orphanet Journal of Rare Diseases, 9 (1), 78</li>\n	<li>\n		Mancuso, R., del Valle, J., Modol, L., Martinez, A., Granado-Serrano, A.B., Ramirez-N&uacute;&ntilde;ez, O., Pall&aacute;s, M., Portero-Otin, M., Osta, R., Navarro, X. Resveratrol Improves Motoneuron Function and Extends Survival in SOD1G93A ALS Mice. (2014) Neurotherapeutics, 11 (2), pp. 419-432.</li>\n	<li>\n		Porquet, D., Gri&ntilde;&aacute;n-Ferr&eacute;, C., Ferrer, I., Camins, A., Sanfeliu, C., Del Valle, J., Pall&agrave;s, M. Neuroprotective role of trans-resveratrol in a murine model of familial alzheimer&#39;s disease. (2014) Journal of Alzheimer&#39;s Disease, 42 (4), pp. 1209-1220.</li>\n	<li>\n		Del Valle, J., Duran-Vilaregut, J., Manich, G., Casades&uacute;s, G., Smith, M.A., Camins, A., Pall&agrave;s, M., Pelegr&iacute;, C., Vilaplana, J. Early amyloid accumulation in the hippocampus of SAMP8 mice. (2010) Journal of Alzheimer&#39;s Disease, 19 (4), pp. 1303-1315.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n','<table height=\"25\" width=\"40\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0002-6703-8244\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/orcid.png\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n			<td>\n				&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=24491613900\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n			<td>\n				&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>\n				&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>\n				&nbsp;</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n'),(57,13,0,'Rosa Maria','Escorihuela Agulló',NULL,'M5 131','Facultat de Medicina','+34 935 813 296','rosamaria.escorihuela@uab.cat',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'<p>\n	See all RM. Escorihuela publication at <a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830790/public/\" target=\"_blank\">PubMed</a>.</p>\n',NULL),(60,21,0,'Olaya','Fernandez Gayol',NULL,'C2 031','Facultat de Biociències','+34 935 811 664','olaya.fernandez@uab.cat',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(61,13,0,'Ester ','Fernández Gimeno',NULL,'V0 129','Facultat de Veterinària','+34 935 813 282','ester.fernandez@uab.cat',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'<p>\n	See all E. Fern&aacute;ndez publication at <a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830799/public/\" target=\"_blank\">PubMed</a>.</p>\n',NULL),(62,14,0,'Isabel ','Fernandez Nicieza',NULL,'M1 104','Facultat de Medicina','+34 935 813 861','isabel.fernandez@uab.cat',NULL,'62DSC00871web.jpg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(63,13,0,'Alberto ','Fernández Teruel','Professor','M5 129','','+34 935 813 456','albert.fernandez.teruel@uab.cat','<p>\n	Department of Psychiatry and Legal Medicine<br />\n	<em>Institut de Neuroci&egrave;ncies</em><br />\n	Faculty&nbsp; of Medicine (room M5-129)<br />\n	<em>Universitat Aut&ograve;noma de Barcelona (UAB)</em><br />\n	Bellaterra Campus 08193-Cerdanyola del Vall&eacute;s</p>\n','63albert fernandez-teruel3.jpg','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	He received the Psychology degree in 1985 and a PhD in Psychology in 1989,&nbsp; both from the Autonomous University of Barcelona. He was working as a predoctoral (PhD) fellow in 1987 at the &ldquo;Istituto Biologico Policattedra&rdquo; (University of Cagliari, Italy), with professors MG. Corda, O. Giorgi and G. Biggio, as postdoctoral fellow at the &ldquo;Dipartimento di Biologia Sperimentale &lsquo;Bernardo Loddo&rsquo;&rdquo;&nbsp; (University of Cagliari, Italy) in 1991, and as a visiting professor at the&nbsp; ETH-Zentrum (Z&uuml;rich, Switzerland) in 1990 and 1994. He obtained a permanent position as Associate Professor of &nbsp;Psychopharmacology and Psychobiology at the University of Santiago de Compostela (Spain;&nbsp; 1996-1998), after which he obtained a permanent position as Associate Professor at the Department of Psychiatry &amp; Forensic Medicine, Autonomous University of Barcelona (UAB, Spain; 1998 to the present). Within this Department he is Coordinator of the Animal Research Laboratory and the &ldquo;Animal and human models of mental disorders&rdquo; research group (SGR). He has published over 125 peer-reviewed international scientific papers and over 30 spanish (non international) articles and book chapters, as well as 6 academic books.&nbsp; He has been awarded, among others, with the &ldquo;&lsquo;<em>Mart&iacute; i Juli&agrave;</em>&rsquo; award&nbsp; for research in Psychology and Psychiatry&rdquo; (<em>&ldquo;Institut d&rsquo;Estudis Catalans&rdquo;</em>) &nbsp;in 1988,&nbsp; the&nbsp; <em>&ldquo;1992 &lsquo;Ciutat the Barcelona Science Award&rsquo;&rdquo;</em>,&nbsp; and the &ldquo;ICREA-Academia 2013&rdquo; (ICREA, Catalan Institution for Research and Advanced Studies) award.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	He has been Partner Principal Investigator within two European research projects involving over 15 european (and USA) laboratories (the EURATools&nbsp; -2006-2010-&nbsp; and EURATRANS -2010-1014-&nbsp; projects).</p>\n','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	The research interests of his group along the last 25 years have focussed on the neurobiology and neurogenetics of anxiety and related processes (stress, depression, addiction, and others), as well as on brain aging, using rodent models.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	They have contributed to the development of novel and unique genetic tools for the high-resolution genetic mapping of complex traits, including biological disease-related phenotypes and behavioural/psychiatry-related traits.</p>\n','<p>\n	See all Alberto Fern&aacute;ndez-Teruel publications at <a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830803/public/\">Pubmed</a></p>\n<p>\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>SELECTED PUBLICATIONS</strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		Oliveras I, Crist&oacute;bal R&iacute;o-&Aacute;lamos, Toni Ca&ntilde;ete, Gloria Bl&aacute;zquez, Esther Mart&iacute;nez-Membrives, Osvaldo Giorgi, Maria G. Corda, Adolf Tobe&ntilde;a , FERNANDEZ-TERUEL A. (2015) Prepulse inhibition predicts spatial working memory performance in the inbred Roman high- and low-avoidance rats and in genetically heterogeneous NIH-HS rats: relevance for studying pre-attentive and cognitive anomalies in schizophrenia. <em>FRONT. &nbsp;BEHAV. &nbsp;NEUROSCI.</em>&nbsp; 18;9:213.</li>\n	<li>\n		R&iacute;o-Ȧlamos C, Ignasi Oliveras, Toni Ca&ntilde;ete, Gloria Bl&aacute;zquez, Esther Mart&iacute;nez-Membrives, Adolf Tobe&ntilde;a, FERNANDEZ-TERUEL A. (2015) Neonatal handling decreases unconditioned anxiety, conditioned fear, and improves two-way avoidance acquisition: a study with the inbred Roman high (RHA-I)- and low-avoidance (RLA-I) rats of both sexes. <em>FRONT. BEHAV. NEUROSCI.</em> &nbsp;10;9:174</li>\n	<li>\n		Tuncel J, Sabrina Haag, Anthony C.Y. Yau, Ulrika Norin, Amelie Baud, Erik L&ouml;nnblom, Klio&nbsp; Maratou, Jimmy Ytterberg, Diana Ekman, Soley Thordardottir, Martina Johannesson, Alan Gillett, EURATRANS Consortium, Pernilla Stridh, Maja Jagodic, Tomas Olsson, ALBERTO FERN&Aacute;NDEZ-TERUEL, Roman A. Zubarev, Richard Mott, Tim