f California in San Francisco (2001-2002; 2005-2006) and at the Institute of Biomedical Research of Barcelona (2000-2001). Gemma is also the principal investigator of a research group that has as its main objective, the evaluation of different treatments which could fundamentally enhance attention and memory processes in animal models of cognitive impairment.&nbsp; In addition, she has been involved in several outreach projects to disseminate public knowledge of Neuroscience.</p>\n','<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>RESEARCH INTEREST</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	Cognitive decline associated with aging and the increased incidence of neurodegenerative disorders are major challenges to modern public health. The effort in developing effective treatments to revert cognitive impairments entails the need to understand the neural mechanisms involved in cognitive processes and their enhancement.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>CURRENT WORK</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	By using rats of different ages, both young and old, the main goal of her present project is to study the effects that glutamate modulating treatments (via AMPA or NMDA receptors) have on learning and memory, as well as their underlying neurophysiologic substrates. Among the different strategies, she has focused her interest on chemical and deep brain electrical stimulation therapies. The research questions stated above are investigated through electrical stimulation, neurochemical lesions, intracerebral infusions, electrophysiological neuronal recordings, receptor autoradiography and in situ hybridization. The behavioral tasks are, among others, the social transmission of food preference, odor-reward discrimination, Morris water maze, visual attention and working memory tasks in the skinner-box.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>COLLABORATIONS</strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		Laboratorio de Psicobiolog&iacute;a, UNED, Madrid ( Dr. Ambrosio, Dr. Migu&eacute;ns)</li>\n	<li>\n		Divisi&oacute;n de Neurociencias, Universidad Pablo de Olavide (UPO), Sevilla (Dr. Delgado-Garc&iacute;a, Dra. Gruart)</li>\n	<li>\n		IDIBAPS (Barcelona) (Dra. S&aacute;nchez-Vives)</li>\n</ul>\n','<p>\n	See all Gemma Guillazo publications at <a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830176/public/\" target=\"_blank\">Pubmed.</a></p>\n','<table height=\"55\" width=\"198\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0002-8297-7100\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/orcid.png\" style=\"width: 26px; height: 26px;\" /></a></td>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"http://www.researcherid.com/rid/E-9765-2011\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/RID.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n			<td>\n				<p>\n					<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=6602654496\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 29px; height: 29px;\" /></a></p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"http://www.researchgate.net/profile/Gemma_Guillazo-Blanch\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"27\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/researchgate.jpg\" width=\"27\" /></a></td>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"http://www.mendeley.com/profiles/gemma-guillazo/\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"29\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/mendeley.png\" width=\"29\" /></a></td>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"https://es.linkedin.com/pub/gemma-guillazo-blanch/17/492/b85\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"31\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Linkedin.jpg\" width=\"39\" /></a></td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n'),(77,14,0,'Cristina','Gutierrez Salvador','Research Assistant','M2 130.2','','+34 935 814 828','cristina.gutierrez.salvador@uab.cat','<p>\n	Department of Biochemistry and Molecular Biology<br />\n	<em>Institut de Neuroci&egrave;ncies</em><br />\n	Faculty&nbsp; of Medicine (room M2-130.2)<br />\n	<em>Universitat Aut&ograve;noma de Barcelona (UAB)</em><br />\n	Bellaterra Campus 08193-Cerdanyola del Vall&eacute;s</p>\n','77DSC01041.JPG','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	Cristina Guti&eacute;rrez is a lab technician at INc&rsquo;s Cell Culture core facility</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	She earned her CFGS in Clinical Laboratory and CFGS in Pathological Anatomy and Cytology, and ended her degree in biochemistry at the UAB in 2013 while working already on the INc.<br />\n	<br />\n	After 3 years of work in the cell culture room of the department of biochemistry and molecular biology at the school of medicine at the UAB, in 2003, she began to manage the cell culture core facility in the beginnings of the foundation of INc until today.</p>\n','<p>\n	During these years she has gained extensive experience in the field of cell culture techniques in both neuronal and glial primary cultures and cell lines as well as other techniques associated with this area.</p>\n<p>\n	All these techniques have been used in studies carried out in the INc and outside, in many areas of neuroscience research such as cell signaling, inflammation, pharmacology, differentiation, biosensors...</p>\n','<p>\n	Cristina has contributed to the training of master students and PhD and providing support in their area of work in many groups of the<em> Institut de Neuroci&egrave;ncies.</em></p>\n<p>\n	<br />\n	She has also participated in educational sessions to school students about the research that is done in our institute.</p>\n<p>\n	For more information you can check our INc <a href=\"http://inc.uab.cat/English/index.php#!/Cell%20Culture_361_1\" target=\"_blank\">Cell Culture core facility webpage</a></p>\n','<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>\n				&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>\n				&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>\n				&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>\n				&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/pub/cristina-gutierrez-salvador/5b/26b/520?trk=pub-pbmap\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Linkedin.jpg\" style=\"width: 35px; height: 29px;\" /></a></td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n'),(78,10,0,'Joaquim','Hernandez Martín','Postdoctoral researcher','M4 117','','+34 935 814 506','joaquim.hernandez@uab.cat','<p>\n	Department of Cellular Biology, Physiology and Immunology<br />\n	<em>Institut de Neuroci&egrave;ncies</em><br />\n	Faculty of Medicine (room M4-117)<br />\n	<em>Universitat Aut&ograve;noma de Barcelona (UAB)</em><br />\n	Bellaterra Campus 08193-Cerdanyola del Vall&eacute;s</p>\n','78DSC00827web.jpg','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	Joaquim Hern&aacute;ndez is a Post-Doc in the Department of Cell Biology, Physiology and Immunology at Universitat Aut&ograve;noma of Barcelona (UAB). He earned a Bachelor of Science degree in Biology from Universitat Aut&ograve;noma of Barcelona in 1991 and received his PhD in Biology from Universitat Aut&ograve;noma of Barcelona in 1998.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	He went to London for a postdoctoral stage at National Blood Service and University College of London (Wolfson Institute for Biomedical Research) in the period 2003-2007. There, He focused in the study of stem cells in central nervous system and haematopoietic model.&nbsp; After this period, he moved in 2009 to his actual position in the Neuroplasticity and Regeneration Group (UAB) to work in cell therapy in spinal cord injury. He has contributed to more than 25 articles and to 1 book chapter.</p>\n',NULL,'<p>\n	See all Joaquim Hernandez Mart&iacute;n publications at Pubmed.</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>SELECTED PUBLICATIONS</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		Torres-Esp&iacute;n, A., Redondo-Castro, E., Hern&aacute;ndez, J. and Navarro, X