. L&oacute;pez obtained his PhD in Biological Sciences in1994 at Hospital Clinic i Provincial de Barcelona, Facultat de Medicina, Universitat de Barcelona. Then, he was a Postdoctoral Research Associate at University of California, Irvine, USA, in the laboratory of Dr. Timothy F. Osborne, working in the transcriptional control of cholesterol and fatty acid biosynthesis. Coming back to Spain he worked as Postdoctoral Research Associate at Departament de Ci&egrave;ncies Fisiol&ograve;giques Humanes i de la Nutrici&oacute;, Universitat de Barcelona, in the laboratory of Dr. Diego Haro; as Associate Professor at Departament de Ci&egrave;ncies Fisiol&ograve;giques II, Universitat de Barcelona in the laboratory of Dr. Joan Gil investigating cell death mechanisms for the treatment of Chronic Lymphocytic Leukemia; and as Postdoctoral Researcher Associate at Centro de Regulaci&oacute;n Gen&oacute;mica (CRG), in the laboratory of Ra&uacute;l Mendez, where he studied the mechanisms of translational control mediated by cytoplasmic polyadenylation. In 2004, he obtained a &ldquo;Ram&oacute;n y Cajal&rdquo; contract at <em>Institut de Neuroci&egrave;ncies</em>, Universitat Aut&ograve;noma de Barcelona, as a Group Leader. From 2011 he is Assistant Professor at Departament de Bioqu&iacute;mica i Biolog&iacute;a Molecular, Universitat Aut&ograve;noma de Barcelona, where he is teaching in the Medicine and Physiotherapy Degrees.</p>\n','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>RESEARCH INTERESTS</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	The overall objective of my group is to understand the mechanisms that regulate osmostress-induced apoptosis. We have reported that calpains and stress protein kinases regulate hyperosmotic shock-induced apoptosis, using <em>Xenopus</em> oocytes as a cell model. Now, we are investigating the role of different JNK and p38 isoforms in the regulation of osmostress-induced apoptosis. In addition, we have characterized <em>Xenopus</em> AMPK, a central regulator of cell metabolism, to study its role in apoptosis and meiosis.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PATENTS</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>L&oacute;pez JM,</strong>Campas C, Gil J.Novel therapeutic use of riboside of 5-aminoimidazole-4-carboxamide (acadesine).ES03/00130, WO 03/080076 A1, Universidad de Barcelona.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	Date: 21-3-2002.</p>\n','<p>\n	See all Jose Manuel Lopez Blanco publications at <a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830965/public/\" target=\"_blank\">PubMed</a>.</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>SELECTED PUBLICATIONS </strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n		<div>\n			Yue J, L&oacute;pez JM. <em>JNK does not regulate meiotic progression in</em>&nbsp;<em>Xenopus</em>&nbsp;<em>oocytes: The strange case of pJNK and pERK. </em>Dev Biol. 416: 42-51, 2016.</div>\n	</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n		<div>\n			Yue J, Ben Messaoud N, L&oacute;pez JM. <em>Hyperosmotic Shock Engages Two Positive Feedback Loops through Caspase-3-dependent Proteolysis of JNK1-2 and Bid. </em>J Biol Chem. 290: 30375-89, 2015.</div>\n	</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n		<div>\n			Ben Messaoud N, Katzarova I, L&oacute;pez JM. <em>Basic Properties of the p38 Signaling Pathway in Response to Hyperosmotic Shock. </em>PLoS One. doi: 10.1371/journal.pone.0135249, 2015.</div>\n	</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n		Ben Messaoud N, Yue J, Valent D, Katzarova I, L&oacute;pez JM. <em>Osmostress-induced apoptosis in Xenopus oocytes: role of stress protein kinases, calpains and Smac/DIABLO</em>. PLoS One. doi: 10.1371/journal.pone.0124482, 2015.</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n		L&oacute;pez JM.<em>Digital kinases: A cell model for sensing, integrating and making choices.</em> Communicative &amp; Integrative Biology. 3: 146-150,&nbsp;2010.</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n		Marti&aacute;&ntilde;ez T, Franc&egrave;s S, L&oacute;pez JM. <em>Generation of digital responses in stress sensors.&nbsp; </em>Journal of Biological Chemistry. 284: 23902-23911,&nbsp;2009.</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n		Piqu&eacute; M, L&oacute;pez JM, Sylvain F, Guig&oacute; R, M&eacute;ndez R. <em>A combinatorial code for CPE-mediated translational control. </em>Cell. 132: 434-448, 2008.</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n		Iglesias-Serret D, Piqu&eacute; M, Gil J, Pons G, L&oacute;pez JM.<em>Transcriptional and translational control of Mcl-1 during apoptosis.</em>Archives of Biochemistry and Biophysics. 417: 141-152, 2003.</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n		L&oacute;pez JM*, Camp&agrave;s C*, Barrag&aacute;n M, Bellosillo B, Colomer D, Gil J.<em>Acadesine activates AMPK and induces apoptosis in B-cell chronic lymphocytic leukemia cells but not in T lymphocytes.</em>Blood. 101: 3674-3680, 2003.*Both should be considered as first author.</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n		L&oacute;pez JM, Santidrian AF, Camp&agrave;s C, Gil J.<em>5-Aminoimidazole-4-carboxamide riboside induces apoptosis in Jurkat cells, but the AMP-activated protein kinase is not involved.</em>Biochemical Journal.370: 1027-1032, 2003.</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n		L&oacute;pez JM, Bombi JA, Valderrama R, Gim&eacute;nez A, Par&eacute;s A, Caballer&iacute;a J, Imperial S, Navarro S. <em>Ef</em><em>fects of prolonged ethanol intake and malnutrition on rat pancreas.</em>Gut. 38: 285-292, 1996.</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n		L&oacute;pez JM, Bennett MK, Sanchez HB, Rosenfeld JM, Osborne TF. Sterol regulation of acetyl CoA carboxylase provides a mechanism for coordinate control of cellular lipid. Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences of the United States of America. 93: 1049-1053, 1996.</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n		L&oacute;pez JM*, Bennett MK*, Sanchez HB, Osborne TF. <em>Sterol regulation of fatty acid synthase promoter: coordinate feedback regulation of two mayor lipid pathways.</em> Journal of Biological Chemistry. 270: 25578-25583, 1995. *Both should be considered as first author.</li>\n</ul>\n','<table>\n	<tbody>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0002-4104-6262\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"28\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/orcid.png\" width=\"28\" /></a></td>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"http://www.researcherid.com/rid/D-1654-2011\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"28\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/RID.jpg\" width=\"28\" /></a></td>\n			<td>\n				<p>\n					<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 29px; height: 29px;\" /></p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n				&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>\n				&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>\n				&nbsp;</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<table>\n	<tbody>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n'),(88,13,0,'Rubèn ','Lopez Valés','Associate Professor','M4 114','','+34 935 811 348','ruben.lopez@uab.cat','<p>\n	Department of Cellular Biology, Physiology and Immunology<br />\n	<em>Institut de Neuroci&egrave;ncies</em><br />\n	Faculty&nbsp; of Medicine (room M4-114)<br />\n	<em>Universitat Aut&ograve;noma de Barcelona (UAB)</em><br />\n	Bellaterra Campus 08193-Cerdanyola del Vall&eacute;s</p>\n','88retoc_rlopez_tamanyok.jpg','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	Rub&egrave;n L&oacute;pez Vales is tenured assistant professor of the Department of Cell Biology, Physiology and Immunology at Universitat Aut&ograve;noma de Barcelona in Spain. He earned a Bachelor of Science degree in Biology from Universitat de Girona in 2001 and received his PhD in Neuroscience from Universitat Aut&ograve;noma de Barcelona in 2005. He performed a postdoctoral stage at McGill University in Canada (2006-2009), and returned to Universitat Aut&ograve;noma of Barcelona in 2009 as tenure-track lecturer in the Department of Cell Biology, Physiology and Immunology. His scientific work is focused at modulating the inflammatory response in central nervous system disorders with the aim at developing novel therapeutic interventions.&nbsp; He has contributed to more than 30 articles and to 3 book chapters. He is also the co-author of 4 patents.</p>\n','<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>RESEARCH INTERESTS</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	The overarching goal of his research is to study the contribution of inflammation to tissue damage after spinal cord injury, and to other neurological conditions such as multiple sclerosis and amyotrophic lateral sclerosis. In particular, the research lines they are currently working are: &nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">\n	1) To understand the molecular mechanisms that mediate the detrimental aspects of macrophage activation in the central nervous system.</p>\n<p style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">\n	2) To assess the therapeutic effects of molecules that actively regulate the resolution programs of the inflammatory response in central nervous system disorders.</p>\n<p style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">\n	3) To identify factors that could create an immune response that is conducive to both neuroprotection and regeneration after spinal cord injury</p>\n','<p>\n	See all Rub&egrave;n Lopez&nbsp; publications at <a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830982/public/\" target=\"_blank\">PubMed</a>.</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>SELECTED PUBLICATIONS</strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		David M, Machuca-Gayet I, Kikuta J, Ottewell P, Mima F, Leblanc R, Bonnelye E, Ribeiro J, Holen I, Lopez Vales R, Jurdic P, Chun J, Clezardin P, Ishii M, Peyruchaud O (2014) Lysophosphatidic acid receptor type 1 (LPA1) plays a functional role in osteoclast differentiation and bone resorption activity. The Journal of biological chemistry.</li>\n	<li>\n		Klopstein A, Santos-Nogueira E, Francos-Quijorna I, Redensek A, David S, Navarro X, Lopez-Vales R (2012) Beneficial effects of alphaB-crystallin in spinal cord contusion injury. The Journal of neuroscience : the official journal of the Society for Neuroscience 32:14478-14488.</li>\n	<li>\n		David S, Lopez-Vales R, Wee Yong V (2012) Harmful and beneficial effects of inflammation after spinal cord injury: potential therapeutic implications. Handbook of clinical neurology 109:485-502.</li>\n	<li>\n		Ifergan I, Kebir H, Terouz S, Alvarez JI, Lecuyer MA, Gendron S, Bourbonniere L, Dunay IR, Bouthillier A, Moumdjian R, Fontana A, Haqqani A, Klopstein A, Prinz M, Lopez-Vales R, Birchler T, Prat A (2011) Role of Ninjurin-1 in the migration of myeloid cells to central nervous system inflammatory lesions. Annals of neurology 70:751-763.</li>\n	<li>\n		Lopez-Vales R, Ghasemlou N, Redensek A, Kerr BJ, Barbayianni E, Antonopoulou G, Baskakis C, Rathore KI, Constantinou-Kokotou V, Stephens D, Shimizu T, Dennis EA, Kokotos G, David S (2011) Phospholipase A2 superfamily members play divergent roles after spinal cord injury. FASEB journal : official publication of the Federation of American Societies for Experimental Biology 25:4240-4252.</li>\n	<li>\n		Ghasemlou N, Bouhy D, Yang J, Lopez-Vales R, Haber M, Thuraisingam T, He G, Radzioch D, Ding A, David S (2010) Beneficial effects of secretory leukocyte protease inhibitor after spinal cord injury. Brain : a journal of neurology 133:126-138.</li>\n	<li>\n		Lopez-Vales R, Redensek A, Skinner TA, Rathore KI, Ghasemlou N, Wojewodka G, DeSanctis J, Radzioch D, David S (2010) Fenretinide promotes functional recovery and tissue protection after spinal cord contusion injury in mice. The Journal of neuroscience : the official journal of the Society for Neuroscience 30:3220-3226.</li>\n	<li>\n		David S, Fry EJ, Lopez-Vales R (2008) Novel roles for Nogo receptor in inflammation and disease. Trends in neurosciences 31:221-226.</li>\n	<li>\n		Lopez-Vales R, Navarro X, Shimizu T, Baskakis C, Kokotos G, Constantinou-Kokotou V, Stephens D, Dennis EA, David S (2008) Intracellular phospholipase A(2) group IVA and group VIA play important roles in Wallerian degeneration and axon regeneration after peripheral nerve injury. Brain : a journal of neurology 131:2620-2631.</li>\n	<li>\n		Lopez-Vales R, Fores J, Verdu E, Navarro X (2006) Acute and delayed transplantation of olfactory ensheathing cells promote partial recovery after complete transection of the spinal cord. Neurobiology of disease 21:57-68.</li>\n</ul>\n','<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0001-7615-9550\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/orcid.png\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"http://www.researcherid.com/rid/E-2150-2011\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/RID.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=6506309428\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"http://www.researchgate.net/profile/Ruben_Lopez-Vales\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/researchgate.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"https://scholar.google.es/citations?user=4f1CQBwAAAAJ&amp;hl=ca&amp;oi=ao\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"29\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/googlescholar.jpg\" width=\"31\" /></a></td>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"https://es.linkedin.com/pub/rub%C3%A8n-l%C3%B3pez-vales/a3/644/57b\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Linkedin.jpg\" style=\"width: 35px; height: 29px;\" /></a></td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n'),(91,13,0,'Margarita ','Martí Nicolovius','Full Professor','B5 041','Facultat de Psicologia','+34 935 812 808','margarita.marti@uab.cat','<p>\n	Department of Psychobiology and Methodology of Health Science<br />\n	<em>Institut de Neuroci&egrave;ncies</em><br />\n	Faculty&nbsp; of Psychology (room B5-041)<br />\n	<em>Universitat Aut&ograve;noma de Barcelona (UAB)</em><br />\n	Bellaterra Campus 08193-Cerdanyola del Vall&eacute;s</p>\n','91mmartiweb.jpg','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	Margarita Mart&iacute; finished her Psychology Degree in 1981 and defended her PhD thesis, supervised by Dr. Ignacio Morgado, in 1986 at the UAB. She has conducted studies and research at the Ruhr Universit&auml;t Bochum (Germany) and the California Institute of Technology (Caltech, USA). She has been director of the Department of Psychobiology and Methodology of Health Sciences at the UAB (2002-2005) and member of the Local Organizing Committee of 35 Annual General Meeting of the European Brain and Behaviour Society (EBBS, Barcelona, 2003). She is an ordinary member of the Spanish Society of Neuroscience (SENC) and coordinates a group of experimental research on caloric restriction, aging and memory.</p>\n','<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>RESEARCH INTERESTS</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	Her research interests are focused on the potential beneficial effects of the dietary caloric restriction (CR) on the aging brain and, specifically, on cognitive functions. Impairment of cognitive abilities associated with aging of the population and the incidence of neurodegenerative diseases constitute a major social and health problem nowadays. Understanding the neurophysiological mechanisms involved in the beneficial effects of CR on cognition implies a challenge of traditional ideas about the relationship between diet and mental health in the search for strategies that would allow us to live longer and better.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>CURRENT WORK</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	Her current work focuses on the study of whether the RC in aged rats reduces cognitive problems compared to unrestricted (ad libitum) old and young animals. She is also interested in investigating the neurophysiological mechanisms underlying the potential beneficial effect of CR by analyzing neurogenesis and expression of glutamate receptors in the hippocampus and other related synaptic plasticity proteins. She also investigates the levels of brain monoamines and plasma levels of hormones such as corticosterone and insulin-like growth factor I to correlate them with the negative effects of age on memory. The achievement of the objectives proposed would allow a better understanding of the neurophysiological mechanisms involved in the aging process and the beneficial effects of CR on cognition to develop guidelines for healthy aging and reduce cognitive decline.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n','<p>\n	See all Margarita Mart&iacute; publications at <a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/49032188/public/\" target=\"_blank\">PubMed</a>.</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>SELECTED PUBLICATIONS</strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n		Portero-Tresserra M, Del Olmo N, Mart&iacute;-Nicolovius M, Guillazo-Blanch G, Vale-Mart&iacute;nez A. D-cycloserine prevents relational memory deficits and suppression of long-term potentiation induced by scopolamine in the hippocampus. Eur Neuropsychopharmacol. <strong>2014</strong>;24(11):1798-807.</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n		Portero-Tresserra M, Crist&oacute;bal-Narv&aacute;ez P, Mart&iacute;-Nicolovius M, Guillazo-Blanch G, Vale-Mart&iacute;nez A. D-cycloserine in prelimbic cortex reverses scopolamine-induced deficits in olfactory memory in rats. PLoS One. <strong>2013</strong>;8(8):e70584.</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n		Yefimenko N, Portero-Tresserra M, Mart&iacute;-Nicolovius M, Guillazo-Blanch G, Vale-Mart&iacute;nez A. The AMPA receptor modulator S18986 in the prelimbic cortex enhances acquisition and retention of an odor-reward association. Neurosci Lett. <strong>2013</strong>;548:105-9.</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n		Portero-Tresserra M, Mart&iacute;-Nicolovius M, Guillazo-Blanch G, Boadas-Vaello P, Vale-Mart&iacute;nez A. D-cycloserine in the basolateral amygdala prevents extinction and enhances reconsolidation of odor-reward associative learning in rats. Neurobiol Learn Mem. <strong>2013</strong>;100:1-11.</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n		Villarejo-Rodr&iacute;guez I, Boadas-Vaello P, Portero-Tresserra M, Vale-Mart&iacute;nez A, Mart&iacute;-Nicolovius M, Guillazo-Blanch G. Learning deficits in an odor reward-task induced by parafascicular thalamic lesions are ameliorated by pretraining D-cycloserine in the prelimbic cortex. Behav Brain Res. <strong>2013</strong>;238:289-92.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n','<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0002-8669-6285\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/orcid.png\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"http://www.researcherid.com/ProfileView.action?SID=W2aNsQjEqBkmt8inNpn&amp;returnCode=ROUTER.Success&amp;queryString=KG0UuZjN5WkTEMnGFsnbmuLLkyr%252FfYHzcUEhmivW4Bo%253D&amp;SrcApp=CR&amp;Init=Yes\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/RID.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=6603427358\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"http://www.researchgate.net/profile/Margarita_Marti-Nicolovius2\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/researchgate.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n			<td>\n				&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>\n				&nbsp;</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n'),(92,13,0,'Maite ','Martín Ibañez',NULL,'V0 131','Facultat Veterinària','+34 935 813 834','maite.martin@uab.cat',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(93,13,0,'Vicente ','Martínez Perea',NULL,'V0 149','Facultat de Veterinària','+34 935 813 834','vicente.martinez@uab.cat',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'<p>\n	See all V. Mart&iacute;nez publication at <a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830977/public/\" target=\"_blank\">PubMed</a>.</p>\n',NULL),(94,14,0,'Emma','Martínez Perez',NULL,'V LAB115','Facultat de Veterinària','+34 935 811 839','emma.martinez@uab.cat',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(96,13,0,'Roser ','Masgrau Juanola',NULL,'M2 117','Facultat de Medicina','+34 935 814 278','roser.masgrau@uab.cat',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'<p>\n	See all R. Masgrau publication at <a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830827/public/\" target=\"_blank\">PubMed</a>.</p>\n',NULL),(97,10,0,'Alfredo Jesús ','Miñano Molina','Postdoctoral researcher','M2 105','','+34 935 811 425','alfredo.minano@uab.cat','<p>\n	Department of Biochemistry and Molecular Biology<br />\n	<em>Institut de Neuroci&egrave;ncies</em><br />\n	School of Medicine (room M2-105)<br />\n	<em>Universitat Aut&ograve;noma de Barcelona (UAB)</em><br />\n	Bellaterra Campus 08193-Cerdanyola del Vall&eacute;s</p>\n','97DSC00831web.jpg','<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PRESENT POSITION</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	I am currently a Postdoctoral Researcher at Centro de Investigaci&oacute;n Biom&eacute;dica en Red &ndash; Neurodegenerative Diseases (CIBERNED), Biochemistry and Molecular Biology Department (<em>Institut de Neuroci&egrave;ncies</em> - Universitat Aut&ograve;noma de Barcelona).</p>\n<p>\n	Other activities:</p>\n<p>\n	Professor, Faculty of Medicine, Medicine Degree.<br />\n	Mentor of the Master&rsquo;s Degree in Neuroscience.<br />\n	Mentor of the PhD Neuroscience Program.<br />\n	Advisor at the PhD Neuroscience Program.<br />\n	Popular Science communicator.</p>\n<p>\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PREVIOUS</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong><em>Post-doctoral stay</em></strong>(&quot;Jos&eacute; Castillejo&quot; Mobility Fellowship) at Nancy Pritzker Lab, Psychiatry &amp; Behavioral Sciences, Stanford University School of Medicine. Palo Alto (California) United States. From March to September, 2012.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	My research at Dr Robert C. Malenka&#39;s laboratory was aimed to elucidate the specific molecular events that are responsible for the exocytosis of neurotransmitter receptors. To accomplish this I used imaging techniques (Confocal Microscopy) and molecular and cell biological approaches to examine the activity-dependent modulation of neurotransmitter receptors.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<br />\n	<strong><em>Pre-doctoral stay</em></strong>at Departamento de Biolog&iacute;a Celular, Facultad de Biolog&iacute;a. Universidad de Valencia. Valencia (Spain). From April to December 2002.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	My research at Dra Isabel Fari&ntilde;as&rsquo; laboratory was aimed to investigate the neurodegenerative effect of alpha-synuclein protein accumulation in front of several cell death stimuli. To accomplish this I used neuronal primary cultures from wild type and alpha-synuclein-knock out mice and molecular and cell biological approaches.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>EDUCATION</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>Teacher Training Program in European Higher Education Area, (FDES program)</strong>; Universitat Aut&ograve;noma de Barcelona (UAB), Barcelona, Spain.2011-2012<strong>. </strong>Within the framework of European university harmonisation, the Teacher Training Plan of UFI aims to provide UAB lecturers with a variety of tools and resources to help them implement innovation initiatives and to improve the quality of their teaching.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>Ph.D., in Biochemistry and Molecular Biology</strong>; Universitat Aut&ograve;noma de Barcelona (UAB), Barcelona, Spain. 2000-2006. Supervisor: Jos&eacute; Rodr&iacute;guez &Aacute;lvarez. PhD project: &ldquo;Effects of 17-beta-estradiol on survival and modulation of neuronal plasticity in cultured rat cerebellar granule neurons.&rdquo;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>Post-graduate Pedagogic Aptitude Certificate, Life Sciences</strong>. Universitat Aut&ograve;noma de Barcelona (UAB), Barcelona, Spain. 2000-2001.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>B.Sc, Biochemistry</strong>, Universitat Aut&ograve;noma de Barcelona (UAB), Barcelona, Spain. 1995-2000.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n','<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>RESEARCH INTEREST</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	We are interested in the molecular events that are responsible for the decrease in glutamatergic neurotransmission elicited by amyloid-beta. Particularly in the relationship between oligomer forms of amyloid-beta, alteration in synaptic glutamatergic receptors and early cognitive deficits related to Alzheimer&rsquo;s disease.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>CURRENT WORK</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	The goals of my present research are:</p>\n<p>\n	(1) To characterize the molecular mechanisms underlying amyloid-beta oligomers-dependent synaptic depression using molecular and cell biological approaches.<br />\n	(2) To analyze the regulation of synaptic proteins in response to synaptic stimuli under amyloid-beta depression conditions using imaging techniques and replacement technology.<br />\n	(3) To implement the molecular replacement technology using stereotaxic injections in vivo in a mouse model of Alzheimer Disease.<br />\n	(4) To find out new biomarkers related with early diagnostic in Alzheimer&rsquo;s disease.</p>\n','<p>\n	See all Alfredo J. Mi&ntilde;ano&nbsp; publications at PubMed.</p>\n<p>\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>SELECTED PUBLICATIONS</strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		Sol&eacute; M, <strong>Mi&ntilde;ano-Molina AJ</strong> &amp; Unzeta M. A cross-talk between A&beta; and endothelial SSAO/VAP-1 accelerates vascular damage and A&beta; aggregation related to CAA-AD. Neurobiol Aging. 2015;36(2):762-75</li>\n	<li>\n		Xifr&oacute; X, <strong>Mi&ntilde;ano-Molina AJ</strong>, Saura CA &amp; Rodr&iacute;guez-Alvarez J. Ras activation is a key event in activity-dependent survival of neurons.J. Biol. Chem (2014) 289:8462-8472.</li>\n	<li>\n		Fad&oacute; R, Moubarak R, <strong>Mi&ntilde;ano-Molina AJ</strong>, Barneda-Zahonero B, Valero J, Saura CA, Mor&aacute;n J, Comella JX &amp; &nbsp;Rodr&iacute;guez-Alvarez J. X-linked inhibitor of apoptosis protein negatively regulates neurite outgrowth through interaction with cRAF and Trk. .Sci Reports. 3:2397 (2013).</li>\n	<li>\n		Jurado S, Goswami D, Zhang Y, <strong>Mi&ntilde;ano-Molina AJ</strong>, S&uuml;dhof TC and Malenka RC. LTP requires a unique postsynaptic SNARE fusion machinery. Neuron 77 (2013) 542-558.</li>\n	<li>\n		Barneda-Zahonero B, Servitja JM, Badiola N, <strong>Mi&ntilde;ano-Molina AJ</strong>, Fad&oacute; R, Saura CA and Rodr&iacute;guez-&Aacute;lvarez J.Nurr1 protein is required for N-Methyl-D-aspartic acid (NMDA) receptor-mediated neuronal survival. BJ Biol Chem. (2012) 287 (14) 11351-11362.</li>\n	<li>\n		<strong>Mi&ntilde;ano-Molina AJ</strong>, Espa&ntilde;a J, Mart&iacute;n E, Barneda-Zahonero B, Fad&oacute; R, Sol&eacute; M, Trull&agrave;s R, Saura CA, Rodr&iacute;guez-&Aacute;lvarez J.Soluble oligomers of amyloid-{beta} peptide disrupt membrane trafficking of {alpha}-amino-3-hydroxy-5-methylisoxazole-4-propionic acid receptor (AMPAR) contributing to early synapse dysfunction. J Biol Chem. (2011) 286 (31) 27311-27321.</li>\n	<li>\n		Badiola N, Penas C, <strong>Mi&ntilde;ano-Molina A</strong>, Barneda-Zahonero B, Fad&oacute; R, S&aacute;nchez-Opazo G, Comella JX, Sabri&aacute; J, Zhu C, Blomgren K, Casas C, Rodr&iacute;guez-Alvarez J.Induction of ER stress in response to oxygen-glucose deprivation of cortical cultures involves the activation of the PERK and IRE-1 pathways and of caspase-12. Cell Death Dis. 2011, April 28; 2:e149.</li>\n	<li>\n		Espa&ntilde;a J. , Valero J., <strong>Mi&ntilde;ano-Molina A.J.</strong> , Masgrau R., Mart&iacute;n E., Guardia-Laguarta C., Lle&oacute; A., Gim&eacute;nez-Llort L., Rodr&iacute;guez-Alvarez J. and Saura C.Ab-Amyloid Disrupts Activity-Dependent Gene Transcription Required for Memory Through the CREB Coactivator CRTC1. .J Neurosci. 2010 Jul; 30(28):9402&ndash;9410.</li>\n	<li>\n		Espa&ntilde;a J, Gim&eacute;nez-Llort L, Valero J, <strong>Mi&ntilde;ano A</strong>, R&aacute;bano A, Rodriguez-Alvarez J, Laferla FM, Saura CA.Intraneuronal beta-Amyloid Accumulation in the Amygdala Enhances Fear and Anxiety in Alzheimer&#39;s Disease Transgenic Mice.&nbsp; Biol Psychiatry. 2010 Mar; 67(6):513-21.</li>\n	<li>\n		Barneda-Zahonero B, <strong>Mi&ntilde;ano-Molina A</strong>, Badiola N, Fad&oacute; R, Xifr&oacute; X, Saura CA, Rodr&iacute;guez-Alvarez J.Bone morphogenetic protein-6 promotes cerebellar granule neurons survival by activation of the MEK/ERK/CREB pathway. Mol Biol Cell. 2009 Dec; 20(24):5051-63.</li>\n	<li>\n		<strong>Mi&ntilde;ano A</strong>, Xifr&oacute; X, P&eacute;rez V, Barneda-Zahonero B, Saura CA, Rodr&iacute;guez-Alvarez J. Estradiol facilitates neurite maintenance by a Src/Ras/ERK signalling pathway. Mol Cell Neurosci. 2008 Oct; 39(2):143-51.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>Book Chapter</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	Xif