u N, Nadal R, Armario A. Prior exposure to repeated immobilization or chronic unpredictable stress protects from some negative sequels of an acute immobilization Behav Brain Res. 2014, 265:155-62.</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n		Echeverry-Alzate V, Gin&eacute; E, B&uuml;hler K, Olmos P, Gorriti MA, Nadal R, Rodriguez de Fonseca F, L&oacute;pez-Moreno JA. The Effects of Topiramate on ethanol-cocaine interactions and DNA methyltransferase gene expression in the rat prefrontal cortex. British J Pharmacol. 2014, 171(12):3023-36.</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n		Feliu-Soler A, Pascual JC, Borr&agrave;s X, Portella MJ, Mart&iacute;n-Blanco A, Armario A, Alvarez E, P&eacute;rez V, Soler J. Effects of dialectical behaviour therapy-mindfulness training on emotional reactivity in borderline personality disorder: preliminary results. Clin Psychol Psychother. 2014;21(4):363-70.</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n		Gagliano H, Delgado-Morales R, Sanz-Garcia A, Armario A. High doses of the histone deacetylase inhibitor sodium butyrate trigger a stress-like response. Neuropharmacology. 2014, 79:75-82.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n','<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				&nbsp;</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0001-8972-2525\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/orcid.png\" style=\"width: 26px; height: 26px;\" /></a></td>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"http://www.researcherid.com/rid/C-7977-2011\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/RID.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=6701731005\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 29px; height: 29px;\" /></a></td>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"http://www.researchgate.net/profile/Roser_Nadal2\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"27\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/researchgate.jpg\" width=\"27\" /></a></td>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"http://www.mendeley.com/profiles/roser-nadal/\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"28\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/mendeley.png\" width=\"28\" /></a></td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				&nbsp;</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n'),(105,13,0,'Xavier ','Navarro Acebes','Full Professor','M4 118','Facultat de Medicina','+34 935 811 966','xavier.navarro@uab.cat','<p>\n	Department of Cellular Biology, Physiology and Immunology<br />\n	<em>Institut de Neuroci&egrave;ncies</em><br />\n	Faculty of Medicine (room M4-118)<br />\n	<em>Universitat Aut&ograve;noma de Barcelona (UAB)</em><br />\n	Bellaterra Campus 08193-Cerdanyola del Vall&eacute;s</p>\n','105XNavarro-jul2014.jpg','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>Xavier Navarro</strong> received the MD degree in 1978 and the PhD degree in 1985 both from the Universitat Aut&ograve;noma de Barcelons (UAB). He completed his speciality training in Neurology at the University of Barcelona, and in Neurophysiology at the University of Minnesota. He was Assistant Professor of the Department of Neurology of the University of Minnesota (1986-1988). He returned in 1988 to the UAB as Associate Professor in the Department of Cell Biology and Physiology, where he is currently full Professor of Physiology from 1999. He is the director of the Department of Cell Biology, Physiology and Immunology since 2010. He was a founder of the Institute of Neurosciences of the UAB. He also serves as scientific advisor of the Institut Guttmann of Neurorehabilitation.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	He has published more than 300 papers in refereed journals and books, with an H index of 44, and directed 22 PhD theses. He has been member of the editorial boards of the journals: Restorative Neurology and Neuroscience, Journal of the Peripheral Nervous System, Muscle and Nerve, Frontiers in Neuroengineering. He has received the awards &ldquo;Ciutat de Barcelona&rdquo; in 1995, &ldquo;Josep Trueta&rdquo; in 2000, and ASPAYM award in 2009 for his scientific research activities.</p>\n','<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>RESEARCH INTERESTS</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	Dr. Navarro&rsquo;s research interests are focused on axonal regeneration, functional restitution after neural injuries, neuroprostheses, peripheral neuropathies, neuropathic pain and neurodegenerative motoneuron diseases.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>Research Group of Neuroplasticity and Regeneration</strong>. The research projects of the group in which Dr Navarro is involved deal with: regeneration and reinnervation after nerve injuries, biocompatible artificial nerve grafts, cell transplants for the repair of peripheral and central nervous injuries, neuropathic pain, motoneuron diseases, peripheral neuropathies, and neural electrodes for interfacing the injured nervous system. The group has also cooperative research in clinical neurosciences, particularly on new nerve repair therapies, and in modulation of neural plasticity after lesions. The group has participated in several EU projects: INTER (ESPRIT #8897), GRIP (ESPRIT LTR#26322), CYBERHAND (IST-2001-35094), NEUROBOTICS (IST-001917), TIME (ICT2008-224012), BIOHYBRID (FP7-278612), MERIDIAN (NMP4-SL-2012-280778).</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	The members of the group have combined expertises in microsurgery, neurophysiology, morphology, cell culture, molecular biology and bioelectronics. It is one of the internationally leading research groups in the fields of peripheral nerve regeneration and bioelectronic interfaces.</p>\n','<p>\n	See all Xavier Navarro&nbsp; publications at <a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830990/public/\" target=\"_blank\">PubMed</a>.</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>S</strong