L,NULL,'<p>\n	See all A. Tobe&ntilde;a publication at <a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/49032219/public/\" target=\"_blank\">PubMed</a>.</p>\n',NULL),(133,13,0,'Meritxell ','Torras García',NULL,'B5 029','Facultat de Psicologia','+34 935 813 260','meritxell.torras@uab.cat',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(134,13,0,'Rafael ','Torrubia Beltri',NULL,'M5 137','','+34 935 811 438','rafael.torrubia@uab.cat',NULL,'1342016-06-07 09.jpg',NULL,NULL,'<p>\n	See all R. Torrubia publication at <a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48831042/public/\" target=\"_blank\">PubMed</a>.</p>\n',NULL),(135,13,0,'Esther','Udina Bonet','Professor of Medical Physiology','M4 129','Facultat de Medicina','+34 935 811 348','esther.udina@uab.cat','<p>\n	Department of Cellular Biology, Physiology and Immunology<br />\n	<em>Institut de Neuroci&egrave;ncies</em><br />\n	Faculty of Medicine (room M4-129)<br />\n	<em>Universitat Aut&ograve;noma de Barcelona (UAB)</em><br />\n	Bellaterra Campus 08193-Cerdanyola del Vall&eacute;s</p>\n','135DSC00601web.jpg','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>Esther Udina</strong> performed her MD degree from 1992 to1999 at the Faculty of Medicine of the UAB. Then, she joined the group of Neuroplasticity and Regeneration of the UAB to do her PhD thesis, under the supervision of Dr Xavier Navarro. She defended her PhD thesis in 2004. In 2005 she went to the laboratory of Dr Tessa Gordon, in the University of Alberta (Edmonton, Canada) to do a postdoctoral stay. She returned to the UAB in September 2007 as a lecturer professor, where she rejoined the group of Neuroplasticity and Regeneration. She is currently associate professor at the Physiology Unit, in the Department of Cell Biology and Physiology.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	She has published &nbsp;&nbsp;more than 40 papers in refereed journals and books and has directed 3 theses. She is actually coordinator of the official master of Neurosciences of the UAB.</p>\n','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>RESEARCH INTERESTS</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	Her research interests are focused on strategies to improve functional recovery after nerve lesions, either by increasing axonal regeneration and specific reinnervation or by modulating the plastic changes that occur after injuries of the nervous system.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>CURRENT WORK</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	Her current interests are focused on strategies to improve functional recovery after peripheral nerve injuries in animal models. they are trying to modulate the plastic changes that occur in the spinal cord after peripheral nerve injuries. The disorganization of these circuits can impair functional recovery and can lead to hypereflexia and neuropathic pain. Among the different strategies, they have focused our interest on activity dependent therapies. They are also working on the design of artificial nerve guides to improve regeneration after severe peripheral nerve lesions, focusing on strategies that could differentially promote specific regeneration of motor and sensory axons. With Dr Jordi Bruna, a clinical neuro-oncologist in the Hospital of Bellvitge, they are also working on murine neuropathic models of chemotherapy-induced neurotoxicity.</p>\n','<p>\n	See all Esther Udina publications at <a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48831045/public/\" target=\"_blank\">PubMed</a>.</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>SELECTED PUBLICATIONS</strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n	<li style=\"margin-left: 17.85pt;\">\n		Arbat-Plana A, Torres-Espin A, Navarro X, Udina E. Activity dependent therapies modulate the spinal changes that motoneurons suffer after a peripheral nerve injury.&nbsp;Exp Neurol&nbsp;2015;263:293-305.</li>\n	<li style=\"margin-left: 17.85pt;\">\n		Allodi I, Mecollari V, Gonz&aacute;lez-P&eacute;rez F, Eggers R, Hoyng S, Verhaagen J, Navarro X, Udina E. Schwann cells transduced with a lentiviral vector encoding Fgf-2 promote motor neuron regeneration following sciatic nerve injury. Glia 2014, 62:1736-46.</li>\n	<li style=\"margin-left: 18pt;\">\n		Al&eacute; A, Bruna J, Morell M, van de Velde H, Monbaliu J, Navarro X, Udina E. Treatment with anti-TNF alpha protects against the neuropathy induced by the proteasome inhibitor bortezomib in a mouse model. Exp Neurol. 2014; 253C:165-173.</li>\n	<li style=\"margin-left: 18pt;\">\n		Allodi I, Casals-D&iacute;az L, Santos-Nogueira E, Gonzalez-Perez F, Navarro X, Udina E. FGF-2 low molecular weight selectively promotes neuritogenesis of motor neurons in vitro. Mol Neurobiol 2013; 47(2):770-81.</li>\n	<li style=\"margin-left: 18pt;\">\n		Allodi I, Guzm&aacute;n-Lenis M, Hern&agrave;ndez J, Navarro X, Udina E. In vitro comparison of motor and sensory neuron outgrowth in a 3D collagen matrix&nbsp; J Neuroscie Meth 2001; 198: 53-61.</li>\n</ul>\n','<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-1954-8562\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/orcid.png\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"http://www.researcherid.com/rid/E-2559-2011\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/RID.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=6506447298\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"http://www.researchgate.net/profile/Esther_Udina\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/researchgate.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n			<td>\n				&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>\n				&nbsp;</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n'),(136,13,0,'Mercè','Unzeta López','Full Professor','M2 125','','+34 935 811 523','mercedes.unzeta@uab.cat','<p>\n	Department of Biochemistry and Molecular Biology<br />\n	<em>Institut de Neuroci&egrave;ncies</em><br />\n	Faculty&nbsp; of Medicine (room M2-125)<br />\n	<em>Universitat Aut&ograve;noma de Barcelona (UAB)</em><br />\n	Bellaterra Campus 08193-Cerdanyola del Vall&eacute;s</p>\n','136IMG_5727.jpg','','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	Dr M.Unzeta research interests are focused on the contribution of the SSAO/VAP-1 Oxidase to the neurovascular disfunction and its relationship with the Parkinson, Cerebral Amyloid Angiopathy and the Alzheimer&acute;s disease.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>Research group of Neuodegeneration and Ageing.</strong>Oxidative stress plays a determinant role in neurodegenerative disorders such as Parkinson&#39;s disease, Amyloid Angiopathy (CAA) and Alzheimer&#39;s disease (AD). Moreover Cerebrovascular system dysfunctions are early events in Alzheimer&rsquo;s disease (AD), which is initiated long before the appearance of clinical symptomatology. One of the main objectives of our research is focused on the &nbsp;study of molecular changes occurring in cerebrovascular system in preclinical AD, with special relevance tothe role that vascular SSAO/VAP-1 Oxidase could play in the vasculopathy associated to these neurological disorders. The group has participated in several national and EU projects : &nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n	<li style=\"margin-left: 36pt;\">\n		INNPRONTA program CDTI (Ministery of Industry 2012-2015)</li>\n	<li style=\"margin-left: 36pt;\">\n		SAF 2012-33304</li>\n	<li style=\"margin-left: 36pt;\">\n		Marat&oacute; de TV3- Foundation (2015-2017)</li>\n	<li style=\"margin-left: 36pt;\">\n		COST Project EU-MC 1103 (2011-2014)</li>\n</ul>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	The members of this research group have expertise in enzymology, molecular Biology, cell culture, &nbsp; inmunocytochemistry, protein expression etc,. It is a leading research group in the field of oxidases and its role in neurodegenerative diseases.</p>\n','<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>SELECTED PUBLICATIONS- Last 10 years related with the project</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n		<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/26362823\">Protective effect of the multitarget compound DPH-4 on human SSAO/VAP-1-expressing hCMEC/D3 cells under oxygen-glucose deprivation conditions, an in vitro experimental model of cerebral ischemia.</a>Sun P, Esteban G, Inokuchi T, Marco-Contelles J, Weksler BB, Romero IA, Couraud PO, <strong>Unzeta M</strong>, Sol&eacute; M.Br J Pharmacol. 2015 Sep 12.</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n		<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/25457560\">Cross-talk between A&beta; and endothelial SSAO/VAP-1 accelerates vascular damage and A&beta; aggregation related to CAA-AD.</a>Sol&eacute; M, Mi&ntilde;ano-Molina AJ, <strong>Unzeta M</strong>.Neurobiol Aging. 2015 Feb;36(2):762-75.</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n		<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/25378907\">Multipotent cholinesterase/monoamine oxidase inhibitors for the treatment of Alzheimer&#39;s disease: design, synthesis, biochemical evaluation, ADMET, molecular modeling, and QSAR analysis of novel donepezil-pyridyl hybrids.</a>Bautista-Aguilera OM, Esteban G, Chioua M, Nikolic K, Agbaba D, Moraleda I, Iriepa I, Soriano E, Samadi A, <strong>Unzeta M</strong>, Marco-Contelles J.Drug Des Devel Ther. 2014 Oct 13;8:1893-910.</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n		<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24503888\">Involvement of SSAO/VAP-1 in oxygen-glucose deprivation-mediated damage using the endothelial hSSAO/VAP-1-expressing cells as experimental model of cerebral ischemia.</a>Sun P, Sol&eacute; M, <strong>Unzeta M</strong>.Cerebrovasc Dis. 2014;37(3):171-80.</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n		<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/23919774\">Multipotent, permeable drug ASS234 inhibits A&beta; aggregation, possesses antioxidant properties and protects from A&beta;-induced apoptosis in vitro.</a>Bolea I, Gella A, Monjas L, P&eacute;rez C, Rodr&iacute;guez-Franco MI, Marco-Contelles J, Samadi A, <strong>Unzeta M</strong>. Curr Alzheimer Res. 2013 Oct;10(8):797-808.</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n		<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/23263540\">A therapeutic approach to cerebrovascular diseases based on indole substituted hydrazides and hydrazines able to interact with human vascular adhesion protein-1, monoamine oxidases (A and B), AChE and BuChE.</a>Esteban G, Bolea I, Sun P, Sol&eacute; M, Samadi A, Marco-Contelles J, <strong>Unzeta M</strong>.J Neural Transm. 2013 Jun;120(6):911-8.</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n		<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/22714978\">Immunohistochemical study of semicarbazide-sensitive amine oxidase/vascular adhesion protein-1 in the hippocampal vasculature: pathological synergy of Alzheimer&#39;s disease and diabetes mellitus.</a>Valente T, Gella A, Sol&eacute; M, Durany N, <strong>Unzeta M</strong>.J Neurosci Res. 2012 Oct;90(10):1989-96.</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n		<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/22133888\">VAP-1/SSAO plasma activity and brain expression in human hemorrhagic stroke.</a>Hernandez-Guillamon M, Sol&eacute; M, Delgado P, Garc&iacute;a-Bonilla L, Giralt D, Boada C, Penalba A, Garc&iacute;a S, Flores A, Rib&oacute; M, Alvarez-Sabin J, Ortega-Aznar A, <strong>Unzeta M</strong>, Montaner J.Cerebrovasc Dis. 2012;33(1):55-63</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n		<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/21819380\">Vascular cell lines expressing SSAO/VAP-1: a new experimental tool to study its involvement in vascular diseases.</a>Sol&eacute; M, <strong>Unzeta M</strong>.Biol Cell. 2011 Nov;103(11):543-57.</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n		<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/20538694\">Plasma VAP-1/SSAO activity predicts intracranial hemorrhages and adverse neurological outcome after tissue plasminogen activator treatment in stroke.</a>Hernandez-Guillamon M, Garcia-Bonilla L, Sol&eacute; M, Sosti V, Par&eacute;s M, Campos M, Ortega-Aznar A, Dom&iacute;nguez C, Rubiera M, Rib&oacute; M, Quintana M, Molina CA, Alvarez-Sab&iacute;n J, Rosell A, <strong>Unzeta M</strong>, Montaner J.Stroke. 2010 Jul;41(7):1528-35.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	See all M. Unzeta publications at <a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48831046/public/\" target=\"_blank\">PubMed</a>.</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n','<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>\n				&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>\n				<p>\n					<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=7003384729\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 29px; height: 29px;\" /></a></p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n				&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>\n				&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>\n				&nbsp;</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n'),(138,13,0,'Patrocinio','Vergara Esteras',NULL,'V0 141','Facultat de Veterinària','+34 935 811 848','patri.vergara@uab.cat',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'<p>\n	See all P. Vergara publication at <a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830981/public/\" target=\"_blank\">PubMed</a>.</p>\n',NULL),(139,13,0,'Elisabet','Vila Calsina',NULL,'M4 110','','+34 935 811 961','elisabet.vila@uab.cat',NULL,'139elisabeth vila3.jpg',NULL,NULL,'<p>\n	See all E. Vila publication at <a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48831052/public/\" target=\"_blank\">PubMed</a>.</p>\n',NULL),(143,13,0,'Victor José','Yuste Mateos',NULL,'M2 115','Facultat de Medicina','+34 935 813 762','victor.yuste@uab.cat',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'<p>\n	See all VJ. 