cat',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(165,14,21,'Cristobal ','Del Río Alamos',NULL,'M5 134','Facultat de Medicina','+34 935 813 517','cristobal.delrio@uab.cat',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(167,10,0,'Lilian','Enríquez Barreto','Postdoctoral Researcher','M2 006','','+34 935 818 140','lilian.enriquez@uab.cat','<p>\n	Department of Biochemistry and Molecular Biology<br />\n	<em>Institut de Neuroci&egrave;ncies</em><br />\n	Faculty&nbsp; of Medicine (room M2-006)<br />\n	<em>Universitat Aut&ograve;noma de Barcelona (UAB)</em><br />\n	Bellaterra Campus 08193-Cerdanyola del Vall&eacute;s</p>\n','167DSC01050web.JPG','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	I am a postdoc at the Laboratory of Neurobiology of Alzheimer&rsquo;s Disease, Department of Biochemistry and Molecular Biology at the<em> Institut de Neuroci&egrave;ncies</em> at UAB. I study the role of the CREB regulated transcription coactivator 1 (CRTC1) in synaptic plasticity, memory and learning in mice models of Alzheimer&rsquo;s Disease. I also collaborate with Jaume Esteve&rsquo;s Micro and NanoTools Group at the Centro Nacional de Microelectr&oacute;nica of the Consejo Superior de Investigaciones Cient&iacute;ficas (CSIC), on the development of micro and nanodevices to activate neuronal networks.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	Currently, I also work as a professor of Neurochemistry at the School of Medicine, UAB.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	During my PhD I studied the functional role of PSA-NCAM in cortical development, focused on the analysis of GABAergic interneurons in the cerebral cortex and the thalamocortical axonal system in NCAM knockout mice. This research was carried out at the Institute of Neuroscience of Alicante, under the supervision of Dr. Alfonso Fair&eacute;n. In the course of my PhD I also had the opportunity to collaborate with Domna Karagogeos, IMBB, Crete Medical School, Heraklion, Crete, Greece; and lately with Patricia Maness&rsquo;s Group at the University of North Carolina. Chapel Hill, USA.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	I started my first postdoc at Miguel Morales&rsquo;s group at the Laboratory of Neurophysiology, Medical School, University of Barcelona. My research project was related to PI3K-mediated synaptogenesis in memory processes. Our group moved to the Center for Biomedical Research of La Rioja (CIBIR) in Logro&ntilde;o, where we founded the Structural Synaptic Plasticity Lab at the Unit of Neurodegenerative Diseases. Once there, I continued studying the PI3K role on dendritic spines formation and structural remodeling in the rat hippocampus.</p>\n','<p>\n	My major research topics are:</p>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		Elucidating and understanding molecular mechanisms underlying neurodegeneration.</li>\n	<li>\n		Studies of synaptic plasticity of neuronal connections and how plasticity is related to learning, memory and behavior.</li>\n	<li>\n		Neuronal migration and the development of axonal projections.</li>\n	<li>\n		Nanotools for Neuroscience.</li>\n</ul>\n','<p>\n	See all Lilian Enr&iacute;quez publications at PubMed</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>SELECTED PUBLICATIONS</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		Parra-Damas A, Chen M, Enriquez-Barreto L, Ortega L, Acosta S, Perna JC, Fullana MN, Aguilera J, Rodr&iacute;guez-Alvarez J, Saura CA. CRTC1 Function During Memory Encoding Is Disrupted in Neurodegeneration. Biol Psychiatry. <strong>2016</strong>.</li>\n	<li>\n		Enriquez-Barreto L, Morales M. The PI3K signaling pathway as a pharmacological target in Autism related disorders and Schizophrenia. Mol Cell Ther. <strong>2016</strong>.</li>\n	<li>\n		Saura CA, Parra-Damas A, Enriquez-Barreto L. Gene expression parallels synaptic excitability and plasticity changes in Alzheimer&#39;s disease. Front Cell Neurosci. <strong>2015</strong>.</li>\n	<li>\n		Cuesto G, Jord&aacute;n-&Aacute;lvarez S, Enriquez-Barreto L, Ferr&uacute;s A, Morales M, Acebes &Aacute;. GSK3&beta; Inhibition Promotes Synaptogenesis in Drosophila and Mammalian Neurons. PLoS One<strong> 2015.</strong></li>\n	<li>\n		Brito V, Giralt A, Enriquez-Barreto L, Puigdell&iacute;vol M, Suelves N, Zamora-Moratalla A, Ballesteros JJ, Mart&iacute;n ED, Dominguez-Iturza N, Morales M, Alberch J, Gin&eacute;s S. Neurotrophin receptor p75NTR mediates Huntington&#39;s disease-associated synaptic and memory dysfunction. J Clin Invest<strong>. 2014.</strong></li>\n	<li>\n		Enriquez-Barreto L<strong>, </strong>Cuesto G, Dominguez-Iturza N, Gavil&aacute;n E, Ruano D, Sandi C, Fern&aacute;ndez-Ruiz A, Mart&iacute;n-V&aacute;zquez G, Herreras O and Morales M. Learning improvement after PI3K activation correlates with de novo formation of functional small spines. Front Mol Neurosci. <strong>2014</strong>.</li>\n	<li>\n		Enriquez-Barreto L, Palazzetti C, Brennaman LH, Maness PF, Fair&eacute;n A. Neural cell adhesion molecule, NCAM, regulates thalamocortical axon pathfinding and the organization of the cortical somatosensory representation in mouse. Front Mol Neurosci<strong>. 2012</strong>.</li>\n	<li>\n		Cuesto G, Enriquez-Barreto L, Caram&eacute;s C, Cantarero M, Gasull X, Sandi C, Ferr&uacute;s A, Acebes &Aacute;, Morales M. Phosphoinositide-3-kinase activation controls synaptogenesis and spinogenesis in hippocampal neurons. J Neurosci<strong>. 2011</strong>.</li>\n	<li>\n		Wright AG, Demyanenko GP, Powell A, Schachner M, Enriquez-Barreto L, Tran TS, Polleux F, Maness PF. Close homolog of L1 and neuropilin 1 mediate guidance of thalamocortical axons at the ventral telencephalon. J Neurosci<strong>. 2007.</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n','<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>\n				&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=23090790200\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n			<td>\n				&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>\n				&nbsp;</t