','+34 935 868 099','pablo.machuca@uab.cat',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(235,13,0,'Assumpció ','Bosch Merino','Professor','H-530','','+34 935 814 203','assumpcio.bosch@uab.cat','<p>\n	Department of Biochemistry and Molecular Biology<br />\n	<em>Institut de Neuroci&egrave;ncies</em><br />\n	CBATEG (room H-530)<br />\n	<em>Universitat Aut&ograve;noma de Barcelona (UAB)</em><br />\n	Bellaterra Campus 08193-Cerdanyola del Vall&eacute;s</p>\n','235ABosch.jpg','<p style=\"margin-left: 1cm; text-align: justify;\">\n	Assumpci&oacute; Bosch obtained her PhD in 1994 (UAB) and did her postdoctoral training on gene therapy strategies using viral vectors was done in Beverly Davidson&rsquo;s (University of Iowa, USA) and Jean Michel Heard&rsquo;s laboratories (Pasteur Institute, Paris, France) from 1995 to 2000, after which she returned to Barcelona. She was awarded with a Ramon y Cajal tenure track in its first call (2002) and she moved to the UAB, starting her own research group in 2005 at CBATEG on Gene therapy strategies for neuropathies. In 2006 she was appointed as Associate Professor at the Department of Biochemistry and Molecular Biology, where she has acted as Director of the Master&rsquo;s Degree and PhD program in Biochemistry, Molecular Biology and Biomedicine (2011-2014) and as Deputy Director of the Department (since 2014). She also holds the Full Professor Advanced Research accreditation from AQU.</p>\n<p style=\"margin-left: 1cm; text-align: justify;\">\n	She has published more than 50 peer-reviewed articles and directed national and European research projects. She is a reviewer for several national and international funding agencies and scientific journals.</p>\n','<p style=\"margin-left: 1cm; text-align: justify;\">\n	The research activity of the group is focused on the development of gene therapy strategies for diseases affecting the nervous system, both central (lysosomal storage diseases) and peripheral (pain, genetic and acquired neuropathies) and on the elucidation of the molecular mechanisms implicated in the development of these pathologies combining the use of animal models, tissue cell culture and viral vectors.</p>\n<p style=\"margin-left: 1cm; text-align: justify;\">\n	Funding: ISCIII; MINECO; EU; Feder-EU; AGAUR, Marat&oacute; TV3; Genzyme.</p>\n','<p style=\"margin-left: 1cm;\">\n	See all publications fo A.Bosch at <a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/49708436/public/\" target=\"_blank\">PubMed</a>.</p>\n<p style=\"margin-left: 1cm;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>SELECTED PUBLICATIONS</strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n	<li style=\"margin-left: 1cm;\">\n		R. Thwaite, G. Pages, M. Chillon, and A. Bosch. AAVrh.10 immunogenicity in mice and humans. relevance of antibody cross-reactivity in human gene therapy. Gene Therapy: 22: 196-201. 2015.</li>\n	<li style=\"margin-left: 1cm;\">\n		L. Ariza, G. Pag&egrave;s, B. Garc&iacute;a-Lareu, X. Navarro, M. Chillon, J. Ruberte, P.Otaegui, and A. Bosch. Experimental diabetes in neonatal mice induces early peripheral sensorimotor neuropathy. Neuroscience: 274:250-9. 2014.</li>\n	<li style=\"margin-left: 1cm;\">\n		L. Ariza, L. Gim&eacute;nez-Llort, A. Cubizolle, G. Pag&egrave;s, B. Garc&iacute;a-Lareu, N. Serratrice, D. Cots, M. Chillon, E. Kremer and A. Bosch. CNS delivery of helper-dependent canine adenovirus corrects neuropathology and behavior in Mucopolysaccharidosis type VII mice. Human Gene Therapy: 25(3):199-211. 2014.</li>\n	<li style=\"margin-left: 1cm;\">\n		J. Homs, G. Pages, L. Ariza, C. Casas, M. Chillon, X. Navarro, A. Bosch. Intrathecal Administration of IGF-I by AAVrh10 Improves Sensory and Motor Deficits in a Mouse Model of Diabetic Neuropathy. Molecular Therapy-Methods &amp; Clinical Development: Jan 15;1:7. 2014.</li>\n	<li style=\"margin-left: 1cm;\">\n		M. Chillon and A. Bosch (Editors). Adenovirus: Methods and Protocols. Methods Molecular Biology, Third Edition, New York, USA. Humana Press. Volumen: 1089. ISBN:978-1-62703-678-8.2014.</li>\n	<li style=\"margin-left: 1cm;\">\n		E. Gil, A. Bosch, D. Lampe, J. M. Lizcano, J. C. Perales, O. Danos, M. Chillon. Functional characterization of the human mariner transposase Hsmar2. Plos One: 8(9): e73227:1-12. 2013.</li>\n</ul>\n','<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0002-7205-2796\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/orcid.png\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"http://www.researcherid.com/rid/C-7593-2015\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/RID.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.uri?authorId=7101699999\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Assumpcio_Bosch\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/researchgate.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n			<td>\n				&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"https://es.linkedin.com/pub/assumpció-bosch/2b/b33/781\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Linkedin.jpg\" style=\"width: 35px; height: 29px;\" /></a></td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n'),(237,13,0,'Miguel ','Chillón Rodríguez','ICREA research professor','H-504','','+34 935 814 199','miguel.chillon@uab.cat','<p>\n	Department of Biochemistry and Molecular Biology<br />\n	<em>Institut de Neuroci&egrave;ncies</em><br />\n	CBATEG (room H-504)<br />\n	<em>Universitat Aut&ograve;noma de Barcelona (UAB)</em><br />\n	Bellaterra Campus 08193-Cerdanyola del Vall&eacute;s</p>\n','237mchillon2.jpg','<p style=\"margin-left: 1cm; text-align: justify;\">\n	Born in Barcelona in 1966. PhD in Genetics at Hospital Duran i Reynals and Universitat de Barcelona, 1994. National Award in Human Genetics by the Spanish Association of Human Genetics in 1995. HHMI postdoctoral fellow on Gene Therapy for Cystic Fibrosis, at the Internal Medicine Dept, University of Iowa, USA (1994-1997). EMBO fellow in Genethon III (Evry, France) (1997-1999) on Development of viral vectors for Gene Therapy. Postdoctoral fellow on Gene Therapy (2000-2001) at the Universitat Aut&ograve;noma de Barcelona (UAB). ICREA Research Professor at the UAB since 2001. Scientific Responsible of the Vector Production Unit, a technological platform to produce viral vectors, since 2004. Assistant Professor of the Biochemistry and Molecular Biology Dept. at the UAB since 2005. Member of the Biosafety Committee of the UAB since 2006. Co-founder of NanoTherapix, a spin-off company in biotechnology, in 2009. He has published more than 70 papers and generated 7 patents in viral vectors.</p>\n<p style=\"margin-left:1.0cm;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n','<p style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>RESEARCH LINES</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"margin-left: 1cm; text-align: justify;\">\n	1) Molecular mechanisms involved in memory formation: Study of altered signaling pathways in CNS in aging and in Alzheimer&#39;s Disease</p>\n<p style=\"margin-left: 1cm; text-align: justify;\">\n	2) Gene Therapy Strategies for Esclerosis Multiple, an autoimmune disease affecting the nervous system</p>\n<p style=\"margin-left: 1cm; text-align: justify;\">\n	3) Generation and development of more selective and less immunogenic viral vectors</p>\n<p style=\"margin-left: 1cm; text-align: justify;\">\n	<a href=\"http://sct.uab.cat/upv/ \">http://sct.uab.cat/upv/ </a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-left: 1cm;\">\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color: rgb(128, 0, 0);\"><strong>FUNDING</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"margin-left: 1cm; text-align: justify;\">\n	ISC-III (#PI15-01270); EU (FP7-286071-BRAINVECTORS), AGAUR ((2014-SGR-1354)), Fundaci&oacute;n Genzyme en Esclerosis M&uacute;ltiple, Agreements with private biotech-companies.</p>\n<p st