csCKeditor/images/orcid.png\" style=\"width: 26px; height: 26px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researcherid.com/rid/C-7977-2011\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/RID.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=6701731005\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 29px; height: 29px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researchgate.net/profile/Roser_Nadal2\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"27\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/researchgate.jpg\" width=\"27\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.mendeley.com/profiles/roser-nadal/\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"28\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/mendeley.png\" width=\"28\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<p>\n					&nbsp;</p>\n				<div>\n					Ra&uuml;l Andero Gal&iacute;</div>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:Raul.Andero@uab.cat\">Raul.Andero@uab.cat</a></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				TEL: +34 935 813 342</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<table>\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								<table>\n									<tbody>\n										<tr>\n											<td>\n												<a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3641-8903\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/orcid.png\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n											<td>\n												&nbsp;</td>\n											<td>\n												<a href=\"https://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.uri?authorId=16066765200\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n											<td>\n												<a href=\"https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Rauel_Andero_Gali\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/researchgate.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n											<td>\n												<a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/ra%C3%BCl-andero-gal%C3%AD-2a177a46/en\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Linkedin.jpg\" style=\"width: 35px; height: 29px;\" /></a><a href=\"https://scholar.google.es/citations?view_op=list_works&amp;hl=es&amp;user=ORHEFhUAAAAJ\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"29\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/googlescholar.jpg\" width=\"31\" /></a></td>\n										</tr>\n									</tbody>\n								</table>\n							</td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Untitled design(1).jpg\" style=\"width: 500px;\" /></p>\n<div>\n	<strong>Membres del Grup:</strong></div>\n<div>\n	Francesc Xavier Belda &nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\n	Javier Carrasco<br />\n	In&eacute;s Cord&oacute;n<br />\n	Silvia Fuentes<br />\n	Humberto Gagliano<br />\n	Juan Antonio Ortega<br />\n	Jordi Pastor<br />\n	Mar&iacute;a Sanchis<br />\n	&nbsp;</div>\n<p>\n	Visiteu tamb&eacute;:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.nea-uab.org/ca/\" target=\"_blank\">La WEB de Neurobiologia de l&rsquo;Estr&egrave;s i l&rsquo;Addicci&oacute;</a><br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>OBJECTIUS ESTRAT&Egrave;GICS</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	1. Comprensi&oacute; del processament cerebral dels est&iacute;muls estressants i la utilitat dels diferents marcadors biol&ograve;gics de l&rsquo;activaci&oacute; neuronal.<br />\n	<br />\n	2. Processos i mecanismes involucrats en l&rsquo;adaptaci&oacute; a l&rsquo;estr&egrave;s cr&ograve;nic.<br />\n	<br />\n	3. Impacte de l&rsquo;estr&egrave;s en psicopatologia i mecanismes neurobiol&ograve;gics subjacents.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PRINCIPALS L&Iacute;NIES D&#39;INVESTIGACI&Oacute;</strong></span><br />\n	<br />\n	1. Identificar les &agrave;rees encef&agrave;liques i els fenotipus neuronals activats per l&rsquo;exposici&oacute; als est&iacute;muls estressants emocionals i farmacol&ograve;gics (ex. drogues addictives). Utilitzem gens d&rsquo;expressi&oacute; immediata (IEGs) com el c-fos i l&rsquo;arc i canvis epigen&egrave;tics (ex. fosforilaci&oacute; i acetilaci&oacute; d&rsquo;histones). La nostra hip&ograve;tesi &eacute;s que els canvis epigen&egrave;tics estan m&eacute;s restringits que l&rsquo;expressi&oacute; dels IEGs i que poden ajudar a identificar &agrave;rees cerebrals i tipus de neurones cr&iacute;tiques. Amb aquestes eines estem explorant com l&rsquo;exposici&oacute; simult&agrave;nia a dos est&iacute;muls estressants, o a un est&iacute;mul estressant i una droga addictiva,&nbsp; interacciona en el cervell.<br />\n	<br />\n	2. Despr&eacute;s de l&rsquo;exposici&oacute; repetida a un rang ampli d&rsquo;est&iacute;muls estressants predominantment emocionals, hi ha una reducci&oacute; de la resposta al mateix (homot&iacute;pic) est&iacute;mul estressant, la qual s&rsquo;observa a nivell fisiol&ograve;gic (ex. hormones de l&rsquo;eix hipot&agrave;lem-hipofis&agrave;ri-adrenal o HPA) i conductual. L&rsquo;adaptaci&oacute; tamb&eacute; s&rsquo;observa a nivell de l&rsquo;expressi&oacute; cerebral dels IEGs. Els nostres objectius principals s&oacute;n identificar els processos cognitius i emocionals involucrats en l&rsquo;adaptaci&oacute;, aix&iacute; com les &agrave;rees cerebrals i els mecanismes neuroqu&iacute;mics involucrats. Una de les nostres hip&ograve;tesis principals &eacute;s que l&rsquo;adaptaci&oacute; a l&rsquo;estr&egrave;s repetit no &eacute;s un simple proc&eacute;s d&rsquo;habituaci&oacute;, com s&rsquo;assumeix&nbsp; normalment, sin&oacute; que &eacute;s un proc&eacute;s cerebral complex que involucra aspectes cognitius i senyals associatius. Una segona hip&ograve;tesi &eacute;s que l&rsquo;adaptaci&oacute; a l&rsquo;estr&egrave;s &eacute;s tan dif&iacute;cil de bloquejar farmacol&ograve;gicament o mitjan&ccedil;ant lesions cerebrals perqu&egrave; probablement involucra diferents &agrave;rees cerebrals i diferents processos neuroqu&iacute;mics que actuen en paral&middot;lel i de forma redundant.<br />\n	<br />\n	3. S&rsquo;ha reconegut durant d&egrave;cades que l&rsquo;exposici&oacute; a l&rsquo;estr&egrave;s en humans est&agrave; involucrada en el desenvolupament de psicopatologies incloent l&rsquo;ansietat, la depressi&oacute; i l&rsquo;addicci&oacute; a drogues. M&eacute;s recentment s&rsquo;ha demostrat que una simple exposici&oacute; a certs est&iacute;muls estressants d&rsquo;una certa intensitat pot produir canvis neuroendocrins, cognitius i emocionals de llarga durada, evocadors dels que es troben en el trastorn d&rsquo;estr&egrave;s post-traum&agrave;tic (PTSD). El nostre prop&ograve;sit &eacute;s caracteritzar les propietats dels est&iacute;muls estressants que determinen el seu impacte psicopatol&ograve;gic, aix&iacute; com les bases biol&ograve;giques de les difer&egrave;ncies individuals en la resist&egrave;ncia o vulnerabilitat a les conseq&uuml;&egrave;ncies de l&rsquo;estr&egrave;s. En aquest sentit, ens centrem especialment en l&rsquo;activaci&oacute; de l&rsquo;eix HPA i en el seu regulador cerebral clau, el factor/hormona alliberador de corticotropina (CRF o CRH) el qual s&rsquo;ha demostrat ser un nexe biol&ograve;gic cr&iacute;tic entre estr&egrave;s i psicopatologia. A m&eacute;s, hem obtingut evid&egrave;ncies que l&rsquo;activaci&oacute; de les vies del BDNF-trkB en &agrave;rees cr&iacute;tiques com la formaci&oacute; hipoc&agrave;mpica i l&rsquo;am&iacute;gdala poden ser tamb&eacute; importants per limitar les conseq&uuml;&egrave;ncies negatives dels est&iacute;muls estressants severs.</p>\n<table align=\"left\" border=\"2\" height=\"48\" width=\"402\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"background-color: rgb(204, 0, 51);\">\n				<span style=\"color:#000000;\"><strong>GRUP SGR 2014-1020</strong></span></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"background-color: rgb(204, 0, 51);\">\n				<span style=\"color:#000000;\"><strong>Coordinaci&oacute;: Antonio Armario</strong></span></td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<h2>\n	&nbsp;</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<br />\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>DARRERES PUBLICACIONS</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	&bull; Souza Queiroz J, Mar&iacute;n Blasco I, Gagliano H, Daviu N, G&oacute;mez Rom&aacute;n A, Belda X, Carrasco J, Rocha MC, Palermo Neto J, Armario A. <em>Chlorella vulgaris reduces the impact of stress on hypothalamic-pituitary-adrenal axis and brain c-fos expression</em>. Psychoneuroendocrinology. <strong>2015</strong>;65:1-8.</p>\n<p>\n	&bull; Lalanza JF, Sanchez-Roige S, Cigarroa I, Gagliano H, Fuentes S, Armario A, Capdevila L, Escorihuela RM. <em>Long-term moderate treadmill exercise promotes stress-coping strategies in male and female rats.</em> Sci Rep. <strong>2015</strong>;5:16166.</p>\n<p>\n	&bull; Aguil&oacute; J, Ferrer-Salvans P, Garc&iacute;a-Rozo A, Armario A, Corb&iacute; &Aacute;, Cambra FJ, Bail&oacute;n R, Gonz&aacute;lez-Marcos A, Caja G, Aguil&oacute; S, L&oacute;pez-Ant&oacute;n R, Arza-Vald&eacute;s A, Garz&oacute;n-Rey JM. <em>Project ES3: attempting to quantify and measure the level of stress</em>. Rev Neurol. <strong>2015</strong>;61(9):405-15.</p>\n<p>\n	&bull; Belda X, Fuentes S, Daviu N, Nadal R, Armario A. <em>Stress-induced sensitization: the hypothalamic-pituitary-adrenal axis and beyond</em>. Stress, <strong>2015</strong>, 18:269-79.</p>\n<p>\n	&bull; L&oacute;pez-Moreno JA, Marcos M, Calleja-Conde J, Echeverry-Alzate V, B&uuml;hler K, Costa-Alba P, Bernardo E, Laso FJ, Rodr&iacute;guez de Fonseca F, Nadal R, Viveros MP, Maldonado R, Gin&eacute; E. <em>Histone deacetylase gene expression following binge alcohol consumption in rats and humans</em> Alcohol Clin Exp Res. <strong>2015</strong>, 39:1939-50.</p>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830297/public/\" target=\"_blank\">Veure m&eacute;s publicacions de A. Armario a PubMed.</a></p>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48831252/public/\" target=\"_blank\">Veure m&eacute;s&nbsp; publicacions de R. Nadal a PubMed.</a></p>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=andero+r\">Veure m&eacute;s publicacions de R. Andero a </a><a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=andero+r\" target=\"_blank\">PubMed</a></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n',13,2,0),(262,30,0,'Albert BADIA i Victoria CLOS','<h2>\n	<strong><span style=\"color:#800000;\">Grup de Neurofarmacologia</span></strong></h2>\n<p>\n	<strong>L&iacute;ders del Grup:</strong><br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<table style=\"width: 100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				Albert Badia Sancho</td>\n			<td>\n				Vict&ograve;ria Clos Guill&eacute;n</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:albert.badia@uab.cat\">albert.badia@uab.cat</a></td>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:victoria.clos@uab.cat\">victoria.clos@uab.cat</a></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				+34 93 581 1964</td>\n			<td>\n				+34 93 581 1963</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<table>\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researcherid.com/rid/F-9693-2011\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/RID.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=7005737400\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 29px; height: 29px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researchgate.net/profile/Albert_Badia2\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"28\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/researchgate.jpg\" width=\"28\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n				<table>\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=35582392100\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 29px; height: 29px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/Closdef.jpg\" style=\"width: 100%; margin-top: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px;\" /></p>\n<p>\n	<strong>Membres del Grup:</strong><br />\n	Bel&eacute;n P&eacute;rez Fern&aacute;ndez<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>OBJECTIUS ESTRAT&Egrave;GICS</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	El principal objectiu del&nbsp;Grup de Neurofarmacologia&nbsp;&eacute;s l&#39;estudi de l&#39;activitat i funcions de la acetilcolinesterasa (ACHE) i la seva inhibici&oacute; mitjan&ccedil;ant inhibidors d&rsquo;aquest enzim, ja que fins ara representen el tractament m&eacute;s reeixit de la malaltia d&#39;Alzheimer. Considerant el mecanisme d&#39;acci&oacute; dels inhibidors d&#39;acetilcolinesterasa (IAChE), s&#39;esperava que poguessin tant sols mitigar temporalment alguns dels s&iacute;mptomes. No obstant aix&ograve;, estudis cl&iacute;nics han posat de manifest que els AChEI no nom&eacute;s incrementen la disponibilitat de la ACh en els malalts d&#39;Alzheimer sin&oacute; que poden actuar com a modificadors de la malaltia. D&#39;altra banda, la AChE es troba en teixit neuronal i no neuronal desenvolupant tamb&eacute; funciones no can&ograve;niques. Aquestes funcions no catal&iacute;tiques estan implicades en la morfog&egrave;nesi, hematopoiesi, osteog&egrave;nesi, apoptosi i en la neurog&egrave;nesi. Aquestes funcions s&#39;han relacionat amb dues variants de la ACh: &quot;sin&agrave;ptica&quot; ACHE-S un enzim de membrana (multim&egrave;rica) i a la ACh-R &quot;readthrough&quot; soluble i monom&egrave;rica. En general, ambdues isoformes de ACHE s&oacute;n indu&iuml;bles per lesions neuronals o per IAChE, per&ograve;, l&#39;expressi&oacute; de ACHE-R sembla estar relacionada amb la neuroprotecci&oacute; i reparaci&oacute;, mentre ACHE-S est&agrave; associada de forma majorit&agrave;ria amb lesions i augment de la neurotoxicitat . D&#39;acord amb aix&ograve;, el principal objectiu del nostre projecte &eacute;s analitzar l&#39;efecte dels nous IAChE (huprinas i heterod&iacute;mers) sobre l&#39;expressi&oacute; de les dues variants de ACHE (-S i-R) en diferents condicions experimentals i aproximacions in vitro i in vivo, tenint en compte els processos neurot&ograve;xic i neurog&egrave;nic. L&#39;objectiu ens permetr&agrave; aprofundir en el mecanisme d&#39;acci&oacute; dels IAChE i obtenir informaci&oacute; addicional sobre el paper i les funcions de les isoformes de la ACHE.<br />\n	D&#39;altra banda, i en col&bull;laboraci&oacute; amb el grup de Qu&iacute;mica Farmac&egrave;utica de la Facultat de&nbsp;<br />\n	farm&agrave;cia de la Universitat de Barcelona, estem realitzant la caracteritzaci&oacute; del perfil farmacol&ograve;gic de nous compostos heterodim&egrave;rics amb funcions multidiana, relacionades totes elles amb els factors neuropatol&ograve;gics caracter&iacute;stics de la malaltia de Alzheimer.<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong><span style=\"color:#800000;\">PRINCIPALS L&Iacute;NIES D&#39;INVESTIGACI&Oacute;&nbsp;</span></strong><br />\n	<br />\n	&nbsp;Neurofarmacologia dels trastorns neurodegenaratius:</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	- Sistema colin&egrave;rgic en el desenvolupament de la malaltia d&#39;Alzheimer: paper de les diferents variants de AChE i f&agrave;rmacs anticolinester&agrave;sics en la neurog&egrave;nesi i els processos de neurodegeneraci&oacute;.<br />\n	- L&#39;avaluaci&oacute; farmacol&ograve;gica de nous f&agrave;rmacs multifuncionals.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>DARRERES PUBLICACIONS</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; Di Pietro O, Viayna E, Vicente-Garc&iacute;a E, Bartolini M, Ram&oacute;n R, Ju&aacute;rez-Jim&eacute;nez J, Clos MV, P&eacute;rez B, Andrisano V, Luque FJ, Lavilla R, Mu&ntilde;oz-Torrero D.<em><a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24389509\"><br />\n	1,2,3,4-Tetrahydrobenzo[h][1,6]naphthyridines as a new family of potent peripheral-to-midgorge-site inhibitors of acetylcholinesterase: Synthesis, pharmacological evaluation and mechanistic studies.</a></em><br />\n	Eur J Med Chem. <strong>2014</strong>;73:141-52.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; Viayna E, Sola I, Bartolini M, De Simone A, Tapia-Rojas C, Serrano FG, Sabat&eacute; R, Ju&aacute;rez-Jim&eacute;nez J, P&eacute;rez B, Luque FJ, Andrisano V, Clos MV, Inestrosa NC, Mu&ntilde;oz-Torrero D.<em><a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24568372\"><br />\n	Synthesis and multi-target biological profiling of a novel family of rhein derivatives as disease-modifying anti-Alzheimer agents.</a></em><br />\n	J Med Chem. <strong>2014</strong> . [Epub ahead of print]</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pera M.,&nbsp; Camps P.,&nbsp; Munoz-Torrero D., Perez B., Badia A.,Clos MV.<br />\n	<em>Undifferentiated and Differentiated PC12 Cells Protected by Huprines Against Injury Induced by Hydrogen Peroxide.</em><br />\n	PloS ONE 8(9): e74344. <strong>2013</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ratia M, Gim&eacute;nez-Llort L, Camps P, Mu&ntilde;oz-Torrero D, P&eacute;rez B, Clos MV, Badia A.<br />\n	<em>Huprine X and Huperzine A Improve Cognition and Regulate Some Neurochemical Processes Related with Alzheimer&#39;s Disease in Triple Transgenic Mice (3xTg-AD).</em><br />\n	Neurodegener Dis.&nbsp;<strong>2013</strong>;11(3):129-40.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Galdeano C, Viayna E, Sola I, Formosa X, Camps P, Badia A, Clos MV, Relat J, Ratia M, Bartolini M, Mancini F, Andrisano V, Salmona M, Minguill&oacute;n C, Gonz&aacute;lez-Mu&ntilde;oz GC, Rodr&iacute;guez-Franco MI, Bidon-Chanal A, Luque FJ, Mu&ntilde;oz-Torrero D.<br />\n	<em>Huprine-tacrine heterodimers as anti-amyloidogenic compounds of potential interest against Alzheimer&#39;s and prion diseases.</em><br />\n	J Med Chem.&nbsp;<strong>2012</strong>&nbsp; 26;55(2):661-9.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/49667007/public/\" target=\"_blank\">Veure m&eacute;s publicacions de A. Badia a PubMed.</a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830631/public/\" target=\"_blank\">Veure m&eacute;s publicacions de V. Clos a PubMed.</a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n',14,2,0),(263,30,0,'José Ramón BAYASCAS','<p>\n	<a href=\"javascript:MostraPage(294,1);\">Neurodegeneraci&oacute; i envelliment</a></p>\n<h2>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\">Senyalitzacio en el Sistema Nervi&oacute;s Central</span></h2>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong>L&iacute;der del grup:</strong></p>\n<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				Jos&eacute; Ram&oacute;n Bayascas</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:joseramon.bayascas@uab.cat\">joseramon.bayascas@uab.cat</a></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				TEL: +34 935 813 762</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<table>\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0002-6096-2151\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/orcid.png\" style=\"width: 26px; height: 26px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researcherid.com/rid/C-9450-2011\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/RID.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=6602348616\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 29px; height: 29px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researchgate.net/profile/Jose_Bayascas/publications\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"28\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/researchgate.jpg\" width=\"27\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://scholar.google.com/citations?user=49L6LNQAAAAJ&amp;hl=es\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"28\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/googlescholar.jpg\" width=\"29\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"https://es.linkedin.com/pub/jose-r-bayascas/34/6b6/357\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"33\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Linkedin.jpg\" width=\"42\" /></a></td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/bayascas2014.jpg\" style=\"width: 100%;\" /></p>\n<p>\n	<strong>Membres del grup:</strong><br />\n	LLu&iacute;s Cord&oacute;n Barris<br />\n	Xiangyu Zhou<br />\n	<br />\n	<br />\n	<strong>Membres anteriors:</strong><br />\n	Tinatin Zurashvili<br />\n	Patricia Ortega<br />\n	Juuli Lamberg<br />\n	Esther Caba&ntilde;as<br />\n	Natalia Gorska<br />\n	Laura Kempainnen &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\n	Anna Santaella<br />\n	Shaobin Yang</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>OBJECTIUS ESTRAT&Egrave;GICS</strong></span><br />\n	<br />\n	1) Generar ratolins knock-in condicionals de PDK1 que expressen els alels mutants de PDK Lys465Glu i Leu155Glu de manera espec&iacute;fica en neurones.<br />\n	2) Analitzar el fenotip dels ratolins knock-in condicionals de PDK1.<br />\n	3) Investigar la contribuci&oacute; relativa de les isoformes de PKB, en comparaci&oacute; amb la resta de substrats de PDK1, en la superviv&egrave;ncia neuronal i la diferenciaci&oacute; de cultius primaris de neurones despr&eacute;s d&rsquo;estimulaci&oacute; amb factors neurotr&ograve;fics i sota estr&egrave;s cel.lular.<br />\n	4) Dilucidar la participaci&oacute; dels substrats PDK1 en les vies de senyalitzaci&oacute; intracel.lular indu&iuml;da per factors neurotr&ograve;fics. L&#39;activaci&oacute; i la fosforilaci&oacute; dels substrats fisiol&ograve;gics de PKB implicats en la superviv&egrave;ncia cel lular, aix&iacute; com dels de S6K implicats en la s&iacute;ntesi de prote&iuml;nes i el control del creixement cel lular, seran avaluats.<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PRINCIPALS L&Iacute;NIES D&#39;INVESTIGACI&Oacute;&nbsp;</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	Funci&oacute; de la via de senyalitzaci&oacute; de PDK1 en la superviv&egrave;ncia neuronal: Generaci&oacute; de ratolins knock-in condicionals de PDK1 espec&iacute;fics de sistema nervi&oacute;s.<br />\n	<br />\n	L&#39;objectiu principal d&#39;aquest projecte &eacute;s la caracteritzaci&oacute; de dues soques de ratolins que expressen de forma condicional les mutacions PDK1 Lys465Glu (K465E) i PDK1 Leu155Glu (L155E). Aquestes formes mutants de PDK1 no s&oacute;n capaces d&#39;activar les isoformes de PKB, o altres substrats de PKB (S6K, SGK, RSK i PKC), respectivament. El alel condicional de PDK1 s&#39;expressa en poblacions neuronals espec&iacute;fiques per mitj&agrave; de la tecnologia de la Cre-recombinasa per avaluar la contribuci&oacute; relativa de les isoformes de PKB, en comparaci&oacute; amb la dels altres substrats de PDK1, a la superviv&egrave;ncia d&#39;aquestes poblacions neuronals.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PUBLICACIONS</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull; &nbsp;&nbsp;Zurashvili T, Cord&oacute;n-Barris L, Ruiz-Babot G, Zhou X, Lizcano JM, G&oacute;mez N, Gim&eacute;nez-Llort L, Bayascas JR.&nbsp;<br />\n	Interaction of PDK1&nbsp;with&nbsp;phosphoinositides is essential for neuronal differentiation, but dispensable for neuronal survival.&nbsp;<br />\n	Mol Cell Biol. 2013 Mar;33(5):1027-40.<br />\n	<br />\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Bayascas JR.&nbsp;<br />\n	PDK1: the major transducer of PI 3-kinase actions.&nbsp;<br />\n	Curr Top Microbiol Immunol.&nbsp;2010; 346: 9-29.&nbsp;</p>\n<div>\n	&bull; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Zhou X, Cordon-Barris L, Zurashvili T, Bayascas JR.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>\n	Fine-tuning the intensity of the PKB/Akt signal enables diverse physiological responses. Cell Cycle.&nbsp;2014;13(20):3164-8.</div>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Bayascas JR, Wullschleger S, Sakamoto K, Garc&iacute;a-Mart&iacute;nez JM, Clacher C, Komander D, van Aalten DM, Boini KM, Lang F, Lipina C, Logie L, Sutherland C, Chudek JA, van Diepen JA, Voshol PJ, Lucocq JM, Alessi DR.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	Mutation of the PDK1 PH domain inhibits protein kinase B/Akt, leading to small size and insulin resistance.<br />\n	Mol Cell Biol.&nbsp;2008 ;28(10):3258-72.&nbsp;<br />\n	<br />\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Bayascas JR.&nbsp;<br />\n	Dissecting the role of the 3-phosphoinositide-dependent protein kinase-1 (PDK1) signalling pathways.&nbsp;<br />\n	Cell Cycle.&nbsp;2008;7(19):2978-82.<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830639/public/\" target=\"_blank\">Veure m&eacute;s publicacions de JR: Bayascas a PubMed. </a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;