f=\"https://www.linkedin.com/pub/bernardo-castellano-l%C3%B3pez/2a/218/7a8?trk=pub-pbmap\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"32\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Linkedin.jpg\" width=\"41\" /></a></td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n				<table>\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=7102739324\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"29\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" width=\"29\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/Castdef.jpg\" style=\"width: 100%; margin-top: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px;\" /><br />\n	<br />\n	<strong>Membres del Grup:</strong><br />\n	Beatriz Almolda<br />\n	<a href=\"http://inc.uab.cat/Catala/profile.php?id=21\">Isabella Appiah</a><br />\n	Anna Camps<br />\n	Miguel A. Martil<br />\n	Filip Petkovic<br />\n	Mireia Recasens<br />\n	Nadia Villacampa</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>OBJECTIUS ESTRAT&Egrave;GICS</strong></span><br />\n	<br />\n	&bull;Identificar els senyals que controlen l&#39;activaci&oacute; de les c&egrave;l&middot;lules glials en diferents paradigmes<br />\n	&bull;Identificar les vies de senyalitzaci&oacute; que poden ser una possible diana d&#39;interacci&oacute; per evitar la neurodegeneraci&oacute; i promoure la regeneraci&oacute;<br />\n	&bull;Identificar la pres&egrave;ncia de c&egrave;l&middot;lules presentadores d&#39;ant&iacute;gens en el SNC tant en condicions normals com patol&ograve;giques<br />\n	&bull;Identificar les senyals que intervenen en la regulaci&oacute; de la resposta inflamat&ograve;ria i immunit&agrave;ria en el SNC<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PRINCIPALS L&Iacute;NIES D&#39;INVESTIGACI&Oacute;</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	1) Estudi de la senyalitzaci&oacute; diferencial i mecanismes moleculars implicats en la modulaci&oacute; de l&#39;activaci&oacute;, proliferaci&oacute; i mort de les c&egrave;l&middot;lules glials en diferents models experimentals d&#39;immunitat innata i adquirida: lesions excitot&ograve;xiques, axotomia del nervi facial, desaferentitzaci&oacute; de la f&agrave;scia dentada de l&#39;hipocamp , inducci&oacute; d&#39;encefalopatia autoimmune experimental (EAE), etc.<br />\n	2) Implicaci&oacute; de les c&egrave;l&middot;lules glials en la regulaci&oacute; de la resposta inflamat&ograve;ria i immunit&agrave;ria associada. Especialment estem interessats en estudiar la regulaci&oacute; que exerceixen les c&egrave;l&middot;lules microglials, macr&ograve;fags i c&egrave;l&middot;lules dendr&iacute;tiques en la modulaci&oacute; de l&#39;entrada, activaci&oacute;, proliferaci&oacute;, anergia i apoptosi de limf&ograve;cits infiltrats. Aquests estudis el&rsquo;s desenvolupem en rata Lewis i tamb&eacute; en ratolins transg&egrave;nics que sobreexpressen citocines inflamat&ograve;ries (IL6) i antiinflamat&ograve;ries (IL10).<br />\n	3) Estudi dels canvis en l&#39;expressi&oacute; de mol&egrave;cules de la matriu extracel&middot;lular i dels seus receptors cel&middot;lulars, les integrines, en neurones i c&egrave;l&middot;lules glials en diferents paradigmes de dany cerebral: excitotoxicitat, axotomia i EAE en rates i ratolins normals i tamb&eacute; en ratolins transg&egrave;nics que sobreexpressen IL6 i IL10.<br />\n	4) Interacci&oacute; amb els mecanismes que regulen en el SNC l&#39;expressi&oacute; d&#39;enzims i citocines inflamat&ograve;ries d&#39;origen glial mitjan&ccedil;ant la utilitzaci&oacute; de f&agrave;rmacs inhibidors dels factors de transcripci&oacute; implicats en l&#39;activaci&oacute; de micr&ograve;glia i astr&ograve;glia, per tal de reduir la mort neuronal secund&agrave;ria subseg&uuml;ent a una lesi&oacute; experimental.<br />\n	5) Avaluaci&oacute; de la possible utilitzaci&oacute; de complexos moleculars d&#39;origen no-v&iacute;ric com a vectors en estrat&egrave;gies de ter&agrave;pia g&egrave;nica per promoure la neuroprotecci&oacute;.</p>\n<table align=\"left\" border=\"2\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"background-color: rgb(204, 0, 51);\">\n				<strong><span style=\"color:#000000;\">GRUP SGR 2014 1464</span></strong></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"background-color: rgb(204, 0, 51);\">\n				<span style=\"color:#000000;\"><strong>Coordinaci&oacute;: Bernardo Castellano</strong></span></td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PUBLICACIONS SELECCIONADES</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	&bull; &nbsp;&nbsp; Almolda B, Villacampa N, Manders P, Hidalgo J, Campbell IL, Gonz&aacute;lez B and Castellano B.<br />\n	<em>Effects of astrocyte-targeted production of interleukin-6 in the mouse on the host response to nerve injury.</em><br />\n	Glia, 62: 1142- 1161 (<strong>2014</strong>)</p>\n<p>\n	&bull; &nbsp;&nbsp; Almolda B., Gonz&aacute;lez B. and B. Castellano<br />\n	<em>Microglia detection by enzymatic histochemistry.</em><br />\n	Methods Mol Biol 1041: 243-59 (<strong>2013</strong>)</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp; Gonzalez P., Peluffo H., Acarin L., Villaverde A., Gonzalez B.&nbsp; and Castellano B.<br />\n	<em>Interleukin-10 overexpression does not synergize with the neuroprotective action of RGD-containing vectors after postnatal brain excitotoxicity but modulates the main inflammatory cell&nbsp;responses.</em><br />\n	J Neurosci Res. 90:143-59 (<strong>2012</strong>)</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull; &nbsp;&nbsp; Almolda B., Costa M., Montoya M., Gonz&aacute;lez B. and Castellano B.<br />\n	<em>Increase in Th17 and T-reg lymphocytes and decrease of IL22 correlate with the recovery phase of acute EAE in rat.</em><br />\n	PLoS One,&nbsp;2011;6(11):e27473. (<strong>2011</strong>)</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull; &nbsp;&nbsp; Almolda B., Gonz&aacute;lez B. and Castellano B<br />\n	<em>Antigen presentation in EAE: role of microglia, macrophages and dendritic cells.</em><br />\n	Frontiers in Biosciences, 16:1157-71,&nbsp;Review (<strong>2011</strong>)<br />\n	<br />\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830665/public/\" target=\"_blank\">Veure m&eacute;s publicacions de B. Castellano a PubMed.</a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830680/public/\" target=\"_blank\">Veure m&eacute;s publicacions de B. Gonz&aacute;lez a PubMed.</a><br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n',16,2,0),(265,30,0,'Enrique CLARO i Fernando PICATOSTE','<p>\n	<a href=\"javascript:MostraPage(294,1); \">Neurodegeneraci&oacute; i envelliment</a></p>\n<h2>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>Metabolisme dels L&iacute;pids i la Mort&nbsp; Cel&middot;lular</strong></span></h2>\n<p>\n	<strong>L&iacute;ders del grup:</strong></p>\n<table style=\"width: 100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				Enrique Claro</td>\n			<td>\n				Fernando Picatoste</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:enrique.claro@uab.es\">enrique.claro@uab.es</a></td>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:fernando.picatoste@uab.cat\">fernando.picatoste@uab.cat</a></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				+34 935814150</td>\n			<td>\n				+34 935811574</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<table>\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0002-7592-7906\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/orcid.png\" style=\"width: 26px; height: 26px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researcherid.com/rid/D-5612-2009\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/RID.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"https://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=7003847422\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 29px; height: 29px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researchgate.net/profile/Enrique_Claro\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/researchgate.jpg\" style=\"width: 27px; height: 27px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n				<table>\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								<p>\n									<a href=\"https://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=6701819691\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 29px; height: 29px;\" /></a></p>\n							</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/ClaPidef.jpg\" style=\"width: 100%; margin-top: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px;\" /><br />\n	<strong>Membres del grup:</strong><br />\n	Meritxell Asensio<br />\n	Ainara G. Cabodevilla<br />\n	<br />\n	<strong>Membres anteriors:</strong><br />\n	Alberto G. Andreolotti<br />\n	Miquel Barcel&oacute;<br />\n	David Barneda<br />\n	Albert Gubern<br />\n	Eleni Nintou<br />\n	Ra&uuml;l Pardo<br />\n	Bel&eacute;n Ramos<br />\n	Laura S&aacute;nchez</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>OBJECTIUS ESTRAT&Egrave;GICS</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	Volem explicar algunes funcions del metabolisme de fosfol&iacute;pids en els processos fisiol&ograve;gics com ara la mort cel&middot;lular programada, l&#39;autof&agrave;gia, i la secreci&oacute;. Fosfatidilcolina (PtdCho) &eacute;s el fosfol&iacute;pid important en les membranes cel&middot;lulars, per&ograve; la seva implicaci&oacute; en molts aspectes de la fisiologia i la patologia, alguns d&#39;ells relacionats amb el sistema nervi&oacute;s, ha comen&ccedil;at a ser desentranyat.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>L&Iacute;NIES DE RECERCA</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	1 .- Mecanismes de mort cel&middot;lular associada a la inhibici&oacute; de la s&iacute;ntesi de PtdCho<br />\n	Diversos f&agrave;rmacs inhibeixen la s&iacute;ntesi de PtdCho mitjan&ccedil;ant la seva interacci&oacute; amb la CTP: cytidylyltransferase fosfocolina (CCT), un dels&nbsp; tres enzims de la via de la CDP-colina, la qual cosa es tradueix en la inducci&oacute; de mort cel&middot;lular. En l&rsquo;actualitat estem estudiant les c&egrave;l&middot;lules CHO-MT58, que tenen una CCT&alpha; termosensible. El proc&eacute;s de mort cel&middot;lular no implica mecanismes d&#39;apoptosi, i pel que sembla es porta a terme amb els t&iacute;pics trets d&rsquo; autof&agrave;gia.<br />\n	<br />\n	2 .- La biog&egrave;nesi de les gotes de l&iacute;pids i el seu paper en la superviv&egrave;ncia cel&middot;lular<br />\n	Les gotes lip&iacute;diques (LD) s&oacute;n org&agrave;nuls que emmagatzemen triglic&egrave;rids i &egrave;sters de colesterol, d&#39;alguna manera semblants a la gran gota dels adip&ograve;cits; a difer&egrave;ncia d&#39;aquests, per&ograve;, les LD s&oacute;n molt m&eacute;s petites i es troben gaireb&eacute; a tots els tipus cel&middot;lulars incloent-hi neurones i astr&ograve;cits. Les LD s&oacute;n org&agrave;nuls molt din&agrave;mics que apareixen en el citosol quan les c&egrave;l&middot;lules capten lipoprote&iuml;nes o &agrave;cids grassos lliures del medi. Les LD apareixen tamb&eacute; en l&#39;abs&egrave;ncia de fonts externes de l&iacute;pids, en situacions d&rsquo;estr&egrave;s: en aquest cas, les LD confereixen resist&egrave;ncia a l&#39;estr&egrave;s, i els triglic&egrave;rids continguts a les LD hem vist que procedeixen dels fosfol&iacute;pids de les pr&ograve;pies membranes de la c&egrave;l&middot;lula.</p>\n<p>\n	<img alt=\"LD stained with nile red\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/Investigacio/ld-fl.jpg\" style=\"width: 50%; float: left; text-align: justify;\" /></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<img alt=\"http://inc.uab.cat/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/Investigacio/ld-tem.jpg\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/Investigacio/ld-tem.jpg\" style=\"width: 50%;\" /></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;<img alt=\"http://inc.uab.cat/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/Investigacio/1.jpg\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/Investigacio/1.jpg\" style=\"width: 100%;\" /></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PUBLICACIONS&nbsp; DESTACADES</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; Cabodevilla AG, S&aacute;nchez-Caballero L, Nintou E, Boiadjieva VG, Picatoste F, Gubern A, Claro E.<br />\n	<em>Cell survival during complete nutrient deprivation depends on lipid droplet-fueled &beta;-oxidation of fatty acids.</em><br />\n	J Biol Chem. 2013 Sep 27;288(39):27777-88.Epub <strong>2013</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A. Gubern, M. Barcel&oacute;-Torns, D. Barneda, R. Masgrau, F. Picatoste, J. Casas, J. Balsinde, M.A. Balboa, E. Claro.<br />\n	<em>Lipid droplet biogenesis induced by stress involves triacylglycerol synthesis that depends on Group VIA phospholipase A2.</em><br />\n	J Biol Chem. <strong>2009</strong>;284(9):5697-708.<br />\n	<br />\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A. Gubern, M. Barcel&oacute;-Torns, D. Barneda, J.M. L&oacute;pez, R. Masgrau, F. Picatoste, C.E. Chalfant, J. Balsinde, M.A. Balboa, E. Claro.<br />\n	<em>JNK and ceramide kinase govern the biogenesis of lipid droplets through activation of Group IVA phospholipase A2.</em><br />\n	J Biol Chem. <strong>2009</strong>;284(47):32359-69.<br />\n	<br />\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A. Gubern, J. Casas, M. Barcel&oacute;-Torns, D. Barneda, X. de la Rosa, R. Masgrau, F. Picatoste, J. Balsinde, M.A. Balboa, E. Claro.<br />\n	<em>Group IVA phospholipase A2 is necessary for the biogenesis of lipid droplets.</em><br />\n	J Biol Chem. <strong>2008</strong>;283(41):27369-82.<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830780/public/\">Veure m&eacute;s publicacions de E. Claro a PubMed.</a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830787/public/\" target=\"_blank\">Veure m&eacute;s publicacions de F. Picatoste a PubMed.</a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n',17,2,0),(267,30,0,'Rosa Maria ESCORIHUELA','<p>\n	<a href=\"javascript:MostraPage(296,1); \">Neurobiologia de la ment normal i alterada</a></p>\n<h2>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\">Estils de Vida i Salut Mental</span></h2>\n<p>\n	<strong>L&iacute;der del Grup:</strong></p>\n<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				Rosa M. Escorihuela Agull&oacute;</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:RosaMaria.Escorihuela@uab.cat\">RosaMaria.Escorihuela@uab.cat</a></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				TEL: +34 935 813 296</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<table>\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0001-9368-5173\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/orcid.png\" style=\"width: 27px; height: 27px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researcherid.com/rid/L-4524-2014\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/RID.jpg\" style=\"width: 27px; height: 27px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<p>\n									<a href=\"https://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=16938862000\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 29px; height: 29px;\" /></a></p>\n							</td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researchgate.net/profile/Rosa_Escorihuela\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/researchgate.jpg\" style=\"width: 27px; height: 27px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"https://scholar.google.es/citations?hl=ca&amp;user=rN2tDIgAAAAJ&amp;view_op=list_works\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"28\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/googlescholar.jpg\" width=\"29\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/RMescdef.jpg\" style=\"width: 100%; margin-top: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px;\" /><br />\n	<strong>Membres del Grup:</strong><br />\n	Igor Ivan Cigarroa Cuevas<br />\n	Oier Pastor</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>OBJECTIUS ESTRAT&Egrave;GICS</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	El principal objectiu del nostre programa de recerca &eacute;s avaluar el impacte a llarg termini que tenen les condicions ambientals i els h&agrave;bits de vida del subjecte en diverses etapes de la vida sobre les funcions cerebrals i la salut mental. Utilitzem l&rsquo;enriquiment ambiental, la manipulaci&oacute; infantil i, m&eacute;s recentment, l&rsquo;exercici f&iacute;sic com eines per a millorar el funcionament del cervell en l&rsquo;edat adulta i l&rsquo;envelliment. Sotmeten a les rates (mascles i femelles) a sessions de 30min d&rsquo;entrenament moderat al tap&iacute;s rodant (12m/min, 5 dies/setmana) per tal de reproduir un protocol &agrave;mpliament recomanat als humans. Estem introduint una dieta amb un alt contingut de greixos i sucres per tal d&rsquo;estudiar la interacci&oacute; de la pr&agrave;ctica regular de l&rsquo;exercici amb els mals h&agrave;bits alimentaris. Fem servir un model animal de senesc&egrave;ncia accelerada com a segona estrat&egrave;gia i col&middot;loquen a aquest tipus d&rsquo;animals en g&agrave;bies que contenen rodes d&rsquo;activitat per tal que facin exercici volunt&agrave;riament.&nbsp; Els efectes de les diferents formes d&rsquo;exercici practicat a llarg termini s&oacute;n avaluats en l&rsquo;edat adulta i en l&rsquo;envelliment a nivell conductual, bioqu&iacute;mic i fisiol&ograve;gic. Mesurem els efectes de l&rsquo;exercici sobre la funci&oacute; cardiovascular a trav&eacute;s d&rsquo;implants telem&egrave;trics col&bull;locats en la cavitat abdominal dels animals.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<br />\n	<strong><span style=\"color:#800000;\">PRINCIPALS L&Iacute;NIES D&#39;INVESTIGACI&Oacute;</span></strong><br />\n	<br />\n	1. Determinar los efectos del ejercicio moderado y regular en la ansiedad, respuesta al estr&eacute;s, depresi&oacute;n y funciones cognitivas en machos y hembras.<br />\n	2. Avaluar si l&rsquo;exercici pot disminuir el impacte del deteriorament associat a l&rsquo;envelliment i a les malalties neurodegeneratives.<br />\n	3.&nbsp; Investigar la interacci&oacute; de l&rsquo;exercici moderat i regular amb els mals h&agrave;bits alimentaris, en termes de canvis conductuals.<br />\n	4. Caracteritzar els perfils conductuals dels subjectes molt predisposats i dels subjectes poc predisposats a practicar exercici regularment i a incorporar greixos i sucres a la seva dieta.<br />\n	5. Investigar els efectes de l&rsquo;exercici com a tractament per a disminuir la impulsivitat i millorar l&rsquo;execuci&oacute; en tasques d&rsquo;atenci&oacute;.<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<br />\n	<strong><span style=\"color:#800000;\">PUBLICACIONS DESTACADES</span></strong></p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp; Lalanza, J.F., Caimari, A., Del Bas, J.M., (...), Arola, L., Escorihuela, R.M.<br />\n	<em>Effects of a post-weaning cafeteria diet in young rats: Metabolic syndrome, reduced activity and low anxiety-like behaviour</em><br />\n	PLoS ONE, <strong>2014</strong>, 9 (1), e85049</p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp; Lalanza, J.F., Sanchez-Roige, S., Gagliano, H., (...), Armario, A., Escorihuela, R.M.<br />\n	<em>Physiological and behavioural consequences of long-term moderate treadmill exercise</em><br />\n	Psychoneuroendocrinology, <strong>2012</strong> , 37 (11), pp. 1745-1754</p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp; Bayod, S., del Valle, J., Lalanza, J.F., (...), Escorihuela, R.M., Pall&agrave;s, M.<br />\n	<em>Long-term physical exercise induces changes in sirtuin 1 pathway and oxidative parameters in adult rat tissues</em><br />\n	Experimental Gerontology ,<strong>2012</strong> ,47 (12), pp. 925-935</p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp; Kaliman P, P&aacute;rrizas , Lalanza JF, Camins A,Escorihuela RM, Pall&agrave;s M.<br />\n	<em>Neurophysiological and epigenetic effects of physical exercise on the aging process.</em><br />\n	Ageing Res Rev. <strong>2011</strong> ;10(4):475-86.</p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp; Garc&iacute;a-Gonz&aacute;lez MA, Fern&aacute;ndez-Chimeno M, Ferrer J, Escorihuela RM, Parrado E, Capdevila L, Ben&iacute;tez A, Angulo R, Rodr&iacute;guez FA, Iglesias X, Besc&oacute;s R, Marina M, Padull&eacute;s JM, Ramos-Castro J.&nbsp;<br />\n	<em>New indices for quantification of the power spectrum of heart rate variability time series without the need of any frequency band definition.</em><br />\n	Physiol Meas. <strong>2011</strong>;32(8):995-1009.</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830790/public/\" target=\"_blank\">Veure m&eacute;s publicacions de RM. Escorihuela a PubMed. </a></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n',18,2,0),(268,30,0,'Ester FERNÁNDEZ','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<a href=\"javascript:MostraPage(294,1); \">Neurodegeneraci&oacute; i envelliment</a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\">Grup d&rsquo;Investigaci&oacute; en Inflamaci&oacute; i Toler&agrave;ncia: Noves aproximacions terap&egrave;utiques</span></h2>\n<p>\n	<strong>L&iacute;der del Grup:</strong></p>\n<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				Ester Fern&aacute;ndez Gimeno</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:Ester.Fernandez@uab.cat\">Ester.Fernandez@uab.cat</a></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				+34 93 581 3282</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<table>\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								<p>\n									<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=7402179023\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 29px; height: 29px;\" /></a></p>\n							</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/Eferdef.jpg\" style=\"width: 100%; margin-top: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px;\" /><br />\n	<strong>Membres del Grup:</strong><br />\n	Joan Francesc Burgue&ntilde;o Ban&uacute;s<br />\n	Elena Eyre S&aacute;nchez<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong><span style=\"color:#800000;\">OBJECTIUS&nbsp; ESTRAT&Egrave;GICS</span></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Progressar en el coneixement de la funci&oacute; del sistema nervi&oacute;s ent&egrave;ric i com interacciona amb la resta de tipus cel&middot;lulars que es troben a l&rsquo;intest&iacute; per a poder comprendre com es regula a aquest nivell&nbsp; la resposta immune innata, el manteniment de la toler&agrave;ncia i la transici&oacute; de toler&agrave;ncia a inflamaci&oacute; i d&rsquo;infamaci&oacute; a tumorog&egrave;nesi.<br />\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Explorar la interacci&oacute; entre els receptors de reconeixement de patrons moleculars,&nbsp; &ndash;i particularment els receptors toll-like- , i altres vies de senyalitzaci&oacute;.<br />\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;La nostra recerca combina aproximacions moleculars, cel&middot;lulars i estudis en animals utilitzant una &agrave;mplia varietat de t&egrave;cniques i models.&nbsp;<br />\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Mitjan&ccedil;ant aquests estudis pretenem plantejar noves estrat&egrave;gies d&#39;intervenci&oacute; terap&egrave;utica basades en l&#39;&uacute;s de noves eines, dianes i vehicles incloent vectors de ter&agrave;pia g&egrave;nica.<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PRINCIPALS L&Iacute;NIES D&rsquo;INVESTIGACI&Oacute;</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp; Valoraci&oacute; de l&rsquo;efic&agrave;cia terap&egrave;utica d&rsquo;estrategies de Knock down g&egrave;nic in vitro i in vivo en models animals d&#39;inflamaci&oacute; (MII) i c&agrave;ncer de c&ograve;lon.<br />\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;Valoraci&oacute; de l&rsquo;efic&agrave;cia terap&egrave;utica d&rsquo;estrategies de sobreexpressi&oacute; g&egrave;nica in vitro i in vivo en models animals d&#39;inflamaci&oacute; (MII) i c&agrave;ncer de c&ograve;lon.<br />\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; Funcions immunomoduladores de les neurones i la glia ent&egrave;riques.<br />\n	Inter-relaci&oacute; de les vies activades per l&rsquo;estimulaci&oacute; de receptors de reconeixment de patrons moleculars i TLR&nbsp; amb altres cascades de senyalitzaci&oacute;<br />\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Mecanismes implicats en la quimio-resist&egrave;ncia adquirida.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PUBLICACIONES</strong></span><br />\n	<br />\n	&bull;&nbsp;Ocampo SM, Romero C, Avi&ntilde;&oacute; A, Burgue&ntilde;o J, Gassull MA, Berm&uacute;dez J, Eritja R, Fernandez E, Perales JC.<br />\n	<em>Functionally enhanced siRNA targeting TNF&alpha;attenuates DSS-induced colitis and TLR-mediated immunostimulation in mice.</em><br />\n	Mol Ther.&nbsp;<strong>2012</strong> ;20(2):382-90.<br />\n	<br />\n	&bull;&nbsp;Aul&iacute; M, Nasser Y, Ho W, Burgue&ntilde;o JF, Keenan CM, Romero C, Sharkey KA, Fern&aacute;ndez E.<br />\n	<em>Neuromuscular changes in a rat model of colitis.</em><br />\n	Auton.&nbsp; Neurosci-Basic Clin.&nbsp;<strong>2008 </strong>;141(1-2):10-21.&nbsp;<br />\n	<br />\n	&bull; R&iacute;o A, Gassull MA, Aldeguer X, Ojanguren I, Cabr&eacute; E, Fern&aacute;ndez E.<br />\n	<em>Reduced liver injury in the interleukin-6 knockout mice by chronic carbon tetrachloride administration.</em><br />\n	Eur J Clin Invest.&nbsp;<strong>2008</strong>;38(5):306-16.<br />\n	<br />\n	&bull;&nbsp;Aul&iacute; M, Fern&aacute;ndez E.<br />\n	<em>Time course of neural and contractile disturbances in a rat model of colitis induced by Trichinella spiralis.</em><br />\n	Life Sci.&nbsp;<strong>2007</strong> 81(14):1117-29.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong><span style=\"color:#800000;\">PATENTS</span></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<em>T&iacute;tle:</em>&nbsp;Methods and Reagents of efficient and targeted gene transfer to monocytes and&nbsp; macrophages.&nbsp; Inventors:&nbsp; Chillon, M, Rio A, Fern&aacute;ndez E, Gassull MA. European Patent application: EP09159001.8 Priority: EUROPE.Priority date:&nbsp;29-04-2009.Extended to:&nbsp; PCT, Argentina, Uruguay.&nbsp;Ownership:Universitat Autonoma de Barcelona, Fundaci&oacute; Institut de Recerca Hospital Univ. Germans Trias i Pujol, Institut Catal&agrave; de Recerca i Estudis Avan&ccedil;ats (ICREA), Gr&iacute;fols S.A.&nbsp;Licensed to:&nbsp; Nanotherapix S.L.<br />\n	<br />\n	<em>T&iacute;tle:</em>&nbsp;Derivados de peque&ntilde;os ARN de interferencia y su uso.&nbsp;Inventors: Eritja R, Ocampo S.M., Perales J.C., Fern&aacute;ndez, E. Romero, C., Burgue&ntilde;o J.F. P201031622&nbsp; Pa&iacute;s de prioridad: Espa&ntilde;a.&nbsp;&nbsp;Priority date:&nbsp;04-11-2010.&nbsp;Extended to:&nbsp; PCT, Argentina, Uruguay.&nbsp;&nbsp;Ownership:&nbsp;Consejo Superior de Investigaciones Cient&iacute;ficas (CSIC); Universitat de Barcelona; Universitat Autonoma de Barcelona.Licensed to:&nbsp;( Dealing)</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830799/public/\" target=\"_blank\"><br />\n	Veure m&eacute;s publicacions de E. Fern&aacute;ndez a PubMed.</a></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n',19,2,0),(269,30,0,'Alberto FERNANDEZ-TERUEL','<p>\n	<a href=\"javascript:MostraPage(296,1); \">Neurobiologia de la ment normal i alterada</a></p>\n<h2>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\">Bases Neurobiol&ograve;giques I Gen&egrave;tiques de Malalties Mentals I Neurol&ograve;giques</span></h2>\n<p>\n	<strong>L&iacute;der del Grup:</strong></p>\n<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				Alberto Fern&aacute;ndez Teruel</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:Albert.Fernandez.Teruel@uab.cat\">Albert.Fernandez.Teruel@uab.cat</a></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				TEL: +34 935 813 456</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<table>\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0001-5993-7058\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/orcid.png\" style=\"width: 26px; height: 26px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researcherid.com/rid/F-9374-2011\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/RID.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<p>\n									<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=7003727625\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 29px; height: 29px;\" /></a></p>\n							</td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researchgate.net/profile/Alberto_Fernandez-Teruel\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"27\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/researchgate.jpg\" width=\"27\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"https://scholar.google.es/citations?hl=en&amp;user=4Qa9JG4AAAAJ\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"29\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/googlescholar.jpg\" width=\"29\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/AFernandezA3_opt.jpg\" style=\"width: 400px; height: 266px;\" /></p>\n<p>\n	<br />\n	<strong>Membres del Grup:</strong><br />\n	Gloria Bl&aacute;zquez Romero<br />\n	Antoni Ca&ntilde;ete Ram&iacute;rez<br />\n	Crist&oacute;bal del R&iacute;o Alamos<br />\n	Cristina Gerbol&eacute;s Freixas<br />\n	Carme Mont Cardona<br />\n	Ignasi Oliveras Puigdelivol<br />\n	Ana S&aacute;nchez Gonz&aacute;lez<br />\n	Adolf Tobe&ntilde;a Pallar&eacute;s<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>OBJECTIUS ESTRAT&Egrave;GICS&nbsp;</strong></span><br />\n	<br />\n	Les investigacions actuals i futures del nostre grup de laboratori tenen com a objectiu millorar el coneixement sobre les bases psicol&ograve;giques, neurobiol&ograve;gics i gen&egrave;tiques de diverses malalties psicol&ograve;giques i neurol&ograve;giques. El progr&eacute;s cap a aquests objectius es basa en l&#39;&uacute;s de diversos recursos i enfocaments experimentals, a saber: 1)Les rates picogen&egrave;ticament seleccionades RHA-I i RLA-I , que difereixen notablement&nbsp; en ansietat / estr&egrave;s (conductuals i hormonals) i les respostes als incentius / de recerca de drogues, s&oacute;n un bon model per estudiar les bases neurobiol&ograve;giques i gen&egrave;tiques de l&#39;ansietat i l&#39;addicci&oacute; a les drogues. 2) A m&eacute;s de l&#39;&uacute;s d&#39;aquestes soques ARS-I i RLA-I,&nbsp; la poblaci&oacute; de rates gen&egrave;ticament heterog&egrave;nies N / NIH-HS (que es mantenen en el nostre laboratori) &eacute;s un poder&oacute;s recurs que s&#39;utilitza pel mapeig gen&egrave;tic del complex fenotips relacionats amb la malaltia com l&#39;ansietat / por, depressi&oacute;, esclerosi m&uacute;ltiple, la pressi&oacute; arterial, les caracter&iacute;stiques relacionades amb la diabetis i altres trets endocrins i immunol&ograve;gics. 3) Els ratolins triple transg&egrave;nics&nbsp; 3xTgAD s&oacute;n tamb&eacute; un model de gran abast per a la dem&egrave;ncia d&#39;Alzheimer, que s&#39;utilitza en el nostre laboratori per investigar les possibilitats de prevenir o retardar l&#39;aparici&oacute; dels s&iacute;mptomes neuropatol&ograve;gics i conductuals de la demencia&nbsp; infantil / juvenil amb tractaments del medi ambient enriquit.&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PRINCIPALS L&Iacute;NIES D&#39;INVESTIGACI&Oacute;</strong></span><br />\n	<br />\n	<em>Neurogen&egrave;tica de l&#39;ansietat i de malalties relacionades amb fenotips neuronals i no neuronals en rates.</em><br />\n	Utilitzant dades en N / NIH-HS i RHA / rates RLA, i finan&ccedil;at pel SAF-2003-03.480 (IP: A. Fern&aacute;ndez-Teruel), per la Welcome Trust (J. Flint, Regne Unit) i per una subvenci&oacute; europea FP6 (IP: Timothy Aitman, Londres IP col &middot; laborador 11:. A. Fern&aacute;ndez-Teruel), aquesta l&iacute;nia d&#39;investigaci&oacute; es porta a terme en col &middot; laboraci&oacute; amb els grups dels Drs. Jonathan Flint (Oxford), Peter Driscoll (Su&iuml;ssa), Tomas Olsson (Su&egrave;cia), Dominique Gauguier (Oxford), Norbert Hubner (Berl&iacute;n), Rickard Holdmdal (Su&egrave;cia), Anna Dominizak (Esc&ograve;cia) i 10 laboratoris d&#39;altres centres de recerca europeus</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<em>Efectes de l&#39;estimulaci&oacute; postnatal (maneig de nadons) i de l&#39;enriquiment ambiental sobre anomalies en el comportament relacionades amb l&#39;envelliment i la dem&egrave;ncia.</em><br />\n	En col &middot; laboraci&oacute; amb el Dr F.M. LaFerla (Calif&ograve;rnia, EUA) una col&ograve;nia de 3xTgAD ratolins (un model de malaltia d&#39;Alzheimer molt recent) s&#39;ha establert en el nostre laboratori. El finan&ccedil;ament d&#39;aquesta l&iacute;nia d&#39;investigaci&oacute; ha estat obtinguda de R + D (Ministeri Espanyol d&#39;Educaci&oacute; i Ci&egrave;ncia, 2006-2008) i &quot;Marat&oacute; de TV3&quot; (PI: Lydia Gim&eacute;nez-Llort, Col &middot; laboradors: Dr FM LaFerla, UCI, EE . EUA. i el Dr. B. Johansson, Institut Karolinska, d&#39;Estocolm, el Dr C. Sanfeliu, Barcelona, ??CSIC, Espanya).</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<em>Enriquiment ambiental, exercici f&iacute;sic i / o dietes especials en rosegadors: Efectes a llarg termini en el comportament i la bioqu&iacute;mica.</em>Aquesta l&iacute;nia de recerca s&#39;est&agrave; desenvolupant en col &middot; laboraci&oacute; amb la Professora Margarita Prunell (Universitat de La Laguna, Espanya), la Dra Yolanda Pe&ntilde;a (Universitat de Essex, Regne Unit), Professora Mercedes Unzeta (Departament de Bioqu&iacute;mica de la UAB), els Professors. Juan Hidalgo i Antonio Armario (Departament de Biologia Cel &middot; lular Fisiologia I), i la Professora Roser Nadal (Psicobiologia, Facultat de Psicologia, UAB).</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>DARRERES PUBLICACIONS</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	&bull; &nbsp;&nbsp; Bl&aacute;zquez G, Ca&ntilde;ete T, Tobe&ntilde;a A, Gim&eacute;nez-Llort L, Fern&aacute;ndez-Teruel A.<br />\n	<em>Cognitive and emotional profiles of aged Alzheimer&#39;s disease (3&times;TgAD) mice: Effects of environmental enrichment and sexual dimorphism.</em><br />\n	Behav Brain Res. <strong>2014</strong> Jul 15;268:185-201.</p>\n<p>\n	&bull; &nbsp;&nbsp; Alam I, Koller DL, Ca&ntilde;ete T, Bl&aacute;zquez G, L&oacute;pez-Aumatell R, Mart&iacute;nez-Membrives E, D&iacute;az-Mor&aacute;n S, Tobe&ntilde;a A, Fern&aacute;ndez-Teruel A, Stridh P, Diez M, Olsson T, Johannesson M, Baud A, Econs MJ, Foroud T.<br />\n	<em>High-Resolution Genome Screen for Bone Mineral Density in Heterogeneous Stock Rat.</em><br />\n	J Bone Miner Res. <strong>2014</strong> [Epub ahead of print]</p>\n<p>\n	&bull; &nbsp;&nbsp; Tuncel J, Haag S, Yau AC, Norin U, Baud A, L&ouml;nnblom E, Maratou K, Ytterberg AJ, Ekman D, Thordardottir S, Johannesson M, Gillett A; EURATRANS Consortium, Stridh P, Jagodic M, Olsson T, Fern&aacute;ndez-Teruel A, Zubarev RA, Mott R, Aitman TJ, Flint J, Holmdahl R.<br />\n	<em>Natural polymorphisms in Tap2 influence negative selection and CD4?CD8 lineage commitment in the rat.</em><br />\n	PLoS Genet. <strong>2014</strong> ;10(2):e1004151.</p>\n<p>\n	&bull; &nbsp;&nbsp; Klein AB, Ultved L, Adamsen D, Santini MA, Tobe&ntilde;a A, Fernandez-Teruel A, Flores P, Moreno M, Cardona D, Knudsen GM, Aznar S, Mikkelsen JD.<br />\n	<em> 5-HT(2A) and mGlu2 receptor binding levels are related to differences in impulsive behavior in the Roman Low- (RLA) and High- (RHA) avoidance rat strains.</em><br />\n	Neuroscience. <strong>2014</strong> ;263:36-45.</p>\n<p>\n	&bull; &nbsp;&nbsp; Manzo L, G&oacute;mez MJ, Callejas-Aguilera JE, Fern&aacute;ndez-Teruel A, Papini MR, Torres C.<br />\n	<em>Anti-anxiety self-medication induced by incentive loss in rats.</em><br />\n	Physiol Behav. <strong>2014</strong>;123:86-92.</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830803/public/\">Veure m&eacute;s publicaciones de A. Fern&aacute;ndez-Teruel a PubMed. </a></p>\n',20,2,0),(271,30,0,'Lydia GIMENEZ-LLORT','<p>\n	Neurodegeneraci&oacute; i envelliment</p>\n<h2>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\">Neuroci&egrave;ncia Conductual<br />\n	</span></h2>\n<p>\n	<br />\n	<strong>L&iacute;der del Grup:</strong></p>\n<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				Lydia Gim&eacute;nez-Llort</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:lidia.gimenez@uab.cat\" target=\"_blank\">lidia.gimenez@uab.cat</a></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				TEL: +34 935 812 378</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<table>\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								<p>\n									<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=6701506831\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 29px; height: 29px;\" /></a></p>\n							</td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researchgate.net/profile/Lydia_Gimenez-Llort\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"29\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/researchgate.jpg\" width=\"29\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"http:// www.saberenvejecer.es\">www.saberenvejecer.es</a><br />\n	<a href=\"http:// www.neurodeg.net\"> www.neurodeg.net</a><br />\n	<a href=\"http:// www.4th5.net\"> www.4th5.net</a></p>\n<p>\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/Gimdef.jpg\" style=\"width: 100%; margin-top: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px;\" /></p>\n<p>\n	<br />\n	<strong>Membres del Grup:</strong><br />\n	Adriana Serrano<br />\n	Aida Muntsant Soria<br />\n	Anna Roquer<br />\n	<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>OBJECTIUS ESTRAT&Egrave;GICS</strong></span><br />\n	<br />\n	Modelar i caracteritzar els fenotips conductuals i neuroimmunoendocrins relacionats amb l&#39;envelliment i aquells que s&oacute;n caracter&iacute;stics de malalties neurodegeneratives o neurol&ograve;giques as esdev&eacute; un repte necessari si volem disposar d&#39;eines &uacute;tils per a estudiar els mecanismes subjacents a la patofisiologia per&ograve; tamb&eacute; per assajar el potencial preventiu i terap&egrave;utic de noves ter&agrave;pies.&nbsp;?La nostra recerca es focalitza en la neuroci&egrave;ncia conductual (caracteritzaci&oacute; conductual, farmacologia conductual i aproximacions no farmacol&ograve;giques) intentant, en la mesura que ens &eacute;s possible, de fer una aproximaci&oacute; translacional. Tamb&eacute; estem interessats en les relacions socials i intergeneracionals humanes i llur impacte en la qualitat de vida de la gent gran; un aspecte que intentem perfilar tamb&eacute; des de la recerca b&agrave;sica.&nbsp;?Som membres del SGR1354 2014 (Coordinador: Miguel Chill&oacute;n), RETICEF (RD06/0013/0003), UCM-CM ENEROINN 910379 (UCM, IP: M&oacute;nica De la Fuente), el Network 4the5 (Fundadora: Lydia Gim&eacute;nez-Llort), Neurogenet Consortium (IGTP, CSIC, UAB; Coordinador: Antoni Matilla). La Dra. Lydia Gim&eacute;nez-Llort &eacute;s la representant espanyola al European Cooperation in the Field of Scientific and Technical Research COST-action TD1005 &lsquo;Pain Assessmment in Patients with Impaired Cognition, especially Dementia&rsquo;.?L&#39;aproximaci&oacute; translational es planteja gr&agrave;cies a acords i convenis de col&middot;laboraci&oacute; amb els Hospital Karolinska de l&#39;Institut Karolinska, Estocolm, Su&egrave;cia (IP: Bj&ouml;rn Johansson), l&rsquo;Hospital Santa Katerina, Salt, Girona (IP: Secund&iacute; L&oacute;pez-Pousa) i l&rsquo;Hospital Sagrat Cor de Martorell (IP: Manel S&aacute;nchez)<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PRINCIPALS L&Iacute;NIES D&#39;INVESTIGACI&Oacute;</strong></span><br />\n	<br />\n	1. Establiment de la colonia espanyola de ratolins 3xTg-AD i la seva soca salvatge.&nbsp; Caracteritzaci&oacute; conductual de defici&egrave;ncies cognitives i s&iacute;mptomes de tipus SPCD en models per envelliment i demencia.?<br />\n	2. Avaluaci&oacute; conductual d&#39;estrategies preventives i/o terap&egrave;utiques no-farmacol&ograve;giques (handling, enriquiment ambiental, exercici)&nbsp; en models animals d&#39;envelliment i malalties neurogeneratives, amb prioritat a la nostra colonia de ratolins 3xTg-AD.?<br />\n	3 . Farmacologia conductual de les interaccions entre NMDA-DA-Adenosina en models animals per a trastorns psiqui&agrave;trics i neurol&ograve;gics.?</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>Col&ograve;nia espanyola de 3xTgAD ratolins.</strong></span><br />\n	La Dra. Lydia Gim&eacute;nez-Llort va establir la colonia espanyola de ratolins 3xTg-AD i la soca de tipus salvatge a la UAB, gr&agrave;cies a Material Transfer Agreements (2004, 2007) amb el Dr. F.M. LaFerla (Universitat de California Irvine, EE.UU.). Els ratolins triple-transg&egrave;nics 3xTg-AD (Oddo et al, 2003, Neuron, 39: 409-421) que alberguen els transgens PS1M146V, APPswe i tauP301L, desenvolupen progressivament les plaques &beta;A i els cabdells neurofibril amb un perfil temporal i regional espec&iacute;fics, que s&#39;assemblen molt al seu desenvolupament en el cervell hum&agrave; AD. La disfunci&oacute; sin&agrave;ptica i cognitives es manifesten en l&#39;edat i el sexe de forma dependent, per&ograve; abans que la patologia de placa i els capells neurofibrilars. Avui dia, aquest model &eacute;s una de les eines m&eacute;s prometedores per estudiar els mecanismes d&#39;acci&oacute; de la contribuci&oacute; fisiopatol&ograve;gica de &beta;A intracel.lular l&#39;any, i tractar de determinar qu&egrave; tan extensa placa, aix&iacute; com patologies neuroembolic poden contribuir a l&#39;&uacute;ltima etapa de d&egrave;ficits cognitius, avaluar segona generaci&oacute; d&#39;estrat&egrave;gies terap&egrave;utiques i preventives que s&#39;acosta a mida s&oacute;n capa&ccedil;os de millorar els fenotips conductuals i patol&ograve;giques.?</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PUBLICACIONS DESTACADES</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp; Johansson, B.,&nbsp; Halldner, L., Dunwiddie, T.V., Masino, S.A., Poelchen, W., Gim&eacute;nez-Llort, L., Escorihuela, R.M., Fern&aacute;ndez-Teruel, A., Wiesenfeld-Hallin, Z., Xu X.-J., H&aring;rdemark, A., Betsholtz, Ch., Herlenius, E., Fredholm, B.<br />\n	<em>Hyperalgesia, anxiety, and decreased hypoxic neuroprotection in mice lacking the adenosine A1 receptor.</em><br />\n	Proc. Nat. Acad. Sciences98 (16), 9407-9412.<strong>2001</strong></p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp; Gim&eacute;nez-Llort, L.*, Bl&aacute;zquez, G., Ca&ntilde;ete, T., Johansson, B., Oddo,S., Tobe&ntilde;a,A, LaFerla, F.M., Fern&aacute;ndez-Teruel, A.<br />\n	<em>Modeling behavioral and neuronal symptoms of Alzheimer disease in mice: a role for intraneuronal&nbsp; amyloid.</em><br />\n	Neurosci Biobehav Rev. 31(1):125-47,<strong>2007</strong></p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp; Espa&ntilde;a J, Gim&eacute;nez-Llort L, Valero J, Mi&ntilde;ano A, R&aacute;bano A, Rodriguez-Alvarez J, LaFerla FM, Saura CA<br />\n	<em>Intraneuronal beta-Amyloid Accumulation in the Amygdala Enhances Fear and Anxiety in Alzheimer&#39;s Disease Transgenic Mice.</em><br />\n	Biol Psychiatry.67(6): 513-521, <strong>2010</strong></p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp; Sol&eacute;-Dom&egrave;nech S, Sj&ouml;vall P, Vukojevi? V, Fernando R, Codita A, Salve S, Bogdanovi? N, Mohammed AH, Hammarstr&ouml;m P, Nilsson KP, Laferla FM, Jacob S, Berggren PO, Gim&eacute;nez-Llort L, Schalling M, Terenius L, Johansson B.<br />\n	<em>Localization of cholesterol, amyloid and glia in Alzheimer&#39;s disease transgenic mouse brain tissue using time-of-flight secondary ion mass spectrometry (ToF-SIMS) and immunofluorescence imaging.</em><br />\n	Acta Neuropathol. 125(1):145-57. <strong>2013</strong></p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp; Gim&eacute;nez-Llort L, Torres-Lista V, De la Fuente M.<br />\n	<em>Crosstalk between the nervous and the immune system during the prodromal stages of Alzheimer&rsquo;s disease. </em>In: Special Issue &ldquo;Crosstalk between the nervous and the immune system in health and in sicknes&rdquo;. Curr Pharm Des. <strong>2014</strong>;20(29):4723-32.</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830910/public/\" target=\"_blank\">Veure m&eacute;s publicacions de L. Gim&eacute;nez-Llort a PubMed.</a></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n',22,2,0),(272,30,0,'Jesús GIRALDO','<h2>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\">Laboratori de Farmacologia de Sistemes i Bioinform&agrave;tica</span></h2>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong>L&iacute;der del Grup:</strong></p>\n<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				Jes&uacute;s Giraldo Arjonilla</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:Jesus.Giraldo@uab.cat\">Jesus.Giraldo@uab.cat</a></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				TEL: +34 935 813 813</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<table>\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0001-7082-4695\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"27\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/orcid.png\" width=\"27\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researcherid.com/rid/F-9881-2011\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/RID.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<p>\n									<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=7003797712\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 29px; height: 29px;\" /></a></p>\n							</td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researchgate.net/profile/Jesus_Giraldo\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/researchgate.jpg\" style=\"width: 27px; height: 27px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/DSC00222.JPG\" style=\"width: 100%;\" /><br />\n	<br />\n	<strong>Membres del Grup:</strong><br />\n	James Dalton,PhD<br />\n	David Roche, PhD</p>\n<p>\n	<strong>Estudiants de doctorat: </strong><br />\n	Agustin Bruzzese<br />\n	Martha Iv&oacute;n C&aacute;rdenas<br />\n	Joan Font<br />\n	Xavier G&oacute;mez<br />\n	Juan Serra<br />\n	Bin Zhou</p>\n<p>\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>OBJECTIUS ESTRAT&Egrave;GICS</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	El Laboratori de Farmacologia de Sistemes i Bioinform&agrave;tica es un grup interdisciplinari compost de qu&iacute;mics, bi&ograve;legs i matem&agrave;tics. El nostre objectiu principal es investigar mitjan&ccedil;ant m&egrave;todes computacionals els mecanismes responsables de les respostes biol&ograve;giques per obtenir nous coneixements que puguin tenir un impacte terap&egrave;utic. Amb aquesta finalitat, hem seleccionat la superfam&iacute;lia dels receptors acoblats a&nbsp; les prote&iuml;nes G (GPCRs) com &agrave;rea principal de la nostra recerca. Els GPCRs estan involucrats en nombrosos processos fisiol&ograve;gics y malalties, per aquesta ra&oacute;, s&oacute;n una de les principals dianes de la recerca farmac&egrave;utica actual. Al nostre grup seguim una <strong>aproximaci&oacute; integradora que inclou simulacions moleculars i matem&agrave;tiques</strong> a diferents escales de complexitat. Aquesta investigaci&oacute; es realitza en col&middot;laboraci&oacute; amb experimentals (Drs. J.Ortiz, J. Sabri&agrave; y C.Gil) dins del nostre grup SGR: <em>The Laboratory of Molecular Neuropharmacology and Bioinformatics. </em><br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PRINCIPALS L&Iacute;NIES D&#39;INVESTIGACI&Oacute;</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>1. Modelitzaci&oacute; molecular i simulacions de din&agrave;mica molecular de GPCRs. </strong>El nostre objectiu es assolir un millor coneixement dels mecanismes moleculars associats a la complexitat de l&rsquo;estructura i funci&oacute; dels receptors, particularment <strong>homo- i heterodimeritzaci&oacute; dels receptors, modulaci&oacute; al&middot;lost&egrave;rica, activitat constitutiva dels receptors i selectivitat funcional.</strong> En particular, focalitzem la nostra atenci&oacute; als <strong>receptors metabotr&ograve;pics de glutamat</strong>, que pertanyen a la classe C dels GPCRs, les seves interaccions heterom&egrave;riques amb els GPCRs de la classe A i la seva implicaci&oacute; en diverses malalties neurol&ograve;giques incloent <strong>dolor cr&ograve;nic, esquizofr&egrave;nia i depressi&oacute;</strong>. Creiem que es d&rsquo;especial rellev&agrave;ncia el fet que aquesta recerca tamb&eacute; inclou el control de l&rsquo;activitat als receptors mitjan&ccedil;ant <strong>compostos foto-commutables.</strong> Aix&iacute; mateix, fem servir les t&egrave;cniques <em>in silico</em> m&eacute;s actuals com <strong>modelitzaci&oacute; dels receptors per homologia</strong>, <em>induced-fit docking</em>, <strong>interaccions prote&iuml;na-prote&iuml;na i simulacions de din&agrave;mica molecular.</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>2. Modelitzaci&oacute; matem&agrave;tica dels GPCRs</strong>. Aquesta l&iacute;nia de recerca es desenvolupa en paral&middot;lel amb la nostra investigaci&oacute; molecular, de forma que es complementen entre s&iacute;. El nostre objectiu es construir models matem&agrave;tics que incloguin a les seves expressions els temes m&eacute;s actuals sobre farmacologia de receptors, com agonisme invers, superagonisme, modulaci&oacute; al&middot;lost&egrave;rica y oligomeritzaci&oacute; de receptors. Estem desenvolupant models matem&agrave;tics dins del marc del model operacional d&rsquo;agonisme i al&middot;losterisme (vegeu Roche et al. Br J Pharmacol. 2013;169(6):1189-202) amb una atenci&oacute; especial als aspectes mecan&iacute;stics de l&rsquo;acci&oacute; dels f&agrave;rmacs.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>3. Ci&egrave;ncia computacional, bioinform&agrave;tica i bioestad&iacute;stica</strong>. El nostre objectiu es la construcci&oacute; de noves aplicacions bioinform&agrave;tiques per a un an&agrave;lisi m&eacute;s rigor&oacute;s i eficient de les dades. Hem desenvolupat un <strong>algoritme d&rsquo;optimitzaci&oacute; evolutiva</strong>, que pot obtenir els valors estimats d&rsquo;equacions amb molts par&agrave;metres i m&iacute;nims locals (t&iacute;pics de les condicions farmacol&ograve;giques complexes). Col.laborem amb especialistes en intel.lig&egrave;ncia artificial (Alfredo Vellido i Ren&eacute; Alqu&eacute;zar, UPC) a l&rsquo;an&agrave;lisi sistem&agrave;tic de la classificaci&oacute; dels GPCRs mitjan&ccedil;ant m&egrave;todes de <strong><em>machine learning. </em></strong>Aix&iacute; mateix, som tamb&eacute; actius en <strong><em>data mining</em></strong> i <strong><em>big data</em></strong> en biologia i farmacologia.</p>\n<p>\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PROJECTES ACTUALS</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>T&iacute;tol del projecte: </strong>Integrated mathematical, computational and biochemical investigation of the crosstalk between metabotropic glutamate receptor 5 and dopamine D2 receptor: Relevance for the treatment of schizophrenia<br />\n	<strong>Entitat finan&ccedil;adora:</strong> Ministerio de Econom&iacute;a y Competitividad (REF. SAF2014-58396-R)<br />\n	<strong>Entitats&nbsp; participants:</strong> Universitat Aut&ograve;noma de Barcelona.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>T&iacute;tol del projecte:</strong> Deciphering the role of peripheral and central nervous system metabotropic glutamate receptors in neuropathic pain with photoactivable ligands<br />\n	<strong>Entitat finan&ccedil;adora:</strong> ERA-NET NEURON Call for transnational research projects 2012 (REF. PCIN-2013-018-C03-02)<br />\n	<strong>Entitats&nbsp; participants:</strong> El projecte coordinat inclou 5 subprojectes amb els seg&uuml;ents Investigadors Principals: Amadeu Llebaria, SP1 (Institut de Qu&iacute;mica Avan&ccedil;ada de Catalunya (IQAC-CSIC), Barcelona); Jes&uacute;s Giraldo, SP2 (Universitat Aut&ograve;noma de Barcelona (UAB), Barcelona); Francisco Ciruela, SP3 (Universitat de Barcelona (UB), Barcelona); Ferdinando Nicoletti, SP4 (IRCCS Neuromed, University La Sapienza, Rome) i Jean-Philippe Pin, SP5 (Institut de G&eacute;nomique Fonctionnelle (IGF), CNRS, Universit&eacute; de Montpellier, INSERM, Montpellier)</p>\n<p>\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>COL.LABORACIONS AMB ALTRES GRUPS</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	Actualment estem col&middot;laborant amb els seg&uuml;ents investigadors:<br />\n	<br />\n	<strong>Jean-Philippe Pin i Cyril Goudet</strong>. Institut de G&eacute;nomique Fonctionnelle, CNRS UMR 5203, Universit&eacute; de Montpellier, Montpellier, France; INSERM, U661, Montpellier, France.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>Michael Conn.</strong> Department of Internal Medicine, Center for Membrane Protein Research, Texas Tech University Health Sciences Center, Lubbock, TX, USA; Department of Cell Biology/Biochemistry, Center for Membrane Protein Research, Texas Tech University Health Sciences Center, Lubbock, TX, USA.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>Katja Schmitz.</strong> Technische Universit&auml;t Darmstadt, Clemens-Sch&ouml;pf-Institut, Alarich-Weiss-Stra&szlig;e 4, 64287 Darmstadt, Germany.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>Nuska Tschammer.</strong> Department of&nbsp; Chemistry and Pharmacy, Medicinal Chemistry,&nbsp; Emil Fischer Center, Friedrich Alexander University Schuhstra&szlig;e 19, 91052 Erlangen, Germany.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>Amadeu Llebaria.</strong> Department of Biomedicinal Chemistry, Institut de Qu&iacute;mica Avan&ccedil;ada de Catalunya (IQAC-CSIC), Jordi Girona 18-26, 08034 Barcelona, Spain.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>Pau Gorostiza. </strong>Institute for Bioengineering of Catalonia (IBEC), Baldiri Reixac 15-21, Barcelona 08028, Spain.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>Francisco Ciruela.</strong> Unitat de Farmacologia, Departament Patologia i Terap&egrave;utica Experimental, Facultat de Medicina, IDIBELL-Universitat de Barcelona, Barcelona, Spain.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>Alfons Macaya. </strong>Grup de Recerca en Neurologia Pedi&agrave;trica, Institut de Recerca Vall d&#39;Hebron, Universitat Aut&ograve;noma de Barcelona, Barcelona, Spain.</p>\n<p>\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PUBLICACIONS SELECCIONADES</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp; Giraldo J.<br />\n	<em>Operational models of allosteric modulation: caution is needed.</em><br />\n	Trends in Pharmacological Sciences <strong>2015</strong>;36(1):1-2</p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp; Rovira X, Malhaire F, Scholler P, Rodrigo J, Gonzalez-Bulnes P, Llebaria A, Pin JP, Giraldo J, Goudet C<br />\n	<em>Overlapping binding sites drive allosteric agonism and positive cooperativity in type 4 metabotropic glutamate receptors</em><br />\n	The FASEB Journal <strong>2015</strong>;29(1):116-30</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp; Lans I, Dalton JA, Giraldo J<br />\n	<em>Helix 3 acts as a conformational hinge in Class A GPCR activation: An analysis of interhelical interaction energies in crystal structures.</em><br />\n	Journal of Structural Biology <strong>2015</strong>. pii: S1047-8477(15)30096-4.<em> </em></p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pittolo S, G&oacute;mez-Santacana X, Eckelt K, Rovira X, Dalton J, Goudet C, Pin J-P, Llobet A, Giraldo J, Llebaria A, Gorostiza P<br />\n	<em>An allosteric modulator to control endogenous G protein-coupled receptors with light</em><br />\n	Nature Chemical Biology <strong>2014</strong>;10(10):813-5</p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Dalton JA, G&oacute;mez-Santacana X, Llebaria A, Giraldo J.<br />\n	<em>Computational Analysis of Negative and Positive Allosteric Modulator Binding and Function in Metabotropic Glutamate Receptor 5 (In)Activation.</em><br />\n	J Chem Inf Model. <strong>2014</strong></p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; Roche D, Gil D, and Giraldo J<br />\n	<em>Multiple active receptor conformation, agonist efficacy and maximum effect of the system: The conformation-based operational model of agonism</em><br />\n	Drug Discovery Today <strong>2013</strong>;18:365-371&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830921/public/\" target=\"_blank\">Veure m&eacute;s publicacions de J. Giraldo a PubMed. </a></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n',23,2,0),(273,30,0,'Gemma GUILLAZO BLANCH','<p>\n	<a href=\"javascript:MostraPage(296,1);\">Neurobiologia de la ment normal i alterada</a></p>\n<h2>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\">Neurobiologia de l&#39;Aprenentatge i la Mem&ograve;ria</span></h2>\n<p>\n	<strong>L&iacute;der del Grup:</strong></p>\n<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				Gemma Guillazo-Blanch</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:Gemma.Guillazo@uab.cat\">Gemma.Guillazo@uab.cat</a></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				Tel:93 5812543</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<table height=\"55\" width=\"198\">\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0002-8297-7100\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/orcid.png\" style=\"width: 26px; height: 26px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researcherid.com/rid/E-9765-2011\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/RID.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<p>\n									<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=6602654496\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 29px; height: 29px;\" /></a></p>\n							</td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researchgate.net/profile/Gemma_Guillazo-Blanch\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"27\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/researchgate.jpg\" width=\"27\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.mendeley.com/profiles/gemma-guillazo/\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"29\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/mendeley.png\" width=\"29\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"https://es.linkedin.com/pub/gemma-guillazo-blanch/17/492/b85\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"31\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Linkedin.jpg\" width=\"39\" /></a></td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/gemma guill.jpg\" style=\"width: 450px; height: 285px;\" /></p>\n<div>\n	<br />\n	<strong>Membres del Grup:</strong></div>\n<div>\n	<a href=\"http://inc.uab.cat/Catala/profile.php?id=91\">Margarita Mart&iacute;-Nicolovius</a></div>\n<div>\n	Divka Rojic&nbsp;&nbsp;Becker</div>\n<div>\n	Anna Vale Mart&iacute;nez</div>\n<div>\n	Joan Visa Bombardo</div>\n<p>\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>OBJECTIUS ESTRAT&Egrave;GICS</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	El nostre projecte pret&eacute;n investigar diferents tractaments cerebrals que podrien potenciar fonamentalment processos d&#39;atenci&oacute; i mem&ograve;ria en models animals de d&egrave;ficit cognitiu derivat de l&#39;envelliment i de lesions o inactivacions cerebrals que imiten algunes alteracions observades en determinades malalties neurodegeneratives, com l&#39;Alzheimer o Parkinson, o s&iacute;ndromes cl&iacute;nics, com l&#39;amn&egrave;sia diencef&agrave;lica. Per assolir aquest objectiu fem servir models de d&egrave;ficit cognitiu en rates velles, i tamb&eacute; en rates joves, amb infusions d&#39;antagonistes colin&egrave;rgics o glutamat&egrave;rgics en estructures diana del prosenc&egrave;fal basal (PB) o amb lesions o inactivacions reversibles dels nuclis tal&agrave;mics intralaminars (ILN). El principal objectiu &eacute;s revertir el deteriorament cognitiu mitjan&ccedil;ant la infusi&oacute; intracerebral, en regions de projecci&oacute; del PB i dels ILN, de compostos que actualment s&#39;estan valorant com a possibles potenciadors cognitius: d-cicloserina o S18986 (potenciadors glutamat&egrave;rgics) o FG7142 (inhibidor gaba&egrave;rgic). L&#39;efic&agrave;cia d&#39;aquests tractaments es valora en models conductuals basats en tasques olfact&ograve;ries de rellev&agrave;ncia etol&ograve;gica i cl&iacute;nica, i tamb&eacute; en paradigmes de condicionament instrumental que ens permeten avaluar processos d&#39;atenci&oacute;, mem&ograve;ria de treball i flexibilitat cognitiva. A m&eacute;s de l&#39;avan&ccedil; en el desenvolupament de possibles tractaments dirigits a millorar certes funcions cognitives, la consecuci&oacute; dels objectius proposats permetr&agrave; dilucidar les bases neurofisiol&ograve;giques dels efectes d&#39;aquests tractaments. Aquesta informaci&oacute; &eacute;s rellevant per con&egrave;ixer possibles dianes cerebrals o mecanismes neuroqu&iacute;mics sobre els quals puguin actuar nous m&egrave;todes terap&egrave;utics efectius per potenciar l&#39;atenci&oacute;, la mem&ograve;ria o la flexibilitat conductual, entre altres funcions cognitives.</p>\n<p>\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PRINCIPALS L&Iacute;NIES D&#39;INVESTIGACI&Oacute;</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	El nostre projecte principal &quot;Potenciaci&oacute; de l&#39;atenci&oacute; i de la mem&ograve;ria en models animals de d&egrave;ficit cognitiu per envelliment i lesi&oacute; cerebral&quot; inclou diferents l&iacute;nies de treball amb els objectius seg&uuml;ents:<br />\n	1) Investigar la capacitat de moduladors glutamat&egrave;rgics de revertir d&egrave;ficits cognitius en animals joves amb lesi&oacute; o inactivaci&oacute; d&#39;estructures clau en certes patologies neurodegeneratives.<br />\n	2) Investigar la capacitat de moduladors glutamat&egrave;rgics i gaba&egrave;rgics de revertir d&egrave;ficits cognitius en animals vells amb alteracions funcionals associades al proc&eacute;s normal d&#39;envelliment.<br />\n	3) Estudiar els mecanismes neurofisiol&ograve;gics subjacents als tractaments de potenciaci&oacute; de les funcions cognitives.</p>\n<p>\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>T&Egrave;CNIQUES</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	Les q&uuml;estions plantejades en l&#39;apartat anterior s&#39;investiguen a trav&eacute;s de t&egrave;cniques d&#39;immunohistoqu&iacute;mica per a l&#39;expressi&oacute; de c-fos, estimulaci&oacute; el&egrave;ctrica intracerebral, lesions neuroqu&iacute;miques, infusions intracerebrals, autorradiografia de receptors i hibridaci&oacute; in situ. Les tasques conductuals utilitzades s&oacute;n, entre altres, la transmissi&oacute; social de prefer&egrave;ncies aliment&agrave;ries, la discriminaci&oacute; simple d&#39;olors, el laberint aqu&agrave;tic de Morris, l&#39;atenci&oacute; visual i la mem&ograve;ria de treball en la g&agrave;bia de Skinner.<br />\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\">Col.laboracions:</span><br />\n	-Laboratorio de Psicobiolog&iacute;a, UNED, Madrid (Emilio Ambrosio, Miguel Migu&eacute;ns)<br />\n	-Divisi&oacute;n de Neurociencias, Universidad Pablo de Olavide (UPO),&nbsp;Sevilla (Dr. Delgado-Garc&iacute;a, Dra.&nbsp;Gruart)<br />\n	-IDIBAPS (Barcelona) (Dra. S&aacute;nchez-Vives)</p>\n<p>\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>DARRERES PUBLICACIONS</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp; Portero-Tresserra M, Crist&oacute;bal-Narv&aacute;ez P, Mart&iacute;-Nicolovius M, Guillazo-Blanch , G, Vale-Mart&iacute;nez A. <em>D-cycloserine in prelimbic cortex reverses scopolamine-induced deficits in olfactory memory in rats. </em>PLoS One. <strong>2013</strong>, 2;8(8):e70584.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;Yefimenko N, Portero-Tresserra M, Mart&iacute;-Nicolovius M, Guillazo-Blanch G, Vale-Mart&iacute;nez A.&nbsp;(2013). <em>The AMPA receptor modulator S18986 in the prelimbic cortex enhances acquisition and retention of an odor-reward association. </em>Neurosci Lett.&nbsp;<strong>2013</strong> pii: S0304-3940(13)00467-9.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;Villarejo-Rodr&iacute;guez I, Boadas-Vaello P, Portero-Tresserra M, Vale-Mart&iacute;nez A, Mart&iacute;-Nicolovius M, Guillazo-Blanch G.<em> Learning deficits in an odor reward-task induced by parafascicular thalamic lesions are ameliorated by pretraining D-cycloserine in the prelimbic cortex. </em>Behav Brain Res.&nbsp;<strong>2013</strong> ;238:289-92.&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;Portero-Tresserra M, Mart&iacute;-Nicolovius M, Guillazo-Blanch G, Boadas-Vaello P, Vale-Mart&iacute;nez A.<em> D-cycloserine in the basolateral amygdala prevents extinction and enhances reconsolidation of odor-reward associative learning in rats.</em> Neurobiol Learn Mem.&nbsp;<strong>2013</strong>;100:1-11.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp; Portero-Tresserra M, Crist&oacute;bal-Narv&aacute;ez P, Mart&iacute;-Nicolovius M, Guillazo-Blanch G, Vale-Mart&iacute;nez A. D-cycloserine in prelimbic cortex reverses scopolamine-induced deficits in olfactory memory in rats. PLoS One. <strong>2013</strong>; 8(8):e70584. PMCID: PMC3732227</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830176/public/\" target=\"_blank\">Veure m&eacute;s publicacions de G. Guillazo a PubMed. </a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n',24,2,0),(274,30,0,'Juan HIDALGO','<p>\n	<a href=\"javascript:MostraPage(294,1); \">Neurodegeneraci&oacute; i envelliment</a></p>\n<h2>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\">Neuroinflamaci&oacute; i Estr&egrave;s Oxidatiu</span></h2>\n<p>\n	<strong>L&iacute;der del Grup:</strong></p>\n<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				Juan Hidalgo Pareja</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:Juan.Hidalgo@uab.cat\">Juan.Hidalgo@uab.cat</a></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				TEL: +34 935 812 037</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<table>\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-0921-1122\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/orcid.png\" style=\"width: 26px; height: 26px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researcherid.com/rid/C-9082-2011\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/RID.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<p>\n									<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=7101787664\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 29px; height: 29px;\" /></a></p>\n							</td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researchgate.net/profile/Juan_Hidalgo5\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"27\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/researchgate.jpg\" width=\"27\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"https://scholar.google.es/citations?hl=ca&amp;user=-1UMmesAAAAJ\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"29\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/googlescholar.jpg\" width=\"31\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/JHidalgoFotogrupo.jpg\" style=\"width: 100%;\" /><br />\n	<br />\n	<strong> Membres del Grup:</strong><br />\n	Gemma Comes Orpinell<br />\n	Merc&egrave; Giralt Carbonell<br />\n	Amalia Molinero Egea<br />\n	Olaya Fern&aacute;ndez Gayol<br />\n	<br />\n	<strong>Membres anteriors:</strong><br />\n	Mar&iacute;a Erta Caba&ntilde;ate<br />\n	Beatriz Ferrer Villahoz<br />\n	Javier Carrasco Trancoso</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>OBJECTIUS ESTRAT&Egrave;GICS</strong></span><br />\n	<br />\n	Els objectius fonamentals del grup es centren en l&#39;estudi dels mecanismes b&agrave;sics de la neuroinflamaci&oacute; i l&rsquo;estr&egrave;s oxidatiu, amb un particular &egrave;mfasi en el paper de la interleucina 6 (IL-6) en models animals de malalties neurodegeneratives com l&#39;Alzheimer i l&#39;esclerosi m&uacute;ltiple (EM) i en models de lesions traum&agrave;tiques cerebrals.<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PRINCIPALS L&Iacute;NIES D&#39;INVESTIGACI&Oacute;</strong></span><br />\n	<br />\n	1. Les lesions traum&agrave;tiques cerebrals (TBI) s&oacute;n una de les principals causes de mort i incapacitat, especialment entre la gent jove. Citocines com la IL-6 i el TNFa estan implicades en la resposta del SNC al dany cerebral, mitjan&ccedil;ant l&#39;&uacute;s de ratolins KO condicionals produ&iuml;ts en el nostre laboratori, analitzarem la import&agrave;ncia de les fonts cel&middot;lulars d&#39;IL-6 en un model de TBI. A m&eacute;s, usant ratolins KO condicionals per al receptor de la IL-6 tamb&eacute; determinarem la import&agrave;ncia de la resposta cel&middot;lular espec&iacute;fica a la IL-6. En aquest moment ens estem centrant en la principal c&egrave;l&middot;lula glial, l&#39;astr&ograve;cit .<br />\n	2. Models d&#39;Alzheimer. Un dels models d&#39;Alzheimer m&eacute;s utilitzat &eacute;s el ratol&iacute; APP2576, la import&agrave;ncia de l&#39;estr&egrave;s oxidatiu en aquest model s&#39;est&agrave; avaluant analitzant el fenotip de ratolins APP creuats amb ratolins amb nivells alterats de la prote&iuml;na antioxidant metal&middot;lotione&iuml;na.<br />\n	3. Models d&#39;Esclerosi M&uacute;ltiple. Existeixen diversos models d&#39;EM, i la Encefalitis Autoimmune Experimental (EAE) &eacute;s un dels m&eacute;s utilitzats. Mitjan&ccedil;ant els ratolins transg&egrave;nics abans esmentats estem analitzant la import&agrave;ncia de la IL-6 en aquest model.<br />\n	4. Exercici i obesitat. Import&agrave;ncia de la IL-6 en la resposta a l&#39;exercici i l&#39;obesitat indu&iuml;da per dietes enriquides en greixos.<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>DARRERES PUBLICACIONS </strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull; Giralt M, Ramos R, Quintana A, Ferrer B, Erta M, Castro-Freire M, Comes G, Sanz E, Unzeta M, Pifarr&eacute; P, Garc&iacute;a A, Campbell IL, <strong>Hidalgo J</strong>. Induction of atypical EAE mediated by transgenic production of IL-6 in astrocytes in the absence of systemic IL-6. Glia 61 (<strong>2013</strong>) 587-600.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>&bull; </strong>Pifarr&eacute; P, Gutierrez-Mecinas M, Prado J, Usero L, Roura-Mir C, Giralt M, <strong>Hidalgo J</strong>, Garc&iacute;a A. Phosphodiesterase 5 inhibition at disease onset prevents experimental autoimmune encephalomyelitis progression through immunoregulatory and neuroprotective actions. Exp. Neurol. 251 (<strong>2014</strong>) 58-71.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>&bull; </strong>Campbell IL, Erta M, Lim SL, Frausto R, May U, Rose-John S, Scheller J, <strong>Hidalgo J</strong>. Trans-signaling is a dominant mechanism for the pathogenic actions of interleukin-6 in the brain. J. Neurosci. 34 (<strong>2014</strong>) 2503-2513.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp; Ferrer B, Navia B, Giralt M, Comes G, Carrasco J, Molinero A, Quintana A, Se&ntilde;ar&iacute;s R, <strong>Hidalgo J.</strong> Muscle-specific interleukin-6 deletion influences body weight and body fat in a sex-dependent manner. Brain, Behav. Immun. 40 (<strong>2014</strong>) 121-130.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp; Manso Y, Comes G, L&oacute;pez-Ramos JC, Belfiore M, Molinero A, Giralt M, Carrasco J, Adlard PA, Bush AI, Delgado-Garc&iacute;a JM, <strong>Hidalgo J</strong>. Overexpression of metallothionein-1 modulates the phenotype of the Tg2576 mouse model of Alzheimer&rsquo;s disease. J. Alzheimer&rsquo;s Dis. 51 (<strong>2016</strong>) 81-95.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830937/public/\" target=\"_blank\">Veure m&eacute;s publicacions de J. Hidalgo a PubMed.</a></p>\n',25,2,0),(275,30,0,'Marcel JIMENEZ','<p>\n	<a href=\"javascript:MostraPage(294,1); \">Neurodegeneraci&oacute; i envelliment</a></p>\n<h2>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\">Neurogastroenterologia</span></h2>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong>L&iacute;der del Grup:</strong></p>\n<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				Marcel &nbsp;Jim&eacute;nez Farrerons</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:Marcel.Jimenez@uab.cat\">Marcel.Jimenez@uab.cat</a></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				TEL: +34 935 811 566</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<table>\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0002-6602-7332\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"29\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/orcid.png\" width=\"29\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://: 	http://www.researcherid.com/rid/C-6995-2008\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/RID.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<p>\n									<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=35551030000\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 29px; height: 29px;\" /></a></p>\n							</td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Marcel_Jimenez\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"30\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/researchgate.jpg\" width=\"27\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"https://scholar.google.es/citations?user=iX8zMYIAAAAJ&amp;hl=ca&amp;oi=ao\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"28\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/googlescholar.jpg\" width=\"29\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/Marcdef.jpg\" style=\"width: 100%; margin-top: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px;\" /><br />\n	<strong>Membres del Grup:</strong><br />\n	M&ordf; Teresa Mart&iacute;n Ib&aacute;&ntilde;ez</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>OBJECTIUS ESTRAT&Egrave;GICS</strong></span><br />\n	<br />\n	L&rsquo; objectiu de la nostra recerca es centra en l&#39;estudi de la motilitat gastrointestinal en condicions fisiol&ograve;giques i en diversos estats patol&ograve;gics. Els nostres estudis es realitzen en teixits humans i en models animals de malaltia. La nostra recerca es basa en l&#39;estudi de neurogastroenterologia des de diferents punts de vista incloent la Neurotransmissi&oacute; en el sistema nervi&oacute;s ent&egrave;ric, l&#39;activitat de marcapassos i la relaci&oacute; entre el sistema immune i el sistema nervi&oacute;s ent&egrave;ric.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PRINCIPALS L&Iacute;NIES D&#39;INVESTIGACI&Oacute;</strong></span><br />\n	<br />\n	&bull; Motilitat gastrointestinal: Estudi de la motilitat gastrointestinal i la seva regulaci&oacute; hormonal i nervi&oacute;s. Estudis farmacol&ograve;gics.<br />\n	&bull;&nbsp;Neurogastroenterologia: Funci&oacute; de marcapassos, relaci&oacute; entre les neurones motores i el m&uacute;scul llis. Les c&egrave;l lules intersticials de Cajal (ICC). Electrofisiologia.&nbsp;<br />\n	&bull;&nbsp;Neurotransmissors gasosos. L&#39;&ograve;xid n&iacute;tric i el sulfh&iacute;dric. Regulaci&oacute; de la motilitat gastrointestinal en el teixit normal com inflamat. Mecanisme d&#39;acci&oacute;. Paper dels&nbsp; inhibidors de la s&iacute;ntesi de NO i H2S.&nbsp;<br />\n	&bull;&nbsp;La s&iacute;ndrome de l&#39;intest&iacute; irritable (SII). Desenvolupament de models animals per estudiar l&#39;alteraci&oacute; de la motilitat gastrointestinal en el SII. Enfocament farmacol&ograve;gic del tractament del SII.&nbsp;<br />\n	&bull;&nbsp;La malaltia inflamat&ograve;ria intestinal: desenvolupament de models animals per estudiar l&#39;alteraci&oacute; de la motilitat gastrointestinal en la inflamaci&oacute; intestinal. Enfocament farmacol&ograve;gic del tractament de patrons motors alterats durant la inflamaci&oacute; intestinal.<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PUBLICACIONS</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp; Gallego D, Gil V, Martinez-Cutillas M, Mane N, Martin MT, Jimenez M. <em>Purinergic neuromuscular transmission is absent in the colon of P2Y(1) knocked out mice.</em><br />\n	J Physiol <strong>2012</strong>;590(Pt 8):1943-1956.</p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp; Lies B, Gil V, Groneberg D, Seidler B, Saur D, Wischmeyer E, Jimenez M, Friebe A.<br />\n	<em>Interstitial cells of Cajal mediate nitrergic inhibitory neurotransmission in the murine gastrointestinal tract. </em><br />\n	Am J Physiol Gastrointest Liver Physiol <strong>2014</strong>;307(1):G98-106.</p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp; Mane N, Gil V, Martinez-Cutillas M, Martin MT, Gallego D, Jimenez M. <em>Dynamics of inhibitory co-transmission, membrane potential and pacemaker activity determine neuromyogenic function in the rat colon. </em>Pflugers Arch <strong>2014</strong>.</p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp; Mane N, Gil V, Martinez-Cutillas M, Clav&eacute; P, Gallego D, Jimenez M. <em>Differential functional role of purinergic and nitrergic inhibitory cotransmitters in human colonic relaxation.</em><br />\n	Acta Physiologica (Oxf) <strong>2014</strong> Dec;212(4):293-305.</p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp; Jim&eacute;nez M, Clav&eacute; P, Accarino A, Gallego D.<br />\n	<em>Purinergic neuromuscular transmission in the gastrointestinal tract; functional basis for future clinical and pharmacological studies</em>. &nbsp;<br />\n	Br J Pharmacol. <strong>2014</strong> Oct;171(19):4360-75</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830944/public/\" target=\"_blank\">Veure m&eacute;s publicacions de M. Jimenez a PubMed.</a></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n',28,2,0),(276,30,0,'José M LIZCANO i Néstor GÓMEZ','<p>\n	<a href=\"javascript:MostraPage(294,1);\">Neurodegeneraci&oacute; i envelliment</a></p>\n<h2>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\">Prote&iuml;nes quinases i transducci&oacute; de senyals</span></h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<br />\n	<strong>L&iacute;ders del Grup:</strong><br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<table style=\"width: 100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				Jose Miguel Lizcano&nbsp;&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>\n				N&eacute;stor Gomez</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:josemiguel.lizcano@uab.cat\">josemiguel.lizcano@uab.cat </a></td>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"http://nestor.gomez@uab.cat\">Nestor.gomez@uab.cat</a></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				TEL: +34 935 813 076&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>\n				TEL: +34 935 813 076</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<table align=\"left\">\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0002-3154-5383\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/orcid.png\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researcherid.com/rid/E-6080-2010\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/RID.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=55226571500\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=3rSTvT8AAAAJ&amp;hl=es\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"