le=\"width: 450px; height: 394px;\" /></p>\n<div>\n	<strong>Membres del Grup:</strong><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong></div>\n<div>\n	Dra. Tatiana Erazo&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\n	Pau Mu&ntilde;oz Guardiola&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</div>\n<div>\n	Nora Di&eacute;guez&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</div>\n<div>\n	Rub&eacute;n Melgarejo &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</div>\n<div>\n	Elisabet Meg&iacute;as</div>\n<div>\n	Valeria Rizzuto</div>\n<div>\n	&nbsp;</div>\n<div>\n	<strong>Membres anteriors:</strong><br />\n	Dra. Ana Moreno Iglesias<br />\n	Dra. Margarita Espona</div>\n<div>\n	Dra. Arantza Rodr&iacute;guez Asia&iacute;n</div>\n<div>\n	Dr. Gerad Ruiz Babot</div>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>OBJECTIUS ESTRAT&Egrave;GICS</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	<em>Prote&iuml;nes quinases i transducci&oacute; de senyals en c&agrave;ncer</em></p>\n<p>\n	Gaireb&eacute; tots els aspectes de la vida cel&middot;lular s&oacute;n controlats per la fosforilaci&oacute; reversible de prote&iuml;nes. Per tant, la comprensi&oacute; del control molecular de la fisiologia cel&middot;lular requereix la identificaci&oacute; dels substrats espec&iacute;fics de les prote&iuml;nes quinases. Nombrosos estudis han identificat alteracions en gens que codifiquen per quinases i que causen malalties, com ara el c&agrave;ncer o les malalties neurodegeneratives. La nostra recerca es centra en analitzar noves vies de senyalitzaci&oacute; cel&middot;lular que controlen la proliferaci&oacute; i diferenciaci&oacute; de les c&egrave;l&middot;lules canceroses. Estudiem las noves prote&iuml;nes quinases ERK5 (una Map quinasa) i la supressora de tumors LKB1, per&ograve; tamb&eacute; estem interessats en la via de la Akt-mTORC1. Col&middot;laborem amb companyies biofarmac&egrave;utiques en el desenvolupament precl&iacute;nic de nous medicaments antitumorals.</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PRINCIPALS L&Iacute;NIES D&rsquo;INVESTIGACI&Oacute;</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	Utilitzem dues perspectives diferents per abordar els problemes fonamentals:</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"margin-left:36.0pt;\">\n	<em>1)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </em><em>Recerca b&agrave;sica.</em></p>\n<p style=\"margin-left:36.0pt;\">\n	An&agrave;lisi dels mecanismes pels quals les quinases LKB1, Akt i ERK5 exerceixen un control en la proliferaci&oacute; i la superviv&egrave;ncia de les c&egrave;l&middot;lules tumorals. Hem contribu&iuml;t a proposar un nou mecanisme molecular per a la regulaci&oacute; de la prote&iuml;na quinasa Akt; a descobrir que la quinasa supressora de tumors LKB1 funciona com a m&agrave;ster quinasa; o, m&eacute;s recentment, que hem establert un nou mecanisme pel qual la ERK5 transloca al nucli on regula la proliferaci&oacute; de c&egrave;l&middot;lules tumorals, malgrat la seva activitat enzim&agrave;tica.</p>\n<p style=\"margin-left:36.0pt;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"margin-left:36.0pt;\">\n	2)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em>Recerca dirigida a la intervenci&oacute; farmacol&ograve;gica en c&agrave;ncer.</em><br />\n	Estem implicats en potenciar els aspectes translacionals dels nostres recursos. Col&middot;laborem activament amb Abilty Pharmaceuticals SL en el desenvolupament precl&iacute;nic/cl&iacute;nic d&rsquo;un nou medicament antitumoral ABTL0812, que acaba de finalitzar la fase d&rsquo;assajos cl&iacute;nics I/Ib, primer en humans (NCT02201823) en pacients de c&agrave;ncer amb tumors s&ograve;lids. Hem descobert una nova via de senyalitzaci&oacute; cel&middot;lular en la que ABTL0812 exerceix la seva acci&oacute; antitumoral: ABTL0812 activa la transcripci&oacute; mediada per PPARa/g de la pseudoquinasa TRIB-3, que, al seu torn, s&rsquo;uneix i inhibeix Akt, provocant la inhibici&oacute; de mTORC1, el fre del creixement la mort de les c&egrave;l&middot;lules canceroses per autof&agrave;gia mediada. Finalment, hem col&middot;laborat activament amb altres laboratoris acad&egrave;mics caracteritzant nous inhibidors de la ERK5 que mostren activitat antitumoral.</p>\n<p align=\"justify\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p align=\"justify\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PUBLICACIONS SELECCIONADES</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp; Erazo T, Lorente M, L&oacute;pez-Plana A, Mu&ntilde;oz-Guardiola P&hellip;, Lizcano JM.<em> The New Antitumor Drug ABTL0812 Inhibits the Akt/mTORC1 Axis by Upregulating Tribbles-3 Pseudokinase. </em>Clinical Cancer Research 2015 Dec 15. [Epub ahead of print]. <strong>2016&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp; Erazo T, Moreno A, Ruiz-Babot G, Rodr&iacute;guez-Asiain A, Morrice NA, Espadamala J, Bayascas JR, G&oacute;mez N, Lizcano JM. <em>Canonical and kinase activity-independent mechanisms for extracellular signal-regulated kinase 5 (ERK5) nuclear translocation require dissociation of Hsp90 from the ERK5-Cdc37 complex. </em>Molecular&nbsp;and Cellular Biology&nbsp;33:1671-86. <strong>2013&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp; Elkins JM, Wang J, Deng X, Pattison MJ, Arthur JS, Erazo T, Gomez N, Lizcano JM, Gray NS, Knapp S. <em>X-ray crystal structure of ERK5 (MAPK7) in complex with a specific inhibitor. </em>Journal of Medicinal Chemistry&nbsp;56:4413-21. <strong>2013 </strong></p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp; Villagrasa P, D&iacute;az VM, Vi&ntilde;as-Castells R, Peir&oacute; S, Del Valle-P&eacute;rez B, Dave N, Rodr&iacute;guez-Asiain A, Casal JI, Lizcano JM, Du&ntilde;ach M, Garc&iacute;a de Herreros A. <em>Akt2 interacts with Snail1 in the E-cadherin promoter. </em>Oncogene 31:4022-33. <strong>2012</strong></p>\n<p>\n	<br />\n	&bull;&nbsp; Lizcano JM, Goransson O, Toth R, Deak M, Morrice NA, Boudeau J, Hawley SA, Udd L, Makela TP, Hardie DG, Alessi DR. <em>LKB1 is a master kinase that activates 13 kinases of the AMPK subfamily,including MARK/PAR1 </em>EMBO Journal 23: 833-43. <strong>2004</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830948/public/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Veure m&eacute;s publicacions de JM. Lizcano a PubMed.</strong></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830954/public/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Veure m&eacute;s publicacions de N. G&oacute;mez a PubMed.</strong></a></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong><span style=\"color:#800000;\">PROJECTES ACTIUS</span></strong></p>\n<div>\n	<em>Nuevas aproximaciones terap&eacute;uticas basadas en derivados de &aacute;cidos grasos esenciales dirigidos a enfermedades oncol&oacute;gicas y neurol&oacute;gicas no cubiertas.</em></div>\n<div>\n	Ministerio de Econom&iacute;a y Competitividad. Programa INNPACTO&nbsp; (Ref IPT-2012-0614-010000)</div>\n<div>\n	&nbsp;</div>\n<div>\n	<em>Desarrollo de nuevas herramientas farmacol&oacute;gicas antitumorales que dirijan su acci&oacute;n al silenciamiento o a la inhibici&oacute;n de la MAP kinasa ERK5. </em></div>\n<div>\n	Ministerio de Econom&iacute;a y Competitividad. Plan Nacional de I+D+I 2016-2018. Programa Biomedicina (Ref SAF2015-64237-R).</div>\n',27,2,0),(277,30,0,'José Manuel LÓPEZ','<p>\n	<a href=\"javascript:MostraPage(294,1); \">Neurodegeneraci&oacute; i envelliment</a></p>\n<h2>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\">Prote&iuml;nes Quinases d&#39;Estr&egrave;s</span></h2>\n<p>\n	<strong>L&iacute;der del Grup:</strong></p>\n<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				Jos&eacute; Manuel L&oacute;pez</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:josemanuel.lopez@uab.es\">josemanuel.lopez@uab.es</a></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				Tel: 935 814 278</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<table>\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0002-4104-6262\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"28\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/orcid.png\" width=\"28\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researcherid.com/rid/D-1654-2011\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"28\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/RID.jpg\" width=\"28\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<p>\n									<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=55685078300&amp;amp;eid=2-s2.0-84865604296\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 29px; height: 29px;\" /></a></p>\n							</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/JMBladef.jpg\" style=\"width: 100%; margin-top: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px;\" /></p>\n<p>\n	<strong>Membres del Grup:</strong><br />\n	Nabil Ben Messaoud<br />\n	Jicheng Yue</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>OBJECTIUS ESTRAT&Egrave;GICS</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	Funcionant com sensors i interruptors les prote&iuml;nes quinases tenen un paper cr&iacute;tic en la regulaci&oacute; de les decisions cel&middot;lulars. El nostre grup d&rsquo;investigaci&oacute; est&agrave; interessat en el control de&nbsp;l&#39;apoptosi&nbsp;i la&nbsp;meiosi&nbsp;perprote&iuml;nes quinases d&rsquo;estr&egrave;s&nbsp;i fem servir els o&ograve;cits de&nbsp;Xenopus&nbsp;com a model cel&middot;lular per a estudiar els mecanismes que governen aquests processos biol&ograve;gics irreversibles. Tamb&eacute; volem investigar com l&#39;acumulaci&oacute; d&#39;un nucle&ograve;tid (ZMP) i l&#39;activaci&oacute; d&#39;una prote&iuml;na quinasa d&#39;estr&egrave;s (AMPK) pot influir en el desenvolupament de la&nbsp;malaltia de Lesch Nyhan, una greu malaltia neurol&ograve;gica a l&#39;home.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PRINCIPALS L&Iacute;NIES D&#39;INVESTIGACI&Oacute;&nbsp;</strong></span><br />\n	<br />\n	1) Estudiar la funci&oacute; de les prote&iuml;nes quinases d&rsquo;estr&egrave;s en la mort cel&middot;lular i la meiosi.&nbsp;L&#39;objectiu d&#39;aquest projecte &eacute;s determinar el paper de les prote&iuml;nes quinases d&#39;estr&egrave;s AMPK, JNK i p38 en la mort d&#39;ov&ograve;cits indu&iuml;da pel xoc osm&ograve;tic i en la progressi&oacute; mei&ograve;tica indu&iuml;da per progesterona. Estudiarem en detall la regulaci&oacute; de l&#39;alliberament de citocrom c i l&#39;activaci&oacute; de les caspases per aquestes prote&iuml;nes quinases. Tamb&eacute; investigarem el paper de la AMPK i JNK en el control de la traducci&oacute; durant la progressi&oacute; mei&ograve;tica. Utilitzarem com a model els o&ograve;cits de&nbsp;Xenopus, que tenen grans avantatges per a la manipulaci&oacute; bioqu&iacute;mica.<br />\n	2) Estudiar el paper de l&#39;acumulaci&oacute; de ZMP i l&#39;activaci&oacute; de la AMPK en el desenvolupament de la malaltia de Lesch-Nyhan.&nbsp;La malaltia de Lesch-Nyhan provoca greus efectes neurol&ograve;gics com a conseq&uuml;&egrave;ncia d&#39;una defici&egrave;ncia de l&#39;enzim hipoxantina-guanina fosforribosiltransferasa (HPRT). Segueix sent un misteri com una simple modificaci&oacute; en el metabolisme de les purines produeix efectes dram&agrave;tics en el comportament hum&agrave;. La defici&egrave;ncia de HPRT s&#39;associa amb una disfunci&oacute; relativament selectiva dels sistemes dopamin&eacute;rgics al cervell. S&rsquo;han proposat diferents hip&ograve;tesis, com l&#39;acumulaci&oacute; d&#39;un metab&ograve;lit t&ograve;xic al cervell. Pensem que el nucle&ograve;tid ZMP &eacute;s l&#39;agent t&ograve;xic, i que actuant de forma pleiotr&ograve;pica induiria diversos canvis a la c&egrave;l&middot;lula produint la disfunci&oacute; cerebral. Un dels primers canvis seria l&#39;activaci&oacute; de la prote&iuml;na quinasa AMPK.<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PUBLICACIONS DESTACADES:</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	&bull; Yue J, L&oacute;pez JM. <em>JNK does not regulate meiotic progression in</em>&nbsp;<em>Xenopus</em>&nbsp;<em>oocytes: The strange case of pJNK and pERK. </em>Dev Biol. 416: 42-51, <strong>2016</strong>.</p>\n<p>\n	&bull; Yue J, Ben Messaoud N, L&oacute;pez JM. <em>Hyperosmotic Shock Engages Two Positive Feedback Loops through Caspase-3-dependent Proteolysis of JNK1-2 and Bid. </em>J Biol Chem. 290: 30375-89, <strong>2015</strong>.</p>\n<p>\n	&bull; Ben Messaoud N, Katzarova I, L&oacute;pez JM. <em>Basic Properties of the p38 Signaling Pathway in Response to Hyperosmotic Shock. </em>PLoS One. doi: 10.1371/journal.pone.0135249, <strong>2015</strong>.</p>\n<p>\n	&bull; Ben Messaoud N, Yue J, Valent D, Katzarova I, L&oacute;pez JM. <em>Osmostress-induced apoptosis in</em>&nbsp;<em>Xenopus</em>&nbsp;<em>oocytes: role of stress protein kinases, calpains and Smac/DIABLO. </em>PLoS One. doi: 10.1371/journal.pone.0124482, <strong>2015</strong>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;L&oacute;pez JM.<br />\n	<em>Digital kinases: A cell model for sensing, integrating and making choices.</em><br />\n	Communicative &amp; Integrative Biology. 3: 146-150,&nbsp;<strong>2010</strong>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;Marti&aacute;&ntilde;ez T, Franc&egrave;s S, L&oacute;pez JM.&nbsp;<br />\n	<em>Generation of digital responses in stress sensors.&nbsp;</em><br />\n	Journal of Biological Chemistry. 284: 23902-23911,&nbsp;<strong>2009</strong>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;Piqu&eacute; M, L&oacute;pez JM, Sylvain F, Guig&oacute; R, M&eacute;ndez R.&nbsp;<br />\n	<em>A combinatorial code for CPE-mediated translational control.&nbsp;</em><br />\n	Cell. 132: 434-448,<strong>2008</strong>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830965/public/\" target=\"_blank\">Veure m&eacute;s publicacions de JM. L&oacute;pez a PubMed.</a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n',30,2,0),(278,30,0,'Vicente MARTÍNEZ i Patrocinio VERGARA','<p>\n	<a href=\"javascript:MostraPage(294,1); \">Neurodegeneraci&oacute; i envelliment</a></p>\n<h2>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\">Neuroinmunogastroenterologia i&nbsp;Microbiota Intestinal</span></h2>\n<p>\n	<strong>L&iacute;ders del Grup:</strong></p>\n<table style=\"width: 100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				Vicente Mart&iacute;nez&nbsp; Perea</td>\n			<td>\n				Patrocinio Vergara Esteras</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:vicente.martinez@uab.cat\">vicente.martinez@uab.cat</a></td>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:patri.vergara@uab.cat\">patri.vergara@uab.cat</a></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				TEL: +34 93 581 3834</td>\n			<td>\n				TEL: +34 93 581 1848</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<table height=\"25\" width=\"40\">\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=35466861100\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"29\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" width=\"29\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n				<table>\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0002-9220-6406\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"28\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/orcid.png\" width=\"28\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researcherid.com/rid/M-6468-2013\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"27\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/RID.jpg\" width=\"27\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=7006757890\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"29\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" width=\"29\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"https://scholar.google.es/citations?user=l23MH60AAAAJ&amp;hl=ca\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"29\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/googlescholar.jpg\" width=\"29\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/Martvergdef.jpg\" style=\"width: 100%; margin-top: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px;\" /><br />\n	<br />\n	<strong> Membres del Grup:</strong><br />\n	Sergio Berd&uacute;n Mar&iacute;n<br />\n	Eva Maria Cepeda Romero<br />\n	Javier Est&eacute;vez Medina<br />\n	Marina Ferrer Clotas<br />\n	Sergio L&oacute;pez Est&eacute;vez<br />\n	Emma Mart&iacute;nez P&eacute;rez<br />\n	Maria Asunci&oacute;n Molina Romero</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>OBJECTIUS ESTRAT&Egrave;GICS</strong></span><br />\n	<br />\n	Els nostres interessos en recerca se centren en el camp de la neurogastroenterologia (neuroci&egrave;ncies ent&egrave;riques), en particular en l&#39;estudi de les interaccions neuro-immuns en el tracte gastrointestinal, incloent les interaccions amb la microbiota comensal de l&rsquo;intest&iacute;. El nostre objectiu final &eacute;s comprendre els mecanismes fisiopatol&ograve;gics b&agrave;sics dels trastorns funcionals i inflamatoris gastrointestinals a l&rsquo;esp&egrave;cie humana, amb la finalitat d&rsquo;identificar i caracteritzar dianes potencials d&rsquo;intervenci&oacute; terap&egrave;utica.&nbsp;<br />\n	Per aconseguir aquest objectius seguim un enfocament multidisciplinar, en el qual s&rsquo;integren treballs in vivo en models animals amb estudis molecular i de biologia cel&middot;lular.<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PRINCIPALS L&Iacute;NIES D&#39;INVESTIGACI&Oacute;</strong></span><br />\n	<br />\n	-Desenvolupament i caracteritzaci&oacute; de models animals de trastorns gastrointestinals: malaltia inflamat&ograve;ria intestinal i s&iacute;ndrome d&#39;intest&iacute; irritable.<br />\n	-Implicacions dels mast&ograve;cits a la fisiopatologia dels trastorns gastrointestinals inflamat&ograve;ries i relacionats amb al&middot;l&egrave;rgies alimentaries.<br />\n	-Mast&ograve;cits i remodelaci&oacute; neuronal en el tracte gastrointestinal.<br />\n	-Mecanismes i farmacologia del dolor visceral d&#39;origen intestinal.<br />\n	-Microbiota intestinal: Relaci&oacute; amb mecanismes sensorials viscerals i amb la funci&oacute; barrera intestinal.<br />\n	-Eix sistema nervi&oacute;s central-tracte gastrointestinal: Efectes de l&#39;estr&egrave;s sobre la funci&oacute; gastrointestinal.<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PUBLICACIONS </strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	&bull; Jard&iacute; F, Fern&aacute;ndez-Blanco JA, <strong>Mart&iacute;nez V</strong>, <strong>Vergara P</strong>. Persistent alterations in colonic afferent innervation in a rat model of postinfectious gut dysfunction: Role for changes in peripheral neurotrophic factors. Neurogastroenterol Motil. <strong>2016 </strong>Gen; <span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial, helvetica, clean, sans-serif; font-size: 11.999px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: 16.6138px; orphans: auto; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 1; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; display: inline !important; float: none; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">28(5):693-704. doi: 10.1111/nmo.12766. Epub 2016</span>.</p>\n<p>\n	&bull; Fern&aacute;ndez-Blanco JA, Est&eacute;vez J, Shea-Donohue T, <strong>Mart&iacute;nez V</strong>, <strong>Vergara P</strong>. Changes in Epithelial Barrier Function in Response to Parasitic Infection: Implications for IBD Pathogenesis. J Crohns Colitis. <strong>2015 </strong>Jun; 9(6):463&ndash;76. doi: 10.1093/ecco-jcc/jjv056. Epub 2015.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	&bull; Berd&uacute;n S, Rychter J, <strong>Vergara P</strong>. Effects of nerve growth factor antagonist k252a on peritoneal mast cell degranulation: implications for rat postoperative ileus. American Journal of Physiology - Gastrointestinal and Liver Physiology&nbsp;<strong>2015 </strong>Sep; 309 G801-6. doi:10.1152/ajpgi.00152.2015</p>\n<p>\n	&bull; Jardi F, Aguilera M, <strong>Vergara P, Martinez V</strong>. Lipopolysaccharides facilitate colonic motor alterations associated to the sensitization to a luminal antigen in rats. J Neurogastroenterol Motil. <strong>2015 </strong>Mar; 21(2):222&ndash;35. doi: 10.5056/jnm14136</p>\n<p>\n	&bull; Rychter J, Ortega O, Berdun S, Arenas C, Lopez I, Espin F, <strong>Vergara P</strong>, et al. Mast cell degranulation inhibits motor patterns of human ileum and sigmoid colon in vitro: relevance for postoperative ileus. Neurogastroenterol Motil. <strong>2015</strong> Aug; 27(8):1098&ndash;109. doi: 10.1111/nmo.12589. Epub 2015</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830977/public/\" target=\"_blank\">Veure m&eacute;s publicacions de V. Mart&iacute;nez a PubMed.</a></p>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830981/public/\" target