di.Ortiz@uab.cat\">Jordi.Ortiz@uab.cat</a></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				TEL: +34 935 814 827</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<table>\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0002-9748-2290\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/orcid.png\" style=\"width: 26px; height: 26px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researcherid.com/rid/E-9018-2011\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/RID.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<p>\n									<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=7203050650\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 29px; height: 29px;\" /></a></p>\n							</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://scholar.google.es/citations?sortby=pubdate&amp;hl=ca&amp;user=aaPO4uoAAAAJ&amp;view_op=list_works\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"30\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/googlescholar.jpg\" width=\"30\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://es.linkedin.com/pub/jordi-ortiz/60/717/511\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"34\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Linkedin.jpg\" width=\"43\" /></a></td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/JOrtizweb.jpg\" style=\"width: 100%; margin-top: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px;\" /></p>\n<p>\n	<strong>Group members:</strong><br />\n	Doaa Abass<br />\n	Vict&ograve;ria Garcia<br />\n	<a href=\"http://inc.uab.cat/English/profile.php?id=69\" target=\"_blank\">Carles Gil Gir&oacute;</a><br />\n	Bernat Granell<br />\n	<a href=\"http://inc.uab.cat/English/profile.php?id=175\" target=\"_blank\">Marta Gonz&aacute;lez-Sep&uacute;lveda</a><br />\n	Teresa M&iacute;nguez<br />\n	Josefa Sabri&agrave;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong><span style=\"color:#800000;\">STRATEGIC OBJECTIVES</span></strong><br />\n	<br />\n	Our goal is to help generate new pharmacological tools for the treatment of mental disorders and addictions. In particular, we study potential new drug targets to improve their mechanisms of action in the therapy of psychoses, addictions and other disorders. In particular, we study the interactions between receptors of dopamine, glutamate, histamine, GABA and other neurotransmitters, its signal transduction in brain tissue, the localization of their receptors and the effects caused by its ligands. We are also interested in the mechanisms involved in vulnerability to mental disorders and their biological characterization using biomarkers.<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong><span style=\"color:#800000;\">MAIN RESEARCH LINES</span></strong><br />\n	<br />\n	SEARCH FOR PHARMACOLOGICAL TOOLS TO TREAT COCAINE ADDICTION<br />\n	At present we use animal models of cocaine self-administration under the working hypothesis that drug seeking could be modulated by new histaminergic and dopaminergic agents.<br />\n	Simultaneously, we use brain slices to study the effects of several receptor ligands on dopamine synthesis and release and the phosphorylation of transcription factor CREB and protein kinase ERK. These studies could be useful to evaluate new candidate molecules for the treatment of addictive and other psychiatric disorders.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	FUNDING 2006-2012 by Plan Nacional de Investigaci&oacute;n y Desarrollo, Spain<br />\n	<br />\n	<br />\n	<strong><span style=\"color:#800000;\">SELECTED PUBLICATIONS</span></strong></p>\n<p>\n	&bull; Ma GF, Raivio N; Sabria J, Ortiz J<br />\n	<em>Agonist and antagonist effects of aripiprazole on D2-like receptors controlling rat brain dopamine synthesis depend on the dopaminergic tone</em><br />\n	International Journal of Neuropsychopharmacology in press</p>\n<p>\n	&bull; Moreno E, Moreno-Delgado D, Navarro G, Hoffmann HM, Fuentes S, Rosell-Vilar S, Gasperini P, Rodr&iacute;guez-Ruiz M, Medrano M, Mallol J, Cort&eacute;s A, Casad&oacute; V, Llu&iacute;s C, Ferr&eacute; S, Ortiz J, Canela E, McCormick PJ<br />\n	<em>Cocaine disrupts histamine H3 receptor modulation of dopamine D1 receptor signaling: sigma1-D1-H3 receptor complexes as key targets for reducing cocaine&#39;s effects</em><br />\n	Journal of Neuroscience, <strong>2014</strong> Mar 5;34(10):3545-58.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp;Gonz&aacute;lez-Sep&uacute;lveda M, Rosell S, Hoffmann HM, Castillo-Ruiz M, Mignon V, Moreno-Delgado D, Vignes M, D&iacute;az J, Sabri&aacute; J, Ortiz J<br />\n	<a href=\"http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S2210533612001347\" target=\"_blank\"><em>Cellular distribution of the histamine H3 receptor in the basal ganglia:&nbsp; Functional modulation of dopamine and glutamate neurotransmission</em></a><br />\n	Basal Ganglia.&nbsp;<strong>2013 </strong><br />\n	<br />\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;Gallego X, Ruiz-Medina J, Valverde O, Molas S, Robles N, Sabri&agrave; J, Crabbe JC, Dierssen M.<br />\n	<em>Transgenic over expression of nicotinic receptor alpha 5, alpha 3, and beta 4 subunit genes reduces ethanol intake in mice.&nbsp;</em><br />\n	Alcohol.&nbsp;<strong>2012</strong>;46(3):205-15.<br />\n	<br />\n	&bull;&nbsp;Hoffmann H, Nadal R, Vignes M and Ortiz J.<br />\n	<em>Chronic cocaine self-administration modulates ERK1/2 and CREB responses to dopamine receptor agonists in striatal slices</em><br />\n	Addict Biol.<strong>&nbsp;2012</strong>;17(3):565-75.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/JOrtiz-AltresPublicacions.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>OTHER PUBLICATIONS</strong></span></a></p>\n',39,2,2),(430,45,0,'Marc Pallarès','<h2>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\">Neuroesteroids and Behavior</span></h2>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong>Group leader:</strong></p>\n<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				Marc Pallar&eacute;s A&ntilde;&oacute;</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:Marc.Pallares@uab.cat\">Marc.Pallares@uab.cat</a></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				TEL: +34 935 812 542</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<table>\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								<p>\n									<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=7004926195\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 29px; height: 29px;\" /></a></p>\n							</td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Marc_Pallares3/publications\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"30\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/researchgate.jpg\" width=\"30\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/MPalldef.jpg\" style=\"width: 100%; margin-top: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px;\" /></p>\n<p>\n	<strong>Group members:</strong><br />\n	Iris Bartolom&eacute; Torrell<br />\n	S&ograve;nia Darbra Marges<br />\n	Anna Llid&oacute;</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>STRATEGIC OBJECTIVES&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</strong></span><br />\n	<br />\n	Characterization of the perinatal endogenous neurosteroids role in the GABA systems maturation using an animal model of psychopathology based on the development, analyzing the alteration of neonatal allopregananolone levels on adult behaviour (anxious behaviour, depressive and psychotic symptoms).<br />\n	Characterization of the GABA-positive neurosteroids role in different aspects of the alcohol addiction (tolerance, withdrawal, relapse, etc.). Determinate the relations between the alteration of the endogenous perinatal neurosteroids levels&nbsp; and the vulnerability to alcoholism.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\n	<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>MAIN RESEARCH LINES&nbsp; &nbsp;</strong></span><br />\n	<br />\n	1.-&nbsp; Role of neurosteroids&nbsp; on brain maturation (hippocampus and thalamus-cortical system) and behavior in adolescence and adult age .<br />\n	The alteration of the perinatal allopregnanolone levels induces behavioral alterations in the adult age (i.e. novelty induced exploration), and decreases the efficacy of anxiolytic drugs.<br />\n	We emphasize in psychopathology models based on alterations in brain development.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\n	2.-&nbsp; Effects of neurosteroids on alcohol addiction in rats, and also on several alcoholism effects, as cognitive impairment, withdrawal or anxiety.<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PUBLICATIONS</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	&bull; Darbra, S.; M&ograve;dol, L.; Llid&oacute;, A.; Casas, K.; Vall&eacute;e, M.; Pallar&egrave;s, M. <em>Neonatal allopregnanolone levels alteration: effects on behavior and role of the hippocampus.</em><br />\n	Progress in Neurobiology 113:577-585.<strong>2014</strong></p>\n<p>\n	&bull; M&ograve;dol, L.; Casas, K.; Navarro, X.; Llid&oacute;, A.; Vall&eacute;e, M.; Pallar&egrave;s, M.;Darbra, S.&nbsp;<br />\n	<em>Neonatal finasteride administration alters hippocampal &alpha;4 and &delta; GABAAR subunits expression and behavioral responses to progesterone in adult rats. </em><br />\n	The International Journal of Neuropsychopharmacology 17(2):259-273.<strong>2014</strong></p>\n<p>\n	&bull; Llid&oacute;, A.; M&ograve;dol, L.; Darbra, S.; Pallar&egrave;s, M.<br />\n	<em>Interaction between neonatal allopregnanolone administration and early maternal separation: effects on adolescent and adult behaviour in male </em>rats.<br />\n	Hormones and Behavior 63(4):577-585. <strong>2013</strong></p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp;M&ograve;dol L, Darbra S, Vall&egrave;e M, Pallar&egrave;s M.<br />\n	<em>Alteration of neonatal Allopregnanolone levels affects exploration, anxiety, aversive learning and adult behavioural response to intrahippocampal neurosteroids.</em><br />\n	Behav Brain Res.&nbsp;<strong>2013</strong> 15;241:96-104.</p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp;Darbra S, Modol L, Vall&eacute;e M, Pallar&egrave;s M.<br />\n	<em>Neonatal neurosteroid levels are determinant in shaping adult prepulse inhibition response to hippocampal allopregnanolone in rats.</em><br />\n	Psychoneuroendocrinology 38(8): 1397-1406.&nbsp; <strong>2013</strong></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830997/public/\" target=\"_blank\">See more M. Pallar&egrave;s in PubMed. </a></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n',40,2,2),(431,45,0,'Olga Pol Rigau','<p>\n	<a href=\"javascript:MostraPage(373,1); \">Neuroregeneration and repair</a></p>\n<h2>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\">Molecular Neuropharmacology</span></h2>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td colspan=\"6\">\n				<strong>Group leader:</strong></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td colspan=\"6\">\n				Olga Pol Rigau</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td colspan=\"6\">\n				<a href=\"mailto:Olga.Pol@uab.cat\">Olga.Pol@uab.cat</a></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td colspan=\"6\">\n				TEL: 619 757 054</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0002-4621-8457\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/orcid.png\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"http://www.researcherid.com/rid/C-9194-2011\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/RID.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n			<td>\n				<p>\n					<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=6701603494\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 29px; height: 29px;\" /></a></p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"http://www.researchgate.net/profile/Olga_Pol\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/researchgate.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n			<td>\n				&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>\n				&nbsp;</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/2016-06-02 09_opt.jpg\" style=\"width: 400px; height: 319px;\" /></p>\n<p>\n	<strong>Group members:</strong><br />\n	Alba Grayston<br />\n	Sergi Le&aacute;nez<br />\n	Christina McDonnell<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>STRATEGIC OBJECTIVES</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	Chronic pain affects a high percentage of the adult population and is difficult to treat even with the most potent analgesic compounds, being one of the main challenges in the current research of pain. Our main objective is to investigate new effective strategies for the treatment of different types of pain by using genetic, molecular and pharmacological approaches.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>MAIN RESEARCH LINES</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	1) Study the antinociceptive effects produced by the activation of several transcription factors in animals with acute (inflammatory, visceral, response to heat) and chronic pain (arthritis, inflammatory, neuropathic) as well as its interaction with other neurotransmitter systems.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	2) Establish new strategies to enhance the analgesic actions of opioids and/or cannabinoids during acute and chronic pain in mice, avoiding the development of side effects.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	3) Identify new approaches for treating painful diabetic neuropathy and oxidative stress, two main complications of diabetes, by using specific drug combinations.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	4) Investigate the role played by nitric oxide-carbon monoxide systems in the modulation of the emotional and nociceptive responses induced by a chronic peripheral inflammation in the central nervous system of mice.</p>\n<p>\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>FEATURED PUBLICATIONS</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull; Carcol&eacute; M, Castany S, L&eacute;anez S, Pol O<br />\n	<em>Treatment with a heme oxygenase 1 inducer enhances the antinociceptive effects of &micro;-opioid, &delta;-opioid, and cannabinoid 2 receptors during inflammatory pain</em><br />\n	Journal of Pharmacology and Experimental Therapeutics. <strong>2014</strong>, 351:224-232&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull; Hervera A, Le&aacute;nez S, Motterlini R, Pol O<br />\n	<em>Treatment with carbon monoxide-releasing molecules and an HO-1 inducer enhances the effects and expression of &micro;-opioid receptors during neuropathic pain</em><br />\n	Anesthesiology. <strong>2013</strong>, 118:1180&ndash;1197<br />\n	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &bull; Hervera A, Gou G, Le&aacute;nez S, Pol O<br />\n	<em>Effects of treatment with a carbon monoxide-releasing molecule and a heme oxygenase 1 inducer in the antinociceptive effects of morphine in different models of acute and chronic pain in mice</em><br />\n	Psychopharmacology. <strong>2013</strong>, 228:463&ndash;477</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull; Negrete R, Hervera A, Le&aacute;nez S, Mart&iacute;n-Campos JM, Pol O<br />\n	<em>The antinociceptive effects of JWH-015 in chronic inflammatory pain are produced by nitric oxide-cGMP-PKG-KATP pathway activation mediated by opioids</em><br />\n	PLoS ONE. <strong>2011</strong>, 6(10): e26688</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull; Hervera A, Negrete R, Le&aacute;nez S, Mart&iacute;n-Campos JM, Pol O<br />\n	<em>The role of nitric oxide in the local antiallodynic and antihyperalgesic effects and expression of &delta;-opioid and cannabinoid-2 receptors during neuropathic pain in mice&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </em><br />\n	Journal of Pharmacology and Experimental Therapeutics. <strong>2010</strong>, 334:887-896</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48831001/public/\" target=\"_blank\">See more O. Pol in PubMed. </a></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n',41,2,2),(432,45,0,'Isabel Portell','<p>\n	<a href=\"javascript:MostraPage(374,1)\">Neurobiology of the normal and disturbed mind</a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\">Memory facilitation and reversion of cognitive deficits in healthy animals and in animals with brain damage: physical exercise and epinephrine</span><br />\n	&nbsp;</h2>\n<p>\n	<strong>Group leader:</strong></p>\n<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				Isabel Portell</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:jose.aguilera@uab.cat\">Isabel.Portell@uab.cat</a></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				TEL: +34 935 813 220</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<table>\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0002-7710-0101\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/orcid.png\" style=\"width: 26px; height: 26px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researcherid.com/rid/C-5991-2011\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/RID.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<p>\n									<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=6602337878\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 29px; height: 29px;\" /></a></p>\n							</td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researchgate.net/profile/Isabel_Portell-Cortes\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"27\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/researchgate.jpg\" width=\"27\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/IPortellGroup2.jpg\" style=\"width: 100%;\" /></p>\n<p>\n	<strong>Membres del Grup:</strong><br />\n	<a href=\"http://inc.uab.cat/English/profile.php?id=46\">Margalida Coll Andreu</a><br />\n	David Costa Miserachs<br />\n	Meritxell Torras Garcia<br />\n	Laura Amor&oacute;s Aguilar</p>\n<p>\n	<strong>Membres anteriors:</strong><br />\n	Silvia Garc&iacute;a Capdevila<br />\n	Alejandra Jacotte Simancas</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>STRATEGIC OBJECTIVES</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	Our research group studies the effects of regular exercise and epinephrine on cognitive processes. Currently, our research is mainly aimed at reducing cognitive impairment caused by traumatic brain injury by means of physical exercise treatment, and at studying the neurobiological mechanisms (neurogenesis, neuroprotection, etc.) that may mediate the effects of this treatment. Additionally, we want to study whether certain drugs, such as citicoline or edaravone, can be combined with physical exercise to enhance the benefits of the latter.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<em>Keywords</em>: Physical exercise, epinephrine, traumatic brain injury, learning and memory, object recognition memory, cognitive deficits, neurogenesis, neuroprotection.<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>MAIN RESEARCH LINES</strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		Improvement of learning and memory by post-training epinephrine administration.</li>\n	<li>\n		Improvement of learning and memory by voluntary physical exercise.</li>\n	<li>\n		Reduction of cognitive deficits produced by traumatic brain injury by physical exercise treatment.</li>\n	<li>\n		Study of the ability of several pharmacological agents, when used in combination with physical exercise, to enhance the benefits of the latter on cognitive deficits induced by traumatic brain injury.<br />\n		&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>SELECTED PUBLICATIONS</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Jacotte-Simancas, A.; Costa-Miserachs, D.; Coll-Andreu, M.; Torras-Garcia, M.; Borlongan, C.; Portell-Cort&eacute;s, I.<br />\n	<em>Effects of voluntary physical exercise, citicoline, and combined treatment on object recognition memory, neurogenesis and neuroprotection after traumatic brain injury in rats. </em><br />\n	Journal of Neurotrauma, 32 (739-751) (<strong>2015</strong>)</p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Amor&oacute;s-Aguilar, L.; Portell-Cort&eacute;s, I.; Costa-Miserachs, D.; Torras-Garcia, M.; &nbsp;Coll-Andreu, M.<br />\n	<em>Traumatic Brain Injury in Late Adolescent Rats: Effects on Adulthood Memory and Anxiety.</em><br />\n	Behavioral Neuroscience, 129 (2), 149-159 (<strong>2015</strong>)</p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Jacotte-Simancas, A.; Costa-Miserachs, D.; Torras-Garcia, M., Coll-Andreu, M.;Portell-Cort&eacute;s, I.<br />\n	<em>Effects of voluntary physical exercise and post-training epinephrine on acquisition in a spatial task in the Barnes maze.</em><br />\n	Behavioural Brain Research. 247, pp. 178 - 181.(<strong>2013</strong>).</p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Jurado-Berbel P, Costa-Miserachs D, Torras-Garcia M, Coll-Andreu M, Portell-Cort&eacute;s I.<br />\n	<em>Standard object recognition memory and &ldquo;what&rdquo; and &ldquo;where&rdquo; components: Improvement by post-training epinephrine in highly habituated rats.</em><br />\n	Behav Brain Res. <strong>2010</strong>;207(1):44-50.</p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Garc&iacute;a-Capdevila, S., Portell-Cort&eacute;s, I., Torras-Garcia, M., Coll-Andreu, M, Costa-Miserachs, D.<br />\n	<em>Effects of long-term voluntary exercise on learning and memory processes:dependency of the task and level of exercise</em>.<br />\n	Behav Brain Res. <strong>2009</strong>;202(2):162-70.</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48831024/public/\" target=\"_blank\">See more I. Portell in PubMed. </a></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n',42,2,2),(433,45,0,'José Rodríguez Alvarez','<p>\n	<a href=\"javascript:MostraPage(372,1); \">Neurodegeneration and ageing</a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\">Molecular biology of synaptic dysfuction in neurodegenerative diseases </span><br />\n	&nbsp;</h2>\n<p>\n	<strong>Group leader:</strong></p>\n<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				Jos&eacute; Rodr&iacute;guez-Alvarez</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:Jose.Rodriguez@uab.cat\">Jose.Rodriguez@uab.cat</a></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				TEL: +34 935 811 525</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<table>\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0001-8582-8082\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"26\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/orcid.png\" width=\"26\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researcherid.com/rid/F-8403-2011\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/RID.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<p>\n									<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=7005924608\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 29px; height: 29px;\" /></a></p>\n							</td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researchgate.net/profile/Jose_Rodriguez-Alvarez\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"29\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/researchgate.jpg\" width=\"29\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://es.linkedin.com/in/peperodriguez\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"31\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Linkedin.jpg\" width=\"38\" /></a></td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/pepe grup.jpg\" style=\"width: 100%;\" /></p>\n<p>\n	<strong>Group members:</strong><br />\n	Judith Catal&agrave; Solsona- Master student<br />\n	<a href=\"http://inc.uab.cat/English/profile.php?id=97\"><span style=\"color:#000000;\">Alfredo Jes&uacute;s Mi&ntilde;ano Molina- Postdoctoral scientist</span></a><br />\n	Amaia Ochoa de Am&aacute;rzaga- PhD student<br />\n	Ricardo Quiroz Baez- Visiting scientist<br />\n	Dolores Siedlecki- PhD student<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong>Past members:</strong><br />\n	Dr. Guillem Sanchez Opazo<br />\n	Dr. Wen wen Chen<br />\n	Dr. Nahuai Badiola Benito<br />\n	Dra. Bruna Barneda Zahonero<br />\n	Dr. Xavi Xifr&oacute; Collsamata<br />\n	Dra. Cristina Malagelada Grau</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>STRATEGIC OBJECTIVES</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	Since 2000, one of the basic objectives of my research team has been the study of the cellular and molecular mechanism involved in brain neurodegeneration. Two main questions have guided our research effort during these years: 1.- Which molecular mechanisms are involved in the control of neuronal apoptosis? ; 2.- Why synaptic activity is altered in Alzheimer&#39;s Disease (AD)?.<br />\n	<br />\n	During the last years, the basic objective of our research team has been the study of the cellular and molecular mechanisms involved in the synaptic dysfunction and neuronal death as a straight approach for the understanding neurodegenerative pathologies, in particular AD. We&rsquo;ve been mainly interested in the mechanisms that are associated to the early cognitive dysfunction observed in AD. We want to know through which mechanisms synaptic activity is altered in AD well before neurodegeneration happens. We have focused in the effects on AMPA subtype of glutamate receptors since during the last years we have accumulated in the laboratory several evidences suggesting that oA&beta;-mediated reduction in synaptic GluA1-containing AMPAR could participate in early synaptic dysfunction in AD. For this reason, we believe that understanding the effects of oA&beta; on synaptic AMPAR dynamics may allow the identification of molecular targets for novel therapeutic and diagnostic approaches at early stages of AD.<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>FEATURED&nbsp; PUBLICATIONS:</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#000000;\">&bull;&nbsp; </span>Fado R., Soto D., Mi&ntilde;ano-Molina A., Pozo M., Carrasco P., Yefimenko N., <strong>Rodr&iacute;guez-Alvarez J</strong> &amp; Casals N. Specific regulation of GluA subunit synthesis and AMPA receptor-mediated synaptic function by CPT1C in the hippocampus. J Biol Chem 290:25548-25560 (<strong>2015</strong>)</p>\n<p>\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#000000;\">&bull; </span>Parra-Damas, A., Valero, J., Chen, M., Espa&ntilde;a, J., Mart&iacute;n, E., Ferrer, I., <strong>Rodr&iacute;guez-Alvarez, J </strong>&amp; C.A. Saura.CRTC1 activates a transcriptional program deregulated at early Alzheimer&rsquo;s disease-related stages.&nbsp;J Neurosci. 34:5576-5787 (<strong>2014</strong>)</p>\n<p>\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#000000;\">&bull;</span> Fad&oacute;, R., Moubarak, R., Mi&ntilde;ano-Molina, A.J., Barneda-Zahonero, B., Valero, J., Saura, C.A., Mor&aacute;n, J., Comella, J.X. &amp; <strong>J. Rodr&iacute;guez-Alvarez</strong>.&nbsp;&nbsp;X-linked inhibitor of apoptosis protein negatively regulates neurite outgrowth through interaction with cRAF and Trk.&nbsp;Sci. Reports 3:2397 (<strong>2013</strong>) doi: 10.1038/srep02397</p>\n<p>\n	&bull; Barneda-Zahonero, B., Servitja, J.M., Badiola, N., Mi&ntilde;ano-Molina, A.J., Fad&oacute;, R., Saura, C.A. &amp; <strong>J. Rodriguez-Alvarez</strong>.&nbsp;Nurr1 is required for NMDA receptor-mediated neuronal survival.&nbsp;J. Biol. Chem. 287:11351-11362 (<strong>2012</strong>)</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	&bull; Mi&ntilde;ano-Molina, A.J., Espa&ntilde;a, J., Martin, E. Barneda-Zahonero, B., Fad&oacute;, R., Sol&eacute; M., Trull&aacute;s, R., Saura, C.A. &amp; <strong>J. Rodr&iacute;guez-Alvarez</strong>. &nbsp;Soluble oligomers of amyloid-beta peptide disrupt AMPA receptors membrane trafficking contributing to early synapse dysfunction.&nbsp;J Biol. Chem. 286:27311-27321 (<strong>2011</strong>)</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48831035/public/\" target=\"_blank\">See more J. Rodr&iacute;guez-&Aacute;lvarez in PubMed.</a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n',43,2,2),(434,45,0,'Carlos A. Saura','<p>\n	<a href=\"javascript:MostraPage(372,1);\">Neurodegeneration and ageing</a></p>\n<h2>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\">Neurobiology of Alzheimer&#39;s Disease</span></h2>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong>Group leader:</strong></p>\n<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				Carlos A. Saura</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:carlos.saura@uab.es\">carlos.saura@uab.es</a></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				TEL: +34- 935 868 398</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<table>\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3692-5657\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/orcid.png\" style=\"width: 26px; height: 26px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researcherid.com/rid/D-2727-2011\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/RID.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<p>\n									<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=6701471293\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 29px; height: 29px;\" /></a></p>\n							</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	<br />\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/FotolabCSaura2014.jpg\" style=\"width: 100%;\" /></p>\n<div>\n	<strong>Group members:</strong></div>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"http://inc.uab.cat/Catala/profile.php?id=167\">Dr. Lilian Enr&iacute;quez</a><br />\n	Miriam Javier Torrent</p>\n<div>\n	Laura Rubi&oacute; Ferrarons</div>\n<div>\n	Carlos Soto Fagu&aacute;s</div>\n<div>\n	Ohiane Ussia</div>\n<div>\n	<div>\n		Anna del Ser</div>\n	<div>\n		Paula Conde Rubio</div>\n</div>\n<div>\n	&nbsp;</div>\n<div>\n	&nbsp;</div>\n<div>\n	<strong>Past members</strong>:<br />\n	Dr. Sergi Marco Mart&iacute;n<br />\n	Dr. Judit Espa&ntilde;a<br />\n	Dr. Vidalba Rocher Ros<br />\n	Dr. Jorge Valero<br />\n	Dr. Meng Chen</div>\n<div>\n	Dr. Arnaldo Parra Damas</div>\n<div>\n	Dr. Muriel Arim&oacute;n Bed&oacute;s</div>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong><u><a href=\"http://www.sauralab.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Visit their website</a></u></strong></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>STRATEGIC OBJECTIVES</strong></span><br />\n	<br />\n	Alzheimer&acute;s disease (AD) is a neurodegenerative disorder characterized by progressive memory loss caused by early synaptic dysfunction in brain regions essential for memory encoding and storage, such as the hippocampus and enthorrinal cortex. Accumulation of amyloid plaques containing &beta;-amyloid (A&beta;) peptides, which are generated by presenilin (PS)/&gamma;-secretase-dependent processing of the &beta;-amyloid precursor protein (APP), and phosphorylated tau are key events in the disease process. Our hypothesis is that cognitive impairment in normal and pathological aging is associated with synaptic dysfunction as a result of changes in gene expression networks. Our investigations combine genetics, transcriptomics and proteomics approaches to better understand the molecular mechanisms by which gene expression changes due to PS and A&beta; underlie synaptic and cognition dysfunction and neurodegeneration in AD. Progress in understanding the cellular processes regulating gene expression changes in cognition is relevant to develop therapeutic interventions for age-related cognitive disorders.&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>MAIN RESEARCH LINES</strong></span><br />\n	<br />\n	1. Mechanisms of synaptic dysfunction in Alzheimer&acute;s disease<br />\n	The molecular mechanisms underlying gene expression changes and synapse and cognitive dysfunction in cognitive disorders are largely unknown. Recent studies from our lab indicate that specific gene expression programs induced by synaptic activity are essential for memory processing, whereas deregulation of these programs causes memory impairment in mouse models of AD. We investigate the role of the transcription factor cAMP-response element binding protein (CREB) and its transcripcional coactivators CREB binding protein (CBP) and CREB-regulated transcription coactivator-1 (CRTC1) on regulation of specific gene expression programs in cells and transgenic mice that overexpress mutant APP and presenilin genes. Our results indicate that deregulation of specific CREB-dependent gene expression programs plays a role in synaptic and cognitive dysfunction, and regulation of specific gene networks is relevant to develop therapeutic interventions for age-related cognitive disorders. These signaling pathways are being tested as potential drug targets in AD experimental models.<br />\n	<br />\n	2. Novel therapeutic strategies in Alzheimer&acute;s disease<br />\n	The discovery of novel molecular mechanisms underlying synaptic dysfunction and memory loss in transgenic and knockout mouse models of AD allow us to design new therapeutic strategies to prevent and/or reverse cognitive dysfunction in this disease. We have described that inactivation of presenilin-1/&gamma;-secretase reduces age-dependent amyloid pathology and memory deficits in APP transgenic mice, whereas inactivation of both presenilins results in memory deficits and neurodegeneration through deregulation of synaptic proteins and the CREB signaling pathway. Similarly, accumulation of A&beta; alters expression of CREB target genes required for memory by deregulating the coactivator CRTC1. We are currently employing novel gene therapy and pharmacological approaches to activate&nbsp; CRTC1 signaling and reverse memory deficits in transgenic mouse models of AD. Finally, we study the cellular mechanisms by which cognitive stimulation has beneficial effects on adult neurogenesis and memory in AD.<br />\n	<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>FEATURED PUBLICATIONS</strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		<p>\n			Parra-Damas A., Chen M., Enr&iacute;quez-Barreto L., Ortega L., Acosta S., Camats Perna J., Fullana N., Aguilera J., Rodr&iacute;guez-Alvarez J., and Saura C.A. <em>&nbsp;CRTC1 function during memory encoding is disrupted in neurodegeneration</em> (2017). Biol Psychiatry 81 (2). Featured cover</p>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n		<p>\n			Sarroca S., Molina-Mart&iacute;nez P., Arest&eacute; C., EtzrodtM., Garc&iacute;a de FrutosP., GasaR., AntonellA., MolinuevoJL, S&aacute;nchez-ValleR., SauraC.A., Llad&oacute;A., Sanfeliu C. <em>Preservation of cell survival mechanisms by the presenilin-1 K239N mutation may cause its milder clinical phenotype</em> (2016). Neurobiology of Aging 46: 169-179.</p>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n		<p>\n			Saura C.A., Parra-Damas AJ and Enr&iacute;quez-Barreto L. <em>Gene expression parallels synaptic excitability and plasticity changes in Alzheimer&acute;s disease</em>. Front. Cell. Neurosci. 2015. 9:318</p>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n		<p>\n			Parra-Damas A., Valero J., Chen M., Espa&ntilde;a J., Martin E., Ferrer I., Rodr&iacute;guez-Alvarez J. and Saura C.A.&nbsp; <em>Crtc1 activates a transcriptional program deregulated at early Alzheimer&acute;s disease-related stages</em>. J. Neuroscience. 2014. 34(17): 5776-87. Featured cover</p>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n		<p>\n			Xifr&oacute; X, Mi&ntilde;ano-Molina A.J, Saura CA, Rodr&iacute;guez-&Aacute;lvarez J. Ras protein activation is a key event in activity-dependent&nbsp; survival of cerebellar granule neurons. J Biol Chem. 2014. 289(12):8462-72</p>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n		<p>\n			Balmaceda V., Cuchillo-Iba&ntilde;ez, I., Pujadas, L., Garcia-Ayll&oacute;n, M-S., Saura C.A., Nimpf, J., Soriano, E. and S&aacute;ez-Valero J. <em>ApoER2 processing by presenilin-1 modulates reelin expression</em>. FASEB J.&nbsp; 2014. 28(4): 1543-54</p>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n		<p>\n			Saura C.A. <em>CREB regulated transcription coactivator 1-dependent transcription in Alzheimer&acute;s disease mice</em> . Neurodegener Dis. 2012.10 (1-4): 250-2</p>\n	</li>\n</ul>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48831037/public/\" target=\"_blank\">See more CA. Saura in PubMed. </a></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n',44,2,2),(435,45,0,'Pilar Segura','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<a href=\"javascript:MostraPage(374,1)\">Neurobiology of the normal and disturbed mind</a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\">Facilitation of Learning and Memory by Intracranial Electrical Self Stimulation (ICSS)</span><br />\n	&nbsp;</h2>\n<div>\n	<strong>Group leader:</strong></div>\n<div>\n	&nbsp;</div>\n<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				Pilar Segura-Torres</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:pilar.segura@uab.es\">pilar.segura@uab.es</a></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				+34 93 581 3221</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<table>\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								<p>\n									<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=6603103863\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 29px; height: 29px;\" /></a></p>\n							</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/PSegdef.jpg\" style=\"width: 100%; margin-top: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px;\" /></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>Group members:</strong><br />\n	Laura Aldavert Vera<br />\n	Neus Biosca Sim&oacute;n<br />\n	<a href=\"http://inc.uab.cat/English/profile.php?id=103\">Ignacio Morgado Bernal</a><br />\n	<br />\n	<strong> Collaborations:</strong><br />\n	Department of Molecular Biology , Universitat de Girona (Gemma Huguet, Elisabet K&aacute;d&aacute;r)<br />\n	Ram&oacute;n y Cajal Institute (CSIC), Madrid (Javier de Felipe, Miguel Migu&eacute;ns)</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>STRATEGIC OBJECTIVES</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	Our research is addressed to study the cognitive-behavioral processes, the neural systems and the molecular mechanisms involved in learning and memory modulation by intracranial self-stimulation (ICSS) in normal animals, as well as in brain damaged rats. We use Intracranial Self-Stimulation (ICSS) as a way to facilitate memory formation in normal rats or in rats with reduced memory capacities caused by aging or brain damage. We analyze different kinds of learning and memory tasks: implicit (Two-way active avoidance) and explicit (Morris water maze; Radial mazes). Our main goal is to better understand the contribution of different brain structures (basal ganglia, hippocampus and amygdala) to the memory modulatory effect of ICSS, as well as the cellular and molecular mechanisms that underlay such enhancing cognitive effects. Those works will allow to establish hypotheses and to progress in the knowledge about the way through which ICSS facilitates memory, so that they will contribute, from the perspective of basic science, to the development of techniques and therapies capable of preventing or reducing neurodegeneration and its adverse effects on cognitive (memory) processes.<br />\n	<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>CURRENT PROJECTS</strong></span><br />\n	<br />\n	Our main project entitled &ldquo;Potentiation and recovery of memory by intracranial self-stimulation in rats with or without brain damage: behaviour, neural systems and molecular mechanisms&rdquo; includes different experiments aimed at studying:<br />\n	<br />\n	1.&nbsp;the ability of ICSS treatment to revert or compensate memory deficits induced by experimental brain damage<br />\n	2.&nbsp;the possible involvement of brain orexin system on the facilitative effect of ICSS<br />\n	3.&nbsp;the involvement of changes in dendrites spines as putative substrate of memory facilitation<br />\n	4.&nbsp;the detection of regions that are differentially activated by ICSS and likely involved on its memory facilitative effect<br />\n	5.&nbsp;putative genes, and proteins, activated by ICSS in regions such as hippocampus and amygdala that could be related to the ICSS facilitative effects on learning and memory.<br />\n	<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>TECHNIQUES</strong></span><br />\n	<br />\n	<strong> </strong>The research questions stated above are investigated through intracranial electrical self-stimulation (ICSS), electrolytic lesions, orexin agonists and antagonists, immunohistochemical determination of c-fos and Nurr-1 expression, DNA microarrays, real time PCR and fluorescence protein colocalization. The behavioral tasks are, among others, two-way active avoidance and Morris water maze.<br />\n	<br />\n	<strong> </strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong><strong>FEATURED PUBLICATIONS</strong></strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	&bull; K&aacute;d&aacute;r E, Vico-Varela E, Aldavert-Vera L, Huguet G, Morgado-Bernal I, Segura-Torres P.&nbsp;<em>Increase in c-Fos and Arc protein in retrosplenial cortex after memory-improving lateral hypothalamic electrical stimulation treatment.&nbsp;</em>Neurobiol Learn Mem, 128:117-24. (<strong>2016</strong>)</p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Chamorro-L&oacute;pez J, Migu&eacute;ns M, Morgado-Bernal I, Kastanauskaite A, Selvas A, Caban&eacute;-Cucurella A, Aldavert-Vera L, DeFelipe J, Segura-Torres P.&nbsp;<em>Structural plasticity in hippocampal cells related to the facilitative effect of intracranial self-stimulation on a spatial memory task.</em>&nbsp;Behav Neurosci,129(6):720-30. (<strong>2015</strong>)</p>\n<p>\n	&bull; K&aacute;d&aacute;r E, Ramoneda M, Aldavert-Vera L, Huguet G, Morgado-Bernal I, Segura-Torres P.&nbsp;<em>Rewarding brain stimulation reverses the disruptive effect of amygdala damage on emotional learning.&nbsp;</em>Behavioural Brain Research, 274, 43-52(<strong>2014</strong>).</p>\n<p>\n	&bull; K&aacute;d&aacute;r E, Huguet G, Aldavert-Vera L, Morgado-Bernal, Segura-Torres P.<br />\n	<em>Intracranial self-stimulation upregulates the expression of CREB-dependent synaptic plasticity related genes, and Arc protein expression in rat hippocampus</em>.<br />\n	Genes Brain &amp; Behavior, 12, 771-779.(<strong>2013</strong>)</p>\n<p>\n	&bull; Aldavert-Vera L, Huguet G, Costa-Miserachs D, Pe&ntilde;a de Ortiz S, K&aacute;d&aacute;r E, Morgado-Bernal I, Segura-Torres P.<br />\n	<em>Intracranial self-stimulation facilitates active-avoidance retention and induces expression of c-Fos and Nurr1 in rat brain memory systems.&nbsp;</em>Behavioural Brain Research, 250, 46-57. (<strong>2013</strong>)</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48831039/public/\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">See more P. Segura in PubMed.</a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n',45,2,2),(436,45,0,'Rafael Torrubia','<p>\n	<a href=\"javascript:MostraPage(374,1)\">Neurobiology of the normal and disturbed mind</a></p>\n<h2>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\">Human Lab, Medical Psychology Unit</span><br />\n	&nbsp;</h2>\n<p>\n	<strong>Group leader:</strong></p>\n<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				Rafael Torrubia Beltri</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:Rafael.Torrubia@uab.cat\">Rafael.Torrubia@uab.cat</a></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				TEL: +34 935 811 438</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<table>\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researcherid.com/rid/C-4815-2009\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/RID.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<p>\n									<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=6602475775\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 29px; height: 29px;\" /></a></p>\n							</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/RTorrubiaA1_opt.jpg\" style=\"width: 400px; height: 266px;\" /></p>\n<p>\n	<strong>Group members:</strong><br />\n	&Oacute;scar Andi&oacute;n P&eacute;rez<br />\n	Xavier Caseras Vives<br />\n	Miquel A. Fullana Rivas<br />\n	<a href=\"http://inc.uab.cat/English/profile.php?id=182\">Esther Martinez Membrives</a><br />\n	Beatriz Molinuevo Alonso<br />\n	Yolanda Pardo Cladellas<br />\n	David Torrents Rodas</p>\n<p>\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>STRATEGIC OBJECTIVES&nbsp;</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	The study of vulnerability to a number of mental disorders (personality disorders, anxiety disorders and affective disorders) related to the functioning of the aversive and the appetitive neural systems. This aim implies research on the basic psychological processes involved in the onset and maintenance of the disorders, individual differences in these processes and the relating neurobiological structures. Research methodology includes: a) development and adaptation of assessment scales for the selection of samples; neuropsychological laboratory tasks; psychophysiological measures; and d) structural and functional neuroimage techniques. &nbsp;<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>MAIN RESEARCH LINES</strong></span><br />\n	<br />\n	<em>Psychophysiology of vulnerability to anxiety disorders</em><br />\n	Research of the basic psychological mechanisms involved in the processes of fear and anxiety acquisition in subclinical populations using startle reflex and electrodermal activity as indexes of affective processing.<br />\n	<br />\n	<em>Neurobiological correlates of mental disorders using neuroimage techniques</em><br />\n	Research, using fMRI techniques, of the brain functioning associated with a number of mental disorders (mainly anxiety) and of possible vulnerability factors for suffering these disorders. &nbsp;<br />\n	<br />\n	<em>The aversive and appetitive neural systems as vulnerability dimensions to psychopathology</em><br />\n	Study of the role of aversive and appetitive systems as vulnerability factors to&nbsp; several disorders (obsessive-compulsive, major depression, bipolar disorder and psychopathic personality). A psychometric methodological approach is used in clinical and subclinical populations and, in some cases, neuropsychological and learning laboratory tasks.<br />\n	<br />\n	<em> Adaptation and standardization of instruments for psychological&nbsp; diagnosis and assessment</em><br />\n	This line of research has the aim of providing the scientific community with a number of assessment instruments which are relevant for research and clinical purposes. It encompasses the adaptation of published questionnaires to our cultural context and the development of new ones.</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>FEATURED PUBLICATIONS</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; Torrents-Rodas, D., Fullana, M.A., Bonillo, A., Andi&oacute;n, O., Molinuevo, B., Caseras, X., Torrubia, R.<br />\n	<em>Testing the temporal stability of individual differences in the acquisition and generalization of fear. </em><br />\n	Psychophysiology, 51,&nbsp; 697 &ndash; 705.(<strong>2014</strong>)</p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; Vega, D.,&nbsp; Soto, A.,&nbsp; Amengual, J.L., Ribas, J., Torrubia, R., Rodr&iacute;guez-Fornells, A., Marco-Pallar&eacute;s, J.<br />\n	<em>Negative reward expectations in Borderline Personality Disorder patients: Neurophysiological evidence. </em><br />\n	Biological Psychology, 94, 388-396.(<strong>2013</strong>).</p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; Caseras, X., Murphy, K., Mataix-Cols, D., L&oacute;pez-Sol&agrave;, M., Soriano-Mas, C., Ortriz, H., Pujol, J., Torrubia, R.<br />\n	<em>Anatomical and functional overlap within the insula and anterior cingulated cortex during interocepcion and phobic symptom provocation. </em>Human Brain Mapping, 34, 1220-1229.(<strong>2013</strong>).</p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; Torrents-Rodas, D., Fullana, M.A., Bonillo, A., Caseras, X., Andi&oacute;n, O., Torrubia, R.<br />\n	<em>No effect of trait anxiety on differential fear conditioning or fear generalization. </em><br />\n	Biological Psychology, 92, 185-190.(<strong>2013</strong>).</p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; Torrents-Rodas, D., Fullana, M.A., Arias, B., Bonillo, A., Caseras, X., Andi&oacute;n, O., Mitjans, M., Fa&ntilde;an&aacute;s, L., Torrubia, R.<br />\n	<em>Acquisition and generalization of fear conditioning are not modulated by the BDNF-val66met polymorphism in humans. </em><br />\n	Psychophysiology, 49, 713-719.(<strong>2012</strong>).</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48831042/public/\" target=\"_blank\">See more R. Torrubia in PubMed. </a></p>\n',46,2,2),(437,45,0,'Mercedes Unzeta','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<a href=\"javascript:MostraPage(372,1); \">Neurodegeneration and ageing</a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\">Contribution of SSAO/VAP-1 Amine Oxidase to the neurovascular dysfunction and its relationship with the Stroke, the Cerebral Amyloid Angiopathy and Alzheimer&#39;s disease</span><br />\n	&nbsp;</h2>\n<p>\n	<strong>Group leader:</strong></p>\n<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				Mercedes Unzeta L&oacute;pez</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:mercedes.unzeta@uab.cat\">mercedes.unzeta@uab.cat</a></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				TEL: +34 93 581 1523</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<table>\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								<p>\n									<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=7003384729\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 29px; height: 29px;\" /></a></p>\n							</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/MUnzeta.jpg\" style=\"width: 100%; margin-top: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px;\" /></p>\n<p>\n	<strong>Group members:</strong><br />\n	<a href=\"http://inc.uab.cat/English/profile.php?id=130\"><span style=\"color:#000000;\">Montse Sol&eacute; Pi&ntilde;ol</span></a><br />\n	Gerard Esteban<br />\n	Ping Sun</p>\n<p>\n	<strong>Past members:</strong><br />\n	Irene Bolea Tom&aacute;s<br />\n	Laura Fernandez</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>STRATEGIC OBJECTIVES</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	Oxidative stress plays a determinant role in neurodegenerative disorders such as Parkinson&#39;s disease and Alzheimer&#39;s disease (AD). One of the main objectives of our research is focused on the possible contribution of different amine oxidases to these pathologies, with special relevance to the role that vascular SSAO/VAP-1 Oxidase could play in the vasculopathy associated to the Stroke condition, the Cerebral Amyloid Angiopathy (CAA) and Alzheimer&rsquo;s dementia. Stroke increases significantly the risk for AD and in turn AD increases the risk for intracerebral hemorrhage. This research line is based upon the concept of the &ldquo;neurovascular unit&rdquo; a functional unit integrated by neurons, astrocytes and endothelial cells as well, that contributes to the brain homeostasis maintenance, and whose dysfunction is associated to Alzheimer&acute;s disease.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	Moreover in the context of the therapeutic approach, our group is collaborating since 20 years ago with the CSIC (Madrid) in the design of novel multipotent molecules as modulator agents for amine oxidases and other enzymes involved in these pathologies. Its therapeutic potential is assessed in different experimental models. In the same research line, we are studying the neuroprotective effect of several natural products rich in polyphenols, which are able to delay the ageing process, the onset and progression of Alzheimer&rsquo;s disease. In order to develop these scientific activities, our group collaborates with other national and international scientific groups: it is an integral part of an SGR group (2009 SGR 1322), and currently is part of a research network of the European Union COST (European Cooperation in Science and Technology; COST-EU MC1103- 2011-2015). At present, the group funding comes from the following projects:<br />\n	<br />\n	-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; INNPRONTA program- CDTI (Ministry of Industry 2012-2015)<br />\n	-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; SAF project (SAF2012-33304)<br />\n	-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; COST Project (COST-EU MC 1103 2011-2014)<br />\n	-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &quot;La Marat&oacute; de TV3&quot; Foundation (2015-2017)</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>MAIN RESEARCH LINES</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	1- Contribution of the SSAO/VAP-1 Oxidase to the neurovascular disfunction and its relationship with the Stroke, the Cerebral Amyloid Angiopathy and the Alzheimer&acute;s disease.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	2- Design and biological evaluation of novel multipotential molecules as modulator agents of the amine oxidase and acetylcholinesterase activities, assessment of its anti-aggregating &beta;-amiloide effect, and evaluation of its possible therapeutic use in the treatment of Parkinson&rsquo;s and Alzheimer&rsquo;s diseases.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	3.-Selection and analysis of active principles present in natural products, able to decrease the cardiovascular risks factors, in order to delay aging and the Alzheimer&#39;s type dementia.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>FEATURED PUBLICATIONS </strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	<strong>&bull; </strong>Ismaili L, Refouvelet B, Benchekroun M, Brogi S, Brindisi M, Gemma S, Campiani G, Filipic S, Agbaba D, Esteban G, <strong>Unzeta M</strong>, Nikolic K, Butini S, Marco-Contelles J. Multitarget compounds bearing tacrine- and donepezil-like structural and functional motifs for the potential treatment of Alzheimer&#39;s disease. Prog Neurobiol. <strong>2016 </strong>Jan 18. pii: S0301-0082(15)00162-8. doi: 10.1016/j.pneurobio.2015.12.003. [Epub ahead of print] Review.</p>\n<p>\n	&bull; Wu MY, Esteban G, Brogi S, Shionoya M, Wang L, Campiani G, <strong>Unzeta M</strong>, Inokuchi T, Butini S, Marco-Contelles J.Donepezil-like multifunctional agents: Design, synthesis, molecular modeling and biological evaluation<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/26471320\">.</a> Eur J Med Chem. <strong>2015 </strong>Oct 9. pii: S0223-5234(15)30283-X. doi: 10.1016/j.ejmech.2015.10.001. [Epub ahead of print]</p>\n<p>\n	&bull; Sun P, Esteban G, Inokuchi T, Marco-Contelles J, Weksler BB, Romero IA, Couraud PO, <strong>Unzeta M</strong>, Sol&eacute; M. Protective effect of the multitarget compound DPH-4 on human SSAO/VAP-1-expressing hCMEC/D3 cells under oxygen-glucose deprivation conditions: an in vitro experimental model of cerebral ischaemia. Br J Pharmacol. <strong>2015</strong> Nov;172(22):5390-402. doi: 10.1111/bph.13328. Epub 2015 Oct 27.</p>\n<p>\n	&bull;Sol&eacute; M, Mi&ntilde;ano-Molina AJ, <strong>Unzeta M</strong>. Cross-talk between A&beta; and endothelial SSAO/VAP-1 accelerates vascular damage and A&beta; aggregation related to CAA-AD. Neurobiol Aging. <strong>2015 </strong>Feb;36(2):762-75. doi: 10.1016/j.neurobiolaging.2014.09.030. Epub 2014 Oct 13.</p>\n<p>\n	&bull;Sol&eacute; M, <strong>Unzeta M</strong>. Vascular cell lines expressing SSAO/VAP-1: a new experimental tool to study its involvement in vascular diseases. Biol Cell. <strong>2011 </strong>Nov;103(11):543-57. doi: 10.1042/BC20110049.</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48831046/public/\" target=\"_blank\">See more M. Unzeta in PubMed. </a></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n',47,2,2),(438,45,0,'Elisabeth Vila','<p>\n	<a href=\"javascript:MostraPage(372,1); \">Neurodegeneration and ageing</a></p>\n<h2>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\">Vascular Pharmacology</span></h2>\n<p>\n	<strong>Group leader:</strong></p>\n<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				Elisabet Vila Calsina</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:Elisabet.Vila@uab.cat\">Elisabet.Vila@uab.cat</a></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				TEL: +34 935 811 961</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<table>\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								<p>\n									<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=7006115687\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 29px; height: 29px;\" /></a></p>\n							</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/EVildef.jpg\" style=\"width: 100%; margin-top: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px;\" /></p>\n<p>\n	<strong>Group members:</strong><br />\n	Roger Cugota Canals<br />\n	<a href=\"http://inc.uab.cat/English/profile.php?id=82\">Francesc Jim&eacute;nez Altay&oacute;</a><br />\n	Yara Onetti</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>STRATEGIC OBJECTIVES&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</strong></span><br />\n	<br />\n	The main objective is to deeply analyse the functional, structural, morphological and biochemical modifications induced at vascular level paralleled by the putative mechanisms that could account to the observed changes after focal cerebral ischemia and mesenteric ischemia-reperfusion (I/R).<br />\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong> </strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>MAIN RESEARCH LINES</strong></span><br />\n	<br />\n	<em>Vascular alterations (function, structure and biochemistry) after I/R: therapeutic strategies.</em>&nbsp;<br />\n	We have evaluated the changes on the vascular structure as well as the morphological variations induced in the middle cerebral artery after focal cerebral ischemia in rat analysing the role of an antioxidant drug on the changes observed.<br />\n	<br />\n	<em>Influence of intestinal I/R on vascular structure, mechanics and function.</em><br />\n	We have observed in rat, that intestinal I/R potentiated the vasoconstrictor response to endotheline-1 (ET-1) in mesenteric resistance artery. The observed potentiation seem to be due to up regulation of muscular ETB receptors. Furthermore, a decrease on nitric oxide bioavailability is also involved.&nbsp; We are also analysing the structural and morphological changes (pressure miography, confocal microscopy) induced by intestinal I/R. We have observed a vascular wall hypertrophy linked to an increase on plasma ET-1 levels and superoxide anion production. We are also analyzing the role of ET receptors by means of a non-selective ET receptor antagonist.<br />\n	<br />\n	<em>Middle cerebral artery alterations in a rat chronic hypoperfusion model.</em><br />\n	We have evaluated the structural, miogenic and biochemical alterations that occur on the middle cerebral artery after 15 days of hypoperfusion using the bilateral common carotid artery occlusion model in rat. The observed changes on the vascular wall seem to be due to a collagen I/III decrease linked to increases on MMPs<em>.</em><br />\n	<br />\n	<em> <em>Study of the influence of ageing and Western diet on the functional responses and vascular remodelling.</em></em><br />\n	Our group is also interested on analysing the effect of cardiovascular risk factors like age and rich fat diet, as well as their interrelationship, on the functional responses (vasodilatation, vasoconstriction) and remodelling on a muscular vessel like the aorta and resistance arteries as the mesenteric artery branches. For this purpose we are using mice with accelerate senescence (SAM-P8), described as a good model to study cardiovascular alteration by ageing<br />\n	<br />\n	<em> <em>&beta;-adrenoceptor function and biochemistry on several vascular beds.</em></em><br />\n	In this study we deeply analyse the presence (immunofluorescence, Rt-PCR, Western Blott) and the function (vasodilator responses, second messenger production) for all the subtypes of these adrenoceptors in either aorta or resistance mesenteric artery.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>FEATURED PUBLICATIONS</strong></span>:</p>\n<p>\n	&bull; Onetti Y, Meirelles T, Dantas AP, Schr&ouml;der K, Vila E, Egea G, Jim&eacute;nez-Altay&oacute; F. <a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/26945079\"><em>NADPH oxidase 4 attenuates cerebral artery changes during the progression of Marfan syndrome</em>.</a> Am J Physiol Heart Circ Physiol.<strong> 2016</strong></p>\n<p>\n	&bull; Onetti Y, Dantas AP, P&eacute;rez B, Cugota R Chamorro A Planas AM, Vila E, Jim&eacute;nez-Altay&oacute; F. <em>Middle cerebral artery remodeling following transient brain ischemia is linked to early postischemic hyperemia: a target of uric acid treatment</em>. <a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/25637543\" title=\"American journal of physiology. Heart and circulatory physiology.\">Am J Physiol Heart Circ Physiol.</a><strong> 2015</strong> 308(8):H862-74</p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp; Amaro S, Llull L, Ren&uacute; A, Laredo C, Perez B, Vila E, Torres F, Planas AM, Chamorro &Aacute; <a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/25627874\"><em>Uric acid improves glucose-driven oxidative stress in human ischemic stroke</em>.</a> Ann Neurol. <strong>2015</strong>,77(5):775-83</p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp; Dantas AP, Onetti Y, Oliveira MA, Carvalho MH, Heras M, Vila E, Jim&eacute;nez-Altay&oacute; F.<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24607550\"><em>Western diet consumption promotes vascular remodeling in non-senescent mice consistent with accelerated senescence, but does not modify vascular morphology in senescent ones</em>.</a> Exp Gerontol. <strong>2014</strong>, 55:1-11</p>\n<p>\n	&bull; Jim&eacute;nez-Altay&oacute; F, Onetti Y, Heras M, Dantas AP, Vila E. <em>Western-style diet modulates contractile responses to phenylephrine differently in mesenteric arteries from senescence-accelerated prone (SAMP8) and resistant (SAMR1) mice</em>. <a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/22777652\" title=\"Age (Dordrecht, Netherlands).\">Age (Dordr).</a> <strong>2013</strong> 35(4):1219-34.</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48831052/public/\" target=\"_blank\">See more E. Vila in PubMed. </a></p>\n',48,2,2),(439,45,0,'Victor J. Yuste','<p>\n	<a href=\"javascript:MostraPage(372,1); \">Neurodegeneration and ageing</a></p>\n<h2>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\">Cell Death, Senescence an Survival</span></h2>\n<p>\n	<strong>Group leader:</strong></p>\n<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				Victor J. Yuste Mateos</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:Victor.Yuste@uab.cat\">Victor.Yuste@uab.cat</a></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				TEL: +34 935 813 762</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				LAB TEL: +34 935 868 141</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<table>\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0001-5322-9261\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/orcid.png\" style=\"width: 26px; height: 26px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researcherid.com/rid/C-7071-2008\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/RID.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<p>\n									<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=6602688559\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 29px; height: 29px;\" /></a></p>\n							</td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researchgate.net/profile/Victor_Yuste\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"28\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/researchgate.jpg\" width=\"28\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://scholar.google.es/citations?user=veBnYWoAAAAJ&amp;hl=es\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"28\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/googlescholar.jpg\" width=\"29\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/VYustdef.jpg\" style=\"width: 100%; margin-top: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px;\" /></p>\n<p>\n	<strong>Group members:</strong><br />\n	Ana Arp&oacute;n Miranda<br />\n	Laura Martinez Escard&oacute;<br />\n	Mar&iacute;a S&aacute;nchez Osuna<br />\n	<br />\n	<strong>Former group members:</strong><br />\n	Elisenda Casanelles Abella<br />\n	Irene Casanova Salas<br />\n	Gisela Gabernet Garriga<br />\n	Merc&egrave; Garcia Belinchon<br />\n	Estel Gil Gui&ntilde;on<br />\n	Victoria Iglesias Guimarais<br />\n	Jorge Urresti Ib&aacute;&ntilde;ez<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>STRATEGIC OBJECTIVES</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	1) To establish which chemical compounds are the most efficient inducing cell death in glioblastoma multiform cells (GBM) derived human cell lines and to determine which type of cell death is provoked.<br />\n	2) To verify the existence of a main and common pathway among all the toxic drugs and to analyze the different components of this pathway to fix the major actors in both cell lines and primary tumors.<br />\n	3) With the aim to study the therapeutic potential of the above described drugs, we will analyze the effect and the molecular mechanism involved in cell death induction in our primary cultures.<br />\n	4) An in vitro study will be carried out to answer if there is a phagocytic and/or immune response stimulated by GBM cells that have been sensitive to different apoptotic stimuli.<br />\n	mechanisms.<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>MAIN RESEARCH LINES</strong></span><br />\n	<br />\n	<em>Analysis of the mechanisms involved in the resistance against death receptor-triggered apoptosis in glioblastoma multiform cells.</em><br />\n	The mail goal of the project is based on the study of the molecular mechanisms involved, and not yet characterized, in the inherent resistance of glioblastoma multiform cells (GBM) from TRAIL-mediated cytotoxicity. The data obtained in different research laboratories are disappointing: most of GBM are resistant to TRAIL-triggered apoptosis needing the addition of an inhibitor of the macromolecular synthesis to become sensitive. For this reason, we will study the implication of the DISC endogenous inhibitors in the acquisition of this resistance, as well as the role that the anti-apoptotic members of Bcl-2&rsquo;s family play in TRAIL-induced cell death. Moreover, we will approach the study of the relevance of the apoptotic nucleases in the regulation of TRAIL-mediated apoptotic cell death.<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>FEATURED PUBLICATIONS</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp; S&aacute;nchez-Osuna M, Garcia-Belinch&oacute;n M, Iglesias-Guimarais V, Gil-Gui&ntilde;&oacute;n E, Casanelles E, Yuste VJ.<br />\n	<em>Caspase-activated DNase is necessary and sufficient for oligonucleosomal DNA breakdown, but not for chromatin disassembly during caspase-dependent apoptosis of LN-18 glioblastoma cells. </em><br />\n	J Biol Chem. <strong>2014 </strong>289(27):18752-69.</p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp; Iglesias-Guimarais V, Gil-Gui&ntilde;on E, S&aacute;nchez-Osuna M, Casanelles E, Garc&iacute;a-Belinch&oacute;n M, Comella JX, Yuste VJ.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\n	<em>Chromatin collapse during caspase-dependent apoptotic cell death requires DNA fragmentation factor, 40-kDa subunit-/caspase-activated deoxyribonuclease-mediated 3&#39;-OH single-strand DNA breaks.&nbsp;</em><br />\n	J Biol Chem.&nbsp;<strong>2013</strong> ;288(13):9200-15..&nbsp;<br />\n	<br />\n	&bull;&nbsp; Casanelles E, Gozzelino R, Marqu&eacute;s-Fern&aacute;ndez F, Iglesias-Guimarais V, Garcia-Belinch&oacute;n M, S&aacute;nchez-Osuna M, Sol&eacute; C, Moubarak RS, Comella JX, Yuste VJ.&nbsp;<br />\n	<em>NF-&kappa;B activation fails to protect cells to TNF&alpha;-induced apoptosis in the absence of Bcl-xL, but not Mcl-1, Bcl-2 or Bcl-w.&nbsp;</em><br />\n	Biochim Biophys Acta.&nbsp;<strong>2013</strong> ;1833(5):1085-95.<br />\n	<br />\n	&bull;&nbsp; Iglesias-Guimarais V, Gil-Gui&ntilde;on E, Gabernet G, Garc&iacute;a-Belinch&oacute;n M, S&aacute;nchez-Osuna M, Casanelles E, Comella JX, Yuste VJ.&nbsp;<br />\n	<em> Apoptotic DNA degradation into oligonucleosomal fragments, but not apoptotic nuclear morphology, relies on a cytosolic pool of DFF40/CAD endonuclease.&nbsp;</em><br />\n	J Biol Chem.&nbsp;<strong>2012 </strong>;287(10):7766-79.</p>\n<p>\n	<br />\n	&bull;&nbsp;Dieker J, Iglesias-Guimarais V, D&eacute;cossas M, Stevenin J, van der Vlag J, Yuste VJ, Muller S.&nbsp;<br />\n	<em>Early Apoptotic Reorganization of Spliceosomal Proteins Involves Caspases, CAD and Rearrangement of NuMA.&nbsp;</em><br />\n	Traffic.&nbsp;<strong>2011 </strong></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48831052/public/\" target=\"_blank\">See more VJ. Yuste in PubMed. </a></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n',49,2,2),(441,52,0,'José Aguilera','<p>\n	<a href=\"javascript:MostraPage(377,1); \">Neurodegeneraci&oacute;n y envejecimiento</a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\">Grupo de Neuroprotecci&oacute;n Molecular</span></h2>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong>L&iacute;der del grupo:</strong></p>\n<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				Jose Aguilera</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:jose.aguilera@uab.cat\">jose.aguilera@uab.cat&nbsp;&nbsp;</a></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				TEL: +34 935 811 673</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<table>\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0002-9906-8034\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"27\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/orcid.png\" width=\"27\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=6507775989\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 29px; height: 29px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researchgate.net/profile/Jose_Aguilera3/publications\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"26\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/researchgate.jpg\" width=\"26\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/GrupJAguilera.jpg\" style=\"width: 100%; margin-top: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px;\" /></p>\n<p>\n	<strong>Miembros del Grupo:</strong><br />\n	Ana Candalija Iserte<br />\n	<a href=\"http://inc.uab.cat/Castellano/profile.php?id=212\">Laura Ortega</a><br />\n	Victoria <span>Palafox S&aacute;nchez</span></p>\n<p>\n	<strong>Miembros anteriores:</strong><br />\n	Roger Cub&iacute; Piqu&eacute;<br />\n	Carles Gil Gir&oacute;<br />\n	Daniel A. Mart&iacute;nez Quintero<br />\n	Natalia Moreno Galarza<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>OBJECTIVOS ESTRAT&Eacute;GICOS</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	Las neurotoxinas clostridiales producen graves patolog&iacute;as como el t&eacute;tanos y el botulismo. En nuestro Grupo se estudia el potencial farmacol&oacute;gico del miembro m&aacute;s inexplorado de la familia, la toxina tet&aacute;nica, y en especial, se estudia el fragmento C-terminal&nbsp; de su cadena pesada (Hc-TeTx), carente de toxicidad. El fragmento Hc-TeTx, debido a sus caracter&iacute;sticas de uni&oacute;n, internalizaci&oacute;n, y transporte retroaxonal, puede ser utilizado como un veh&iacute;culo para transportar compuestos al SNC. Por otra parte, nuestro Grupo ha descrito la acci&oacute;n neurotr&oacute;fica, as&iacute; como la modulaci&oacute;n selectiva de transporte de serotonina por Hc-TeTx, lo que indica potencial como antidepresivo. Por lo tanto, nuestro objetivo es describir completamente su capacidad de protecci&oacute;n frente a agentes inductores de estr&eacute;s en los sistemas neuronales. Los resultados, in vivo e in vitro, nos llevan a proponer al fragmento Hc-TeTx como agente neuroprotector en patolog&iacute;as neurodegenerativas y a estudiar los mecanismos de se&ntilde;alizaci&oacute;n relacionados con su capacidad tr&oacute;fica.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PRINCIPALES L&Iacute;NEAS DE INVESTIGACI&Oacute;N</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	1. La identificaci&oacute;n de los receptores de alta afinidad de las neurotoxinas clostridiales, su localizaci&oacute;n subcelular y su relaci&oacute;n din&aacute;mica con los dominios lip&iacute;dicos enriquecidos en colesterol y esfingol&iacute;pidos (lipid rafts o rafts).<br />\n	<br />\n	2. La caracterizaci&oacute;n estructural y de composici&oacute;n de rafts en diferentes modelos neuronales y su papel en los diferentes eventos de la fisiolog&iacute;a neuronal.<br />\n	<br />\n	3. La determinaci&oacute;n de la cin&eacute;tica farmacol&oacute;gica del fragmento Hc-TeTx como agente proserotonin&eacute;rgico.<br />\n	<br />\n	4. La determinaci&oacute;n de la capacidad neuroprotectora del fragmento Hc-TeTx en los procesos degenerativos asociados con las enfermedades mentales.<br />\n	<br />\n	5. La caracterizaci&oacute;n de la acci&oacute;n neurotr&oacute;fica llevada a cabo por el fragmento Hc-TeTx: evaluaci&oacute;n de su capacidad terap&eacute;utica en el tratamiento de enfermedades neurodegenerativas.&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<br />\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PUBLICACIONES</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Patricio-Mart&iacute;nez A,&nbsp;Mendieta L,&nbsp;Mart&iacute;nez I,&nbsp;Aguilera&nbsp;J,&nbsp;Lim&oacute;n ID.<br />\n	<em>The recombinant C-terminal fragment of tetanus toxin protects against cholinotoxicity by intraseptal injection of &beta;-amyloid peptide (25-35) in rats.</em> Neuroscience.&nbsp;<strong>2016</strong> Feb 19;315:18-30</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Candalija A, Cub&iacute; R,&nbsp; Ortega A, Aguilera J, and Gil C.<br />\n	<em>Trk receptors need neutral sphingomyelinase activity to promote cell viability.</em><br />\n	FEBS Letters<strong> </strong><strong>2014</strong>, 588: 167-174.(ISSN 0014-5793, Elsevier)</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Mart&iacute;nez D, Garc&iacute;a L, Aguilera J and Ortega A.<br />\n	<em>An acute Glutamate exposure induces long-term down regulation of GLAST/EAAT1 uptake activity in cultured Bermann glia cells.</em><br />\n	Neurochemistry Research (In press <strong>2014</strong>).</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Balderas A., Guillem A.M., Mart&iacute;nez-Lozada Z., Hern&aacute;ndez-Kelly L.C., Aguilera J. and Ortega A.<br />\n	<em>GLAST/EAAT1 regulation in cultured Bergmann glia cells: Role of the NO/cGMP signalling pathway.</em><br />\n	Neurochemistry International , In press<strong> 2014</strong>( ISSN 0197-0186, Elsevier BV, Netherlands &ndash; Scopus 2009: 74/303)</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp; Cub&iacute; R, Matas L.A. , Pou M. , Aguilera J. and C. Gil.<br />\n	<em>Differencial sensitivity to detergents of actin cytoskeleton from nerve endings.</em><br />\n	Biochimica et Biophysica Acta (Biomembranes) 1828: 2385-2393,<strong>2013</strong>(ISSN 0005-2736, Elsevier)</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830283/public/\" target=\"_blank\">Ver m&aacute;s publicaciones de J. Aguilera en PubMed. </a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n',18,2,1),(442,52,0,'Antonio Armario, Roser Nadal y Raül Andero','<p>\n	<a href=\"javascript:MostraPage(379,1); \">Neurobiolog&iacute;a de la mente normal y alterada</a></p>\n<h2>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\">Neurobiolog&iacute;a del Estr&eacute;s y la Adicci&oacute;n</span></h2>\n<p>\n	<strong>L&iacute;deres del Grupo:</strong></p>\n<table style=\"width: 100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				Antonio Armario</td>\n			<td>\n				Roser Nadal</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				TEL: +34 935 811 840</td>\n			<td>\n				TEL: +34 935 868 535</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:antonio.armario@uab.cat\">antonio.armario@uab.cat</a></td>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:roser.nadal@uab.cat\">roser.nadal@uab.cat</a></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<table>\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0001-9524-3635\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/orcid.png\" style=\"width: 26px; height: 26px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researcherid.com/ProfileView.action?SID=S1VOcsKWWHF8mvCPi46&amp;returnCode=ROUTER.Success&amp;queryString=KG0UuZjN5WkTEMnGFsnbmvjTPBd2a4rriGfK3U1Twjc%253D&amp;SrcApp=CR&amp;Init=Yes\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/RID.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=7005836750\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 29px; height: 29px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researchgate.net/profile/Antonio_Armario\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"27\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/researchgate.jpg\" width=\"27\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n				<table>\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0001-8972-2525\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/orcid.png\" style=\"width: 26px; height: 26px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researcherid.com/rid/C-7977-2011\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/RID.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=6701731005\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 29px; height: 29px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researchgate.net/profile/Roser_Nadal2\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"27\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/researchgate.jpg\" width=\"27\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.mendeley.com/profiles/roser-nadal/\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"28\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/mendeley.png\" width=\"28\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<div>\n					Ra&uuml;l Andero Gal&iacute;</div>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:Raul.Andero@uab.cat\">Raul.Andero@uab.cat</a></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				TEL: +34 935 813 342</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<table>\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								<table>\n									<tbody>\n										<tr>\n											<td>\n												<a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3641-8903\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/orcid.png\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n											<td>\n												&nbsp;</td>\n											<td>\n												<a href=\"https://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.uri?authorId=16066765200\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n											<td>\n												<a href=\"https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Rauel_Andero_Gali\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/researchgate.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n											<td>\n												<a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/ra%C3%BCl-andero-gal%C3%AD-2a177a46/en\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Linkedin.jpg\" style=\"width: 35px; height: 29px;\" /></a><a href=\"https://scholar.google.es/citations?view_op=list_works&amp;hl=es&amp;user=ORHEFhUAAAAJ\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"29\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/googlescholar.jpg\" width=\"31\" /></a></td>\n										</tr>\n									</tbody>\n								</table>\n							</td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Untitled design(1).jpg\" style=\"width: 500px; height: 375px;\" /></p>\n<div>\n	<strong>Miembros del Grupo:</strong></div>\n<div>\n	Francesc Xavier Belda &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\n	In&eacute;s Cord&oacute;n<br />\n	Silvia Fuentes<br />\n	Humberto Gagliano<br />\n	Juan Antonio Ortega<br />\n	Jordi Pastor<br />\n	Mar&iacute;a Sanchis</div>\n<p>\n	<br />\n	Visita tambi&eacute;n la web: <a href=\"http://www.nea-uab.org/es/\">Neurobiolog&iacute;a del estr&eacute;s y la adicci&oacute;n</a></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>OBJETIVOS ESTRAT&Eacute;GICOS</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	1. Comprender el procesamiento cerebral de los est&iacute;mulos estresantes y la utilidad de los diferentes marcadores biol&oacute;gicos de la activaci&oacute;n neuronal.<br />\n	2. Procesos y mecanismos involucrados en la adaptaci&oacute;n al estr&eacute;s cr&oacute;nico.<br />\n	3. Impacto del estr&eacute;s en psicopatolog&iacute;a y mecanismos neurobiol&oacute;gicos subyacentes.<br />\n	<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PRINCIPALES L&Iacute;NEAS DE INVESTIGACI&Oacute;N</strong></span><br />\n	<br />\n	1. Identificar las &aacute;reas cerebrales y los fenotipos neuronales activados por la exposici&oacute;n a est&iacute;mulos estresantes emocionales y farmacol&oacute;gicos (p.e. drogas adictivas). Utilizamos genes de expresi&oacute;n inmediata (IEGs) como el c-fos y el arc y cambios epigen&eacute;ticos (p.e. fosforilaci&oacute;n y acetilaci&oacute;n de histonas). Nuestra hip&oacute;tesis es que los cambios epigen&eacute;ticos est&aacute;n m&aacute;s restringidos que la expresi&oacute;n de los IEGs y pueden ayudar a identificar &aacute;reas y neuronas cerebrales cr&iacute;ticas. Con estas herramientas estamos explorando c&oacute;mo la exposici&oacute;n simult&aacute;nea a dos est&iacute;mulos estresantes o a un est&iacute;mulo estresante y a una droga adictiva interaccionan en el cerebro.<br />\n	2. Despu&eacute;s de la exposici&oacute;n repetida a un rango amplio de est&iacute;mulos estresantes predominantemente emocionales, existe una reducci&oacute;n de la respuesta al mismo (homot&iacute;pico) est&iacute;mulo estresante que se observa a nivel fisiol&oacute;gico (p.e. hormonas del eje hipotal&aacute;mico-hipofisario-adrenal o HPA) y conductual. La adaptaci&oacute;n se observa tambi&eacute;n en la expresi&oacute;n cerebral de los IEGs. Nuestros objetivos principales son identificar los procesos cognitivos y emocionales involucrados en la adaptaci&oacute;n, as&iacute; como las &aacute;reas cerebrales y los mecanismos neuroqu&iacute;micos involucrados. Una de nuestras hip&oacute;tesis principales es que la adaptaci&oacute;n al estr&eacute;s repetido no es un simple proceso de habituaci&oacute;n, como se considera habitualmente, sino que es un proceso cerebral complejo que involucra aspectos cognitivos y se&ntilde;ales asociativas. Una segunda hip&oacute;tesis es que la adaptaci&oacute;n al estr&eacute;s es tan dif&iacute;cil de bloquear farmacol&oacute;gicamente o mediante lesiones cerebrales porque probablemente involucra diferentes circuitos cerebrales y procesos neuroqu&iacute;micos que act&uacute;an de forma paralela y redundante.<br />\n	3. Ha sido reconocido durante d&eacute;cadas que la exposici&oacute;n al estr&eacute;s en humanos est&aacute; involucrada en el desarrollo de psicopatolog&iacute;as incluyendo los trastornos de ansiedad, depresi&oacute;n y conducta adictiva. M&aacute;s recientemente, se ha demostrado que una simple exposici&oacute;n a ciertos est&iacute;mulos estresantes de naturaleza severa puede producir cambios neuroendocrinos, cognitivos y emocionales a largo plazo, semejantes a los que se encuentran en el trastorno de estr&eacute;s post-traum&aacute;tico (PTSD). Nuestro prop&oacute;sito es caracterizar las propiedades de los est&iacute;mulos estresantes que determinan su impacto psicopatol&oacute;gico, as&iacute; como las bases biol&oacute;gicas de las diferencias individuales en la resistencia o vulnerabilidad a las consecuencias del estr&eacute;s. En este sentido, uno de nuestros centros de&nbsp; inter&eacute;s es la activaci&oacute;n del eje HPA y su regulador cerebral, el factor/hormona liberador de corticotropina (CRF o CRH), el cual se ha demostrado que constituye un nexo biol&oacute;gico cr&iacute;tico entre el estr&eacute;s y la psicopatolog&iacute;a. Adem&aacute;s, hemos obtenido evidencias de que la activaci&oacute;n de las v&iacute;as del BDNF-trkB en &aacute;reas cr&iacute;ticas como la formaci&oacute;n hipoc&aacute;mpica y la am&iacute;gdala pueden ser importantes para mitigar las consecuencias negativas de est&iacute;mulos estresantes severos.<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<table align=\"left\" border=\"2\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"background-color: rgb(204, 0, 51);\">\n				<span style=\"color:#000000;\"><strong>GRUPO SGR 2014-1020</strong></span></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"background-color: rgb(204, 0, 51);\">\n				<span style=\"color:#000000;\"><strong>Coordinaci&oacute;n: Antonio Armario</strong></span></td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<h2>\n	&nbsp;</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>&Uacute;LTIMAS PUBLICACIONES</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	&bull; Souza Queiroz J, Mar&iacute;n Blasco I, Gagliano H, Daviu N, G&oacute;mez Rom&aacute;n A, Belda X, Carrasco J, Rocha MC, Palermo Neto J, Armario A. <em>Chlorella vulgaris reduces the impact of stress on hypothalamic-pituitary-adrenal axis and brain c-fos expression</em>. Psychoneuroendocrinology. <strong>2015</strong>;65:1-8.</p>\n<p>\n	&bull; Lalanza JF, Sanchez-Roige S, Cigarroa I, Gagliano H, Fuentes S, Armario A, Capdevila L, Escorihuela RM. <em>Long-term moderate treadmill exercise promotes stress-coping strategies in male and female rats.</em> Sci Rep. <strong>2015</strong>;5:16166.</p>\n<p>\n	&bull; Aguil&oacute; J, Ferrer-Salvans P, Garc&iacute;a-Rozo A, Armario A, Corb&iacute; &Aacute;, Cambra FJ, Bail&oacute;n R, Gonz&aacute;lez-Marcos A, Caja G, Aguil&oacute; S, L&oacute;pez-Ant&oacute;n R, Arza-Vald&eacute;s A, Garz&oacute;n-Rey JM. <em>Project ES3: attempting to quantify and measure the level of stress</em>. Rev Neurol. <strong>2015</strong>;61(9):405-15.</p>\n<p>\n	&bull; Belda X, Fuentes S, Daviu N, Nadal R, Armario A. <em>Stress-induced sensitization: the hypothalamic-pituitary-adrenal axis and beyond</em>. Stress, <strong>2015</strong>, 18:269-79.</p>\n<p>\n	&bull; L&oacute;pez-Moreno JA, Marcos M, Calleja-Conde J, Echeverry-Alzate V, B&uuml;hler K, Costa-Alba P, Bernardo E, Laso FJ, Rodr&iacute;guez de Fonseca F, Nadal R, Viveros MP, Maldonado R, Gin&eacute; E. <em>Histone deacetylase gene expression following binge alcohol consumption in rats and humans</em> Alcohol Clin Exp Res. <strong>2015</strong>, 39:1939-50.</p>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830297/public/\" target=\"_blank\"><br />\n	<strong>Ver m&aacute;s publicaciones de A. Armario a PubMed.</strong></a></p>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48831252/public/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Ver m&aacute;s publicaciones de R. Nadal a PubMed. </strong></a></p>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=andero+r\">Ver m&aacute;s publicaciones de R. Andero a </a><a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=andero+r\" target=\"_blank\">PubMed</a>.</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n',19,2,1),(443,52,0,'Albert Badia y Victoria Clos','<h2>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\">Grupo de Neurofarmacolog&iacute;a</span></h2>\n<p>\n	<strong>L&iacute;deres del Grupo:</strong><br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<table style=\"width: 100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				Albert Badia Sancho</td>\n			<td>\n				Vict&ograve;ria Clos Guill&eacute;n</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:albert.badia@uab.cat\">albert.badia@uab.cat</a></td>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:victoria.clos@uab.cat\">victoria.clos@uab.cat</a></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				+34 93 581 1964</td>\n			<td>\n				+34 93 581 1963</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<table>\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researcherid.com/rid/F-9693-2011\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/RID.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=7005737400\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 29px; height: 29px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researchgate.net/profile/Albert_Badia2\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"28\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/researchgate.jpg\" width=\"28\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n				<table>\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=35582392100\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 29px; height: 29px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/Closdef.jpg\" style=\"width: 100%; margin-top: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px;\" /></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>Miembros del Grupo:</strong><br />\n	Bel&eacute;n P&eacute;rez Fern&aacute;ndez<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>OBJETIVOS ESTRAT&Eacute;GICOS&nbsp;</strong></span><br />\n	<br />\n	El principal objetivo del Grupo de Neurofarmacolog&iacute;a es el estudio de la actividad y funciones de la Acetilcolinesterasa (AChE) y su inhibici&oacute;n mediante inhibidores de la acetilcolinesterasa, ya que hasta el momento representan el tratamiento m&aacute;s exitoso de la enfermedad de Alzheimer. Considerando el mecanismo de acci&oacute;n de los inhibidores de acetilcolinesterasa (IAChE), se espera que puedan mitigar s&oacute;lo temporalmente algunos de los s&iacute;ntomas. Sin embargo, algunos estudios cl&iacute;nicos han puesto de manifiesto que los IAchE no s&oacute;lo incrementan la disponibilidad de la ACh en los enfermos de Alzheimer sino que pueden actuar como modificadores de la enfermedad. Por otro lado, la AChE se encuentra en el tejido neuronal y no neuronal desarrollando tambi&eacute;n funcionas no can&oacute;nicas. Estas funciones no catal&iacute;ticas est&aacute;n implicadas en la morfog&eacute;nesis, hematopoiesis, osteog&eacute;nesis, apoptosis y en la neurog&eacute;nesis. Estas funciones se han asdcrito a dos variantes de la ACh: &ldquo;sin&aacute;ptica&rdquo; AChE-S una enzima de membrana y multim&eacute;rica y a la ACh-R &ldquo; readthrough&rdquo; soluble y monom&eacute;rica. En general, ambas isoformas de AChE son inducibes por lesiones neuronales o por IAChE; sin embargo, la expresi&oacute;n de AChE-R parece estar relacionada con la neuroprotecci&oacute;n y reparaci&oacute;n, mientras AChE-S est&aacute; asociada de forma mayoritaria con lesiones y aumento de la neurotoxicidad. De acuedo con esto, el principal objetivo del presente proyecto es analizar el efecto de los nuevos IAChE (huprinas y heterodimeros) sobre la expresi&oacute;n de las dos variantes de AChE (-S y &ndash;R) en diferentes condiciones experimentales y aproximaciones in vitro e&nbsp; in vivo, teniendo en cuenta los procesos neurot&oacute;xico y neurog&eacute;nico. El objetivo nos permitir&aacute; profundizar en el mecanismo de acci&oacute;n de los IAChE y obtener informaci&oacute;n adicional sobre el papel y las funciones de las isoformas de la AChE.<br />\n	Por otro lado, y en colaboraci&oacute;n con el grupo de Qu&iacute;mica Farmac&eacute;utica de la Facultad de farmacia de la Universidad de Barcelona, realizamos la caracterizaci&oacute;n del perfil farmacol&oacute;gico de nuevos compuestos heterodim&eacute;ricos con funciones multidiana, relacionadas todas ellas con los factores neuropatol&oacute;gicos caracter&iacute;sticos de la enfermedad de Alzheimer.<br />\n	<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong><span style=\"color:#800000;\">PRINCIPALES L&Iacute;NEAS DE INVESTIGACI&Oacute;N&nbsp;</span></strong><br />\n	<br />\n	<em>Neurofarmacolog&iacute;a de los trastornos neurodegenarativos:</em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;- Sistema colin&eacute;rgico en el desarrollo de la enfermedad de Alzheimer: papel de las diferentes variantes de AChE y f&aacute;rmacos anticolinester&aacute;sicos en la neurog&eacute;nesis y los procesos de neurodegeneraci&oacute;n.<br />\n	&nbsp;- La evaluaci&oacute;n farmacol&oacute;gica de nuevos f&aacute;rmacos multifuncionales.<br />\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong> </strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>&Uacute;LTIMAS PUBLICACIONES&nbsp;</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; Di Pietro O, Viayna E, Vicente-Garc&iacute;a E, Bartolini M, Ram&oacute;n R, Ju&aacute;rez-Jim&eacute;nez J, Clos MV, P&eacute;rez B, Andrisano V, Luque FJ, Lavilla R, Mu&ntilde;oz-Torrero D.<em><a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24389509\"><br />\n	1,2,3,4-Tetrahydrobenzo[h][1,6]naphthyridines as a new family of potent peripheral-to-midgorge-site inhibitors of acetylcholinesterase: Synthesis, pharmacological evaluation and mechanistic studies.</a></em><br />\n	Eur J Med Chem. <strong>2014</strong>;73:141-52.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; Viayna E, Sola I, Bartolini M, De Simone A, Tapia-Rojas C, Serrano FG, Sabat&eacute; R, Ju&aacute;rez-Jim&eacute;nez J, P&eacute;rez B, Luque FJ, Andrisano V, Clos MV, Inestrosa NC, Mu&ntilde;oz-Torrero D.<em><a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24568372\"><br />\n	Synthesis and multi-target biological profiling of a novel family of rhein derivatives as disease-modifying anti-Alzheimer agents.</a></em><br />\n	J Med Chem. <strong>2014</strong> . [Epub ahead of print]</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pera M.,&nbsp; Camps P.,&nbsp; Munoz-Torrero D., Perez B., Badia A.,Clos MV.<br />\n	<em>Undifferentiated and Differentiated PC12 Cells Protected by Huprines Against Injury Induced by Hydrogen Peroxide.</em><br />\n	PloS ONE 8(9): e74344. <strong>2013</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ratia M, Gim&eacute;nez-Llort L, Camps P, Mu&ntilde;oz-Torrero D, P&eacute;rez B, Clos MV, Badia A.<br />\n	<em>Huprine X and Huperzine A Improve Cognition and Regulate Some Neurochemical Processes Related with Alzheimer&#39;s Disease in Triple Transgenic Mice (3xTg-AD).</em><br />\n	Neurodegener Dis.&nbsp;<strong>2013</strong>;11(3):129-40.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Galdeano C, Viayna E, Sola I, Formosa X, Camps P, Badia A, Clos MV, Relat J, Ratia M, Bartolini M, Mancini F, Andrisano V, Salmona M, Minguill&oacute;n C, Gonz&aacute;lez-Mu&ntilde;oz GC, Rodr&iacute;guez-Franco MI, Bidon-Chanal A, Luque FJ, Mu&ntilde;oz-Torrero D.<br />\n	<em>Huprine-tacrine heterodimers as anti-amyloidogenic compounds of potential interest against Alzheimer&#39;s and prion diseases.</em><br />\n	J Med Chem.&nbsp;<strong>2012</strong>&nbsp; 26;55(2):661-9.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/49667007/public/\" target=\"_blank\">Ver m&aacute;s publicaiones de A. Badia en PubMed.</a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830631/public/\" target=\"_blank\">Ver m&aacute;s publicaciones de V. Clos en PubMed.</a></p>\n',20,2,1),(444,52,0,'Jose Ramón Bayascas','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<a href=\"javascript:MostraPage(377,1);\">Neurodegeneraci&oacute;n i envejecimiento</a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\">Se&ntilde;alizaci&oacute;n en el Sistema Nervioso Central</span></h2>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>L&iacute;der del Grupo:</strong></p>\n<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				Jos&eacute; Ram&oacute;n Bayascas</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:joseramon.bayascas@uab.cat\">joseramon.bayascas@uab.cat</a></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				TEL: +34 935 813 762</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<table>\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0002-6096-2151\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/orcid.png\" style=\"width: 26px; height: 26px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researcherid.com/rid/C-9450-2011\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/RID.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=6602348616\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 29px; height: 29px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researchgate.net/profile/Jose_Bayascas/publications\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"28\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/researchgate.jpg\" width=\"27\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://scholar.google.com/citations?user=49L6LNQAAAAJ&amp;hl=es\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"29\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/googlescholar.jpg\" width=\"31\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"https://es.linkedin.com/pub/jose-r-bayascas/34/6b6/357\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"33\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Linkedin.jpg\" width=\"42\" /></a></td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<br />\n	<br />\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/bayascas2014.jpg\" style=\"width: 100%;\" /></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>Miembros del grupo:</strong><br />\n	LLu&iacute;s Cord&oacute;n Barris<br />\n	Xiangyu Zhou<br />\n	<br />\n	<strong>Miembros anteriores:</strong><br />\n	Tinatin Zurashvili<br />\n	Patricia Ortega<br />\n	Juuli Lamberg<br />\n	Esther Caba&ntilde;as<br />\n	Natalia Gorska<br />\n	Laura Kempainnen &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\n	Anna Santaella<br />\n	Shaobin Yang</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>OBJETIVOS ESTRAT&Eacute;GICOS</strong></span><br />\n	<br />\n	1) Generar ratones knock-in condicionales de PDK1 que expresan los alelos mutantes de PDK Lys465Glu y Leu155Glu de manera espec&iacute;fica en neuronas.<br />\n	2) Analizar el fenotipo de los ratones knock-in condicionales de PDK1.<br />\n	3) Investigar la contribuci&oacute;n relativa de las isoformas de PKB, en comparaci&oacute;n con el resto de sustratos de PDK1, en la supervivencia neuronal y la diferenciaci&oacute;n de cultivos primarios de neuronas tras estimulaci&oacute;n con factores neurotr&oacute;ficos y bajo estr&eacute;s celular.<br />\n	4) Dilucidar la participaci&oacute;n de los sustratos PDK1 en las v&iacute;as de se&ntilde;alizaci&oacute;n intracelular inducida por factores neurotr&oacute;ficos. La activaci&oacute;n y la fosforilaci&oacute;n de los sustratos fisiol&oacute;gicos de PKB implicados en la supervivencia celular, as&iacute; como los de S6K implicados en la s&iacute;ntesis de prote&iacute;nas y el control del crecimiento celular, ser&aacute;n evaluados.<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PRINCIPALES L&Iacute;NEAS DE INVESTIGACI&Oacute;N</strong></span><br />\n	<br />\n	<em>Funci&oacute;n de la v&iacute;a de se&ntilde;alizaci&oacute;n de PDK1 en la supervivencia neuronal: Generaci&oacute;n de ratones knock-in condicionales de PDK1 espec&iacute;ficos de sistema nervioso.</em><br />\n	El objetivo principal de este proyecto es la caracterizaci&oacute;n de dos cepas de ratones que expresan de forma condicional las mutaciones PDK1 Lys465Glu (K465E) y PDK1 Leu155Glu (L155E). Estas formas mutantes de PDK1 no son capaces de activar las isoformas de PKB, u otros sustratos de PKB (S6K, SGK, RSK y PKC), respectivamente. El alelo condicional PDK1 se expresa en poblaciones neuronales espec&iacute;ficas por medio de la tecnolog&iacute;a de la Cre-recombinasa para evaluar la contribuci&oacute;n relativa de las isoformas de PKB, en comparaci&oacute;n con la de los otros sustratos de PDK1, a la supervivencia de estas poblaciones neuronales.<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PUBLICACIONES</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Zurashvili T, Cord&oacute;n-Barris L, Ruiz-Babot G, Zhou X, Lizcano JM, G&oacute;mez N, Gim&eacute;nez-Llort L, Bayascas JR.&nbsp;<br />\n	<em>Interaction of PDK1&nbsp;with&nbsp;phosphoinositides is essential for neuronal differentiation, but dispensable for neuronal survival.&nbsp;</em><br />\n	Mol Cell Biol. <strong>2013</strong> Mar;33(5):1027-40.<br />\n	<br />\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Bayascas JR.&nbsp;<br />\n	<em>PDK1: the major transducer of PI 3-kinase actions.&nbsp;</em><br />\n	Curr Top Microbiol Immunol.&nbsp;<strong>2010</strong>; 346: 9-29.<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<div>\n	&bull; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Zhou X, Cordon-Barris L, Zurashvili T, Bayascas JR.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>\n	Fine-tuning the intensity of the PKB/Akt signal enables diverse physiological responses. Cell Cycle.&nbsp;2014;13(20):3164-8.</div>\n<p>\n	<br />\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Bayascas JR, Wullschleger S, Sakamoto K, Garc&iacute;a-Mart&iacute;nez JM, Clacher C, Komander D, van Aalten DM, Boini KM, Lang F, Lipina C, Logie L, Sutherland C, Chudek JA, van Diepen JA, Voshol PJ, Lucocq JM, Alessi DR.&nbsp;<br />\n	<em>Mutation of the PDK1 PH domain inhibits protein kinase B/Akt, leading to small size and insulin resistance.</em><br />\n	Mol Cell Biol.&nbsp;<strong>2008</strong> ;28(10):3258-72.&nbsp;<br />\n	<br />\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Bayascas JR.&nbsp;<br />\n	<em>Dissecting the role of the 3-phosphoinositide-dependent protein kinase-1 (PDK1) signalling pathways.&nbsp;</em><br />\n	Cell Cycle.&nbsp;<strong>2008</strong>;7(19):2978-82.</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830639/public/\" target=\"_blank\">Ver m&aacute;s publicaciones de JR. Bayascas en PubMed. </a></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n',21,2,1),(445,52,0,'Bernardo Castellano y Berta González','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<a href=\"javascript:MostraPage(377,1); \">Neurodegeneraci&oacute;n y envejecimiento</a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\">BBG - Grupo de Investigaci&oacute;n en C&eacute;lulas Gliales</span></h2>\n<p>\n	<strong>L&iacute;deres del Grupo:</strong></p>\n<table style=\"width: 100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				Bernardo Castellano L&oacute;pez</td>\n			<td>\n				Berta Gonz&aacute;lez de Mingo</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:bernardo.castellano@uab.cat\">bernardo.castellano@uab.cat</a></td>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:berta.gonzalez@uab.cat\">berta.gonzalez@uab.cat</a></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				TEL: +34 935 811 875</td>\n			<td>\n				TEL: +34 935 811 875</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<table height=\"25\" width=\"40\">\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-1976-971X\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/orcid.png\" style=\"width: 26px; height: 26px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researcherid.com/rid/G-1428-2010\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/RID.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=7003547186\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 29px; height: 29px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Bernardo_Castellano?ev=hdr_xprf\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"27\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/researchgate.jpg\" width=\"27\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/pub/bernardo-castellano-l%C3%B3pez/2a/218/7a8?trk=pub-pbmap\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"32\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Linkedin.jpg\" width=\"41\" /></a></td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n				<table>\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=7102739324\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"29\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" width=\"29\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/Castdef.jpg\" style=\"width: 100%; margin-top: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px;\" /></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>Miembros del Grupo:</strong><br />\n	Beatriz Almolda<br />\n	<a href=\"http://inc.uab.cat/Castellano/profile.php?id=21\">Isabella Appiah</a><br />\n	Anna Camps<br />\n	Miguel A. Martil<br />\n	Filip Petkovic<br />\n	Mireia Recasens<br />\n	Nadia Villacampa</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>OBJETIVOS ESTRAT&Eacute;GICOS</strong></span><br />\n	<br />\n	&bull;Identificar las se&ntilde;ales que controlan la activaci&oacute;n de las c&eacute;lulas gliales en diferentes paradigmas<br />\n	&bull;Identificar las v&iacute;as de se&ntilde;alizaci&oacute;n que pueden ser una posible diana de interacci&oacute;n para evitar la neurodegeneraci&oacute;n y promover la regeneraci&oacute;n<br />\n	&bull;Identificar la presencia de c&eacute;lulas presentadoras de ant&iacute;genos en el SNC tanto en condiciones normales como patol&oacute;gicas<br />\n	&bull;Identificar las se&ntilde;ales que intervienen en la regulaci&oacute;n de la respuesta inflamatoria e inmunitaria en el SNC<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PRINCIPALES L&Iacute;NEAS DE INVESTIGACI&Oacute;N</strong></span><br />\n	<br />\n	1) Estudio de la se&ntilde;alizaci&oacute;n diferencial y mecanismos moleculares implicados en la modulaci&oacute;n de la activaci&oacute;n, proliferaci&oacute;n y muerte de las c&eacute;lulas gliales en diferentes modelos experimentales de inmunidad innata y adquirida: lesiones excitot&oacute;xicas, axotom&iacute;a del nervio facial, deaferentaci&oacute;n de la fascia dentada del hipocampo, inducci&oacute;n de encefalopat&iacute;a autoinmune experimental (EAE), etc.<br />\n	2) Implicaci&oacute;n de las c&eacute;lulas gliales en la regulaci&oacute;n de la respuesta inflamatoria e inmunitaria asociadas. Especialmente estamos interesados en estudiar la regulaci&oacute;n que ejercen las c&eacute;lulas microgliales, macr&oacute;fagos y c&eacute;lulas dendr&iacute;ticas en la modulaci&oacute;n de la entrada, activaci&oacute;n, proliferaci&oacute;n, anergia y apoptosis de linfocitos infiltrados. Estos estudios los desarrollamos en rata Lewis y tambi&eacute;n en rat&oacute;nes transg&eacute;nicos que sobrexpresan citocinas inflamatorias (IL6) y antinflamatorias (IL10).<br />\n	3) Estudio de los cambios en la expresi&oacute;n de mol&eacute;culas de la matriz extracelular y de sus receptores celulares, las integrinas, en neuronas y c&eacute;lulas gliales en diferentes paradigmas de da&ntilde;o cerebral: excitotoxicidad, axotomia y EAE en ratas y ratones normales y tambi&eacute;n en ratones transg&eacute;nicos que sobrexpresan IL6 e IL10.<br />\n	4) Interacci&oacute;n con los mecanismos que regulan en el SNC la expresi&oacute;n de enzimas y citocinas inflamatorias de origen glial mediante la utilizaci&oacute;n de f&aacute;rmacos inhibidores de los factores de transcripci&oacute;n implicados en la activaci&oacute;n de microglia y astroglia, con el objeto de reducir la muerte neuronal secundaria subsiguiente a una lesi&oacute;n experimental<br />\n	5) Evaluaci&oacute;n de la posible utilizaci&oacute;n de complejos moleculares de origen no-v&iacute;rico como vectores en estrategias de terapia g&eacute;nica para promover la neuroprotecci&oacute;n</p>\n<table align=\"left\" border=\"2\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"background-color: rgb(204, 0, 51);\">\n				<strong><span style=\"color:#000000;\">GRUPO SGR 2014 1464</span></strong></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"background-color: rgb(204, 0, 51);\">\n				<span style=\"color:#000000;\"><strong>Coordinaci&oacute;n: Bernardo Castellano</strong></span></td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PUBLICACIONES SELECCIONADAS</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	&bull; &nbsp;&nbsp; Almolda B, Villacampa N, Manders P, Hidalgo J, Campbell IL, Gonz&aacute;lez B and Castellano B.<br />\n	<em>Effects of astrocyte-targeted production of interleukin-6 in the mouse on the host response to nerve injury.</em><br />\n	Glia, 62: 1142- 1161 (<strong>2014</strong>)</p>\n<p>\n	&bull; &nbsp;&nbsp; Almolda B., Gonz&aacute;lez B. and B. Castellano<br />\n	<em>Microglia detection by enzymatic histochemistry.</em><br />\n	Methods Mol Biol 1041: 243-59 (<strong>2013</strong>)</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp; Gonzalez P., Peluffo H., Acarin L., Villaverde A., Gonzalez B.&nbsp; and Castellano B.<br />\n	<em>Interleukin-10 overexpression does not synergize with the neuroprotective action of RGD-containing vectors after postnatal brain excitotoxicity but modulates the main inflammatory cell&nbsp;responses.</em><br />\n	J Neurosci Res. 90:143-59 (<strong>2012</strong>)</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull; &nbsp;&nbsp; Almolda B., Costa M., Montoya M., Gonz&aacute;lez B. and Castellano B.<br />\n	<em>Increase in Th17 and T-reg lymphocytes and decrease of IL22 correlate with the recovery phase of acute EAE in rat.</em><br />\n	PLoS One,&nbsp;2011;6(11):e27473. (<strong>2011</strong>)</p>\n<p>\n	&bull; &nbsp;&nbsp; Almolda B., Gonz&aacute;lez B. and Castellano B<br />\n	<em>Antigen presentation in EAE: role of microglia, macrophages and dendritic cells.</em><br />\n	Frontiers in Biosciences, 16:1157-71,&nbsp;Review (<strong>2011</strong>)</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830665/public/\" target=\"_blank\">Ver m&aacute;s publicaciones de B. Castellano en PubMed.</a></p>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830680/public/\" target=\"_blank\">Ver m&aacute;s publicaciones de B. Gonz&aacute;lez en PubMed.</a></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n',22,2,1),(446,52,0,'Enrique Claro y Fernando Picatoste','<p>\n	<a href=\"javascript:MostraPage(377,1); \">Neurodegeneraci&oacute;n y envejecimiento</a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\">Metabolismo de los L&iacute;pidos y la Muerte Celular</span></h2>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong>L&iacute;deres del Grupo:</strong></p>\n<table style=\"width: 100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				Enrique Claro</td>\n			<td>\n				Fernando Picatoste</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:enrique.claro@uab.es\">enrique.claro@uab.es</a></td>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:fernando.picatoste@uab.cat\">fernando.picatoste@uab.cat</a></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				+34 935814150</td>\n			<td>\n				+34 935811574</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<table>\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0002-7592-7906\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/orcid.png\" style=\"width: 26px; height: 26px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researcherid.com/rid/D-5612-2009\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/RID.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"https://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=7003847422\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 29px; height: 29px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researchgate.net/profile/Enrique_Claro\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/researchgate.jpg\" style=\"width: 27px; height: 27px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n				<table>\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								<p>\n									<a href=\"https://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=6701819691\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 29px; height: 29px;\" /></a></p>\n							</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/ClaPidef.jpg\" style=\"width: 100%; margin-top: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px;\" /></p>\n<p>\n	<strong>Miembros del grupo:</strong><br />\n	Meritxell Asensio<br />\n	Ainara G. Cabodevilla<br />\n	<br />\n	<strong>Miembros anteriores:</strong><br />\n	Alberto G. Andreolotti<br />\n	Miquel Barcel&oacute;<br />\n	David Barneda<br />\n	Albert Gubern<br />\n	Eleni Nintou<br />\n	Ra&uuml;l Pardo<br />\n	Bel&eacute;n Ramos<br />\n	Laura S&aacute;nchez</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>OBJETIVOS ESTRAT&Eacute;GICOS</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	Queremos explicar algunas funciones del metabolismo de fosfol&iacute;pidos en procesos fisiol&oacute;gicos tales como la muerte celular programada, la autofagia, y la secreci&oacute;n. La fosfatidilcolina (PtdCho) es el principal fosfol&iacute;pido en las membranas celulares, pero su implicaci&oacute;n en muchos aspectos de la fisiopatol&oacute;gicos, algunos de ellos relacionados con el sistema nervioso, s&oacute;lo est&aacute; empezando a conocerse.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>L&Iacute;NIAS DE INVESTIGACI&Oacute;N</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<em>1 .- Mecanismos de muerte celular asociada a la inhibici&oacute;n de la s&iacute;ntesis de PtdCho</em><br />\n	Varios f&aacute;rmacos inhiben la s&iacute;ntesis de PtdCho debido a su interacci&oacute;n con la CTP: cytidylyltransferase fosfocolina (CCT), una de las tres enzimas de la v&iacute;a de la CDP-colina, y esto se traduce en la inducci&oacute;n de muerte celular. En la actualidad estamos estudiando las c&eacute;lulas CHO-MT58, que poseen una enzima CCT&alpha; termosensible. El proceso de muerte celular no implica mecanismos de apoptosis, y al parecer se lleva a cabo con los t&iacute;picos rasgos de autofagia.<br />\n	<br />\n	<em> 2 .- Biog&eacute;nesis de gotas lip&iacute;dicas y su papel en la supervivencia celular</em><br />\n	Las gotitas de lip&iacute;dicas (LD) son org&aacute;nulos que almacenan triglic&eacute;ridos y &eacute;steres de colesterol, de alguna manera similares a la gran gota de los adipocitos; las LD, en cambio, son mucho m&aacute;s peque&ntilde;as y se encuentran en pr&aacute;cticamente todos los tipos de c&eacute;lulas incluyendo neuronas y astrocitos. Las LD son org&aacute;nulos muy din&aacute;micos que aparecen en el citosol cuando las c&eacute;lulas incorporan lipoprote&iacute;nas o &aacute;cidos grasos libres del medio. Las LD aparecen tambi&eacute;n en la ausencia de fuentes externas de l&iacute;pidos cuando las c&eacute;lulas est&aacute;n sometidas a estr&eacute;s: en este caso, las LD confieren resistencia al estr&eacute;s, y los triglic&eacute;ridos contenidos en las LD derivan de los fosfol&iacute;pidos de las propia membranas celulares.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/Investigacio/ld-fl.jpg\" style=\"width: 50%; float: left;\" /><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/Investigacio/ld-tem.jpg\" style=\"width: 50%; float: right;\" /></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/Investigacio/1.jpg\" style=\"width: 100%;\" /></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PUBLICACIONES DESTACADAS</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; Cabodevilla AG, S&aacute;nchez-Caballero L, Nintou E, Boiadjieva VG, Picatoste F, Gubern A, Claro E.<br />\n	<em>Cell survival during complete nutrient deprivation depends on lipid droplet-fueled &beta;-oxidation of fatty acids.</em><br />\n	J Biol Chem. 2013 Sep 27;288(39):27777-88.Epub <strong>2013</strong></p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A. Gubern, M. Barcel&oacute;-Torns, D. Barneda, R. Masgrau, F. Picatoste, J. Casas, J. Balsinde, M.A. Balboa, E. Claro.<br />\n	<em>Lipid droplet biogenesis induced by stress involves triacylglycerol synthesis that depends on Group VIA phospholipase A2.</em><br />\n	J Biol Chem. <strong>2009</strong>;284(9):5697-708.<br />\n	<br />\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A. Gubern, M. Barcel&oacute;-Torns, D. Barneda, J.M. L&oacute;pez, R. Masgrau, F. Picatoste, C.E. Chalfant, J. Balsinde, M.A. Balboa, E. Claro.<br />\n	<em>JNK and ceramide kinase govern the biogenesis of lipid droplets through activation of Group IVA phospholipase A2.</em><br />\n	J Biol Chem. <strong>2009</strong>;284(47):32359-69.<br />\n	<br />\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A. Gubern, J. Casas, M. Barcel&oacute;-Torns, D. Barneda, X. de la Rosa, R. Masgrau, F. Picatoste, J. Balsinde, M.A. Balboa, E. Claro.<br />\n	<em>Group IVA phospholipase A2 is necessary for the biogenesis of lipid droplets.</em><br />\n	J Biol Chem. <strong>2008</strong>;283(41):27369-82.</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830780/public/\" target=\"_blank\">Ver m&aacute;s publicaciones de E. Claro en PubMed.</a></p>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830787/public/\" target=\"_blank\">Ver m&aacute;s publicaciones de F. Picatoste en PubMed.</a></p>\n',23,2,1),(448,52,0,'Rosa Maria Escorihuela','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<a href=\"javascript:MostraPage(379,1); \">Neurobiolog&iacute;a de la mente normal y alterada</a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\">Estilos de Vida y Salud Mental</span></h2>\n<p>\n	<strong>L&iacute;der del Grupo:</strong></p>\n<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				Rosa M. Escorihuela Agull&oacute;</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:RosaMaria.Escorihuela@uab.cat\">RosaMaria.Escorihuela@uab.cat</a></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				TEL: +34 935 813 296</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<table>\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								<p>\n									<a href=\"https://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=16938862000\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 29px; height: 29px;\" /></a></p>\n							</td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researchgate.net/profile/Rosa_Escorihuela\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"30\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/researchgate.jpg\" width=\"30\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/RMescdef.jpg\" style=\"width: 100%; margin-top: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px;\" /></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>Miembros del Grupo:</strong><br />\n	Igor Ivan Cigarroa Cuevas<br />\n	Oier Pastor</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>OBJETIVOS ESTRAT&Eacute;GICOS</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	El principal objetivo de nuestro programa de investigaci&oacute;n es avaluar el impacto a largo t&eacute;rmino de las condiciones ambientales y los h&aacute;bitos de vida en diversas etapas de la vida sobre les funciones cerebrales y la salud mental. Utilizamos el enriquecimiento ambiental, la manipulaci&oacute;n infantil y, m&aacute;s recientemente, el ejercicio f&iacute;sico como instrumentos para mejorara el funcionamiento del cerebro en la edad adulta y el envejecimiento. Sometemos a las ratas (machos y hembras) a sesiones de 30min de entrenamiento moderado en el tapiz rodante (12m/min, 5 d&iacute;as/semana) con el objetivo de reproducir un protocolo ampliamente recomendado a los humanos. Estamos introduciendo una dieta con un alto contenido en grasa y az&uacute;car para estudiar la interacci&oacute;n de la pr&aacute;ctica regular del ejercicio con los malos h&aacute;bitos alimentarios. Utilizamos un modelo animal de senescencia acelerada como segunda estrategia y colocamos estos animales en jaulas que contienen ruedas de actividad para que hagan ejercicio voluntariamente. Los efectos de las diferentes formas de ejercicio practicado a largo t&eacute;rmino son evaluados en la edad adulta y en la vejez a nivel conductual, bioqu&iacute;mico y fisiol&oacute;gico. Valoramos los efectos del ejercicio sobre la funci&oacute;n cardiovascular a trav&eacute;s de implantes telem&eacute;tricos colocados en la cavidad abdominal de los animales.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PRINCIPALES L&Iacute;NEAS DE INVESTIGACI&Oacute;N</strong></span><br />\n	<br />\n	1. Determinar los efectos del ejercicio moderado y regular en la ansiedad, respuesta al estr&eacute;s, depresi&oacute;n y funciones cognitivas en machos y hembras.<br />\n	2. Avaluar si el ejercicio puede disminuir el impacto del deterioro asociado al envejecimiento y a les enfermedades neurodegenerativas.<br />\n	3. Investigar la interacci&oacute;n del ejercicio moderado y regular con los malos h&aacute;bitos alimentarios, en t&eacute;rminos de cambios conductuales.<br />\n	4. Caracterizar los perfiles conductuales de los sujetos muy predispuestos y de los sujetos poco predispuestos a practicar ejercicio regularmente y a incorporar grasas y az&uacute;cares en su dieta.<br />\n	5. Investigar los efectos del ejercicio como tratamiento para disminuir la impulsividad y mejorar la ejecuci&oacute;n en tareas de atenci&oacute;n.<br />\n	&nbsp;<br />\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong> PUBLICACIONES DESTACADAS</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp; Lalanza, J.F., Caimari, A., Del Bas, J.M., (...), Arola, L., Escorihuela, R.M.<br />\n	<em>Effects of a post-weaning cafeteria diet in young rats: Metabolic syndrome, reduced activity and low anxiety-like behaviour</em><br />\n	PLoS ONE, <strong>2014</strong>, 9 (1), e85049</p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp; Lalanza, J.F., Sanchez-Roige, S., Gagliano, H., (...), Armario, A., Escorihuela, R.M.<br />\n	<em>Physiological and behavioural consequences of long-term moderate treadmill exercise</em><br />\n	Psychoneuroendocrinology, <strong>2012</strong> , 37 (11), pp. 1745-1754</p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp; Bayod, S., del Valle, J., Lalanza, J.F., (...), Escorihuela, R.M., Pall&agrave;s, M.<br />\n	<em>Long-term physical exercise induces changes in sirtuin 1 pathway and oxidative parameters in adult rat tissues</em><br />\n	Experimental Gerontology ,<strong>2012</strong> ,47 (12), pp. 925-935</p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp; Kaliman P, P&aacute;rrizas , Lalanza JF, Camins A,Escorihuela RM, Pall&agrave;s M.<br />\n	<em>Neurophysiological and epigenetic effects of physical exercise on the aging process.</em><br />\n	Ageing Res Rev. <strong>2011</strong> ;10(4):475-86.</p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp; Garc&iacute;a-Gonz&aacute;lez MA, Fern&aacute;ndez-Chimeno M, Ferrer J, Escorihuela RM, Parrado E, Capdevila L, Ben&iacute;tez A, Angulo R, Rodr&iacute;guez FA, Iglesias X, Besc&oacute;s R, Marina M, Padull&eacute;s JM, Ramos-Castro J.&nbsp;<br />\n	<em>New indices for quantification of the power spectrum of heart rate variability time series without the need of any frequency band definition.</em><br />\n	Physiol Meas. <strong>2011</strong>;32(8):995-1009.</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830790/public/\" target=\"_blank\">Ver m&aacute;s publicaciones de RM. Escorihuela en PubMed.</a></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n',25,2,1),(449,52,0,'Ester Fernández','<p>\n	<a href=\"javascript:MostraPage(377,1); \">Neurodegeneraci&oacute;n y envejecimiento</a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\">Grupo de Investigaci&oacute;n en Inflamaci&oacute;n y Tolerancia: Nuevas aproximaciones terap&eacute;uticas</span></h2>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong>L&iacute;der del Grupo:</strong></p>\n<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				Ester Fern&aacute;ndez Gimeno</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:Ester.Fernandez@uab.cat\">Ester.Fernandez@uab.cat</a></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				+34 93 581 3282</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<table>\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								<p>\n									<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=7402179023\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 29px; height: 29px;\" /></a></p>\n							</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/Eferdef.jpg\" style=\"width: 100%; margin-top: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px;\" /></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>Miembros del grupo:</strong><br />\n	Joan Francesc Burgue&ntilde;o Ban&uacute;s<br />\n	Elena Eyre S&aacute;nchez<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>OBJETIVOS ESTRAT&Eacute;GICOS</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Progresar en el conocimiento de la funci&oacute;n del sistema nervioso ent&eacute;rico y c&oacute;mo interacciona con el resto de tipos celulares que se encuentran en el intestino para poder comprender c&oacute;mo se regula en este nivel la respuesta inmune innata, el mantenimiento de la tolerancia y la transici&oacute;n de situaciones de tolerancia a inflamaci&oacute;n y de infamaci&oacute;n a tumorog&eacute;nesis.<br />\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Explorar la interacci&oacute;n entre los receptores de reconocimiento de patrones moleculares , - y en particular los receptores toll-like-con otras v&iacute;a de se&ntilde;alizaci&oacute;n.<br />\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Nuestra investigaci&oacute;n combina aproximaciones moleculares, celulares y estudios en animales utilizando una amplia variedad de t&eacute;cnicas y modelos.<br />\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Mediante estos estudios pretendemos plantear estrategias novedosas de intervenci&oacute;n terap&eacute;utica basadas en el uso de nuevas herramientas, dianas y veh&iacute;culos incluyendo vectores de terapia g&eacute;nica.<br />\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong> </strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PRINCIPALES L&Iacute;NEAS DE INVESTIGACI&Oacute;N</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Valoraci&oacute;n de la eficacia terap&eacute;utica de estrategias de Knock down g&eacute;nico in vitro e&nbsp; in vivo en modelos animales de inflamaci&oacute;n (EII) y cancer de colon.<br />\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Valoraci&oacute;n de la eficacia terap&eacute;utica de estrategias de sobreexpresi&oacute;n g&eacute;nica in vitro e&nbsp; in vivo en modelos animales de inflamaci&oacute;n (EII) y cancer de colon.<br />\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Funciones inmunomoduladores de las neuronas yla glia ent&eacute;ricas.<br />\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Interrelaci&oacute;n de las vias activadas por la estimulaci&oacute;n de receptores de reconocimineto de patrones moleculares y&nbsp; TLR&nbsp; con otras cascadas de se&ntilde;alizaci&oacute;n<br />\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Mecanismos implicados en la quimio-resist&egrave;ncia adquirida.<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PUBLICACIONES</strong></span><br />\n	<br />\n	&bull;&nbsp;Ocampo SM, Romero C, Avi&ntilde;&oacute; A, Burgue&ntilde;o J, Gassull MA, Berm&uacute;dez J, Eritja R, Fernandez E, Perales JC.<br />\n	<em>Functionally enhanced siRNA targeting TNF&alpha;attenuates DSS-induced colitis and TLR-mediated immunostimulation in mice.</em><br />\n	Mol Ther.&nbsp;<strong>2012</strong> ;20(2):382-90.<br />\n	<br />\n	&bull;&nbsp;Aul&iacute; M, Nasser Y, Ho W, Burgue&ntilde;o JF, Keenan CM, Romero C, Sharkey KA, Fern&aacute;ndez E.<br />\n	<em>Neuromuscular changes in a rat model of colitis.</em><br />\n	Auton.&nbsp; Neurosci-Basic Clin.&nbsp;<strong>2008 </strong>;141(1-2):10-21.&nbsp;<br />\n	<br />\n	&bull; R&iacute;o A, Gassull MA, Aldeguer X, Ojanguren I, Cabr&eacute; E, Fern&aacute;ndez E.<br />\n	<em>Reduced liver injury in the interleukin-6 knockout mice by chronic carbon tetrachloride administration.</em><br />\n	Eur J Clin Invest.&nbsp;<strong>2008</strong>;38(5):306-16.<br />\n	<br />\n	&bull;&nbsp;Aul&iacute; M, Fern&aacute;ndez E.<br />\n	<em>Time course of neural and contractile disturbances in a rat model of colitis induced by Trichinella spiralis.</em><br />\n	Life Sci.&nbsp;<strong>2007</strong> 81(14):1117-29.<br />\n	<br />\n	<br />\n	<strong><span style=\"color:#800000;\">PATENTES</span></strong><br />\n	<br />\n	T&iacute;tle: Methods and Reagents of efficient and targeted gene transfer to monocytes and&nbsp; macrophages.&nbsp; Inventors:&nbsp; Chillon, M, Rio A, Fern&aacute;ndez E, Gassull MA. European Patent application: EP09159001.8 Priority: EUROPE. Priority date: 29-04-2009.Extended to:&nbsp; PCT, Argentina, Uruguay. Ownership: Universitat Autonoma de Barcelona, Fundaci&oacute; Institut de Recerca Hospital Univ. Germans Trias i Pujol, Institut Catal&agrave; de Recerca i Estudis Avan&ccedil;ats (ICREA), Gr&iacute;fols S.A. Licensed to:&nbsp; Nanotherapix S.L.<br />\n	<br />\n	T&iacute;tle: Derivados de peque&ntilde;os ARN de interferencia y su uso. Inventors: Eritja R, Ocampo S.M., Perales J.C., Fern&aacute;ndez, E. Romero, C., Burgue&ntilde;o J.F. P201031622&nbsp; Pa&iacute;s de prioridad: Espa&ntilde;a.&nbsp; Priority date: 04-11-2010. Extended to:&nbsp; PCT, Argentina, Uruguay.&nbsp; Ownership: Consejo Superior de Investigaciones Cient&iacute;ficas (CSIC); Universitat de Barcelona; Universitat Autonoma de Barcelona. Licensed to: ( Dealing)</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830799/public/\" target=\"_blank\">Ver mas publicaciones de E. Fern&aacute;ndez en PubMed.</a></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n',26,2,1),(450,52,0,'Alberto Fernandez Teruel','<p>\n	<a href=\"javascript:MostraPage(379,1); \">Neurobiolog&iacute;a de la mente normal y alterada</a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\">Bases Neurobiol&oacute;gicas y Gen&eacute;ticas de Enfermedades Mentales y Neurol&oacute;gicas</span></h2>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong>L&iacute;der del Grupo:</strong></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				Alberto Fern&aacute;ndez Teruel</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:Albert.Fernandez.Teruel@uab.cat\">Albert.Fernandez.Teruel@uab.cat</a></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				TEL: +34 935 813 456</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<table>\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researcherid.com/rid/F-9374-2011\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/RID.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<p>\n									<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=7003727625\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 29px; height: 29px;\" /></a></p>\n							</td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researchgate.net/profile/Alberto_Fernandez-Teruel\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"30\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/researchgate.jpg\" width=\"30\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/AFernandezA3_opt.jpg\" style=\"width: 400px; height: 266px;\" /></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>Miembros del Grupo:</strong><br />\n	Gloria Bl&aacute;zquez Romero<br />\n	Antoni Ca&ntilde;ete Ram&iacute;rez<br />\n	Crist&oacute;bal del R&iacute;o Alamos<br />\n	Carme Mont Cardona<br />\n	Ignasi Oliveras Puigdelivol<br />\n	Ana S&aacute;nchez Gonz&aacute;lez<br />\n	Adolf Tobe&ntilde;a Pallar&eacute;s</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>OBJETIVOS ESTRAT&Eacute;GICOS</strong></span><br />\n	<br />\n	Las investigaciones actuales y futuras de nuestro grupo&nbsp; de investigaci&oacute;n tienen como objetivo mejorar el conocimiento sobre las bases psicol&oacute;gicas, neurobiol&oacute;gicos y gen&eacute;ticas de varias enfermedades psicol&oacute;gicas y neurol&oacute;gicas. El progreso hacia estos objetivos se basa en el uso de varios recursos y enfoques experimentales, a saber: 1) Ratas psicogen&eacute;ticamente seleccionadas RHA-I y RLA i que difieren notablemente en ansiedad/estr&eacute;s (conductuales y hormonales) y las respuestas a los incentivos&nbsp; de b&uacute;squeda de drogas, representan un buen modelo para estudiar las bases neurobiol&oacute;gicas y gen&eacute;ticas de la ansiedad y la adicci&oacute;n a las drogas. 2) Adem&aacute;s del uso de estas ARS-I y RLA-I cepas, el N / NIH-HS poblaci&oacute;n de ratas gen&eacute;ticamente heterog&eacute;neas (que se mantienen en nuestro laboratorio) es un poderoso recurso que se utiliza para el mapeo gen&eacute;tico del complejo fenotipos relacionados con la enfermedad como la ansiedad / miedo, depresi&oacute;n, esclerosis m&uacute;ltiple, la presi&oacute;n arterial, las caracter&iacute;sticas relacionadas con la diabetes y otros rasgos endocrinos e inmunol&oacute;gicos. 3) Los ratones&nbsp; triple transg&eacute;nicos 3xTgAD son tambi&eacute;n un modelo de gran alcance para la demencia de Alzheimer, que se utiliza en nuestro laboratorio para investigar las posibilidades de prevenir o retrasar la aparici&oacute;n de los s&iacute;ntomas neuropatol&oacute;gicos y conductuales de la demencia infantil / juvenil con&nbsp; tratamientos del medio ambiente enriquecido..&nbsp;<br />\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong> </strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PRINCIPALES L&Iacute;NEAS DE INVESTIGACI&Oacute;N</strong></span><br />\n	<br />\n	<em> Neurogen&eacute;tica de la ansiedad y de enfermedades relacionadas con fenotipos neuronales y no neuronales en ratas.</em><br />\n	Utilizando datos en N/NIH-HS y RHA/ratas RLA, y financiado por el SAF-2003-03480 (IP: A. Fern&aacute;ndez-Teruel), por la Welcome Trust (J. Flint, Reino Unido) y por una subvenci&oacute;n europea FP6 (IP : Timothy Aitman, Londres IP colaborador 11:. A. Fern&aacute;ndez-Teruel), esta l&iacute;nea de investigaci&oacute;n se lleva a cabo en colaboraci&oacute;n con los grupos de los Dres. Jonathan Flint (Oxford), Peter Driscoll (Suiza), Tomas Olsson (Suecia), Dominique Gauguier (Oxford), Norbert Hubner (Berl&iacute;n), Rickard Holdmdal (Suecia), Anna Dominizak (Escocia) y 10 laboratorios de otros centros de investigaci&oacute;n europeos.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<em>Efectos de la estimulaci&oacute;n postnatal (manejo de reci&eacute;n nacidos) y del enriquecimiento ambiental sobre anomal&iacute;as en el comportamiento relacionadas con el envejecimiento y la demencia.</em><br />\n	En colaboraci&oacute;n con el Dr. F.M. LaFerla (California, EE.UU.) una colonia de ratones 3xTgAD (un modelo de enfermedad de Alzheimer muy reciente) se ha establecido en nuestro laboratorio. La financiaci&oacute;n de esta l&iacute;nea de investigaci&oacute;n ha sido obtenida de I + D (Ministerio Espa&ntilde;ol de Educaci&oacute;n y Ciencia, 2006-2008) y &quot;Marat&oacute; de TV3&quot; (IP: Lydia Gim&eacute;nez-Llort, Colaboradores: Dr. FM LaFerla, UCI, EE.UU. i y el Dr. B. Johansson, Instituto Karolinska, de Estocolmo, el Dr. C. Sanfeliu, Barcelona, CSIC, Espa&ntilde;a).</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<em>Enriquecimiento ambiental, ejercicio f&iacute;sico y/o dietas especiales en roedores: Efectos a largo plazo en el comportamiento y la bioqu&iacute;mica.</em><br />\n	Esta l&iacute;nea de investigaci&oacute;n se est&aacute; desarrollando en colaboraci&oacute;n con la profesora Margarita Prunell (Universidad de La Laguna, Espa&ntilde;a), la Dra. Yolanda Pe&ntilde;a (Universidad de Essex, Reino Unido), la &nbsp;profesora Mercedes Unzeta (Departamento de Bioqu&iacute;mica de la UAB), los profesores &nbsp;Juan Hidalgo y Antonio Armario (Departamento de Biolog&iacute;a Cel&middot;lular Fisiologia I ), y la Profesora Roser Nadal (Psicobiologia, Facultat de Psicologia, UAB).</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>&Uacute;LTIMAS PUBLICACIONES&nbsp;</strong></span><br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	&bull; &nbsp;&nbsp; Bl&aacute;zquez G, Ca&ntilde;ete T, Tobe&ntilde;a A, Gim&eacute;nez-Llort L, Fern&aacute;ndez-Teruel A.<br />\n	<em>Cognitive and emotional profiles of aged Alzheimer&#39;s disease (3&times;TgAD) mice: Effects of environmental enrichment and sexual dimorphism.</em><br />\n	Behav Brain Res. <strong>2014</strong> Jul 15;268:185-201.</p>\n<p>\n	&bull; &nbsp;&nbsp; Alam I, Koller DL, Ca&ntilde;ete T, Bl&aacute;zquez G, L&oacute;pez-Aumatell R, Mart&iacute;nez-Membrives E, D&iacute;az-Mor&aacute;n S, Tobe&ntilde;a A, Fern&aacute;ndez-Teruel A, Stridh P, Diez M, Olsson T, Johannesson M, Baud A, Econs MJ, Foroud T.<br />\n	<em>High-Resolution Genome Screen for Bone Mineral Density in Heterogeneous Stock Rat.</em><br />\n	J Bone Miner Res. <strong>2014</strong> [Epub ahead of print]</p>\n<p>\n	&bull; &nbsp;&nbsp; Tuncel J, Haag S, Yau AC, Norin U, Baud A, L&ouml;nnblom E, Maratou K, Ytterberg AJ, Ekman D, Thordardottir S, Johannesson M, Gillett A; EURATRANS Consortium, Stridh P, Jagodic M, Olsson T, Fern&aacute;ndez-Teruel A, Zubarev RA, Mott R, Aitman TJ, Flint J, Holmdahl R.<br />\n	<em>Natural polymorphisms in Tap2 influence negative selection and CD4?CD8 lineage commitment in the rat.</em><br />\n	PLoS Genet. <strong>2014</strong> ;10(2):e1004151.</p>\n<p>\n	&bull; &nbsp;&nbsp; Klein AB, Ultved L, Adamsen D, Santini MA, Tobe&ntilde;a A, Fernandez-Teruel A, Flores P, Moreno M, Cardona D, Knudsen GM, Aznar S, Mikkelsen JD.<br />\n	<em> 5-HT(2A) and mGlu2 receptor binding levels are related to differences in impulsive behavior in the Roman Low- (RLA) and High- (RHA) avoidance rat strains.</em><br />\n	Neuroscience. <strong>2014</strong> ;263:36-45.</p>\n<p>\n	&bull; &nbsp;&nbsp; Manzo L, G&oacute;mez MJ, Callejas-Aguilera JE, Fern&aacute;ndez-Teruel A, Papini MR, Torres C.<br />\n	<em>Anti-anxiety self-medication induced by incentive loss in rats.</em><br />\n	Physiol Behav. <strong>2014</strong>;123:86-92.</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830803/public/\" target=\"_blank\">Ver m&aacute;s publicaciones de A. Fern&aacute;ndez-Teruel en PubMed.</a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n',27,2,1),(452,52,0,'Lydia Gimenez Llort','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	Neurodegeneraci&oacute;n y envejecimiento</p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\">Neurociencia Conductual<br />\n	</span></h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>L&iacute;der del Grupo:</strong></p>\n<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				Lydia Gim&eacute;nez-Llort</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:lidia.gimenez@uab.cat\" target=\"_blank\">lidia.gimenez@uab.cat</a></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				TEL: +34 935 812 378</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<table>\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								<p>\n									<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=6701506831\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 29px; height: 29px;\" /></a></p>\n							</td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researchgate.net/profile/Lydia_Gimenez-Llort\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"29\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/researchgate.jpg\" width=\"29\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<a href=\"http://%20www.saberenvejecer.es\">www.saberenvejecer.es</a><br />\n	<a href=\"http://%20www.neurodeg.net\"> www.neurodeg.net</a><br />\n	<a href=\"http://%20www.4th5.net\"> www.4th5.net</a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/Gimdef.jpg\" style=\"width: 100%; margin-top: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px;\" /></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>Miembros del Grupo:</strong><br />\n	Adriana Serrano<br />\n	Aida Muntsant Soria<br />\n	Anna Roquer<br />\n	<br />\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>OBJECTIVOS ESTRAT&Eacute;GICOS</strong></span><br />\n	<br />\n	Modelar y caracterizar los fenotipos conductuales y neuroimmunoendocrinos relacionados con el envejecimiento y aquellos que son caracter&iacute;sticos de enfermedades neurodegenerativas o neurol&oacute;gicas se convierte en un reto necesario si queremos disponer de herramientas &uacute;tiles para estudiar los mecanismos subyacentes a la patofisiolog&iacute;a pero tambi&eacute;n para ensayar el potencial preventivo y terap&eacute;utico de nuevas terapias.?Nuestra investigaci&oacute;n se focaliza en la neurociencia conductual (caracterizaci&oacute;n conductual, farmacolog&iacute;a conductual y aproximaciones no farmacol&oacute;gicas) intentando, en la medida que nos es posible, de hacer una aproximaci&oacute;n traslacional. Tambi&eacute;n estamos interesados en las relaciones sociales e intergeneracionales humanas y su impacto en la calidad de vida de las personas mayores, un aspecto que intentamos perfilar tambi&eacute;n desde la investigaci&oacute;n b&aacute;sica.?Somos miembros del SGR1354 2014 (Coordinador: Miguel Chill&oacute;n), RETICEF (RD06/0013/0003), UCM-CM ENEROINN 910.379 (UCM, IP: M&oacute;nica De la Fuente), el Network 4the5 (Fundadora: Lydia Gim&eacute;nez-Llort), Consorci Neurogenet (IGTP, CSIC, UAB, Coordinador: Antonio Matilla). La Dra. Lydia Gim&eacute;nez-Llort es la representante espa&ntilde;ola en el European Cooperation in the Field of Scientific and Technical Research COST-action TD1005 &lsquo;Pain Assessmment in Patients with Impaired Cognition, especially Dementia&rsquo;.?La aproximaci&oacute;n translational se plantea gracias a acuerdos y convenios de colaboraci&oacute;n con los Hospital Karolinska del Instituto Karolinska, Estocolmo, Suecia (IP: Bj&ouml;rn Johansson), UVAMID Hospital Santa Katerina, Salto, Girona (IP: Secund&iacute; L&oacute;pez-Pousa) y el Hospital Sagrat Cor de Martorell (IP: Manel S&aacute;nchez).</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PRINCIPALES L&Iacute;NEAS DE INVESTIGACI&Oacute;N</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	?1. Establecimiento de la colonia espa&ntilde;ola de ratones 3xTg-AD y de su cepa salvaje. Caracterizaci&oacute;n conductual de deficiencias cognitivas y s&iacute;ntomas de tipo SPCD en modelos por envejecimiento y demencia.<br />\n	2. Evaluaci&oacute;n conductual de estrategias preventivas y/o terap&eacute;uticas no farmacol&oacute;gicas (handling, enriquecimiento ambiental, ejercicio) en modelos animales de envejecimiento y enfermedades neurodegenerativas, con prioridad en nuestra colonia de ratones 3xTg-AD.?<br />\n	3. Farmacolog&iacute;a conductual de las interacciones entre NMDA-DA-Adenosina en modelos animales para trastornos psiqui&aacute;tricos y neurol&oacute;gicos.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong><em>Colonia espa&ntilde;ola de 3xTgAD ratones.</em></strong></span><br />\n	La Dra. Lydia Gim&eacute;nez-Llort estableci&oacute; la colonia espa&ntilde;ola de ratones 3xTg-AD y su cepa de tipo salvaje en la UAB gracias a Material Transfer Agreement (2004, 2007) con el Dr. F.M. LaFerla (Universidad de California Irvine, EE.UU.). Los ratones triple-transg&eacute;nicos 3xTg-AD (Oddo et al, 2003, Neuron, 39, 409-421) que albergan los transgenes PS1M146V, APPswe y tauP301L desarrollan progresivamente placas de &beta;A y ovillos neurofibrilares con un perfil temporal y regionales espec&iacute;ficos, que se asemeja mucho a su desarrollo en el cerebro humano AD. La disfunci&oacute;n sin&aacute;ptica y cognitivas se manifiestan en la edad y el sexo de forma dependiente, pero antes de que la patolog&iacute;a de placa y las mara&ntilde;as neurofibrilares. Hoy en d&iacute;a, este modelo es una de las herramientas m&aacute;s prometedoras para estudiar los mecanismos de acci&oacute;n de la contribuci&oacute;n fisiopatol&oacute;gica de &beta;A intracelular en el da&ntilde;o, y tratar de determinar qu&eacute; tan extensa placa, as&iacute; como patolog&iacute;as de mara&ntilde;as, pueden contribuir a la &uacute;ltima etapa de d&eacute;ficits cognitivos, evaluar segunda generaci&oacute;n de estrategias terap&eacute;uticas y preventivas que se acerca a medida son capaces de mejorar los fenotipos conductuales y patol&oacute;gicos.?<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PUBLICACIONES DESTACADAS</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp; Johansson, B.,&nbsp; Halldner, L., Dunwiddie, T.V., Masino, S.A., Poelchen, W., Gim&eacute;nez-Llort, L., Escorihuela, R.M., Fern&aacute;ndez-Teruel, A., Wiesenfeld-Hallin, Z., Xu X.-J., H&aring;rdemark, A., Betsholtz, Ch., Herlenius, E., Fredholm, B.<br />\n	<em>Hyperalgesia, anxiety, and decreased hypoxic neuroprotection in mice lacking the adenosine A1 receptor.</em><br />\n	Proc. Nat. Acad. Sciences98 (16), 9407-9412.<strong>2001</strong></p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp; Gim&eacute;nez-Llort, L.*, Bl&aacute;zquez, G., Ca&ntilde;ete, T., Johansson, B., Oddo,S., Tobe&ntilde;a,A, LaFerla, F.M., Fern&aacute;ndez-Teruel, A.<br />\n	<em>Modeling behavioral and neuronal symptoms of Alzheimer disease in mice: a role for intraneuronal&nbsp; amyloid.</em><br />\n	Neurosci Biobehav Rev. 31(1):125-47,<strong>2007</strong></p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp; Espa&ntilde;a J, Gim&eacute;nez-Llort L, Valero J, Mi&ntilde;ano A, R&aacute;bano A, Rodriguez-Alvarez J, LaFerla FM, Saura CA<br />\n	<em>Intraneuronal beta-Amyloid Accumulation in the Amygdala Enhances Fear and Anxiety in Alzheimer&#39;s Disease Transgenic Mice.</em><br />\n	Biol Psychiatry.67(6): 513-521, <strong>2010</strong></p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp; Sol&eacute;-Dom&egrave;nech S, Sj&ouml;vall P, Vukojevi? V, Fernando R, Codita A, Salve S, Bogdanovi? N, Mohammed AH, Hammarstr&ouml;m P, Nilsson KP, Laferla FM, Jacob S, Berggren PO, Gim&eacute;nez-Llort L, Schalling M, Terenius L, Johansson B.<br />\n	<em>Localization of cholesterol, amyloid and glia in Alzheimer&#39;s disease transgenic mouse brain tissue using time-of-flight secondary ion mass spectrometry (ToF-SIMS) and immunofluorescence imaging.</em><br />\n	Acta Neuropathol. 125(1):145-57. <strong>2013</strong></p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp; Gim&eacute;nez-Llort L, Torres-Lista V, De la Fuente M.<br />\n	<em>Crosstalk between the nervous and the immune system during the prodromal stages of Alzheimer&rsquo;s disease. </em>In: Special Issue &ldquo;Crosstalk between the nervous and the immune system in health and in sicknes&rdquo;. Curr Pharm Des. <strong>2014</strong>;20(29):4723-32.</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830910/public/\" target=\"_blank\">Ver m&aacute;s publicaciones de L. Gim&eacute;nez-Llort en PubMed.</a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n',29,2,1),(453,52,0,'Jesús Giraldo','<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\">Laboratorio de Farmacolog&iacute;a de Sistemas y Bioinform&aacute;tica</span></h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong>L&iacute;der del Grupo:</strong></p>\n<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				Jes&uacute;s Giraldo Arjonilla</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:Jesus.Giraldo@uab.cat\">Jesus.Giraldo@uab.cat</a></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				TEL: +34 935 813 813</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<table>\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0001-7082-4695\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"27\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/orcid.png\" width=\"27\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researcherid.com/rid/F-9881-2011\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/RID.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<p>\n									<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=7003797712\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 29px; height: 29px;\" /></a></p>\n							</td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researchgate.net/profile/Jesus_Giraldo\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/researchgate.jpg\" style=\"width: 27px; height: 27px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/DSC00222.JPG\" style=\"width: 100%;\" /><br />\n	<br />\n	</strong></span><strong>Miembros del Grupo:</strong><br />\n	James Dalton,PhD<br />\n	David Roche, PhD</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>Estudiantes de Doctorado:</strong><br />\n	Agust&iacute;n Bruzzese<br />\n	Martha Iv&oacute;n C&aacute;rdenas<br />\n	Joan Font<br />\n	Xavier G&oacute;mez<br />\n	Isaias Lans<br />\n	Juan Serra<br />\n	Bin Zhou</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>OBJETIVOS ESTRAT&Eacute;GICOS</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	El Laboratorio de Farmacolog&iacute;a de Sistemas y Bioinform&aacute;tica es un grupo interdisciplinario compuesto de qu&iacute;micos, bi&oacute;logos y matem&aacute;ticos. Nuestro objetivo principal es investigar mediante m&eacute;todos computacionales los mecanismos responsables de las respuestas biol&oacute;gicas para obtener conocimientos novedosos que puedan tener un impacto terap&eacute;utico. Con esta finalidad, hemos seleccionado la superfamilia de los receptores acoplados a las prote&iacute;nas G (GPCRs) como &aacute;rea principal de nuestra investigaci&oacute;n. Los GPCRs est&aacute;n implicados en numerosos procesos fisiol&oacute;gicos y enfermedades y, por ello, son una de las principales dianas de la investigaci&oacute;n farmac&eacute;utica actual. En nuestro grupo seguimos una <strong>aproximaci&oacute;n integradora que incluye modelos y simulaciones moleculares y matem&aacute;ticas</strong> a varias escalas de complejidad. Esta investigaci&oacute;n se realiza en colaboraci&oacute;n con experimentales (Drs. J Ortiz, J Sabri&agrave; y C Gil) dentro de nuestro grupo SGR: <a href=\"index.php#!/Jesús Giraldo- Laboratorio de Neurofarmacología molecular y Bioinformatica_387_1 \"><em>the Laboratory of Molecular Neuropharmacology and Bioinformatics.</em></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PRINCIPALES L&Iacute;NEAS DE INVESTIGACI&Oacute;N</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	1. <strong>Modelizaci&oacute;n molecular y simulaciones de din&aacute;mica molecular de GPCRs. </strong>Nuestro objetivo es alcanzar un mayor conocimiento de los mecanismos moleculares asociados a la complejidad de la estructura y funci&oacute;n de los receptores, en particular <strong>homo-</strong> y <strong>heterodimerizaci&oacute;n de los receptores, modulaci&oacute;n alost&eacute;rica, actividad constitutiva de los receptores y selectividad funcional</strong>. En particular, focalizamos nuestra atenci&oacute;n en los <strong>receptores metabotr&oacute;picos de glutamato</strong>, los cuales pertenecen a la clase C de los GPCRs, sus interacciones heterom&eacute;ricas con los GPCRs de la clase A y su propuesta implicaci&oacute;n en diversas enfermedades neurol&oacute;gicas incluyendo <strong>dolor cr&oacute;nico, esquizofrenia y depresi&oacute;n</strong>. Creemos que es de especial relevancia el hecho de que esta investigaci&oacute;n tambi&eacute;n incluye el control de la actividad de los receptores mediante <strong>compuestos foroconmutables</strong>. Asimismo empleamos las t&eacute;cnicas <em>in silico</em> m&aacute;s actuales como <strong>modelizaci&oacute;n de los receptores por homolog&iacute;a,</strong> <strong><em>induced-fit docking</em>, interacciones prote&iacute;na-prote&iacute;na </strong>y<strong> simulaciones de din&aacute;mica molecular.</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	2. <strong>Modelizaci&oacute;n matem&aacute;tica de los GPCRs. </strong>Esta l&iacute;nea de investigaci&oacute;n se lleva a cabo en paralelo con nuestra investigaci&oacute;n molecular, de manera que son complementan entre s&iacute;.&nbsp; Nuestro objetivo es construir modelos matem&aacute;ticos que incluyan en sus expresiones los temas m&aacute;s actuales sobre farmacolog&iacute;a de receptores, tales como <strong>agonismo inverso, superagonismo, modulaci&oacute;n alost&eacute;rica y oligomerizaci&oacute;n de receptores</strong>. Estamos desarrollando modelos matem&aacute;ticos en el marco del <strong>modelo operacional de agonismo y alosterismo</strong> (v&eacute;ase Roche et al. Br J Pharmacol. 2013;169(6):1189-202) con una atenci&oacute;n especial en los aspectos mecan&iacute;sticos de la acci&oacute;n de los f&aacute;rmacos.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	3. <strong>Ciencia computacional, bioinform&aacute;tica y bioestad&iacute;stica.</strong>Nuestro objetivo es la construcci&oacute;n de nuevas aplicaciones bioinform&aacute;ticas para un an&aacute;lisis m&aacute;s riguroso y eficiente de los datos. Hemos desarrollado un <strong>algoritmo de optimizaci&oacute;n evolutiva</strong>, que puede obtener los valores estimados de ecuaciones con muchos par&aacute;metros y m&iacute;nimos locales (t&iacute;picos de las condiciones farmacol&oacute;gicas complejas). Colaboramos con especialistas en inteligencia artificial (Alfredo Vellido y Ren&eacute; Alqu&eacute;zar, UPC) en el an&aacute;lisis sistem&aacute;tico de la clasificaci&oacute;n de los GPCRs mediante m&eacute;todos de <strong><em>machine learning</em></strong>. Asimismo, somos tambi&eacute;n activos <strong><em>data mining</em></strong> y <strong><em>big data</em> </strong>en biolog&iacute;a y farmacolog&iacute;a.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PROYECTOS ACTUALES</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	<strong>T&iacute;tulo del Proyecto:</strong> Integrated mathematical, computational and biochemical investigation of the crosstalk between metabotropic glutamate receptor 5 and dopamine D2 receptor: Relevance for the treatment of schizophrenia<br />\n	<strong>Entidad Financiadora:</strong> Ministerio de Econom&iacute;a y Competitividad (REF. SAF2014-58396-R)<br />\n	<strong>Entidades participantes:</strong> Universitat Aut&ograve;noma de Barcelona.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>T&iacute;tulo del Proyecto</strong>: Deciphering the role of peripheral and central nervous system metabotropic glutamate receptors in neuropathic pain with photoactivable ligands<br />\n	<strong>Entidad Financiadora:</strong>ERA-NET NEURON Call for transnational research projects 2012 (REF. PCIN-2013-018-C03-02)<br />\n	<strong>Entidades participantes: </strong>El proyecto coordinado incluye 5 subproyectos cuyos Investigadores Principales son: Amadeu Llebaria, SP1 (Institut de Qu&iacute;mica Avan&ccedil;ada de Catalunya (IQAC-CSIC), Barcelona); Jes&uacute;s Giraldo, SP2 (Universitat Aut&ograve;noma de Barcelona (UAB), Barcelona); Francisco Ciruela, SP3 (Universitat de Barcelona (UB), Barcelona); Ferdinando Nicoletti, SP4 (IRCCS Neuromed, University La Sapienza, Rome) y Jean-Philippe Pin, SP5 (Institut de G&eacute;nomique Fonctionnelle (IGF), CNRS, Universit&eacute; de Montpellier, INSERM, Montpellier)</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>COLABORACIONES</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	Actualmente estamos colaborando con los siguientes investigadores:</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>Jean-Philippe Pin and Cyril Goudet</strong>. Institut de G&eacute;nomique Fonctionnelle, CNRS UMR 5203, Universit&eacute; de Montpellier, Montpellier, France; INSERM, U661, Montpellier, France.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>Michael Conn</strong>. Department of Internal Medicine, Center for Membrane Protein Research, Texas Tech University Health Sciences Center, Lubbock, TX, USA; Department of Cell Biology/Biochemistry, Center for Membrane Protein Research, Texas Tech University Health Sciences Center, Lubbock, TX, USA.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>Katja Schmitz</strong>. Technische Universit&auml;t Darmstadt, Clemens-Sch&ouml;pf-Institut, Alarich-Weiss-Stra&szlig;e 4, 64287 Darmstadt, Germany.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>Nuska Tschammer.</strong> Department of&nbsp; Chemistry and Pharmacy, Medicinal Chemistry,&nbsp; Emil Fischer Center, Friedrich Alexander University Schuhstra&szlig;e 19, 91052 Erlangen, Germany.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>Amadeu Llebaria</strong>. Department of Biomedicinal Chemistry, Institut de Qu&iacute;mica Avan&ccedil;ada de Catalunya (IQAC-CSIC), Jordi Girona 18-26, 08034 Barcelona, Spain.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>Pau Gorostiza</strong>. Institute for Bioengineering of Catalonia (IBEC), Baldiri Reixac 15-21, Barcelona 08028, Spain.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>Francisco Ciruela</strong>. Unitat de Farmacologia, Departament Patologia i Terap&egrave;utica Experimental, Facultat de Medicina, IDIBELL-Universitat de Barcelona, Barcelona, Spain.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>Alfons Macaya</strong>. Grup de Recerca en Neurologia Pedi&agrave;trica, Institut de Recerca Vall d&#39;Hebron, Universitat Aut&ograve;noma de Barcelona, Barcelona, Spain.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<br />\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PUBLICACIONES SELECCIONADAS</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp; Giraldo J.<br />\n	<em>Operational models of allosteric modulation: caution is needed.</em><br />\n	Trends in Pharmacological Sciences <strong>2015</strong>;36(1):1-2</p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp; Rovira X, Malhaire F, Scholler P, Rodrigo J, Gonzalez-Bulnes P, Llebaria A, Pin JP, Giraldo J, Goudet C<br />\n	<em>Overlapping binding sites drive allosteric agonism and positive cooperativity in type 4 metabotropic glutamate receptors</em><br />\n	The FASEB Journal <strong>2015</strong>;29(1):116-30</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp; Lans I, Dalton JA, Giraldo J<br />\n	<em>Helix 3 acts as a conformational hinge in Class A GPCR activation: An analysis of interhelical interaction energies in crystal structures.</em><br />\n	Journal of Structural Biology <strong>2015</strong>. pii: S1047-8477(15)30096-4.<em> </em></p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pittolo S, G&oacute;mez-Santacana X, Eckelt K, Rovira X, Dalton J, Goudet C, Pin J-P, Llobet A, Giraldo J, Llebaria A, Gorostiza P<br />\n	<em>An allosteric modulator to control endogenous G protein-coupled receptors with light</em><br />\n	Nature Chemical Biology <strong>2014</strong>;10(10):813-5</p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Dalton JA, G&oacute;mez-Santacana X, Llebaria A, Giraldo J.<br />\n	<em>Computational Analysis of Negative and Positive Allosteric Modulator Binding and Function in Metabotropic Glutamate Receptor 5 (In)Activation.</em><br />\n	J Chem Inf Model. <strong>2014</strong></p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; Roche D, Gil D, and Giraldo J<br />\n	<em>Multiple active receptor conformation, agonist efficacy and maximum effect of the system: The conformation-based operational model of agonism</em><br />\n	Drug Discovery Today <strong>2013</strong>;18:365-371<br />\n	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830921/public/\" target=\"_blank\">Ver m&aacute;s publicaciones de J. Giraldo en PubMed. </a></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n',30,2,1),(454,52,0,'Gemma Guillazo','<p>\n	<a href=\"javascript:MostraPage(379,1);\">Neurobiolog&iacute;a de la mente normal y alterada</a></p>\n<h2>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\">Neurobiolog&iacute;a del Aprendizaje y la Memoria</span></h2>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong>L&iacute;der del Grupo:</strong></p>\n<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				Gemma Guillazo-Blanch</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:Gemma.Guillazo@uab.cat\">Gemma.Guillazo@uab.cat</a></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				Tel:93 5812543</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<table>\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0002-8297-7100\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/orcid.png\" style=\"width: 26px; height: 26px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researcherid.com/rid/E-9765-2011\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/RID.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<p>\n									<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=6602654496\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 29px; height: 29px;\" /></a></p>\n							</td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researchgate.net/profile/Gemma_Guillazo-Blanch\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"29\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/researchgate.jpg\" width=\"29\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.mendeley.com/profiles/gemma-guillazo/\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"29\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/mendeley.png\" width=\"29\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"https://es.linkedin.com/pub/gemma-guillazo-blanch/17/492/b85\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"31\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Linkedin.jpg\" width=\"39\" /></a></td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/gemma guill.jpg\" style=\"width: 450px; height: 285px;\" /></p>\n<div>\n	&nbsp;</div>\n<div>\n	<strong>Miembros del grupo:</strong></div>\n<div>\n	<a href=\"http://inc.uab.cat/Catala/profile.php?id=91\">Margarita Mart&iacute;-Nicolovius</a></div>\n<div>\n	Divka Rojic&nbsp;&nbsp;Becker</div>\n<div>\n	Anna Vale Mart&iacute;nez</div>\n<div>\n	Joan Visa Bombardo</div>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>OBJETIVOS ESTRAT&Eacute;GICOS</strong></span><br />\n	<br />\n	Nuestro proyecto pretende investigar diferentes tratamientos cerebrales que podr&iacute;an potenciar fundamentalmente procesos de atenci&oacute;n y memoria en modelos animales de d&eacute;ficit cognitivo derivado del envejecimiento y de lesiones o inactivaciones cerebrales que remedan algunas alteraciones observadas en determinadas enfermedades neurodegenerativas, como la de Alzheimer o Parkinson, o s&iacute;ndromes cl&iacute;nicos, como la amnesia diencef&aacute;lica. Para ello usamos modelos de d&eacute;ficit cognitivo en ratas viejas y tambi&eacute;n en ratas j&oacute;venes con infusiones de antagonistas colin&eacute;rgicos o glutamat&eacute;rgicos en estructuras diana del prosenc&eacute;falo basal (PB) o con lesiones o inactivaciones reversibles de los n&uacute;cleos tal&aacute;micos intralaminares (ILN). El principal objetivo es revertir el deterioro cognitivo mediante la infusi&oacute;n intracerebral, en regiones de proyecci&oacute;n del PB y de los ILN,&nbsp; de compuestos que actualmente se est&aacute;n valorando como posibles potenciadores cognitivos: d-cicloserina o S18986 (potenciadores glutamat&eacute;rgicos) o FG7142 (inhibidor gaba&eacute;rgico). La eficacia de estos tratamientos&nbsp; se valora en modelos conductuales basados en tareas olfatorias de relevancia etol&oacute;gica y cl&iacute;nica, y tambi&eacute;n en paradigmas de condicionamiento instrumental que nos permitan evaluar procesos de atenci&oacute;n, memoria de trabajo y flexibilidad cognitiva. Adem&aacute;s del avance en el desarrollo de posibles tratamientos dirigidos a mejorar ciertas funciones cognitivas, la consecuci&oacute;n de los objetivos propuestos permitir&aacute; dilucidar las bases neurofisiol&oacute;gicas de los efectos de dichos tratamientos. Esta informaci&oacute;n es relevante para conocer posibles dianas cerebrales o mecanismos neuroqu&iacute;micos sobre los que puedan actuar nuevos m&eacute;todos terap&eacute;uticos efectivos para potenciar la atenci&oacute;n, la memoria o la flexibilidad conductual, entre otras funciones cognitivas.<br />\n	<br />\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PRINCIPALES L&Iacute;NEAS DE INVESTIGACI&Oacute;N</strong></span><br />\n	<br />\n	Nuestro proyecto principal &ldquo;Potenciaci&oacute;n de la atenci&oacute;n y de la memoria en modelos animales de d&eacute;ficit cognitivo por envejecimiento y lesi&oacute;n cerebral&rdquo;&nbsp; incluye diferentes l&iacute;neas de trabajo con los objetivos siguientes:<br />\n	1) Investigar la capacidad de moduladores glutamat&eacute;rgicos de revertir d&eacute;ficits cognitivos en animales j&oacute;venes con lesi&oacute;n o inactivaci&oacute;n de estructuras clave en ciertas patolog&iacute;as neurodegenerativas.<br />\n	2) Investigar la capacidad de moduladores glutamat&eacute;rgicos y gaba&eacute;rgicos de revertir d&eacute;ficits cognitivos en animales viejos con alteraciones funcionales asociadas al proceso normal de envejecimiento.<br />\n	3) Estudiar los mecanismos neurofisiol&oacute;gicos subyacentes a los tratamientos de potenciaci&oacute;n de las funciones cognitivas.<br />\n	<br />\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>T&Eacute;CNICAS</strong></span><br />\n	<br />\n	Las cuestiones planteadas en el apartado anterior se investigan a trav&eacute;s de t&eacute;cnicas de inmunohistoqu&iacute;mica para la expresi&oacute;n de c-fos, estimulaci&oacute;n el&eacute;ctrica intracerebral, lesiones neuroqu&iacute;micas, infusiones intracerebrales, autorradiograf&iacute;a de receptores e hibridaci&oacute;n in situ. Las tareas conductuales utilizadas son, entre otras, la transmisi&oacute;n social de preferencias alimentarias, la discriminaci&oacute;n simple de olores, el laberinto acu&aacute;tico de Morris, la&nbsp; atenci&oacute;n visual y la memoria de trabajo en la jaula de Skinner.<br />\n	<br />\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\">Colaboraciones:</span><br />\n	-Laboratorio de Psicobiolog&iacute;a, UNED, Madrid (Emilio Ambrosio, Miguel Migu&eacute;ns)<br />\n	-Divisi&oacute;n de Neurociencias, Universidad Pablo de Olavide (UPO),&nbsp;Sevilla (Dr. Delgado-Garc&iacute;a, Dra.&nbsp;Gruart)<br />\n	-IDIBAPS (Barcelona) (Dra. S&aacute;nchez-Vives)</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>&Uacute;LTIMAS PUBLICACIONES</strong></span></p>\n<br />\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp; Portero-Tresserra M, Crist&oacute;bal-Narv&aacute;ez P, Mart&iacute;-Nicolovius M, Guillazo-Blanch , G, Vale-Mart&iacute;nez A. <em>D-cycloserine in prelimbic cortex reverses scopolamine-induced deficits in olfactory memory in rats. </em>PLoS One. <strong>2013</strong>, 2;8(8):e70584.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;Yefimenko N, Portero-Tresserra M, Mart&iacute;-Nicolovius M, Guillazo-Blanch G, Vale-Mart&iacute;nez A.&nbsp;(2013). <em>The AMPA receptor modulator S18986 in the prelimbic cortex enhances acquisition and retention of an odor-reward association. </em>Neurosci Lett.&nbsp;<strong>2013</strong> pii: S0304-3940(13)00467-9.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;Villarejo-Rodr&iacute;guez I, Boadas-Vaello P, Portero-Tresserra M, Vale-Mart&iacute;nez A, Mart&iacute;-Nicolovius M, Guillazo-Blanch G.<em> Learning deficits in an odor reward-task induced by parafascicular thalamic lesions are ameliorated by pretraining D-cycloserine in the prelimbic cortex. </em>Behav Brain Res.&nbsp;<strong>2013</strong> ;238:289-92.&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;Portero-Tresserra M, Mart&iacute;-Nicolovius M, Guillazo-Blanch G, Boadas-Vaello P, Vale-Mart&iacute;nez A.<em> D-cycloserine in the basolateral amygdala prevents extinction and enhances reconsolidation of odor-reward associative learning in rats.</em> Neurobiol Learn Mem.&nbsp;<strong>2013</strong>;100:1-11.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp; Portero-Tresserra M, Crist&oacute;bal-Narv&aacute;ez P, Mart&iacute;-Nicolovius M, Guillazo-Blanch G, Vale-Mart&iacute;nez A. D-cycloserine in prelimbic cortex reverses scopolamine-induced deficits in olfactory memory in rats. PLoS One. <strong>2013</strong>; 8(8):e70584. PMCID: PMC3732227</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830176/public/\" target=\"_blank\">Ver m&aacute;s publicaciones de G. Guillazo en PubMed. </a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n',31,2,1),(455,52,0,'Juan Hidalgo','<p>\n	<a href=\"javascript:MostraPage(377,1); \">Neurodegeneraci&oacute;n y envejecimiento</a></p>\n<h2>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\">Neuroinflamaci&oacute;n y Estr&eacute;s Oxidativo</span></h2>\n<p>\n	<strong>L&iacute;der del Grupo:</strong></p>\n<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				Juan Hidalgo Pareja</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:Juan.Hidalgo@uab.cat\">Juan.Hidalgo@uab.cat</a></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				TEL: +34 935 812 037</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<table>\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-0921-1122\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/orcid.png\" style=\"width: 26px; height: 26px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researcherid.com/rid/C-9082-2011\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/RID.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<p>\n									<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=7101787664\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 29px; height: 29px;\" /></a></p>\n							</td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researchgate.net/profile/Juan_Hidalgo5\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"27\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/researchgate.jpg\" width=\"27\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/JHidalgoFotogrupo.jpg\" style=\"width: 100%; margin-top: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px;\" /><br />\n	<strong>Miembros del Grupo:</strong><br />\n	Gemma Comes Orpinell<br />\n	Merc&egrave; Giralt Carbonell<br />\n	Amalia Molinero Egea<br />\n	Olaya Fern&aacute;ndez Gayol<br />\n	<br />\n	<strong>Miembros anteriores:</strong><br />\n	Mar&iacute;a Erta Caba&ntilde;ate<br />\n	Beatriz Ferrer Villahoz<br />\n	Javier Carrasco Trancoso<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>OBJETIVOS ESTRAT&Eacute;GICOS</strong></span><br />\n	<br />\n	Los objetivos fundamentales del grupo se centran en el estudio de los mecanismos b&aacute;sicos de la neuroinflamaci&oacute;n y estr&eacute;s oxidativo, con un particular &eacute;nfasis en el papel de la interleucina 6 (IL-6) en modelos animales de enfermedades neurodegenerativas como el Alzheimer y la Esclerosis M&uacute;ltiple (EM) y en modelos de lesiones traum&aacute;ticas cerebrales.<br />\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"> </span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PRINCIPALES L&Iacute;NEAS DE INVESTIGACI&Oacute;N</strong></span><br />\n	<br />\n	1. Las lesiones traum&aacute;ticas cerebrales (TBI) son una de las principales causas de muerte e incapacidad, especialmente entre la gente joven. Citocinas como la IL-6 y el TNF&alpha; est&aacute;n implicadas en la respuesta del SNC al da&ntilde;o cerebral; mediante el uso de ratones KO condicionales producidos en nuestro laboratorio, analizaremos la importancia de las fuentes celulares de IL-6 en un modelo de TBI. Adem&aacute;s, usando ratones KO condicionales para el receptor de la IL-6 tambi&eacute;n determinaremos la importancia de la respuesta celular espec&iacute;fica a la IL-6. En este momento nos estamos centrando en la principal c&eacute;lula glial, el astrocito.<br />\n	2. Modelos de Alzheimer. Uno de los modelos de Alzheimer m&aacute;s usado es el rat&oacute;n APP2576; la importancia del estr&eacute;s oxidativo en este modelo se est&aacute; evaluando analizando el fenotipo de ratones APP cruzados con ratones con niveles alterados de la prote&iacute;na antioxidante metalotione&iacute;na.<br />\n	3. Modelos de Esclerosis M&uacute;ltiple. Existen varios modelos de EM, siendo la Encefalitis Autoinmune Experimental (EAE) uno de los m&aacute;s utilizados. En un futuro inmediato analizaremos la importancia de la IL-6 en este modelo.<br />\n	4. Ejercicio y obesidad. Importancia de la IL-6 en la respuesta al ejercicio y a la obesidad inducida por dietas grasas.<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong> </strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>&Uacute;LTIMAS PUBLICACIONES </strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull; Giralt M, Ramos R, Quintana A, Ferrer B, Erta M, Castro-Freire M, Comes G, Sanz E, Unzeta M, Pifarr&eacute; P, Garc&iacute;a A, Campbell IL, <strong>Hidalgo J</strong>. Induction of atypical EAE mediated by transgenic production of IL-6 in astrocytes in the absence of systemic IL-6. Glia 61 (<strong>2013</strong>) 587-600.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>&bull; </strong>Pifarr&eacute; P, Gutierrez-Mecinas M, Prado J, Usero L, Roura-Mir C, Giralt M, <strong>Hidalgo J</strong>, Garc&iacute;a A. Phosphodiesterase 5 inhibition at disease onset prevents experimental autoimmune encephalomyelitis progression through immunoregulatory and neuroprotective actions. Exp. Neurol. 251 (<strong>2014</strong>) 58-71.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>&bull; </strong>Campbell IL, Erta M, Lim SL, Frausto R, May U, Rose-John S, Scheller J, <strong>Hidalgo J</strong>. Trans-signaling is a dominant mechanism for the pathogenic actions of interleukin-6 in the brain. J. Neurosci. 34 (<strong>2014</strong>) 2503-2513.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp; Ferrer B, Navia B, Giralt M, Comes G, Carrasco J, Molinero A, Quintana A, Se&ntilde;ar&iacute;s R, <strong>Hidalgo J.</strong> Muscle-specific interleukin-6 deletion influences body weight and body fat in a sex-dependent manner. Brain, Behav. Immun. 40 (<strong>2014</strong>) 121-130.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp; Manso Y, Comes G, L&oacute;pez-Ramos JC, Belfiore M, Molinero A, Giralt M, Carrasco J, Adlard PA, Bush AI, Delgado-Garc&iacute;a JM, <strong>Hidalgo J</strong>. Overexpression of metallothionein-1 modulates the phenotype of the Tg2576 mouse model of Alzheimer&rsquo;s disease. J. Alzheimer&rsquo;s Dis. 51 (<strong>2016</strong>) 81-95.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830937/public/\" target=\"_blank\">Ver m&aacute;s publicaiones de J. Hidalgo en PubMed.</a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n',32,2,1),(456,52,0,'Marcel Jiménez','<p>\n	<a href=\"javascript:MostraPage(377,1); \">Neurodegeneraci&oacute;n y envejecimiento</a></p>\n<h2>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\">Neurogastroenterolog&iacute;a</span></h2>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong>L&iacute;der del Grupo:</strong></p>\n<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				Marcel &nbsp;Jim&eacute;nez Farrerons</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:Marcel.Jimenez@uab.cat\">Marcel.Jimenez@uab.cat</a></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				TEL: +34 935 811 566</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<table>\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0002-6602-7332\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"28\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/orcid.png\" width=\"28\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://:%20http://www.researcherid.com/rid/C-6995-2008\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/RID.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<p>\n									<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=35551030000\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 29px; height: 29px;\" /></a></p>\n							</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/Marcdef.jpg\" style=\"width: 100%; margin-top: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px;\" /></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>Miembros del Grupo:</strong><br />\n	M&ordf; Teresa Mart&iacute;n Ib&aacute;&ntilde;ez</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>OBJETIVOS ESTRAT&Eacute;GICOS</strong></span><br />\n	<br />\n	El objetivo de nuestra investigaci&oacute;n se centra en el estudio de la motilidad gastrointestinal en condiciones fisiol&oacute;gicas y en varios estados patol&oacute;gicos. Nuestros estudios se realizan en tejidos humanos y en modelos animales de enfermedad. Nuestra linea de trabajo principal se basa en el estudio de Neurogastroenterolog&iacute;a desde diferentes puntos de vista incluyendo la neurotransmisi&oacute;n en el sistema nervioso ent&eacute;rico, la actividad de marcapasos y la relaci&oacute;n entre el sistema inmune y el sistema nervioso ent&eacute;rico.<br />\n	<br />\n	<strong> </strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong><span style=\"color:#800000;\">PRINCIPALES L&Iacute;NEAS DE INVESTIGACI&Oacute;N</span></strong><br />\n	<br />\n	&bull; Motilidad gastrointestinal: Estudio de la motilidad gastrointestinal y su regulaci&oacute;n hormonal y nervioso. Estudios farmacol&oacute;gicos.<br />\n	&bull; Neurogastroenterolog&iacute;a: la funci&oacute;n de marcapasos, relaci&oacute;n entre las neuronas motoras y el m&uacute;sculo liso. Las c&eacute;lulas intersticiales de Cajal (ICC).<br />\n	&bull; Neurotransmisores gaseosos. Papel del NO y el sulfh&iacute;drico en la regulaci&oacute;n de la motilidad gastrointestinal en el tejido normal como inflamado. Mecanismo de acci&oacute;n. Papel de Los inhibidores de la s&iacute;ntesis de NO y H2S.<br />\n	&bull; El s&iacute;ndrome del intestino irritable (SII). Desarrollo de modelos animales para estudiar la alteraci&oacute;n de la motilidad gastrointestinal en el SII. Enfoque farmacol&oacute;gico del tratamiento del SII.<br />\n	&bull; La enfermedad inflamatoria intestinal: desarrollo de modelos animales para estudiar la alteraci&oacute;n de la motilidad gastrointestinal en la inflamaci&oacute;n intestinal. Farmacol&oacute;gica enfoque del tratamiento de patrones motores alterados durante la inflamaci&oacute;n intestinal.<br />\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong> </strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PUBLICACIONES</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp; Gallego D, Gil V, Martinez-Cutillas M, Mane N, Martin MT, Jimenez M. <em>Purinergic neuromuscular transmission is absent in the colon of P2Y(1) knocked out mice.</em><br />\n	J Physiol <strong>2012</strong>;590(Pt 8):1943-1956.</p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp; Lies B, Gil V, Groneberg D, Seidler B, Saur D, Wischmeyer E, Jimenez M, Friebe A.<br />\n	<em>Interstitial cells of Cajal mediate nitrergic inhibitory neurotransmission in the murine gastrointestinal tract. </em><br />\n	Am J Physiol Gastrointest Liver Physiol <strong>2014</strong>;307(1):G98-106.</p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp; Mane N, Gil V, Martinez-Cutillas M, Martin MT, Gallego D, Jimenez M. <em>Dynamics of inhibitory co-transmission, membrane potential and pacemaker activity determine neuromyogenic function in the rat colon. </em>Pflugers Arch <strong>2014</strong>.</p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp; Mane N, Gil V, Martinez-Cutillas M, Clav&eacute; P, Gallego D, Jimenez M. <em>Differential functional role of purinergic and nitrergic inhibitory cotransmitters in human colonic relaxation.</em><br />\n	Acta Physiologica (Oxf) <strong>2014</strong> Dec;212(4):293-305.</p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp; Jim&eacute;nez M, Clav&eacute; P, Accarino A, Gallego D.<br />\n	<em>Purinergic neuromuscular transmission in the gastrointestinal tract; functional basis for future clinical and pharmacological studies</em>. &nbsp;<br />\n	Br J Pharmacol. <strong>2014</strong> Oct;171(19):4360-75</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830944/public/\" target=\"_blank\">Ver m&aacute;s publicaciones de M. Jimenez en PubMed.</a></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n',33,2,1),(457,52,0,'José M. Lizcano y Néstor Gómez','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<a href=\"javascript:MostraPage(377,1); \">Neurodegeneraci&oacute;n y envejecimiento</a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\">Prote&iacute;nas Quinasas y Transducci&oacute;n de Se&ntilde;ales</span></h2>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong>L&iacute;deres del Grupo:</strong></p>\n<table style=\"width: 100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				Jose Miguel Lizcano&nbsp;&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>\n				N&eacute;stor Gomez</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:josemiguel.lizcano@uab.cat\">josemiguel.lizcano@uab.cat </a></td>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"http://nestor.gomez@uab.cat\">Nestor.gomez@uab.cat</a></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				TEL: +34 935 813 076&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>\n				TEL: +34 935 813 076</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<table align=\"left\">\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0002-3154-5383\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/orcid.png\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researcherid.com/rid/E-6080-2010\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/RID.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=55226571500\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researchgate.net/profile/Jose_Lizcano?ev=prf_highl\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/researchgate.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/profile/view?trk=tab_pro&amp;id=106361868\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Linkedin.jpg\" style=\"width: 31px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n				<table>\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=7102745796\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	<span id=\"cke_bm_222S\" style=\"display: none;\">&nbsp;</span><span id=\"cke_bm_223S\" style=\"display: none;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p>\n	<strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Imagen_grupo_con_logos_para_Web_INC.jpg\" style=\"width: 450px; height: 394px;\" /></strong></p>\n<div>\n	<strong>Miembros del grupo:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><br />\n	Dra. Tatiana Erazo&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\n	Pau Mu&ntilde;oz Guardiola&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</div>\n<div>\n	Nora Di&eacute;guez&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</div>\n<div>\n	Rub&eacute;n Melgarejo &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</div>\n<div>\n	Elisabet Meg&iacute;as</div>\n<div>\n	Valeria Rizzuto</div>\n<div>\n	&nbsp;</div>\n<div>\n	<strong>Miembros pasados:</strong><br />\n	Dra. Ana Moreno Iglesias<br />\n	Dra. Margarita Espona</div>\n<div>\n	Dra. Arantza Rodr&iacute;guez Asia&iacute;n</div>\n<div>\n	Dr. Gerad Ruiz Babot</div>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>OBJETIVOS ESTRAT&Eacute;GICOS</strong></span><span id=\"cke_bm_223E\" style=\"display: none;\">&nbsp;</span><span id=\"cke_bm_222E\" style=\"display: none;\">&nbsp;</span><br />\n	<br />\n	<em> </em></p>\n<p>\n	<em>Prote&iacute;nas quinasas </em></p>\n<p>\n	<em>Casi todos los aspectos de la vida celular est&aacute;n controlados por la fosforilaci&oacute;n reversible de prote&iacute;nas. Por lo tanto, la comprensi&oacute;n del control molecular de la fisiolog&iacute;a celular requiere la identificaci&oacute;n de los sustratos espec&iacute;ficos de las prote&iacute;nas quinasas. Numerosos estudios han identificado alteraciones en genes que codifican para quinasas y que causan enfermedades, como el c&aacute;ncer o las enfermedades neurodegenerativas. Nuestra investigaci&oacute;n se centra en analizar nuevas v&iacute;as de se&ntilde;alizaci&oacute;n celular que controlen la proliferaci&oacute;n y diferenciaci&oacute;n de las c&eacute;lulas cancerosas. Estudiamos las nuevas prote&iacute;nas quinasas </em>ERK5 (una Map quinasa) y la supressora de tumores LKB1, per&ograve; tambi&eacute;n estamos interesados en la v&iacute;a de la Akt-mTORC1. Colaboramos con compa&ntilde;&iacute;as farmac&eacute;uticas en el desarrollo precl&iacute;nico de nuevos medicament&oacute;s antitumorales.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PRINCIPALES L&Iacute;NEAS DE INVESTIGACI&Oacute;N</strong></span><br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	Usaremos dos perspectives diferentes para abordar problemes fundamentales:</p>\n<p style=\"margin-left:36.0pt;\">\n	<em>1)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </em><em>Investigaci&oacute;n b&aacute;sica</em></p>\n<p style=\"margin-left:36.0pt;\">\n	An&aacute;lisis de los mecanismos por los que las quinasasLKB1, Akt i ERK5ejercen un control en la proliferaci&oacute;n y la supervivencia de las c&eacute;lulas tumorales. Hemos contribuido a proponer un nuevo mecanismo molecular para la regulaci&oacute;n de la prote&iacute;na quinasa Akt; a descubrir que la quinasa supresora de tumores LKB1 funciona como m&aacute;sterquinasa; o, m&aacute;s recientemente, que hemos establecido un nuevo mecanismo por el que ERK5 transloca al n&uacute;cleo, donde regula la proliferaci&oacute;n de c&eacute;lulas tumorales, a pesar de su actividad enzim&aacute;tica.</p>\n<p style=\"margin-left:36.0pt;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"margin-left:36.0pt;\">\n	2)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em>Investigaci&oacute;n dirigida a la intervenci&oacute;n farmacol&oacute;gica en c&aacute;ncer</em><br />\n	Estamos implicados en potenciar los aspectos translacionales de nuestros recursos. Colaboramos activamente con Abilty Pharmaceuticals SL en el desarrollo precl&iacute;nico/cl&iacute;nico de un nuevo medicamento antitumoral ABTL0812, que acaba de finalizar la fase de ensayos cl&iacute;nicos I/Ib, primero en humanos (NCT02201823) en pacientes de c&aacute;ncer con tumores s&oacute;lidos. Hemos descubierto una nueva v&iacute;a de se&ntilde;alizaci&oacute;n celular en la que ABTL0812 ejerce su acci&oacute;n antitumoral: ABTL0812 activa la transcripci&oacute;n mediada por PPARa/g de la pseudoquinasa TRIB-3, que, a su vez, se une i inhibe Akt, provocando la inhibici&oacute;n de mTORC1, el freno del crecimiento y la muerte de las c&eacute;lulas cancerosas por autofagia mediada. Finalmente, hemos colaborado en activamente con otros laboratorios acad&eacute;micos caracterizando nuevos inhibidores de la ERK5 que muestran actividad antitumoral.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<br />\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PUBLICACIONES SELECCIONADAS</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp; Erazo T, Lorente M, L&oacute;pez-Plana A, Mu&ntilde;oz-Guardiola P&hellip;, Lizcano JM.<em> The New Antitumor Drug ABTL0812 Inhibits the Akt/mTORC1 Axis by Upregulating Tribbles-3 Pseudokinase. </em>Clinical Cancer Research 2015 Dec 15. [Epub ahead of print]. <strong>2016&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp; Erazo T, Moreno A, Ruiz-Babot G, Rodr&iacute;guez-Asiain A, Morrice NA, Espadamala J, Bayascas JR, G&oacute;mez N, Lizcano JM. <em>Canonical and kinase activity-independent mechanisms for extracellular signal-regulated kinase 5 (ERK5) nuclear translocation require dissociation of Hsp90 from the ERK5-Cdc37 complex. </em>Molecular&nbsp;and Cellular Biology&nbsp;33:1671-86. <strong>2013&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp; Elkins JM, Wang J, Deng X, Pattison MJ, Arthur JS, Erazo T, Gomez N, Lizcano JM, Gray NS, Knapp S. <em>X-ray crystal structure of ERK5 (MAPK7) in complex with a specific inhibitor. </em>Journal of Medicinal Chemistry&nbsp;56:4413-21. <strong>2013 </strong></p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp; Villagrasa P, D&iacute;az VM, Vi&ntilde;as-Castells R, Peir&oacute; S, Del Valle-P&eacute;rez B, Dave N, Rodr&iacute;guez-Asiain A, Casal JI, Lizcano JM, Du&ntilde;ach M, Garc&iacute;a de Herreros A. <em>Akt2 interacts with Snail1 in the E-cadherin promoter. </em>Oncogene 31:4022-33. <strong>2012</strong></p>\n<p>\n	<br />\n	&bull;&nbsp; Lizcano JM, Goransson O, Toth R, Deak M, Morrice NA, Boudeau J, Hawley SA, Udd L, Makela TP, Hardie DG, Alessi DR. <em>LKB1 is a master kinase that activates 13 kinases of the AMPK subfamily,including MARK/PAR1 </em>EMBO Journal 23: 833-43. <strong>2004</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830948/public/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Ver m&aacute;s publicaciones de JM. Lizcano a PubMed.</strong></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830954/public/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Ver m&aacute;s publicaciones de N. G&oacute;mez a PubMed.</strong></a></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong><span style=\"color:#800000;\">PROYECTOS ACTIVOS</span></strong></p>\n<div>\n	<em>Nuevas aproximaciones terap&eacute;uticas basadas en derivados de &aacute;cidos grasos esenciales dirigidos a enfermedades oncol&oacute;gicas y neurol&oacute;gicas no cubiertas.</em></div>\n<div>\n	Ministerio de Econom&iacute;a y Competitividad. Programa INNPACTO&nbsp; (Ref IPT-2012-0614-010000)</div>\n<div>\n	&nbsp;</div>\n<div>\n	<em>Desarrollo de nuevas herramientas farmacol&oacute;gicas antitumorales que dirijan su acci&oacute;n al silenciamiento o a la inhibici&oacute;n de la MAP kinasa ERK5. </em></div>\n<div>\n	Ministerio de Econom&iacute;a y Competitividad. Plan Nacional de I+D+I 2016-2018. Programa Biomedicina (Ref SAF2015-64237-R).</div>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n',34,2,1),(458,52,0,'José Manuel López','<p>\n	<a href=\"javascript:MostraPage(377,1); \">Neurodegeneraci&oacute;n y envejecimiento</a></p>\n<h2>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\">Prote&iacute;nas Quinasas de Estr&eacute;s</span></h2>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong>L&iacute;der del Grupo:</strong></p>\n<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				Jos&eacute; Manuel L&oacute;pez</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:josemanuel.lopez@uab.es\">josemanuel.lopez@uab.es</a></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				Tel: 935 814 278</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<table>\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n				<table>\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0002-4104-6262\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"28\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/orcid.png\" width=\"28\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researcherid.com/rid/D-1654-2011\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"28\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/RID.jpg\" width=\"28\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<p>\n									<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=55685078300&amp;amp;eid=2-s2.0-84865604296\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 29px; height: 29px;\" /></a></p>\n							</td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n				<table>\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/JMBladef.jpg\" style=\"width: 100%; margin-top: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px;\" /></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>Miembros del Grupo:</strong><br />\n	Nabil Ben Messaoud<br />\n	Jicheng Yue</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>OBJETIVOS ESTRAT&Eacute;GICOS</strong></span><br />\n	<br />\n	Actuando como sensores e interruptores las prote&iacute;nas quinasas tienen un papel cr&iacute;tico en la regulaci&oacute;n de las decisiones celulares. Nuestro grupo de investigaci&oacute;n esta interesado en el control de la apoptosis y la meiosis por prote&iacute;nas quinasas de estr&eacute;s y utilizamos los ovocitos de Xenopus como modelo celular para estudiar los mecanismos que gobiernan estos procesos biol&oacute;gicos irreversibles. Tambi&eacute;n queremos investigar c&oacute;mo la acumulaci&oacute;n de un nucle&oacute;tido (ZMP) y la activaci&oacute;n de una prote&iacute;na quinasa de estr&eacute;s (AMPK) pueden influir en el desarrollo de la enfermedad de Lesch Nyhan, una grave enfermedad neurol&oacute;gica en el hombre.<br />\n	<br />\n	<strong> </strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong><span style=\"color:#800000;\">PRINCIPALES L&Iacute;NEAS DE INVESTIGACI&Oacute;N&nbsp;</span></strong><br />\n	<br />\n	1) Estudiar la funci&oacute;n de las prote&iacute;nas quinasas de estr&eacute;s en la muerte celular y en la meiosis. El objetivo de este proyecto es determinar el papel de las prote&iacute;nas quinasas de estr&eacute;s AMPK, JNK y p38 en la muerte de los ovocitos inducida por el shock osm&oacute;tico y en la progresi&oacute;n mei&oacute;tica inducida por progesterona. Estudiaremos en detalle la regulaci&oacute;n de la liberaci&oacute;n de citocromo c y la activaci&oacute;n de caspasas por estas prote&iacute;nas quinasas. Tambi&eacute;n investigamos el papel de la AMPK y JNK en el control de la traducci&oacute;n durante la progresi&oacute;n mei&oacute;tica. Utilizaremos como modelo los ovocitos de Xenopus, que ofrece grandes ventajas para la manipulaci&oacute;n bioqu&iacute;mica.<br />\n	2) Estudiar el papel de la acumulaci&oacute;n de ZMP y la activaci&oacute;n de la AMPK en el desarrollo de la enfermedad de Lesch-Nyhan. La enfermedad de Lesch-Nyhan provoca graves efectos neurol&oacute;gicos como consecuencia de una deficiencia en el enzima hipoxantina-guanina fosforribosiltransferasa (HPRT). Sigue siendo un misterio c&oacute;mo una simple modificaci&oacute;n en el metabolismo de las purinas produce efectos dram&aacute;ticos en el comportamiento humano. La deficiencia de HPRT se asocia con una disfunci&oacute;n relativamente selectiva de los sistemas dopamin&eacute;rgicos en el cerebro. Se han propuesto diferentes hip&oacute;tesis, como la acumulaci&oacute;n de un metabolito t&oacute;xico en el cerebro. Pensamos que el nucle&oacute;tido ZMP es el agente t&oacute;xico, y que actuando de forma pleiotr&oacute;pica inducir&iacute;a diversos cambios en la c&eacute;lula provocando la disfunci&oacute;n cerebral. Uno de los primeros cambios ser&iacute;a la activaci&oacute;n de la prote&iacute;na quinasa AMPK.<br />\n	<br />\n	<strong><span style=\"color:#800000;\"> </span></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PUBLICACIONES DESTACADAS</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	&bull; Yue J, L&oacute;pez JM. <em>JNK does not regulate meiotic progression in</em>&nbsp;<em>Xenopus</em>&nbsp;<em>oocytes: The strange case of pJNK and pERK. </em>Dev Biol. 416: 42-51, <strong>2016</strong>.</p>\n<p>\n	&bull; Yue J, Ben Messaoud N, L&oacute;pez JM. <em>Hyperosmotic Shock Engages Two Positive Feedback Loops through Caspase-3-dependent Proteolysis of JNK1-2 and Bid. </em>J Biol Chem. 290: 30375-89, <strong>2015</strong>.</p>\n<p>\n	&bull; Ben Messaoud N, Katzarova I, L&oacute;pez JM. <em>Basic Properties of the p38 Signaling Pathway in Response to Hyperosmotic Shock. </em>PLoS One. doi: 10.1371/journal.pone.0135249, <strong>2015</strong>.</p>\n<p>\n	&bull; Ben Messaoud N, Yue J, Valent D, Katzarova I, L&oacute;pez JM. <em>Osmostress-induced apoptosis in</em>&nbsp;<em>Xenopus</em>&nbsp;<em>oocytes: role of stress protein kinases, calpains and Smac/DIABLO. </em>PLoS One. doi: 10.1371/journal.pone.0124482, <strong>2015</strong>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;L&oacute;pez JM.<br />\n	<em>Digital kinases: A cell model for sensing, integrating and making choices.</em><br />\n	Communicative &amp; Integrative Biology. 3: 146-150,&nbsp;<strong>2010</strong>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;Marti&aacute;&ntilde;ez T, Franc&egrave;s S, L&oacute;pez JM.&nbsp;<br />\n	<em>Generation of digital responses in stress sensors.&nbsp;</em><br />\n	Journal of Biological Chemistry. 284: 23902-23911,&nbsp;<strong>2009</strong>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;Piqu&eacute; M, L&oacute;pez JM, Sylvain F, Guig&oacute; R, M&eacute;ndez R.&nbsp;<br />\n	<em>A combinatorial code for CPE-mediated translational control.&nbsp;</em><br />\n	Cell. 132: 434-448,<strong>2008</strong>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830965/public/\" target=\"_blank\">Ver m&aacute;s publicaciones de JM. L&oacute;pez en PubMed. </a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n',35,2,1),(459,52,0,'Vicente Martínez y Patrocinio Vergara','<p>\n	<a href=\"javascript:MostraPage(377,1); \">Neurodegeneraci&oacute;n y envejecimiento</a></p>\n<h2>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\">Neuroinmunogastroenterolog&iacute;a y Microbiota Intestinal</span></h2>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong>L&iacute;deres del Grupo:</strong></p>\n<table style=\"width: 100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				Vicente Mart&iacute;nez&nbsp; Perea</td>\n			<td>\n				Patrocinio Vergara Esteras</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:vicente.martinez@uab.cat\">vicente.martinez@uab.cat</a></td>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:patri.vergara@uab.cat\">patri.vergara@uab.cat</a></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				TEL: +34 93 581 3834</td>\n			<td>\n				TEL: +34 93 581 1848</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<table height=\"25\" width=\"40\">\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n				<table height=\"40\" width=\"97\">\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0002-9220-6406\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"28\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/orcid.png\" width=\"28\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researcherid.com/rid/M-6468-2013\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"27\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/RID.jpg\" width=\"27\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=7006757890\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"30\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" width=\"30\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	<br />\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/Martvergdef.jpg\" style=\"width: 100%; margin-top: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px;\" /></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>Miembros del Grupo:</strong><br />\n	Sergio Berd&uacute;n Mar&iacute;n<br />\n	Eva Maria Cepeda Romero<br />\n	Javier Est&eacute;vez Medina<br />\n	Marina Ferrer Clotas<br />\n	Sergio L&oacute;pez Est&eacute;vez<br />\n	Emma Mart&iacute;nez P&eacute;rez<br />\n	Maria Asunci&oacute;n Molina Romero<br />\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>OBJECTIVOS ESTRAT&Eacute;GICOS</strong></span><br />\n	<br />\n	Nuestros intereses en investigaci&oacute;n se centran en el campo de la neurogastroenterolog&iacute;a (neurociencias ent&eacute;ricas), en particular en el estudio de las interacciones neuro-inmunes en el tracto gastrointestinal, incluyendo las interacciones con la microbiota comensal del intestino. Nuestro objetivo &uacute;ltimo es comprender los mecanismos fisiopatol&oacute;gicos b&aacute;sicos de los trastornos funcionales e inflamatorios gastrointestinales en la especie humana, con la finalidad de identificar y caracterizar dianas potenciales de intervenci&oacute;n terap&eacute;utica.<br />\n	Para ello, seguimos un enfoque multidisciplinar en el que se integran los trabajos in vivo en modelos animales con estudios moleculares&nbsp; y de biolog&iacute;a celular.<br />\n	<br />\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PRINCIPALES L&Iacute;NEAS DE INVESTIGACI&Oacute;N</strong></span><br />\n	<br />\n	-Desarrollo y caracterizaci&oacute;n de modelos animales de trastornos gastrointestinales: enfermedad inflamatoria intestinal y s&iacute;ndrome de intestino irritable.<br />\n	-Implicaciones de los mastocitos en la fisiopatolog&iacute;a de los trastornos gastrointestinales inflamatorios y relacionados con alergias alimentarias.<br />\n	-Mastocitos y remodelaci&oacute;n neuronal en el tracto gastrointestinal.<br />\n	-Mecanismos y farmacolog&iacute;a del dolor visceral de origen intestinal.<br />\n	-Microbiota intestinal: Relaci&oacute;n con mecanismos sensoriales viscerales y con la funci&oacute;n barrera intestinal.<br />\n	-Eje sistema nervioso central-tracto gastrointestinal: Efectos del estr&eacute;s sobre la funci&oacute;n gastrointestinal.<br />\n	<br />\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PUBLICACIONES </strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	&bull; Jard&iacute; F, Fern&aacute;ndez-Blanco JA, <strong>Mart&iacute;nez V</strong>, <strong>Vergara P</strong>. Persistent alterations in colonic afferent innervation in a rat model of postinfectious gut dysfunction: Role for changes in peripheral neurotrophic factors. Neurogastroenterol Motil. <strong>2016 </strong>Gen; <span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial, helvetica, clean, sans-serif; font-size: 11.999px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: 16.6138px; orphans: auto; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 1; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; display: inline !important; float: none; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">28(5):693-704. doi: 10.1111/nmo.12766. Epub 2016</span>.</p>\n<p>\n	&bull; Fern&aacute;ndez-Blanco JA, Est&eacute;vez J, Shea-Donohue T, <strong>Mart&iacute;nez V</strong>, <strong>Vergara P</strong>. Changes in Epithelial Barrier Function in Response to Parasitic Infection: Implications for IBD Pathogenesis. J Crohns Colitis. <strong>2015 </strong>Jun; 9(6):463&ndash;76. doi: 10.1093/ecco-jcc/jjv056. Epub 2015.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	&bull; Berd&uacute;n S, Rychter J, <strong>Vergara P</strong>. Effects of nerve growth factor antagonist k252a on peritoneal mast cell degranulation: implications for rat postoperative ileus. American Journal of Physiology - Gastrointestinal and Liver Physiology&nbsp;<strong>2015 </strong>Sep; 309 G801-6. doi:10.1152/ajpgi.00152.2015</p>\n<p>\n	&bull; Jardi F, Aguilera M, <strong>Vergara P, Martinez V</strong>. Lipopolysaccharides facilitate colonic motor alterations associated to the sensitization to a luminal antigen in rats. J Neurogastroenterol Motil. <strong>2015 </strong>Mar; 21(2):222&ndash;35. doi: 10.5056/jnm14136</p>\n<p>\n	&bull; Rychter J, Ortega O, Berdun S, Arenas C, Lopez I, Espin F, <strong>Vergara P</strong>, et al. Mast cell degranulation inhibits motor patterns of human ileum and sigmoid colon in vitro: relevance for postoperative ileus. Neurogastroenterol Motil. <strong>2015</strong> Aug; 27(8):1098&ndash;109. doi: 10.1111/nmo.12589. Epub 2015</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830977/public/\" target=\"_blank\">Ver m&aacute;s publicaciones de V. Mart&iacute;nez en PubMed.</a></p>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830981/public/\" target=\"_blank\">Ver m&aacute;s publicaciones de P. Vergara en PubMed.</a></p>\n',36,2,1),(461,52,0,'Xavier Navarro','<p>\n	<a href=\"javascript:MostraPage(378,1); \">Neuroregeneraci&oacute;n y reparaci&oacute;n</a></p>\n<h2>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\">Neuroplasticidad y Regeneraci&oacute;n</span></h2>\n<p>\n	<strong>L&iacute;der del grupo:</strong></p>\n<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				Xavier Navarro</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:xavier.navarro@uab.cat\">xavier.navarro@uab.cat</a></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				TEL. +34 93 581 1966</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<table height=\"63\" width=\"94\">\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0001-9849-902X\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/orcid.png\" style=\"width: 26px; height: 26px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researcherid.com/rid/C-9577-2011\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/RID.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<p>\n									<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=22944812800\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 29px; height: 29px;\" /></a></p>\n							</td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researchgate.net/profile/Xavier_Navarro\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"32\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/researchgate.jpg\" width=\"29\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/XNavarro2014.JPG\" style=\"width: 75%; float: left;\" /></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\n	<strong>Investigadores senior:</strong><br />\n	<a href=\"http://inc.uab.cat/Castellano/profile.php?id=38\"><span style=\"color:#000000;\">Caty Casas</span></a><br />\n	Jordi Cuadras<br />\n	Guillermo Garc&iacute;a-Al&iacute;as<br />\n	<a href=\"http://inc.uab.cat/Castellano/profile.php?id=88\">Ruben L&oacute;pez-Vales</a><br />\n	<span style=\"color:#000000;\"> </span><a href=\"http://inc.uab.cat/Castellano/profile.php?id=135\"><span style=\"color:#000000;\">Esther Udina</span></a><br />\n	<strong>Profesores asociados:</strong><br />\n	Jordi Bruna<br />\n	Roser Velasco<br />\n	Jorge J. Vilches<br />\n	<strong>Investigadores&nbsp;<br />\n	posdoctorales</strong>:<br />\n	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <a href=\"http://inc.uab.cat/Castellano/profile.php?id=54\"><span style=\"color:#000000;\">Jaume Del Valle</span></a><br />\n	Ignacio Delgado&nbsp;<br />\n	<a href=\"http://inc.uab.cat/Castellano/profile.php?id=78\"><span style=\"color:#000000;\">Joaquim Hern&aacute;ndez</span></a><br />\n	<a href=\"http://inc.uab.cat/Castellano/profile.php?id=78\">Mireia Herrando</a><br />\n	<strong>Investigadores<br />\n	predoctorales</strong>:<br />\n	Jes&uacute;s Amo<br />\n	Ariadna Arbat<br />\n	Isaac Francos<br />\n	Tatiana Leiva<br />\n	V&iacute;ctor L&oacute;pez<br />\n	Clara L&oacute;pez<br />\n	Anna Mart&iacute;nez<br />\n	Guillem M&ograve;dol<br />\n	Natalia de la Oliva<br />\n	Maria Puigdom&egrave;nech<br />\n	David Romeo<br />\n	Alba Sanchez<br />\n	Irene Sanchez<br />\n	Daniel Santos<br />\n	<strong>Investigadores colaboradores:</strong><br />\n	Jordi Badia<br />\n	Joaquim For&eacute;s<br />\n	<strong>T&eacute;cnicos</strong>:<br />\n	Israel Blasco<br />\n	M&oacute;nica Espejo<br />\n	J&egrave;sica Jaramillo<br />\n	<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<br />\n	<strong><span style=\"color:#800000;\">OBJETIVOS ESTRAT&Eacute;GICOS</span></strong><br />\n	<br />\n	El Grupo de Neuroplasticidad y Regeneraci&oacute;n es un grupo de investigaci&oacute;n multidisciplinario que trabaja en la regeneraci&oacute;n y recuperaci&oacute;n funcional despu&eacute;s de lesiones de los nervios perif&eacute;ricos y de la m&eacute;dula espinal y en enfermedades neurodegenerativas. Los miembros del grupo tienen experiencia combinada en microcirug&iacute;a, neurofisiolog&iacute;a, morfolog&iacute;a, cultivos celulares, neurobiolog&iacute;a molecular y bioelectr&oacute;nica. Los proyectos de investigaci&oacute;n desarrollados durante los &uacute;ltimos a&ntilde;os han tratado sobre: regeneraci&oacute;n y reinervaci&oacute;n despu&eacute;s de lesiones de nervios y de ra&iacute;ces espinales, injertos artificiales biocompatibles, trasplantes gliales para la reparaci&oacute;n de lesiones en el sistema nervioso perif&eacute;rico y central, electrodos neurales para la interfase con el sistema nervioso lesionado. El grupo mantiene investigaci&oacute;n cooperativa en neurociencia cl&iacute;nica, particularmente sobre nuevas terapias reparativas de lesiones nerviosas con el Hospital Clinico de Barcelona, y sobre modulaci&oacute;n de la plasticidad neural en lesiones cerebrales y medulares con el Instituto Guttmann de Neurorehabilitaci&oacute;n.<br />\n	<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PRINCIPALES L&Iacute;NEAS DE INVESTIGACI&Oacute;N</strong></span><br />\n	<br />\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Regeneraci&oacute;n y reinervaci&oacute;n despu&eacute;s de lesiones de nervios perif&eacute;ricos.<br />\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Fisiopatolog&iacute;a y tratamiento del dolor neurop&aacute;tico.<br />\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Evaluaci&oacute;n y fisiopatolog&iacute;a de neuropat&iacute;as perif&eacute;ricas.<br />\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Mecanismos moleculares y celulares en la degeneraci&oacute;n de motoneuronas.<br />\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Desarrollo de injertos nerviosos biocompatibles.<br />\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Trasplante de c&eacute;lulas gliales y progenitoras para la reparaci&oacute;n de lesiones de m&eacute;dula espinal.<br />\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Modulaci&oacute;n de la respuesta inflamatoria en lesiones del SNC.<br />\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Evaluaci&oacute;n de interfases neurales y neuropr&oacute;tesis para la rehabilitaci&oacute;n del sistema nervioso lesionado.<br />\n	<br />\n	<strong><span style=\"color:#800000;\"> </span></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong><span style=\"color:#800000;\">PROYECTOS DE INVESTIGACI&Oacute;N&nbsp;FINANCIADOS EN LOS &Uacute;LTIMOS 5 A&Ntilde;OS&nbsp;</span></strong><br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Proyecto de Investigaci&oacute;n PI060201, <em>Fondo de Investigaci&oacute;n Sanitaria, Inst Salud Carlos III</em>, 2007-09. &ldquo;Transplantes gliales combinados con neuroprotecci&oacute;n y restituci&oacute;n neuronal para la reparaci&oacute;n de lesiones de ra&iacute;ces espinales&rdquo;.<br />\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Proyecto de Investigaci&oacute;n SAF2006-08682, <em>Ministerio de Educaci&oacute;n y Ciencia,</em> 2007-09. &ldquo;Terapia f&aacute;rmaco-celular para la reparaci&oacute;n de la m&eacute;dula espinal lesionada&rdquo;.<br />\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Proyecto de Investigaci&oacute;n 070210, <em>Fundaci&oacute; La Marat&oacute;TV3,</em> 2008-2010. &quot;Trasplantes celulares y tratamiento farmacol&oacute;gico para reducir el dolor neurop&aacute;tico en lesiones de m&eacute;dula espinal&quot;<br />\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Grupo miembro del <em>Centro de Investigaci&oacute;n Biom&eacute;dica en Red sobre Enfermedades Neurodegenerativas (CIBERNED)</em>, <em>Inst Salud Carlos III</em>, 2008-2014. CB06/05/1105.<br />\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Grupo de la <em>Red de Terapia Celular</em> RD06/0010/1004, <em>Instituto de Salud Carlos III,</em> 2008-2012.<br />\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Proyecto de Investigaci&oacute;n FP7 ICT-224012, <em>Comission of the European Communities</em>, 2008-2012. &ldquo;Transverse, Intrafascicular Multichannel Electrode system for induction of sensation and treatment of phantom limb pain in amputees (TIME)&rdquo;.<br />\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Marie Curie Initial Training Network, FP7- MC-214003-2, <em>European Commission</em>, 2008-2012. &ldquo;Axonal regeneration, plasticity and stem cells (AXREGEN)&rdquo;.<br />\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Proyecto de Investigaci&oacute;n PI080598, <em>Fondo de Investigaci&oacute;n Sanitaria, Inst Salud Carlos III</em>, 2008-10. &ldquo;Efectos de la estimulaci&oacute;n el&eacute;ctrica del nervio perif&eacute;rico sobre la plasticidad de los circuitos espinales y la regeneraci&oacute;n axonal despu&eacute;s de lesiones nerviosas o medulares&rdquo;.<br />\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ayuda a la Investigaci&oacute;n, <em>Fundaci&oacute;n Mapfre</em>, 2009. &ldquo;Administraci&oacute;n de AB-cristalina como terapia protectora de las lesiones de la m&eacute;dula espinal&rdquo;.<br />\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Proyecto de Investigaci&oacute;n WFL-SE-008/09, <em>Wings for Life Foundation</em>, 2009-10. &ldquo;Role of lysophosphatidic acid in the pathophysiology of spinal cord 