maps?f=q&amp;source=s_q&amp;hl=es&amp;geocode=&amp;q=Institut+de+Neuroci%C3%A8ncies+(INc),+Barcelona&amp;aq=0&amp;oq=Institut+de+N&amp;sll=41.692248,1.745868&amp;sspn=3.203337,4.938354&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;hq=Institut+de+Neuroci%C3%A8ncies+(INc),&amp;hnear=Barcelona,+Catalu%C3%B1a&amp;ll=41.441059,2.14001&amp;spn=0.138128,0.080144&amp;t=m&amp;output=embed\" width=\"100%\"></iframe><br />\n	<small><a href=\"https://maps.google.es/maps?f=q&amp;source=embed&amp;hl=es&amp;geocode=&amp;q=Institut+de+Neuroci%C3%A8ncies+(INc),+Barcelona&amp;aq=0&amp;oq=Institut+de+N&amp;sll=41.692248,1.745868&amp;sspn=3.203337,4.938354&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;hq=Institut+de+Neuroci%C3%A8ncies+(INc),&amp;hnear=Barcelona,+Catalu%C3%B1a&amp;ll=41.441059,2.14001&amp;spn=0.138128,0.080144&amp;t=m\" style=\"color:#0000FF;text-align:left\">Ver mapa m&aacute;s grande</a></small></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong><u><em>By car or motorcycle:</em></u></strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	-Motorway AP-7, direction Tarragona-Lleida if you come from the north, or direction Girona if you come from Barcelona. Exit:&quot;Universitat Aut&ograve;noma&quot;.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	-Motorway C-58.&nbsp;Barcelona-Sabadell-Terrassa. Exit &quot;Universitat Aut&ograve;noma&quot;.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong><u><em>By train:</em></u></strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	-FGC- Line BCN-SABADELL(<a href=\"http://www.fgc.cat/cat/barcelona-valles.asp?linia=S2\" target=\"_blank\">S2</a>) or BCN-UAB(<a href=\"http://www.fgc.cat/cat/barcelona-valles.asp?linia=S55\" target=\"_blank\">S55</a>)<br />\n	-RENFE- Lines <a href=\"http://www20.gencat.cat/portal/site/rodalies/menuitem.b638815e53e7323fcfd97c10b0c0e1a0/?vgnextoid=3b965c3674002310VgnVCM2000009b0c1e0aRCRD&amp;vgnextchannel=3b965c3674002310VgnVCM2000009b0c1e0aRCRD&amp;vgnextfmt=default&amp;contentid=17b6b1f305762310VgnVCM1000008d0c1e0aRCRD&amp;tipologia=Rodalies&amp;linia=r7\" target=\"_blank\">R7</a> i <a href=\"http://www20.gencat.cat/portal/site/rodalies/menuitem.b638815e53e7323fcfd97c10b0c0e1a0/?vgnextoid=3b965c3674002310VgnVCM2000009b0c1e0aRCRD&amp;vgnextchannel=3b965c3674002310VgnVCM2000009b0c1e0aRCRD&amp;vgnextfmt=default&amp;contentid=5545dbb8f5762310VgnVCM1000008d0c1e0aRCRD&amp;tipologia=Rodalies&amp;linia=r8\" target=\"_blank\">R8</a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong><u><em>By&nbsp; Bus:</em></u></strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	Check the lines that reach to UAB, <a href=\"http://www.uab.cat/servlet/Satellite/by-bus-1273127179779.html\" target=\"_blank\">here</a></p>\n',69,2,2),(530,45,0,'Activities','<div class=\"fuenteContingut\" id=\"DIVContingutPage\" style=\"width: 100%; text-align: justify; display: block;\">\n	<div>\n		<strong><span style=\"color:#800000;\">ACTIVITIES DURING THE BRAIN AWARENESS WEEK:</span></strong></div>\n	<div>\n		&nbsp;</div>\n	<div>\n		<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><b>Thursday 16th March</b></span><br />\n		<b>ESCOLAB visit: Els secrets del sistema nervi&oacute;s</b></div>\n	<div>\n		Private activity</div>\n	<div>\n		&nbsp;</div>\n	<div>\n		<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><b>Friday 17th March</b></span><br />\n		<b>ESCOLAB visit: Com es comuniquen les neurones? La sinapsi</b></div>\n	<div>\n		Private activity</div>\n	<div>\n		&nbsp;</div>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><b>Friday 17th March</b></span>\n	<div>\n		<b>Unistem day 2017</b></div>\n	<div>\n		<div>\n			Private activity</div>\n		<div>\n			&nbsp;</div>\n		<div>\n			&nbsp;</div>\n		<div>\n			___</div>\n		<div>\n			&nbsp;</div>\n		<div>\n			<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>Friday 24th March</strong></span></div>\n		<div>\n			12h Aula Laia Acar&iacute;n (Facultat de Medicina)</div>\n		<div>\n			<div>\n				<strong>INc seminar: <strong>SIGNALLING CONTROLLING NEURONAL MITOPHAGY IN PARKINSON&rsquo;S DISEASE</strong></strong></div>\n			<div>\n				<strong>Dr. James Murray</strong></div>\n			<div>\n				Trinity College Dublin</div>\n			<div>\n				<p>\n					Autophagy functions as a cellular recycling and quality control pathway to provide&nbsp;necessary building blocks for essential&nbsp;de&nbsp;novo&nbsp;biosynthetic pathways during stress&nbsp;and to restrict accumulation of cellular damage. Remnants of autophagic activity&nbsp;are&nbsp;found in Parkinson&rsquo;s Diseased (PD) brains, although whether this is a result of too&nbsp;much or failed autophagic activity is&nbsp;not clear. One critical function of autophagy is&nbsp;maintenance of viable mitochondria by mitophagy. Accumulation of the&nbsp;protein kinase&nbsp;PINK1 on the surface of damaged mitochondria recruits the E3-ligase Parkin, which&nbsp;results in decoration of&nbsp;damaged mitochondria with ubiquitinated epitopes, marking&nbsp;them for autophagic engulfment. The talk will have a general introduction to autophagy and mitophagy, while the data presented will describe the signalling involved in control of mitophagy following mitochondrial damage in SH-SY5Y and iPS Parkinson&rsquo;s disease cell line models.</p>\n			</div>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n</div>\n',70,2,2),(531,52,0,'Actividades','<div>\n	<strong><span style=\"color:#800000;\">ACTIVITIES DURING THE BRAIN AWARENESS WEEK:</span></strong></div>\n<div>\n	&nbsp;</div>\n<div>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><b>Jueves 16 de marzo</b></span><br />\n	<b>Visita ESCOLAB: Els secrets del sistema nervi&oacute;s</b></div>\n<div>\n	Actividad cerrada</div>\n<div>\n	&nbsp;</div>\n<div>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><b>Viernes 17 de marzo</b></span><br />\n	<b>Visita ESCOLAB: Com es comuniquen les neurones? La sinapsi</b></div>\n<div>\n	Actividad cerrada</div>\n<div>\n	&nbsp;</div>\n<div>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><b>Viernes 17 de marzo</b></span></div>\n<div>\n	<b>Unistem day 2017</b></div>\n<div>\n	<div>\n		Actividad cerrada</div>\n	<div>\n		&nbsp;</div>\n	<div>\n		&nbsp;</div>\n	<div>\n		&nbsp;</div>\n	<div>\n		__</div>\n	<div>\n		&nbsp;</div>\n	<div>\n		<div>\n			<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>Viernes 24 de marzo</strong></span></div>\n		<div>\n			12h Aula Laia Acar&iacute;n (Facultat de Medicina)</div>\n		<div>\n			<strong>INc seminar: <strong>SIGNALLING CONTROLLING NEURONAL MITOPHAGY IN PARKINSON&rsquo;S DISEASE</strong></strong></div>\n		<div>\n			<strong>Dr. James Murray</strong></div>\n		<div>\n			Trinity College Dublin</div>\n		<div>\n			<p>\n				Autophagy functions as a cellular recycling and quality control pathway to provide&nbsp;necessary building blocks for essential&nbsp;de&nbsp;novo&nbsp;biosynthetic pathways during stress&nbsp;and to restrict accumulation of cellular damage. Remnants of autophagic activity&nbsp;are&nbsp;found in Parkinson&rsquo;s Diseased (PD) brains, although whether this is a result of too&nbsp;much or failed autophagic activity is&nbsp;not clear. One critical function of autophagy is&nbsp;maintenance of viable mitochondria by mitophagy. Accumulation of the&nbsp;protein kinase&nbsp;PINK1 on the surface of damaged mitochondria recruits the E3-ligase Parkin, which&nbsp;results in decoration of&nbsp;damaged mitochondria with ubiquitinated epitopes, marking&nbsp;them for autophagic engulfment. The talk will have a general introduction to autophagy and mitophagy, while the data presented will describe the signalling involved in control of mitophagy following mitochondrial damage in SH-SY5Y and iPS Parkinson&rsquo;s disease cell line models.</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n</div>\n',70,2,1),(532,30,0,'Activitats','<div>\n	<strong><span style=\"color:#800000;\">ACTIVITIES DURING THE BRAIN AWARENESS WEEK:</span></strong></div>\n<div>\n	&nbsp;</div>\n<div>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><b>Dijous, 16 de mar</b><b>&ccedil;, 10.00 h</b></span><br />\n	<b>Visita ESCOLAB: Els secrets del sistema nervi&oacute;s</b></div>\n<div>\n	Activitat tancada</div>\n<div>\n	&nbsp;</div>\n<div>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><b>Divendres, 17 de mar&ccedil;, 10.00 h</b></span><br />\n	<b>Visita ESCOLAB: Com es comuniquen les neurones? La sinapsi</b></div>\n<div>\n	Activitat tancada</div>\n<div>\n	&nbsp;</div>\n<div>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><b>Divendres 17 de mar&ccedil;</b></span></div>\n<div>\n	<b>Unistem day 2017</b></div>\n<div>\n	<div>\n		Activitat tancada</div>\n	<div>\n		&nbsp;</div>\n	<div>\n		&nbsp;</div>\n	<div>\n		&nbsp;</div>\n	<div>\n		___</div>\n	<div>\n		&nbsp;</div>\n	<div>\n		<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>Divendres 24 de mar&ccedil;</strong></span></div>\n	<div>\n		12h Aula Laia Acar&iacute;n (Facultat de Medicina)</div>\n	<div>\n		<strong>INc seminar: <strong>SIGNALLING CONTROLLING NEURONAL MITOPHAGY IN PARKINSON&rsquo;S DISEASE</strong></strong></div>\n	<div>\n		<strong>Dr. James Murray</strong></div>\n	<div>\n		Trinity College Dublin</div>\n	<div>\n		<p>\n			Autophagy functions as a cellular recycling and quality control pathway to provide&nbsp;necessary building blocks for essential&nbsp;de&nbsp;novo&nbsp;biosynthetic pathways during stress&nbsp;and to restrict accumulation of cellular damage. Remnants of autophagic activity&nbsp;are&nbsp;found in Parkinson&rsquo;s Diseased (PD) brains, although whether this is a result of too&nbsp;much or failed autophagic activity is&nbsp;not clear. One critical function of autophagy is&nbsp;maintenance of viable mitochondria by mitophagy. Accumulation of the&nbsp;protein kinase&nbsp;PINK1 on the surface of damaged mitochondria recruits the E3-ligase Parkin, which&nbsp;results in decoration of&nbsp;damaged mitochondria with ubiquitinated epitopes, marking&nbsp;them for autophagic engulfment. The talk will have a general introduction to autophagy and mitophagy, while the data presented will describe the signalling involved in control of mitophagy following mitochondrial damage in SH-SY5Y and iPS Parkinson&rsquo;s disease cell line models.</p>\n	</div>\n</div>\n',71,2,0),(534,31,0,'','<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\">INc</span><span style=\"color:#800000;\">entivem el coneixement</span></h2>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong>Jaume Ferrer Lalanza, 29 anys</strong></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>T&egrave;cnic de suport a la recerca</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\n	<strong><em><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/jaume f_opt.png\" style=\"width: 350px; height: 263px;\" /></em></strong></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong><em>1.- Hola, Jaume, explica&rsquo;ns quina ha estat la teva traject&ograve;ria fins l&rsquo;actualitat.</em></strong></p>\n<p>\n	Vaig estudiar Psicologia i en l&rsquo;&uacute;ltim curs vaig aprendre com es poden modular &nbsp;conductes humanes amb models animals. Aix&ograve; em va fascinar i em va dur a fer el Pr&agrave;cticum de la carrera a l&rsquo;Institut de Neuroci&egrave;ncies. Despr&eacute;s del Pr&agrave;cticum, el M&agrave;ster i el doctorat. Durant el doctorat vaig poder fer una estada a Vancouver (Canad&agrave;) on vaig aprendre t&egrave;cniques histol&ograve;giques, que dominava menys. Al profunditzar en histologia, per&ograve;, em vaig adonar que el que m&eacute;s m&rsquo;interessava era la part conductual. Despr&eacute;s d&rsquo;un any d&rsquo;acabar el doctorat vaig poder accedir a aquesta pla&ccedil;a de t&egrave;cnic a l&rsquo;INc.</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong><em>2.- Donada la teva formaci&oacute;, creus que estan prou integrades les dues disciplines, psicologia cl&iacute;nica i neuroci&egrave;ncia, en la recerca?</em></strong></p>\n<p>\n	&Eacute;s molt important integrar-les, encara que &eacute;s complicat. Per a mi, la idea fonamental&nbsp; &eacute;s que la Neuroci&egrave;ncia ens permeti entendre els mecanismes cerebrals que intervenen en els diferents processos per&ograve; tamb&eacute; &eacute;s important comprovar com aquest canvis afecten a la conducta. Aix&ograve; tamb&eacute; &eacute;s el que m&eacute;s interessa a la societat.</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong><em>3.- Durant la teva tesi, en quin camp d&rsquo;estudi vas treballar amb el grup de recerca?</em></strong></p>\n<p>\n	Principalment, vam modular en models animals els estils de vida que tenen les persones, en concret la pr&agrave;ctica d&rsquo;exercici f&iacute;sic i com la <em>dieta de cafeteria</em> contribueix a l&rsquo;obesitat, controlant el m&agrave;xim de variables.</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong><em>4.- A qu&egrave; et refereixes amb &ldquo;dieta de cafeteria&rdquo;?</em></strong></p>\n<p>\n	&Eacute;s el menjar poc saludable que podem consumir els humans en un bar o en un establiment de menjar r&agrave;pid: salsitxes de Frankfurt, bac&oacute;, magdalenes, formatgets, ... El sorprenent va ser observar que a nivell fisiol&ograve;gic &eacute;s clarament perjudicial per&ograve; que, en canvi, aquesta dieta tenia efectes beneficiosos: disminu&iuml;a l&rsquo;ansietat dels animals i, sobretot, augmentava la sociabilitat dels animals. La nostra hip&ograve;tesi &eacute;s que aquests efectes psicol&ograve;gics positius podrien estar incrementant el consum d&rsquo;aquest tipus de dietes en la nostra societat.</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong><em>5.- Creus que aquesta recerca que feu en models animals &eacute;s traslladable a l&rsquo;estudi del comportament hum&agrave;? &nbsp;</em></strong></p>\n<p>\n	Nosaltres pensem que &eacute;s traslladable. De fet, hem comen&ccedil;at a partir de conductes humanes (tamb&eacute; la t&iacute;pica recomanaci&oacute; de fer exercici 30 minuts al dia) i ho hem traslladat a un model animal per poder a&iuml;llar el m&agrave;xim de variables. Per exemple, les rates no van al cine, ni tenen problemes a la feina, ni es barallen per rentar els plats. M&eacute;s endavant seria interessant retornar als humans i ajustar les recomanacions que es fan sobre dieta i exercici.</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong><em>6.- Qu&egrave; vau descobrir sobre l&rsquo;exercici </em></strong><strong><em>f&iacute;sic?</em></strong></p>\n<p>\n	Que l&rsquo;exercici proporcionava un benefici a nivell d&rsquo;hormones de l&rsquo;estr&egrave;s: preparava el cos per respondre de manera m&eacute;s eficient a est&iacute;muls que provoquen ansietat.</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong><em>7.- Reivindica la feina del t&egrave;cnic. &nbsp;Quina &eacute;s la vostra funci&oacute; en un grup de recerca?</em></strong></p>\n<p>\n	Principalment donem suport en aspectes en els que els investigadors els falta temps o amb els que no se senten prou segurs per treballar sols. Fem una feina de recolzament en el moment en qu&egrave; el grup de recerca necessita un cop de m&agrave;. Penso que &eacute;s una feina molt important i que en un equip de treball hi ha d&rsquo;haver diferents tipus de perfils, incloent el del t&egrave;cnic.</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong><em>8.- Posa una mica de llum al pessimisme socioecon&ograve;mic actual. Als estudiants que es volen dedicar a la neuroci&egrave;ncia, qu&egrave; els recomanaries en els seus inicis com a cient&iacute;fics?</em></strong></p>\n<p>\n	Els recomanaria que se sentin c&ograve;modes en el grup de treball. &Eacute;s una tasca a vegades for&ccedil;a dura i, per a mi, el m&eacute;s important &eacute;s sentir-te motivat i recolzat pel teu equip. Fins i tot ho poso per davant del fet que el tema t&rsquo;agradi: la neuroci&egrave;ncia &eacute;s un camp apassionant i si el tema es relaciona amb els teus objectius, segur que t&rsquo;ho passes b&eacute;.</p>\n<p>\n	Tamb&eacute; recomano participar en tot tipus d&rsquo;activitats: fer un p&ograve;ster, donar una xerrada de divulgaci&oacute;, etc. A l&rsquo;hora de demanar beques aix&ograve; compta. En el meu cas, no vaig aconseguir una beca postdoctoral per poques d&egrave;cimes i, per tant, animaria a tothom a participar en activitats d&rsquo;aquest tipus.</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<u><a href=\"https://soundcloud.com/user-872279367/entrevista-a-jaume-ferrer\">Escolta l&#39;entrevista completa</a></u></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	Entregues anteriors:</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/RaulAnderocatal%C3%A0.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">- <strong><span style=\"color:#696969;\">Ra&uuml;l Andero</span></strong>- <strong><span style=\"color:#800000;\">Neurobiologia de l&#39;estr&egrave;s i l&#39;addicci&oacute;</span></strong></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/INcentivem_elisenda%20sanz(1).pdf\"><strong><span style=\"color:#800000;\">-</span><span style=\"color:#696969;\"> Elisenda Sanz-</span><span style=\"color:#800000;\"> Neuropatologia mitocondrial</span></strong></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>-<a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/1AMinano-INcentivem.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"> </a></strong></span><a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/1AMinano-INcentivem.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color:#696969;\"><strong>Alfredo J. Mi&ntilde;ano- </strong></span><span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>Mecanismes de Superviv&egrave;ncia Cel.lular</strong></span></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>-</strong></span><a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/INcentivem%20el%20coneixement-Ndaviu2.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong> </strong></span><span style=\"color:#696969;\"><strong>Nuria Daviu-</strong></span><span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong> Neurobiologia de l&#39;estr&egrave;s i l&#39;addicci&oacute;</strong></span></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>-</strong></span><a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/INcentivem%20el%20coneixement-BAlmolda3.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong> </strong></span><span style=\"color:#696969;\"><strong>Beatriz Almolda</strong></span><span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>- Grup de recerca en c&egrave;l.lules glials</strong></span></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>- </strong></span><a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/INcentivem%20el%20coneixement-CBarcia4.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color:#696969;\"><strong>Carlos Barcia</strong></span><span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>- Neuroimmunity</strong></span></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>- </strong></span><a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/INcentivem%20el%20coneixement-JDalton5.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color:#696969;\"><strong>James Dalton- </strong></span><span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>Neurofarmacologia molecular i bioinform&agrave;tica</strong></span></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>-<a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/INcentivem%20el%20coneixement-EUdina6.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"> </a></strong></span><a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/INcentivem%20el%20coneixement-EUdina6.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color:#696969;\"><strong>Esther Udina</strong></span><span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>- Neuroplasticitat i regeneraci&oacute;</strong></span></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong><span style=\"color:#800000;\">- </span><a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/INcentivem%20el%20coneixement-PBarros7.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color:#696969;\">Pol Barr&oacute;s-</span><span style=\"color:#800000;\"> Neurobiologia de l&#39;aprenentatge i la mem&ograve;ria</span></a></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong><span style=\"color:#800000;\">-<a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/INcentivem%20el%20coneixement-DTorrents8.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"> </a></span><a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/INcentivem%20el%20coneixement-DTorrents8.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color:#696969;\">David Torrents-</span><span style=\"color:#800000;\"> Laboratori hum&agrave;</span></a></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong><span style=\"color:#800000;\">- </span><a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/INcentivem%20el%20coneixement-VictoriaClos9.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color:#696969;\">Victoria Clos- </span><span style=\"color:#800000;\">Neurofarmacologia de l&#39;Alzheimer</span></a></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong><span style=\"color:#800000;\">- </span><a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/INcentivem%20el%20coneixement-VMartinez10.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color:#696969;\">Vicente Mart&iacute;nez-</span><span style=\"color:#800000;\"> Neuroimmunogastroenterologia i Microbiota Intestinal</span></a></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong><span style=\"color:#800000;\">- </span><a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/INcentivem%20el%20coneixement-RMasgrau11.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color:#696969;\">Roser Masgrau-</span><span style=\"color:#800000;\"> Astrolab</span></a></strong></p>\n',73,2,0),(535,53,0,'','<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\">INc</span><span style=\"color:#800000;\">entivemos el conocimiento</span></h2>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong>Jaume Ferrer Lalanza, 29 a&ntilde;os</strong></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>T&eacute;cnico de apoyo a la investigaci&oacute;n</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/jaume f_opt.png\" style=\"width: 350px; height: 263px;\" /></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong>1.- <em>Hola, Jaume, expl&iacute;canos cu&aacute;l ha sido tu trayectoria hasta la actualidad.</em></strong></p>\n<p>\n	Estudi&eacute; Psicolog&iacute;a y en el &uacute;ltimo curso aprend&iacute; c&oacute;mo se pueden modular conductas humanas con modelos animales. Esto me fascin&oacute; y me llev&oacute; a realizar el pr&aacute;cticum de la carrera en el Instituto de Neurociencias. Despu&eacute;s del pr&aacute;cticum, segu&iacute; con el m&aacute;ster y el doctorado. Durante el doctorado pude hacer una estancia en Vancouver (Canad&aacute;) donde aprend&iacute; t&eacute;cnicas histol&oacute;gicas, que dominaba menos. Pero al profundizar en Histolog&iacute;a me di cuenta de que lo que m&aacute;s me interesaba era la parte conductual. Despu&eacute;s de un a&ntilde;o de acabar el doctorado pude acceder a esta plaza de t&eacute;cnico en el INc.</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong><em>2.- </em></strong><strong><em>Dada tu formaci&oacute;n, &iquest;crees que est&aacute;n suficientemente integradas les dos disciplines, Psicolog&iacute;a y Neurociencia, en la investigaci&oacute;n?</em></strong></p>\n<p>\n	Es muy importante integrarlas, aunque es complicado. Para m&iacute;, la idea fundamental es que la Neurociencia nos permita entender los mecanismos cerebrales que intervienen en los diferentes procesos, pero tambi&eacute;n es importante comprobar c&oacute;mo estos cambios afectan a la conducta. Muchas veces, estos efectos conductuales son los m&aacute;s relevantes de cara a transferir el conocimiento del laboratorio a la sociedad.</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong><em>3.- Durante tu tesis, &iquest;en qu&eacute; campo de estudio trabajaste con tu grupo de investigaci&oacute;n?</em></strong></p>\n<p>\n	Principalmente, modulamos en modelos animales los estilos de vida que tienen las persones, en concreto la pr&aacute;ctica de ejercicio f&iacute;sico y c&oacute;mo la <em>dieta de cafeter&iacute;a </em>contribuye a la obesidad y sus efectos psicol&oacute;gicos, controlando el m&aacute;ximo de variables.</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong><em>4.- &iquest;A qu&eacute; te refieres con &ldquo;dieta de cafeter&iacute;a&rdquo;?</em></strong></p>\n<p>\n	Es la comida poco saludable que podemos consumir los humanos en un bar o en un establecimiento de comida r&aacute;pida: salchichas de Frankfurt, bac&oacute;n, magdalenas, quesitos&hellip; Lo sorprendente fue observar que a nivel fisiol&oacute;gico es claramente perjudicial pero, en cambio, esta dieta ten&iacute;a efectos beneficiosos: Disminu&iacute;a la ansiedad de los animales y, sobre todo, aumentaba su sociabilidad. Tenemos la hip&oacute;tesis de que estos efectos psicol&oacute;gicos positivos podr&iacute;an estar incrementando en parte el consumo de este tipo de dietas en nuestra sociedad.</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong><em>5.- &iquest;Crees que esta investigaci&oacute;n que hab&eacute;is hecho en modelos animales es trasladable al estudio del comportamiento humano?</em></strong></p>\n<p>\n	Nosotros pensamos que es trasladable. De hecho, hemos empezado a partir de conductas humanas (tambi&eacute;n la t&iacute;pica recomendaci&oacute;n de hacer ejercicio 30 minutos al d&iacute;a) y las hemos trasladado a un modelo animal para poder aislar el m&aacute;ximo de variables. Por ejemplo, las ratas no van al cine, ni tienen problemas en el trabajo, ni discuten por qui&eacute;n lava los platos. M&aacute;s adelante ser&iacute;a interesante retornar a los humanos y ajustar las recomendaciones que se hacen sobre dieta y ejercicio.</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong><em>6.- &iquest;Qu&eacute; descubristeis sobre el ejercicio f&iacute;sico?</em></strong></p>\n<p>\n	Lo m&aacute;s relevante fue que el ejercicio proporcionaba un beneficio a nivel de las hormonas del estr&eacute;s: preparaba el cuerpo para responder de forma m&aacute;s eficiente a est&iacute;mulos que provocan ansiedad.</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong><em>7.- Reivindica el trabajo del t&eacute;cnico. &iquest;Cu&aacute;l es vuestra funci&oacute;n en un grupo de investigaci&oacute;n?</em></strong></p>\n<p>\n	Principalmente damos soporte en aspectos para los que los investigadores no tienen tiempo o con los que no se sienten suficientemente seguros para trabajar solos. Hacemos un trabajo de apoyo en el momento en que el grupo de investigaci&oacute;n necesita que le echen una mano. Pienso que es una labor muy importante y que en un equipo de trabajo tiene que haber diferentes tipos de perfiles, incluyendo el del t&eacute;cnico.</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong><em>8.-</em></strong><strong><em>Ilumina un poco el pesimismo socioecon&oacute;mico actual. A los estudiantes que se quieren dedicar a la neurociencia, &iquest;qu&eacute; les recomendar&iacute;as en sus inicios como cient&iacute;ficos?</em></strong></p>\n<p>\n	Les recomendar&iacute;a que se sientan c&oacute;modos en su grupo de trabajo. Es un trabajo a veces bastante duro y, para m&iacute;, lo m&aacute;s importante es sentirse motivado y apoyado por tu equipo. Hasta lo pongo por delante y si el tema se relaciona con tus objetivos, aunque no sea al cien por cien, seguro que te lo pasas bien.</p>\n<p>\n	Tambi&eacute;n recomiendo participar en todo tipo de actividades: hacer un p&oacute;ster, dar una charla de divulgaci&oacute;n, etc. A la hora de pedir becas, cuenta. En mi caso, no consegu&iacute; una beca postdoctoral por pocas d&eacute;cimas y, por lo tanto, animar&iacute;a a todos a participar en actividades de este tipo.</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<u><a href=\"https://soundcloud.com/user-872279367/entrevista-a-jaume-ferrer\">Escucha la entrevista entera</a></u></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	Entregas anteriores:</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/RaulAnderocastell%C3%A0(1).pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><strong><span style=\"color:#696969;\">- Ra&uuml;l Andero- </span><span style=\"color:#800000;\">Neurobiolog&iacute;a del estr&eacute;s y la adicci&oacute;n</span></strong></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/INcentivemos%20el%20conocimiento%20-%20Elisenda%20Sanz.pdf\"><strong><span style=\"color:#800000;\">- </span><span style=\"color:#696969;\">Elisenda Sanz -</span> <span style=\"color:#800000;\">Neuropatologia mitocondrial</span></strong></a></p>\n<p>\n	<strong><span style=\"color:#800000;\">-</span><a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/1AMinano-INcentivemos.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"> <span style=\"color:#696969;\">Alfredo J. Mi&ntilde;ano- </span><span style=\"color:#800000;\">Mecanismos de supervivencia celular</span></a></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<strong><span style=\"color:#800000;\">-</span><a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/INcentivemos%20el%20conocimiento-NDaviu2.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"> <span style=\"color:#696969;\">N&uacute;ria Daviu- </span><span style=\"color:#800000;\">Neurobiolog&iacute;a del estr&eacute;s i la adicci&oacute;n</span></a></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<strong><span style=\"color:#800000;\">-</span><a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/INcentivemos%20el%20conocimiento-BAlmolda3.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"> <span style=\"color:#696969;\">Beatriz Almolda</span><span style=\"color:#800000;\">- Grupo de investigaci&oacute;n en c&eacute;lulas gliales</span></a></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<strong><span style=\"color:#800000;\">- </span><a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/INcentivemos%20el%20conocimiento-CBarcia4.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color:#696969;\">Carlos Barcia</span><span style=\"color:#800000;\">- Neuroimmunity</span></a></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<strong><span style=\"color:#800000;\">- </span><a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/INcentivemos%20el%20conocimiento-JDalton5.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color:#696969;\">James Dalton- </span><span style=\"color:#800000;\">Neurofarmacolog&iacute;a molecular y bioinformatica</span></a></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<strong><span style=\"color:#800000;\">- </span><a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/INcentivemos%20el%20conocimiento-EUdina6.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color:#696969;\">Esther Udina</span><span style=\"color:#800000;\">- Neuroplasticidad y regeneraci&oacute;n</span></a></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<strong>-<span style=\"color:#696969;\"> </span><a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/INcentivemos%20el%20conocimiento-PBarros7.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color:#696969;\">Pol Barr&oacute;s-</span> <span style=\"color:#800000;\">Neurobiolog&iacute;a del aprendizaje y la memoria</span></a></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<strong><span style=\"color:#800000;\">- </span><a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/INcentivemos%20el%20conocimiento-DTorrents8.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color:#696969;\">David Torrents-</span><span style=\"color:#800000;\"> Laboratorio humano</span></a></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<strong><span style=\"color:#800000;\">- </span><a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/INcentivemos%20el%20conocimiento-VClos9.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color:#696969;\">Victoria Clos- </span><span style=\"color:#800000;\">Neurofarmacolog&iacute;a del Alzheimer</span></a></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong><span style=\"color:#800000;\">- </span><a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/INcentivemos%20el%20conocimiento-VMartinez10.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color:#696969;\">Vicente Mart&iacute;nez-</span><span style=\"color:#800000;\"> Neuroimmunogastroenterologia y Microbiota Intestinal</span></a></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong><a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/INcentivemos%20el%20conocimiento-RMasgrau11.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color:#696969;\">- Roser Masgrau-</span><span style=\"color:#800000;\"> Astrolab</span></a></strong></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n',71,2,1),(536,46,0,'','<h2 align=\"center\">\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><strong>Inc</strong></span><span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>ite knowledge</strong></span></h2>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong>Jaume Ferrer Lalanza (age 29)</strong></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>Research Support Technician</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/jaume f_opt.png\" style=\"width: 350px; height: 263px;\" /></strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong><em>1.- Jaume, tell us about your career until now.</em></strong></p>\n<p>\n	I studied Psychology and during my last year of degree, I was captivated by the fact that it was possible to mimic and understand human behavior by using animal models. This led me to do my practicum at the <em>Institut de Neuroci&egrave;ncies</em>. Then, I continued with this research topic in my master degree and later on with my PhD project. During my PhD, I also had the chance of doing an international internship in Vancouver (Canada), where I learned different histological techniques, which I did not know well at that time. But the deeper I explored the histological aspect the more I realized that I preferred to dedicate myself to the behavioral aspect of neuroscience. Then, one year after my PhD dissertation, I got this position of supporting technician at the INc.</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong><em>2.- Given your academic training, do you think that both disciplines, Psychology and Neurosciences, are integrated enough in your research?</em></strong></p>\n<p>\n	That integration is very important, but it is not easy to implement. For me, although basic neuroscience allows understanding many of the mechanisms of the brain processing, it is also critical to know how those changes affect behavior. Especially, because understanding these behavioral outcomes are an increasing concern for our society.</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong><em>3.- During you thesis studies, what kind of research did you perform?</em></strong></p>\n<p>\n	Mainly, we tried to simulate people&rsquo;s life styles in animal models. Particularly, we studied how physical exercise and fast food consumption contributes to obesity, and we evaluated its psychological effects, monitoring all the possible variables.</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong><em>4.- What do you mean exactly with fast food?</em></strong></p>\n<p>\n	It is the unhealthy food that we usually consume in some bars or fast food restaurants: such as hot dogs, bacon, muffins, cream cheese, etc. It was surprising to observe that although this diet was clearly harmful in many physiological aspects, it had however some beneficial effects: For example, anxiety in these animals decreased and, intriguingly, their sociability was improved. We hypothesized that these positive psychological effects could be one of the reasons why these types of diets are alarmingly increasing in our society.</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong><em>5.- Do you think that this research with animal models can be transferred to the human behavior?</em></strong></p>\n<p>\n	We think that we can extrapolate many of the data. In fact, our study was based on human routines (for example, the classical recommendation of 30 minutes of exercise) that we adapt to an animal model but minimizing the variables -rats don&rsquo;t go to the movies, they don&rsquo;t have problems at work, or they don&rsquo;t discuss about who has to wash the dishes-. Then, with the results obtained in rat models, it is interesting to go back to the human scenario and use these data to revisit the recommendations that we take about diets and exercise.</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong><em>6.- What did you discover about physical exercise?</em></strong></p>\n<p>\n	The most relevant finding was the fact that exercise provided a benefit regarding the release of particular stress hormones. Exercise prepares the whole organism to respond more efficiently to stimuli that cause anxiety.</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong><em>7.- Vindicate your job as a technician. What is the technician role in a research group?</em></strong></p>\n<p>\n	Mainly, we give technical support in very important aspects of the research, specially when other researchers do not have the right time to dedicate to specific tasks, or providing the expertise of techniques in which they do not feel confident enough to do by themselves etc. I think that is a very important role and I believe that every research group has to integrate people with different profiles, including specialized technicians.</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong><em>8.- Enlighten a little the present socioeconomic pessimism. What would you recommend to students that want to initiate a career in neuroscience?</em></strong></p>\n<p>\n	I would recommend finding the right group in which they feel comfortable. Sometimes working on research is hard and, for me, the most important aspect is to feel motivated and supported by your group. I may say that this aspect cold be even more important than to find your favorite research subject; if it&rsquo;s closely related to your essential goals, you will enjoy it as well.</p>\n<p>\n	I also recommend participating in all kind of activities: poster presentations in meetings; give scientific talks, participate in dissemination activities etc. Everything counts when you need to apply for scholarships. In my case, I didn&rsquo;t get a post-doc scholarship for a few scoring points and, therefore, I would encourage everyone to participate in these kind of activities.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	Listen to the <u><a href=\"https://soundcloud.com/user-872279367/entrevista-raul-andero\" target=\"_blank\">whole interview</a><a href=\"https://soundcloud.com/user-872279367/entrevista-a-jaume-ferrer\" target=\"_blank\"> here</a>.&nbsp;</u></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	Previous releases:</p>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/_RaulAnderoangl%C3%A8s.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">- </a><strong><a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/_RaulAnderoangl%C3%A8s.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color:#696969;\">Ra&uuml;l Andero- </span></a><span style=\"color:#800000;\"><a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/_RaulAnderoangl%C3%A8s.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Neurobiology of stress and addiction</a></span></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/_INcitate%20knowledge%20-%20Elisenda%20Sanz.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><strong><span style=\"color:#800000;\">- </span><span style=\"color:#696969;\">Elisenda Sanz-</span> <span style=\"color:#000000;\">Mitochondrial Neuropthology</span></strong></a></p>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/_INcitate%20knowledge-AMinano1.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><strong><span style=\"color:#800000;\">- </span></strong></a><strong><a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/_INcitate%20knowledge-AMinano1.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color:#696969;\">Alfredo J.Mi&ntilde;ano-</span></a><span style=\"color:#800000;\"><a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/_INcitate%20knowledge-AMinano1.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"> Mollecular and Cellular basis of Neuronal Survival</a></span></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/_INcitate%20knowledge-NDaviu2.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><strong><span style=\"color:#800000;\">- </span></strong></a><strong><a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/_INcitate%20knowledge-NDaviu2.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color:#696969;\">N&uacute;ria Daviu- </span></a><span style=\"color:#800000;\"><a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/_INcitate%20knowledge-NDaviu2.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Neurobiology of stress and adiction</a></span></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/_INcitate%20knowledge-BAlmolda3.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><strong><span style=\"color:#800000;\">- </span></strong></a><strong><a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/_INcitate%20knowledge-BAlmolda3.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color:#696969;\">Beatriz Almolda- </span></a><span style=\"color:#800000;\"><a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/_INcitate%20knowledge-BAlmolda3.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">BBG-Glial research team</a></span></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/_INcitate%20knowledge-CBarcia4.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><strong><span style=\"color:#800000;\">- </span></strong></a><strong><a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/_INcitate%20knowledge-CBarcia4.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color:#696969;\">Carlos Barcia</span></a><span style=\"color:#800000;\"><a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/_INcitate%20knowledge-CBarcia4.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">- Neuroimmunity</a></span></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/_INcitate%20knowledge-JDalton5.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><strong><span style=\"color:#800000;\">- </span></strong></a><strong><a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/_INcitate%20knowledge-JDalton5.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color:#696969;\">James Dalton- </span></a><span style=\"color:#800000;\"><a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/_INcitate%20knowledge-JDalton5.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Molecular Neuropharmacology and Bioinformatics</a></span></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/_INcitate%20knowledge-EUdina6.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><strong><font color=\"#800000\">- </font></strong></a><strong><a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/_INcitate%20knowledge-EUdina6.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color:#696969;\">Esther Udina-</span></a><span style=\"color:#800000;\"><a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/_INcitate%20knowledge-EUdina6.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"> Neuroplasticity and regeneration</a></span></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/_INcitate%20Knowledge-PBarros7.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><strong><span style=\"color:#800000;\">- </span></strong></a><strong><a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/_INcitate%20Knowledge-PBarros7.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color:#696969;\">Pol Barr&oacute;s- </span></a><span style=\"color:#800000;\"><a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/_INcitate%20Knowledge-PBarros7.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Neurobiology of learning and memory research group</a></span></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/_INcitate%20knowledge-%20DTorrents8.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><strong><span style=\"color:#800000;\">- </span></strong></a><strong><a><span style=\"color:#696969;\">David Torrents-</span></a></strong><strong><span style=\"color:#800000;\"><a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/_INcitate%20knowledge-%20DTorrents8.pdf\"> Human Lab</a></span></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/_INcitate%20knowledge-VClos9.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><strong><span style=\"color:#800000;\">- </span></strong></a><strong><a href=\"/DocsCKeditor/files/_INcit