			<a href=\"http://www.researchgate.net/profile/Roser_Masgrau\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"30\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/researchgate.jpg\" width=\"30\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"https://es.linkedin.com/pub/roser-masgrau-juanola/51/19b/800\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"34\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Linkedin.jpg\" width=\"42\" /></a></td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"http://www.icrea.cat/Web/ScientificStaff/Elena-Galea-248\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.icrea.cat/Web/ScientificStaff/Elena-Galea-248</a></p>\n<p>\n	<br />\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/astrolabWEB.jpg\" style=\"width: 100%;\" /></p>\n<p>\n	<strong>Membres del grup:</strong></p>\n<p>\n	Luis Pardo &ndash;estudiant de doctorat<br />\n	Abel Eraso &ndash;estudiant de doctorat<br />\n	Arantxa Golbano &ndash;estudiant de doctorat<br />\n	Raquel Larramona &ndash;estudiant de doctorat<br />\n	Marina Rierola &ndash;estudiant de m&agrave;ster<br />\n	Agust&iacute; Bruzzese &ndash;estudiant de m&agrave;ster</p>\n<p>\n	<strong>Membres anteriors:</strong></p>\n<p>\n	Dra. Paulina Carriba<br />\n	Dra. Gemma Huesa<br />\n	Miquel Barcel&oacute;<br />\n	Mateu Lichtenstein<br />\n	Rub&eacute;n Villalonga<br />\n	Elena Vicario</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>OBJECTIUS ESTRAT&Egrave;GICS</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	Tot i que els astr&ograve;cits han estat menyspreats durant d&egrave;cades, actualment es sap que tenen un paper important&iacute;ssim en la regulaci&oacute; de la transmissi&oacute; sin&agrave;ptica i en la plasticitat neuronal. Aquestes funcions dels astr&ograve;cits s&oacute;n possibles perqu&egrave; s&oacute;n c&egrave;l&middot;lules excitables, tot i que la seva excitabilitat no es basa en potencials d&rsquo;acci&oacute; sin&oacute; en ones de calci intra i inter cel&middot;lulars. Els astr&ograve;cits, a m&eacute;s, protegeixen a les neurones de l&rsquo;estr&eacute;s oxidatiu, i s&rsquo;ha postulat que en malalties neurodegeneratives els astr&ograve;cits poden contribuir a la patologia per p&egrave;rdua de funcionalitat o per prove&iuml;r-se d&rsquo;una funci&oacute; t&ograve;xica.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	Els objectius principals del nostre grup s&oacute;n:</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	1.- Trobar els mecanismes moleculars pels quals els astr&ograve;cits regulen els processos de formaci&oacute; de la mem&ograve;ria<br />\n	2.- Establir els astr&ograve;cits com a diana terap&egrave;utica en la neurodegeneraci&oacute; i l&rsquo;isqu&egrave;mia.</p>\n<p>\n	<br />\n	<strong><span style=\"color:#800000;\">PRINCIPALS L&Iacute;NIES D&#39;INVESTIGACI&Oacute;</span></strong></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	1.<em>El CREB astrocitari</em>. Es pret&eacute;n&nbsp; analitzar el paper de&nbsp;CREB&nbsp;en la plasticitat dels astr&ograve;cits (canvis morfol&ograve;gics o funcionals en aquestes c&egrave;l&middot;lules que afecten a l&#39;efic&agrave;cia sin&agrave;ptica) incloent: gliotransmissors que activin la transcripci&oacute; de CREB;&nbsp; quins gens s&#39;expressen, i si afecten a l&rsquo;excitabilitat astrocit&agrave;ria, &eacute;s a dir, les respostes de calci en astr&ograve;cits, i als models de mem&ograve;ria com la LTP en neurones. Projecte finan&ccedil;at pel Ministeri d&rsquo;Economia i Competitivitat, Gobierno de Espa&ntilde;a. BFU2012-38844 &ndash; El CREB astrocitario como diana terap&eacute;utica del Alzheimer. Gener 2013- Desembre2015</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	2.<em> Els astr&ograve;cits en l&rsquo;Alzheimer.</em> El nostre objectiu &eacute;s definir els astr&ograve;cits en termes moleculars, estructurals i funcionals, aix&iacute; com esbrinar els efectes en les neurones del TNF-alfa produits pels astr&ograve;cits . Projecte finan&ccedil;at per La Marat&oacute; de TV3. 127/c/2014- Dexifrant la relaci&oacute; entre la reactivitat dels astr&ograve;cits i el dany neuronal en la malaltia de l&rsquo;Alzheimer.&nbsp; Gener 2015-Desembre 2017</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<em>3. Els astr&ograve;cits en les &nbsp;leucodistr&ograve;fies.</em> L&rsquo;adrenoleucodistr&ograve;fia lligada al cromossoma X (X-ALD) &eacute;s una malaltia neurodegenerativa caracteritzada per una progressiva desmielietzaci&oacute;, insufici&egrave;ncia adrenal&nbsp; i accumulaci&oacute; d&rsquo;&agrave;cids grassos de cadena molt llarga. El paper dels astr&ograve;cits en aquesta patologia ha estat molt poc estudiada. El nostre objectiu general &eacute;s estudiar els processos patol&ograve;gics comuns entre l&rsquo;X-ALD i l&rsquo;Alzheimer, tals com la disfunci&oacute; del proteosoma, l&rsquo;estress reticular i la defici&egrave;ncia del factor de transcripci&oacute; Nrf2, clau en la resposta antioxidant produ&iuml;da pels astr&ograve;cits. Projecte finan&ccedil;at per la Fundaci&oacute; Europea de Leukodistrofies. ELA-2012-033C1B Cellular proteolysis and oxidative stress as intertwined therapeutic targets in X-ALD: preclinical studies. Septembre 2013- Setembre 2016.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>COL.LABORACIONS</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	- Angel Barco, Institut de Neuroci&egrave;ncies, Alacant.<br />\n	- Grant Churchill, University of Oxford, Oxford, U.K.<br />\n	- Manuel Comabella, Hospital Vall d&#39;Hebron.<br />\n	-Joan Comella, Institut de Recerca Vall d&#39;Hebron, Barcelona.<br />\n	- Antonia Guti&eacute;rrez, Universidad de M&aacute;laga.<br />\n	- Bradley Hyman, Mass General Hospital for Neurodegenerative Disease, Boston, USA<br />\n	- Aurora Pujol, Institut d&#39; Investigaci&oacute; Biomedica Bellvitge, Barcelona.<br />\n	-Eugene Stanley i Will Morrison, Boston University<br />\n	-Javier Vitorica, Instituto de Investigaciones Biom&eacute;dicas, Hospital Virgen del Roc&iacute;o, Sevilla.<br />\n	- Grups del mateix SGR i grups de l&rsquo;INc (UAB)<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PUBLICACIONS DESTACADES</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp; Morat&oacute; L, Galino J, Ruiz M, Calingasan NY, Starkov AA, Dumont M, Naud&iacute; A, Mart&iacute;nez JJ, Aubourg P, Portero-Ot&iacute;n M, Pamplona R, <strong>Galea E</strong>, Beal MF, Ferrer I, Fourcade S, Pujol A.<br />\n	<em>Pioglitazone halts axonal degeneration in a mouse model of X-linked adrenoleukodystrophy.</em><br />\n	Brain. <strong>2013</strong> 136(Pt 8):2432-43.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp; Carriba P, Pardo L, Parra-Damas A, Lichtenstein MP, Saura CA, Pujol A, <strong>Masgrau R, Galea E</strong>.<br />\n	<em>ATP and noradrenaline activate CREB in astrocytes via noncanonical Ca(2+) and cyclic AMP independent pathways.</em><br />\n	Glia. <strong>2012</strong> 60(9):1330-44.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp; <strong>Galea E</strong>, Launay N, Portero-Otin M, Ruiz M, Pamplona R, Aubourg P, Ferrer I, Pujol A.<br />\n	<em>Oxidative stress underlying axonal degeneration in adrenoleukodystrophy: a paradigm for multifactorial neurodegenerative diseases?</em><br />\n	Biochim Biophys Acta. <strong>2012</strong>;1822(9):1475-88</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; Barcel&oacute;-Torns M, Lewis AM, Gubern A, Barneda D, Bloor-Young D, Picatoste F, Churchill GC, Claro E, <strong>Masgrau R</strong>.<br />\n	<em>NAADP mediates ATP-induced Ca2+ signals in astrocytes.</em><br />\n	FEBS Lett. <strong>2011</strong>;585(14):2300-6.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; Lichtenstein MP, Carriba P, <strong>Masgrau R</strong>, Pujol A, <strong>Galea E</strong>.<br />\n	<em>Staging anti-inflammatory therapy in Alzheimer&#39;s disease. </em><br />\n	Front Aging Neurosci. <strong>2010</strong>;2:142.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830816/public/\" target=\"_blank\">Veure m&eacute;s publicacions de E. Galea a PubMed.</a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830827/public/\" target=\"_blank\">Veure m&eacute;s publicacions de R. Masgrau a PubMed.</a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n',21,2,0),(584,52,0,'Elena Galea y Roser Masgrau','<p>\n	<a href=\"javascript:MostraPage(377,1); \">Neurodegeneraci&oacute;n y envejecimiento</a></p>\n<h2>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\">Astrolab</span></h2>\n<p>\n	<br />\n	<strong>L&iacute;deres del Grupo:</strong></p>\n<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				Elena Galea Rodr&iacute;guez de Velasco</td>\n			<td style=\"text-align: center;\">\n				Roser Masgrau Juanola</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:galea.inc@gmail.com\">galea.inc@gmail.com</a></td>\n			<td style=\"text-align: center;\">\n				<a href=\"mailto:Roser.Masgrau@uab.cat\">Roser.Masgrau@uab.cat</a></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				TEL: +34 935 868 143</td>\n			<td>\n				&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; TEL: +34 935 814 278</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<table>\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researcherid.com/rid/E-1362-2011\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/RID.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=7005633898\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 29px; height: 29px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researchgate.net/profile/Elena_Galea\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/researchgate.jpg\" style=\"width: 27px; height: 27px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n				<table>\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0002-6722-5939\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/orcid.png\" style=\"width: 26px; height: 26px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researcherid.com/rid/D-3047-2011\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/RID.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<p>\n									<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=6602791655\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 29px; height: 29px;\" /></a></p>\n							</td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researchgate.net/profile/Roser_Masgrau\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"30\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/researchgate.jpg\" width=\"30\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"https://es.linkedin.com/pub/roser-masgrau-juanola/51/19b/800\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"34\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Linkedin.jpg\" width=\"42\" /></a></td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"http://www.icrea.cat/Web/ScientificStaff/Elena-Galea-248\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.icrea.cat/Web/ScientificStaff/Elena-Galea-248</a></p>\n<p>\n	<br />\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/astrolabWEB.jpg\" style=\"width: 100%;\" /></p>\n<p>\n	<strong>Miembros del grupo:</strong></p>\n<p>\n	Luis Pardo &ndash;estudiante de doctorado<br />\n	Abel Eraso &ndash;estudiante de doctorado<br />\n	Arantxa Golbano &ndash;estudiante de doctorado<br />\n	Raquel Larramona &ndash;estudiante de doctorado<br />\n	Marina Rierola &ndash;estudiante de master<br />\n	Agust&iacute; Bruzzese &ndash;estudiante de master</p>\n<p>\n	<strong>Miembros anteriores:</strong></p>\n<p>\n	Dra. Paulina Carriba<br />\n	Dra. Gemma Huesa<br />\n	Miquel Barcel&oacute;<br />\n	Mateu Lichtenstein<br />\n	Rub&eacute;n Villalonga<br />\n	Elena Vicario</p>\n<p>\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>OBJETIVOS ESTRAT&Eacute;GICOS</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	Aunque los astrocitos han sido despreciados durante d&eacute;cadas, actualmente se sabe que tienen un papel important&iacute;simo en la regulaci&oacute;n de la transmisi&oacute;n sin&aacute;ptica y en la plasticidad neuronal. Estas funciones de los astrocitos son posibles porque son c&eacute;lulas excitables, aunque su excitabilidad no se basa en potenciales de acci&oacute;n sino en olas de calcio intra e inter celulares. Los astrocitos, adem&aacute;s, protegen a las neuronas del estr&eacute;s oxidativo, y se ha postulado que en enfermedades neurodegenerativas los astrocitos pueden contribuir en la patolog&iacute;a por p&eacute;rdida de funcionalidad o para proveerse de una funci&oacute;n t&oacute;xica.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	Los objetivos principales de nuestro grupo son:</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	1. Encontrar los mecanismos moleculares por los cu&aacute;les los astrocitos regulan los procesos de formaci&oacute;n de la memoria.<br />\n	2. Establecer los astrocitos como diana terap&eacute;utica en la neurodegeneraci&oacute;n y la isquemia.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PRINCIPALES L&Iacute;NEAS DE INVESTIGACI&Oacute;N</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	1.<em>El CREB astrocitario</em>. Se pretende analizar el papel de CREB en la plasticidad de los astrocitos (cambios morfol&oacute;gicos o funcionales en estas c&eacute;lulas que afectan a la eficacia sin&aacute;ptica) incluyendo: gliotransmisores que activen la transcripci&oacute;n CREB; qu&eacute; genes se expresan, y si afectan a la excitabilidad astrocitaria, es decir, las respuestas del calcio en los astrocitos, y en los modelos de memoria como la LTP en neuronas. Proyecto financiado por el Ministerio de Econom&iacute;a y Competitividad, Gobierno de Espa&ntilde;a. BFU2012-38844- <em>El CREB astrocitario como diana terap&eacute;utica del Alzheimer. Enero 2013-Diciembre2015.</em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	2. <em>Los astrocitos en Alzheimer</em>. Nuestro objetivo es definir los astrocitos en t&eacute;rminos moleculares, estructurales y funcionales, as&iacute; como averiguar los efectos en las neuronas del TNF- alfa producido por astrocitos. Proyecto financiado por &ldquo;La Marat&oacute; de TV3&rdquo;. 127/C/2014- <em>Dexifrant la relaci&oacute; entre la reactivitat dels astr&ograve;cits i el dany neuronal en la malaltia de l&rsquo;Alzheimer. Gener 2015- Desembre 2017</em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	3. La adrenoleucodistrofialigada al cromosoma X (X-ALD) es una enfermedad neurodegenerativa caracterizada por una progresiva desmielinizaci&oacute;n, insuficiencia adrenal y acumulaci&oacute;n de &aacute;cidos grasos de cadena muy larga. El papel de los astrocitos en esta patolog&iacute;a ha sido casi desconocido. Nuestro objetivo general es estudiar los procesos patol&oacute;gicos comunes entre el X-ALD y el Alzheimer, tales como la disfunci&oacute;n del proteosoma, el estr&eacute;s reticular y la deficiencia del factor de transcripci&oacute;n NRF2, clave en la respuesta antioxidante producida por los astrocitos. Proyecto financiado por la Fundaci&oacute;n Europea de <em>Leukodistrofies. ELA- 2012-033C1B Cellular proteolysis and oxidative stress as intertwined therapeutic targets in X- ALD: preclinical studies. Septiembre 2013- Septiembre 2016</em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>COLABORACIONES</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	- Angel Barco, Institut de Neuroci&egrave;ncies, Alacant.<br />\n	- Grant Churchill, University of Oxford, Oxford, U.K.<br />\n	- Manuel Comabella, Hospital Vall d&#39;Hebron.<br />\n	-Joan Comella, Institut de Recerca Vall d&#39;Hebron, Barcelona.<br />\n	- Antonia Guti&eacute;rrez, Universidad de M&aacute;laga.<br />\n	- Bradley Hyman, Mass General Hospital for Neurodegenerative Disease, Boston, USA<br />\n	- Aurora Pujol, Institut d&#39; Investigaci&oacute; Biomedica Bellvitge, Barcelona.<br />\n	-Eugene Stanley y Will Morrison, Boston University<br />\n	-Javier Vitorica, Instituto de Investigaciones Biom&eacute;dicas, Hospital Virgen del Roc&iacute;o, Sevilla.<br />\n	- Otros grupos de investigaci&oacute;n del INc.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<br />\n	<strong><span style=\"color:#800000;\">PUBLICACIONES DESTACADAS</span></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp; Morat&oacute; L, Galino J, Ruiz M, Calingasan NY, Starkov AA, Dumont M, Naud&iacute; A, Mart&iacute;nez JJ, Aubourg P, Portero-Ot&iacute;n M, Pamplona R, <strong>Galea E</strong>, Beal MF, Ferrer I, Fourcade S, Pujol A.<br />\n	<em>Pioglitazone halts axonal degeneration in a mouse model of X-linked adrenoleukodystrophy.</em><br />\n	Brain. <strong>2013</strong> 136(Pt 8):2432-43.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp; Carriba P, Pardo L, Parra-Damas A, Lichtenstein MP, Saura CA, Pujol A, <strong>Masgrau R, Galea E</strong>.<br />\n	<em>ATP and noradrenaline activate CREB in astrocytes via noncanonical Ca(2+) and cyclic AMP independent pathways.</em><br />\n	Glia. <strong>2012</strong> 60(9):1330-44.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp; <strong>Galea E</strong>, Launay N, Portero-Otin M, Ruiz M, Pamplona R, Aubourg P, Ferrer I, Pujol A.<br />\n	<em>Oxidative stress underlying axonal degeneration in adrenoleukodystrophy: a paradigm for multifactorial neurodegenerative diseases?</em><br />\n	Biochim Biophys Acta. <strong>2012</strong>;1822(9):1475-88</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; Barcel&oacute;-Torns M, Lewis AM, Gubern A, Barneda D, Bloor-Young D, Picatoste F, Churchill GC, Claro E, <strong>Masgrau R</strong>.<br />\n	<em>NAADP mediates ATP-induced Ca2+ signals in astrocytes.</em><br />\n	FEBS Lett. <strong>2011</strong>;585(14):2300-6.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; Lichtenstein MP, Carriba P, <strong>Masgrau R</strong>, Pujol A, <strong>Galea E</strong>.<br />\n	<em>Staging anti-inflammatory therapy in Alzheimer&#39;s disease. </em><br />\n	Front Aging Neurosci. <strong>2010</strong>;2:142.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830816/public/\" target=\"_blank\">Ver m&aacute;s publicaciones de E. Galea en PubMed.</a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830827/public/\" target=\"_blank\">Ver m&aacute;s publicaciones de R. Masgrau en PubMed.</a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n',28,2,1),(585,45,0,'Elena Galea & Roser Masgrau','<p>\n	<a href=\"javascript:MostraPage(372,1); \">Neurodegeneration and ageing</a></p>\n<h2>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\">Astrolab</span></h2>\n<p>\n	<strong>Group leaders:</strong></p>\n<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				Elena Galea Rodr&iacute;guez de Velasco</td>\n			<td style=\"text-align: center;\">\n				Roser Masgrau Juanola</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:galea.inc@gmail.com\">galea.inc@gmail.com</a></td>\n			<td style=\"text-align: center;\">\n				<a href=\"mailto:Roser.Masgrau@uab.cat\">Roser.Masgrau@uab.cat</a></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				TEL: +34 935 868 143</td>\n			<td>\n				&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; TEL: +34 935 814 278</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<table>\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researcherid.com/rid/E-1362-2011\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/RID.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=7005633898\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 29px; height: 29px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researchgate.net/profile/Elena_Galea\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/researchgate.jpg\" style=\"width: 27px; height: 27px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n				<table>\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0002-6722-5939\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/orcid.png\" style=\"width: 26px; height: 26px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researcherid.com/rid/D-3047-2011\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/RID.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<p>\n									<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.url?authorId=6602791655\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 29px; height: 29px;\" /></a></p>\n							</td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://www.researchgate.net/profile/Roser_Masgrau\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"30\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/researchgate.jpg\" width=\"30\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"https://es.linkedin.com/pub/roser-masgrau-juanola/51/19b/800\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"34\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Linkedin.jpg\" width=\"42\" /></a></td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"http://www.icrea.cat/Web/ScientificStaff/Elena-Galea-248\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.icrea.cat/Web/ScientificStaff/Elena-Galea-248</a></p>\n<p>\n	<br />\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/astrolabWEB.jpg\" style=\"width: 100%;\" /></p>\n<p>\n	<strong>Group members:</strong></p>\n<p>\n	Luis Pardo &ndash; PhD student<br />\n	Abel Eraso &ndash; PhD student<br />\n	Arantxa Golbano &ndash; PhD student<br />\n	Raquel Larramona &ndash; PhD student<br />\n	Marina Rierola &ndash; Master student<br />\n	Agust&iacute; Bruzzese &ndash; Master student</p>\n<p>\n	<strong>Former group members:</strong></p>\n<p>\n	Dra. Paulina Carriba<br />\n	Dra. Gemma Huesa<br />\n	Miquel Barcel&oacute;<br />\n	Mateu Lichtenstein<br />\n	Rub&eacute;n Villalonga<br />\n	Elena Vicario</p>\n<p>\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>STRATEGIC OBJECTIVES</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	In healthy brains, astrocytes modulate neurotransmission: they surround synapses and, under the control of calcium transients, respond to, take up and release neurotransmitters, namely glutamate, D-serine, ATP, or TNF-alpha. Astrocytes have been implicated in various cellular processes allegedly related to memory acquisition such as neuronal synchronization, inhibitory synaptic transmission, long-term potentiation (LTP) and synaptic scaling. Astrocytes also protect neurons from oxidative stress. In neurodegenerative diseases, astrocytes may contribute to pathology by loss-of-function or gain of toxic function.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	The general objectives of our research group are:</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	1. To find out molecular mechanisms by which astrocytes regulate memory formation<br />\n	2. To establish astrocytes as a therapeutic target in neurodegeneration</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>MAIN RESEARCH LINES</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<em>1.- Astrocytic CREB</em>- We seek to analyze the role of CREB in astrocyte plasticity (changes in astrocytes, either morphological or functional, that affect synaptic efficiency): i) what gliotransmitters activate CREB-dependent transcription and how, ii) what genes are expressed, and iii) if they evoke a cellular memory changing the overall response of astrocytes, akin to LTP in neurons. Project funded by: Ministerio de Economia y Competividad, Gobierno de Espa&ntilde;a. BFU2012-38844 &ndash; El CREB astrocitario como diana terap&eacute;utica del Alzheimer. January 2013- December2015</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<em>2.-Astrocytes in Alzheimer-</em> Our purpose is to characterize astrocytes in structural, molecular, and functional terms in Alzheimer`s disease as well as we try to elucidate the effects of astrocyte-produced TNF-alpha on neurons. Project funded by: La Marat&oacute; de TV3. 127/c/2014- Dexifrant la relaci&oacute; entre la reactivitat dels astr&ograve;cits i el dany neuronal en la malaltia de l&rsquo;Alzheimer.&nbsp; Jannuary 2015-Desember 2017</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<em>3.- &nbsp;Astrocytes in Leukodystrophies</em>- X-ALD is a severe neurodegenerative disorder characterized by progressive demyelination within the central (CNS) and peripheral nervous system (PNS), adrenal insufficiency and accumulation of very long-chain fatty acids (VLCFA) due to their impaired &beta;-oxidation in peroxisomes. We aim to determine the role of astrocytes on pathological pathways common to X-ALD and AD such asproteasome system (UPS) dysfunction, endoplasmic reticulum (ER) stress and deficiency of the transcription factor Nrf2, a main factor in anti-oxidant defense that is mainly produced by astrocytes. Project funded by: European Leukodystrophies Association ELA-2012-033C1B Cellular proteolysis and oxidative stress as intertwined therapeutic targets in X-ALD: preclinical studies. September 2013- September 2016</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>COLLABORATIONS</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	- Angel Barco, Institut de Neuroci&egrave;ncies, Alacant.<br />\n	- Grant Churchill, University of Oxford, Oxford, U.K.<br />\n	- Manuel Comabella, Hospital Vall d&#39;Hebron.<br />\n	-Joan Comella, Institut de Recerca Vall d&#39;Hebron, Barcelona.<br />\n	- Antonia Guti&eacute;rrez, Universidad de M&aacute;laga.<br />\n	- Bradley Hyman, Mass General Hospital for Neurodegenerative Disease, Boston, USA<br />\n	- Aurora Pujol, Institut d&#39; Investigaci&oacute; Biomedica Bellvitge, Barcelona.<br />\n	-Eugene Stanley and Will Morrison, Boston University<br />\n	-Javier Vitorica, Instituto de Investigaciones Biom&eacute;dicas, Hospital Virgen del Roc&iacute;o, Sevilla.<br />\n	- Other INc research groups<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>FEATURED PUBLICATIONS</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp; Morat&oacute; L, Galino J, Ruiz M, Calingasan NY, Starkov AA, Dumont M, Naud&iacute; A, Mart&iacute;nez JJ, Aubourg P, Portero-Ot&iacute;n M, Pamplona R, <strong>Galea E</strong>, Beal MF, Ferrer I, Fourcade S, Pujol A.<br />\n	<em>Pioglitazone halts axonal degeneration in a mouse model of X-linked adrenoleukodystrophy.</em><br />\n	Brain. <strong>2013</strong> 136(Pt 8):2432-43.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp; Carriba P, Pardo L, Parra-Damas A, Lichtenstein MP, Saura CA, Pujol A, <strong>Masgrau R, Galea E</strong>.<br />\n	<em>ATP and noradrenaline activate CREB in astrocytes via noncanonical Ca(2+) and cyclic AMP independent pathways.</em><br />\n	Glia. <strong>2012</strong> 60(9):1330-44.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp; <strong>Galea E</strong>, Launay N, Portero-Otin M, Ruiz M, Pamplona R, Aubourg P, Ferrer I, Pujol A.<br />\n	<em>Oxidative stress underlying axonal degeneration in adrenoleukodystrophy: a paradigm for multifactorial neurodegenerative diseases?</em><br />\n	Biochim Biophys Acta. <strong>2012</strong>;1822(9):1475-88</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; Barcel&oacute;-Torns M, Lewis AM, Gubern A, Barneda D, Bloor-Young D, Picatoste F, Churchill GC, Claro E, <strong>Masgrau R</strong>.<br />\n	<em>NAADP mediates ATP-induced Ca2+ signals in astrocytes.</em><br />\n	FEBS Lett. <strong>2011</strong>;585(14):2300-6.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; Lichtenstein MP, Carriba P, <strong>Masgrau R</strong>, Pujol A, <strong>Galea E</strong>.<br />\n	<em>Staging anti-inflammatory therapy in Alzheimer&#39;s disease. </em><br />\n	Front Aging Neurosci. <strong>2010</strong>;2:142.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830816/public/\" target=\"_blank\">See more E. Galea in PubMed.</a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48830827/public/\" target=\"_blank\">See more R. Masgrau in PubMed.</a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n',28,2,2),(586,29,0,'TESIS DOCTORALS I TREBALLS DE RECERCA 2015','<p>\n	<strong><span style=\"color:#800000;\">Tesis</span></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>T&iacute;tol: Genetic studies of emotional behaviour in rats</strong><br />\n	Tesi doctoral: Carme Mont Cardona<br />\n	Director: Albert Fern&aacute;ndez Teruel i Jonathan Flint</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>T&iacute;tol: Lipid dorpolet biogenesis: A novel process of self-digestion as a strategy of survival to stress</strong><br />\n	Tesi doctoral: Ainara Gonz&aacute;lez Cabodevilla<br />\n	Director/s: Enrique Claro i Albert Gubern</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>T&iacute;tol: Implication of mast cells, nerve growth factor and splanchnic nerves in postoperative ileus. St