td>\n			<td colspan=\"2\">\n				<p>\n					<a href=\"http://agaur.gencat.cat/ca/beques-i-ajuts/convocatories-per-temes/Ajuts-per-donar-suport-a-les-activitats-dels-grups-de-recerca-SGR-2014-2016?category=38a49d6f-9296-11e5-a40e-005056924a59\" target=\"_blank\">SUPORT GRUP DE RECERCA (AGAUR)</a></p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n				<p>\n					JOS&Eacute; RODR&Iacute;GUEZ &Aacute;LVAREZ</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<p>\n					Models animals i humans en trastorns mentals</p>\n			</td>\n			<td colspan=\"2\">\n				<p>\n					<a href=\"http://agaur.gencat.cat/ca/beques-i-ajuts/convocatories-per-temes/Ajuts-per-donar-suport-a-les-activitats-dels-grups-de-recerca-SGR-2014-2016?category=38a49d6f-9296-11e5-a40e-005056924a59\" target=\"_blank\">SUPORT GRUP DE RECERCA (AGAUR)</a></p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n				<p>\n					ALBERTO FERN&Aacute;NDEZ TERUEL</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<p>\n					Grup de Recerca per a Malalties Autoinmunes Desmielinitzants</p>\n			</td>\n			<td colspan=\"2\">\n				<p>\n					<a href=\"http://agaur.gencat.cat/ca/beques-i-ajuts/convocatories-per-temes/Ajuts-per-donar-suport-a-les-activitats-dels-grups-de-recerca-SGR-2014-2016?category=38a49d6f-9296-11e5-a40e-005056924a59\" target=\"_blank\">SUPORT GRUP DE RECERCA (AGAUR)</a></p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n				<p>\n					MIGUEL CHILL&Oacute;N RODR&Iacute;GUEZ</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n',6,1,2),(727,30,0,'Premis i Mèrits',NULL,14,0,0),(728,30,0,'ICREA Acadèmia','<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<table style=\"width: 100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong>2014</strong></span></td>\n			<td>\n				&nbsp;</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<strong><span style=\"color: rgb(128, 0, 0);\"><span style=\"color: rgb(128, 0, 0);\"><span style=\"color: rgb(128, 0, 0);\">ICREA ACAD&Egrave;MIA, Roser Nadal Alemany</span></span></span></strong></td>\n			<td>\n				&nbsp;</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n				<a href=\"http://inc.uab.cat/Catala/profile.php?id=104\">Roser Nadal</a> &eacute;s professora del Departament de Psicobiologia i de Metodologia de les Ci&egrave;ncies de la Salut i membre de l&#39;Institut de Neuroci&egrave;ncies. La seva recerca tracta sobre els mecanismes pels quals l&#39;estr&egrave;s incrementa la vulnerabilitat a la psicopatologia, com l&#39;ansietat, l&#39;addicci&oacute;, l&#39;estr&egrave;s post-traum&agrave;tic, la depressi&oacute; o la impulsivitat, utilitzant models animals. La Dra. Nadal est&agrave; especialment interessada en les difer&egrave;ncies individuals en la reactivitat a l&#39;estr&egrave;s i els factors involucrats en la resist&egrave;ncia als efectes negatius del mateix.</td>\n			<td>\n				<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\n					<span style=\"color: rgb(128, 0, 0);\"><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Noticies/RNadalICREA.JPG\" style=\"width: 95px; margin: 10px; height: 106px;\" /></strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<br />\n				<span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong>2013</strong></span></td>\n			<td>\n				&nbsp;</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<strong><span style=\"color: rgb(128, 0, 0);\"><span style=\"color: rgb(128, 0, 0);\"><span style=\"color: rgb(128, 0, 0);\">ICREA ACAD&Egrave;MIA, Alberto Fern&aacute;ndez Teruel</span></span></span></strong></td>\n			<td>\n				&nbsp;</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n				<a href=\"http://inc.uab.cat/Catala/profile.php?id=63\">Alberto Fern&aacute;ndez Teruel</a> &eacute;s professor del Departament de Psiquiatria i Medicina Legal i membre de l&#39;Institut de Neuroci&egrave;ncies. Les investigacions del Dr. Fernandez-Teruel tenen com a objectiu millorar el coneixement sobre les bases psicol&ograve;giques, neurobiol&ograve;giques i gen&egrave;tiques de diverses malalties psicol&ograve;giques i neurol&ograve;giques com s&oacute;n els processos relacionats amb l&#39;estr&egrave;s, la impulsivitat, l&#39;addicci&oacute;, l&#39;esquizofr&egrave;nia o l&#39;envelliment.</td>\n			<td>\n				<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\n					<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Noticies/AFerndef.jpg\" style=\"width: 95px; height: 116px; margin: 10px;\" /></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong>2011</strong></span></td>\n			<td>\n				&nbsp;</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<strong><span style=\"color: rgb(128, 0, 0);\"><span style=\"color: rgb(128, 0, 0);\"><span style=\"color: rgb(128, 0, 0);\">ICREA ACAD&Egrave;MIA, Carlos A Saura</span></span></span></strong></td>\n			<td>\n				&nbsp;</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n				<a href=\"http://inc.uab.cat/Catala/profile.php?id=126\">Carlos A. Saura</a> &eacute;s professor del Departament de Bioqu&iacute;mica i Biologia Molecular (Facultat de Medicina) i membre de l&#39;Institut de Neuroci&egrave;ncies, on lidera el grup de Neurobiologia de la malaltia d&#39;Alzheimer. La seva recerca est&agrave; dirigida a dilucidar els mecanismes de disfunci&oacute; neuronal i sin&agrave;ptica en la malaltia d&#39;Alzheimer, aix&iacute; com a dissenyar noves estrat&egrave;gies terap&egrave;utiques per prevenir i/o revertir la disfunci&oacute; cognitiva en aquesta malaltia.</td>\n			<td>\n				<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\n					<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Noticies/ICREACSaura.jpg\" style=\"width: 95px; height: 63px; margin: 10px;\" /></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n',15,1,0),(729,45,0,'Awards and Merits',NULL,14,0,2),(730,45,0,'ICREA Academy','<table style=\"width: 100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong>2014</strong></span></td>\n			<td>\n				&nbsp;</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<span style=\"color: rgb(128, 0, 0);\"><strong>ICREA ACADEMY, Roser Nadal</strong></span></td>\n			<td>\n				&nbsp;</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n				<a href=\"http://inc.uab.cat/English/profile.php?id=104\">Roser Nadal Alemany</a> is Professor at the Department of Psychobiology and Methodology of Health Sciences and member of the <em>Institut de Neuroci&egrave;ncies</em>. Her research deals with the mechanisms by which stress increases vulnerability to psychopathology, such as anxiety, addiction, post-traumatic stress, depression or impulsivity, using animal models. Dr. Nadal is especially interested in individual differences in stress reactivity and the factors involved in resistance to the negative effects of it.</td>\n			<td>\n				<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\n					<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Noticies/RNadalICREA.JPG\" style=\"width: 95px; margin: 10px; height: 106px;\" /></strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<br />\n				<span style=\"color:#000000;\"><strong>2013</strong></span></td>\n			<td>\n				&nbsp;</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>ICREA ACADEMY, Alberto Fern&aacute;ndez Teruel</strong></span></td>\n			<td>\n				&nbsp;</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n				<a href=\"http://inc.uab.cat/English/profile.php?id=63\">Alberto Fernandez Teruel</a> is Professor of Psychiatry and Legal Medicine and member of the <em>Institut de Neuroci&egrave;ncies</em>. The research of Dr. Fernandez Teruel aims to improve the knowledge of the psychological, neurobiological and genetic characteristics of various psychological and neurological diseases such as stress-related processes, impulsiveness, addiction, schizophrenia or aging.</td>\n			<td>\n				<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\n					<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Noticies/AFerndef.jpg\" style=\"width: 95px; height: 116px; margin: 10px;\" /></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<span style=\"color:#000000;\"><strong>2011</strong></span></td>\n			<td>\n				&nbsp;</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>ICREA ACADEMY, Carlos A Saura</strong></span></td>\n			<td>\n				&nbsp;</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n				<a href=\"http://inc.uab.cat/English/profile.php?id=126\">Carlos A. Saura</a> is Professor of Biochemistry and Molecular Biology (Faculty of Medicine) and member of the <em>Institut de Neuroci&egrave;ncies</em>, where he leads the group of Neurobiology of Alzheimer&#39;s disease. His research is aimed at elucidating the mechanisms of neuronal and synaptic dysfunction in Alzheimer&#39;s disease and to design new therapeutic strategies to prevent and/or reverse cognitive dysfunction in this disease.</td>\n			<td>\n				<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\n					<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Noticies/ICREACSaura.jpg\" style=\"width: 95px; height: 63px; margin: 10px;\" /></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n',15,1,2),(731,30,0,'Comitè científic extern',NULL,16,0,0),(732,30,0,'Composició del comitè científic','<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<table height=\"951\" style=\"width: 100%\" width=\"402\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td colspan=\"2\">\n				<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>Prof. James Fawcett</strong></span>, University of Cambridge (UK)</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n					<a href=\"http://www.neuroscience.cam.ac.uk/directory/profile.php?jf108\" target=\"_blank\">James Fawcett</a> &eacute;s President del Centre John van Geest de Reparaci&oacute; Cerebral de la Universitat de Cambridge. El seu inter&egrave;s principal &eacute;s la reparaci&oacute; de danys en el sistema nervi&oacute;s central (SNC), en particular de la medul&middot;la espinal. El seu objectiu principal ha estat estudiar per qu&egrave; la plasticitat i la regeneraci&oacute; axonal deixen de funcionar en el SNC adult, aix&iacute; com trobar la manera de tornar-los a activar. Tamb&eacute; treballa en interf&iacute;cies electr&ograve;niques amb el sistema nervi&oacute;s danyat, i en el disseny de protocols per assaigs cl&iacute;nics de lesi&oacute; de medul&middot;la espinal.</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n				<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/Fawcett final.jpg\" style=\"width: 95px; height: 130px; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px;\" /></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td colspan=\"2\">\n				<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>Prof. Patricia Janak</strong>,</span> Johns Hopkins University (USA)</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n					La <a href=\"http://pbs.jhu.edu/research/janak/facultyinfo/\" target=\"_blank\">Prof. Janak</a> lidera un grup d&#39;investigaci&oacute; en el Departament de Psicologia i Ci&egrave;ncies del Cervell de la Universitat Johns Hopkins a Baltimore, EUA. S&#39;interessa pels mecanismes tant conductuals com neuronals implicats en l&#39;aprenentatge, aix&iacute; com els sistemes neuronals que controlen el comportament guiat per est&iacute;muls despr&eacute;s del proc&eacute;s d&#39;aprenentatge.</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n				<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/Janakweb.jpg\" style=\"width: 95px; height: 133px; margin: 10px;\" /></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td colspan=\"2\">\n				<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>Prof. Kamran Khodakhah</strong>,</span> Albert Einstein College of Medicine (USA)</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n					El <a href=\"http://www.einstein.yu.edu/faculty/8472/Kamran-Khodakhah/\" target=\"_blank\">Dr. Khodakhah </a>&eacute;s professor al Departament de Neuroci&egrave;ncies, al Departament de Psiquiatria i Ci&egrave;ncies del Comportament, i al Departament de Neurologia a l&#39;Albert Einstein College of Medicine, Nova York. L&#39;objectiu de la seva investigaci&oacute; &eacute;s entendre el paper del cerebel i els ganglis basals en la funci&oacute; motora, i tamb&eacute; en trastorns neurol&ograve;gics i del moviment.</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n				<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/Kamranweb.jpg\" style=\"width: 95px; height: 122px; margin: 10px;\" /></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td colspan=\"2\">\n				<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>Prof. Hugh V Perry</strong>, </span>University of Southampton (UK)</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n					El <a href=\"http://www.southampton.ac.uk/biosci/about/staff/vhp.page\" target=\"_blank\">Dr. Perry</a> &eacute;s professor de Neuropatologia Experimental al Centre de Ci&egrave;ncies Biol&ograve;giques de la Universitat de Southampton, Regne Unit. El seu inter&egrave;s principal de recerca &eacute;s el paper de la inflamaci&oacute; en el sistema nervi&oacute;s central i la seva contribuci&oacute; a les malalties neurol&ograve;giques (esclerosi m&uacute;ltiple, malaltia de prions, lupus, degeneraci&oacute; macular relacionada amb l&#39;edat, etc.).</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n				<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/Perryweb.jpg\" style=\"width: 95px; height: 71px; margin: 10px;\" /></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td colspan=\"2\">\n				<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>Prof. Jean-Philippe Pin</strong>,</span> Institute for Functional Genomics of Montpellier (France)</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n					El <a href=\"http://www.igf.cnrs.fr/index.php/en/h-research-en/h-departments-en/h-neuroscience-en/h-pin-prezeau-en\" target=\"_blank\">Dr. Pin</a> estudia els receptors acoblats a prote&iuml;nes G (GPCR), tant la seva funci&oacute; com els seus mecanismes d&#39;activaci&oacute; a nivell molecular i cel&middot;lular. Espec&iacute;ficament se centra en els receptors metabotr&ograve;pics de glutamat (mGlu) i els receptors GABA<sub>B</sub>, i el seu potencial com a dianes terap&egrave;utiques prometedores per al tractament de diversos trastorns neurol&ograve;gics i psiqui&agrave;trics, com ara la malaltia de Parkinson i el dolor.</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n				<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/Pinweb.jpg\" style=\"width: 95px; height: 118px; margin: 10px;\" /></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td colspan=\"2\">\n				<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>Prof. John Salamone</strong>,</span> University of Connecticut (USA)</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n					El <a href=\"http://psych.uconn.edu/faculty/john-salamone/\" target=\"_blank\">Prof. Salamone</a> pertany al Departament de Ci&egrave;ncies Psicol&ograve;giques de la Universitat de Connecticut (EUA), on &eacute;s Cap de la Divisi&oacute; de Neuroci&egrave;ncia del Comportament. S&#39;interessa per una &agrave;mplia gamma de disciplines com la psicofarmacologia, la neuroqu&iacute;mica i el comportament, les funcions de la dopamina i l&#39;acetilcolina en el comportament, la malaltia de Parkinson, l&#39;esquizofr&egrave;nia o la depressi&oacute;.</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n				<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/salamoneweb.jpg\" style=\"width: 95px; height: 72px; margin: 10px;\" /></td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n',17,1,0),(733,52,0,'Comité científico externo',NULL,16,0,1),(734,52,0,'Composición comité científico','<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<table height=\"951\" style=\"width: 100%;\" width=\"402\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td colspan=\"2\">\n				<span style=\"color: rgb(128, 0, 0);\"><strong>Prof. James Fawcett</strong></span>, University of Cambridge (UK)</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n					<a href=\"http://www.neuroscience.cam.ac.uk/directory/profile.php?jf108\" target=\"_blank\">James Fawcett</a> es Presidente del Centro John van Geest de Reparaci&oacute;n Cerebral de la Universidad de Cambridge. Su inter&eacute;s principal es la reparaci&oacute;n de da&ntilde;os en el sistema nervioso central (SNC), en particular de la m&eacute;dula espinal. Su objetivo principal ha sido estudiar por qu&eacute; la plasticidad y la regeneraci&oacute;n axonal dejan de funcionar en el SNC adulto, as&iacute; como encontrar la manera de volver a activarlas. Tambi&eacute;n trabaja en interfaces electr&oacute;nicas con el sistema nervioso da&ntilde;ado, y en el dise&ntilde;o de protocolos para ensayos cl&iacute;nicos de lesi&oacute;n de m&eacute;dula espinal.</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n				<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/Fawcett final.jpg\" style=\"width: 95px; height: 130px; margin: 10px;\" /></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td colspan=\"2\">\n				<span style=\"color: rgb(128, 0, 0);\"><strong>Prof. Patricia Janak</strong>,</span> Johns Hopkins University (USA)</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n					La <a href=\"http://pbs.jhu.edu/research/janak/facultyinfo/\" target=\"_blank\">Prof. Janak</a> lidera un grupo de investigaci&oacute;n en el Departamento de Psicolog&iacute;a y Ciencias del Cerebro de la Universidad Johns Hopkins en Baltimore, EE.UU. Se interesa por los mecanismos tanto conductuales como neuronales implicados en el aprendizaje, as&iacute; como los sistemas neuronales que controlan el comportamiento guiado por est&iacute;mulos despu&eacute;s del proceso de aprendizaje..</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n				<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/Janakweb.jpg\" style=\"width: 95px; height: 133px; margin: 10px;\" /></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td colspan=\"2\">\n				<span style=\"color: rgb(128, 0, 0);\"><strong>Prof. Kamran Khodakhah</strong>,</span> Albert Einstein College of Medicine (USA)</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n					El <a href=\"http:// http://www.einstein.yu.edu/faculty/8472/Kamran-Khodakhah/\" target=\"_blank\">Dr. Khodakhah</a> es profesor en el Departamento de Neurociencias, en el Departamento de Psiquiatr&iacute;a y Ciencias del Comportamiento, y en el Departamento de Neurolog&iacute;a en el Albert Einstein College of Medicine, Nueva York. El objetivo de su investigaci&oacute;n es entender el papel del cerebelo y los ganglios basales en la funci&oacute;n motora, y tambi&eacute;n en trastornos neurol&oacute;gicos y del movimiento.</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n				<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/Kamranweb.jpg\" style=\"width: 95px; height: 122px; margin: 10px;\" /></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td colspan=\"2\">\n				<span style=\"color: rgb(128, 0, 0);\"><strong>Prof. Hugh V Perry</strong>, </span>University of Southampton (UK)</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n					El <a href=\"http://www.southampton.ac.uk/biosci/about/staff/vhp.page\" target=\"_blank\">Dr. Perry</a> es profesor de Neuropatolog&iacute;a Experimental en el Centro de Ciencias Biol&oacute;gicas de la Universidad de Southampton, Reino Unido. Su inter&eacute;s principal de investigaci&oacute;n es el papel de la inflamaci&oacute;n en el sistema nervioso central y su contribuci&oacute;n a las enfermedades neurol&oacute;gicas (esclerosis m&uacute;ltiple, enfermedad de priones, lupus, degeneraci&oacute;n macular relacionada con la edad, etc.).</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n				<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/Perryweb.jpg\" style=\"width: 95px; height: 71px; margin: 10px;\" /></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td colspan=\"2\">\n				<span style=\"color: rgb(128, 0, 0);\"><strong>Prof. Jean-Philippe Pin</strong>,</span> Institute for Functional Genomics of Montpellier (France)</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n					El <a href=\"http://www.igf.cnrs.fr/index.php/en/h-research-en/h-departments-en/h-neuroscience-en/h-pin-prezeau-en\" target=\"_blank\">Dr. Pin</a> estudia los receptores acoplados a prote&iacute;nas G (GPCR), tanto su funci&oacute;n como los mecanismos de activaci&oacute;n a nivel molecular y celular. Espec&iacute;ficamente se centra en los receptores metabotr&oacute;picos de glutamato (mGlu) y los receptores GABA<sub>B</sub>, y su potencial como dianas terap&eacute;uticas prometedoras para el tratamiento de diversos trastornos neurol&oacute;gicos y psiqui&aacute;tricos, tales como la enfermedad de Parkinson y el dolor.</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n				<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/Pinweb.jpg\" style=\"width: 95px; height: 118px; margin: 10px;\" /></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td colspan=\"2\">\n				<span style=\"color: rgb(128, 0, 0);\"><strong>Prof. John Salamone</strong>,</span> University of Connecticut (USA)</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n					El <a href=\"http://psych.uconn.edu/faculty/john-salamone/\" target=\"_blank\">Prof. Salamone</a> pertenece al Departamento de Ciencias Psicol&oacute;gicas de la Universidad de Connecticut (EE.UU.), donde es Jefe de la Divisi&oacute;n de Neurociencia del Comportamiento. Se interesa por una amplia gama de disciplinas como la psicofarmacolog&iacute;a, la neuroqu&iacute;mica y el comportamiento, las funciones de la dopamina y la acetilcolina en el comportamiento, la enfermedad de Parkinson, la esquizofrenia o la depresi&oacute;n.</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n				<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/salamoneweb.jpg\" style=\"width: 95px; height: 72px; margin: 10px;\" /></td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n',17,1,1),(735,45,0,'External scientific advisory board',NULL,16,0,2),(736,45,0,'Composition of the advisory board','<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<table height=\"951\" style=\"width: 100%;\" width=\"402\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td colspan=\"2\">\n				<span style=\"color: rgb(128, 0, 0);\"><strong>Prof. James Fawcett</strong></span>, University of Cambridge (UK)</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n					<a href=\"http://www.neuroscience.cam.ac.uk/directory/profile.php?jf108\" target=\"_blank\">James Fawcett</a> is Chairman of the John van Geest Centre for Brain Repair in the University of Cambridge. His main interest is the repair of CNS damage, particularly in the spinal cord. The main focus has been to work out how both axon regeneration and plasticity are turned off in the adult CNS, and how to restart them. He also works on interfacing electronics with the damaged nervous system and on the design of protocols for clinical trials in spinal cord injury.</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n				<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/Fawcett final.jpg\" style=\"width: 95px; height: 130px; margin: 10px;\" /></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td colspan=\"2\">\n				<span style=\"color: rgb(128, 0, 0);\"><strong>Prof. Patricia Janak</strong>,</span> Johns Hopkins University (USA)</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n					<a href=\"http://pbs.jhu.edu/research/janak/facultyinfo/\" target=\"_blank\">Prof. Janak</a> leads a research group at the Department of Psychological and Brain Sciences, from the Johns Hopkins University in Baltimore, USA. She is interested in the behavioral and neural mechanisms underlying learning, as well as the neural systems that control expression of stimulus-guided behavior after the learning process.</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n				<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/Janakweb.jpg\" style=\"width: 95px; height: 133px; margin: 10px;\" /></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td colspan=\"2\">\n				<span style=\"color: rgb(128, 0, 0);\"><strong>Prof. Kamran Khodakhah</strong>,</span> Albert Einstein College of Medicine (USA)</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n					<a href=\"http://www.einstein.yu.edu/faculty/8472/Kamran-Khodakhah/\" target=\"_blank\">Dr. Khodakhah</a> is Professor in the Department of Neuroscience, Department of Psychiatry and Behavioral Sciences, and Department of Neurology at Albert Einstein College of Medicine. The aim of his research is to understand the role of the cerebellum and basal ganglia in motor function and in movement and neurologic disorders.</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n				<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/Kamranweb.jpg\" style=\"width: 95px; height: 122px; margin: 10px;\" /></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td colspan=\"2\">\n				<span style=\"color: rgb(128, 0, 0);\"><strong>Prof. Hugh V Perry</strong>, </span>University of Southampton (UK)</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n					<a href=\"http://www.southampton.ac.uk/biosci/about/staff/vhp.page\" target=\"_blank\">Dr. Perry</a> is Professor of Experimental Neuropathology within the Centre for Biological Sciences at the University of Southampton (UK). His main research interest is the role of inflammation in the CNS and its contribution to neurological diseases (multiple sclerosis, prion disease, lupus, age-related macular degeneration, etc.).</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n				<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/Perryweb.jpg\" style=\"width: 95px; height: 71px; margin: 10px;\" /></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td colspan=\"2\">\n				<span style=\"color: rgb(128, 0, 0);\"><strong>Prof. Jean-Philippe Pin</strong>,</span> Institute for Functional Genomics of Montpellier (France)</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n					<a href=\"http://www.igf.cnrs.fr/index.php/en/h-research-en/h-departments-en/h-neuroscience-en/h-pin-prezeau-en\" target=\"_blank\">Dr. Pin </a>studies G protein-coupled receptors (GPCR) function and theirmechanisms of activation at molecular and cellular levels. Specifically he focuses on metabotropic glutamate receptors (mGlu) and GABA<sub>B</sub> receptors, and their potential as promising therapeutic targets for the treatment of various neurological and psychiatric disorders, such asParkinson&rsquo;s disease and pain.</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n				<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/Pinweb.jpg\" style=\"width: 95px; height: 118px; margin: 10px;\" /></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td colspan=\"2\">\n				<span style=\"color: rgb(128, 0, 0);\"><strong>Prof. John Salamone</strong>,</span> University of Connecticut (USA)</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n					<a href=\"http://psych.uconn.edu/faculty/john-salamone/\" target=\"_blank\">Prof. Salamone</a> belongs to the Department of Psychological Sciences at the University of Connecticut (USA), where he is Head of the Behavioral Neuroscience Division. He is interested in a broad range of disciplines such as psychopharmacology, neurochemistry and behavior, behavioral functions of dopamine and acetylcholine, Parkinson&#39;s disease, schizophrenia, or depression.</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n				<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/salamoneweb.jpg\" style=\"width: 95px; height: 72px; margin: 10px;\" /></td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n',17,1,2),(738,45,0,'Assumpció BOSCH MERINO','<h2>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><span class=\"short_text\" id=\"result_box\" lang=\"en\"><span class=\"hps\">Gene</span> <span class=\"hps\">therapy</span> <span class=\"hps\">for</span> <span class=\"hps\">neuropathy</span></span></span></h2>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td colspan=\"6\">\n				<strong>Group leader:</strong></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td colspan=\"6\">\n				Assumpci&oacute; Bosch Merino</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td colspan=\"6\">\n				<a href=\"mailto:assumpcio.bosch@uab.cat\">assumpcio.bosch@uab.cat</a></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td colspan=\"6\">\n				TEL: +34 935 814 203</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<table>\n	<tbody>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0002-7205-2796\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/orcid.png\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"http://www.researcherid.com/rid/C-7593-2015\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/RID.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"http://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.uri?authorId=7101699999\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/scopus.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Assumpcio_Bosch\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/researchgate.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n			<td>\n				&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"https://es.linkedin.com/pub/assumpci%C3%B3-bosch/2b/b33/781\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Linkedin.jpg\" style=\"width: 35px; height: 29px;\" /></a></td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<table>\n	<tbody>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Pagines/ABoschgrup.jpg\" style=\"width: 100%;\" /></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>Group members:</strong><br />\n	Bel&eacute;n Garc&iacute;a Lareu<br />\n	Marc Leal Juli&agrave;<br />\n	Rolando Szilveszter Matos<br />\n	Meritxell Puig Ferrer<br />\n	Angela S&aacute;nchez Osuna<br />\n	<br />\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>STRATEGIC OBJECTIVES</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	The research activity of our group is focused on the development of gene therapy strategies affecting the nervous system, both central (lysosomal storage diseases) and peripheral (pain, genetic and acquired neurophaties) and on the elucidation of the molecular mechanisms implicated in the development of these pathologies combining the use of animal models, tissue cell culture and viral vectors.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	Funding: ISCIII; MINECO; EU; Feder-EU; AGAUR; Marat&oacute; TV3; Genzyme</p>\n<p>\n	<br />\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>MAIN RESEARCH LINES</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>1.Study of the tropism of different gene therapy viral vectors in the peripheral nervous system</strong><br />\n	<br />\n	Gene transfer to the peripheral nervous system (PNS) is particularly challenging as it involves several cell types, most of them post-mitotic. Efficient gene transfer to certain cell types of the PNS can be of great interest for gene therapy for neurological diseases or for pain treatment. Also important, delivery or inhibition of target molecules with viral vectors can be used as a tool to analyze physiological processes in the PNS, such as interactions between glia and neurons, retrograde or anterograde transport, nerve regeneration, etc. Within the aim to determine the most efficient gene transfer vectors for each cell type in the PNS, we are characterizing the tropism of different pseudotypes of AAV vectors and different human and non-human adenoviral vectors through different routes of administration.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>2.Gene therapy for diabetic neurological complications</strong><br />\n	<br />\n	Diabetic complications involve both sensorimotor and autonomic components of the peripheral nervous system (PNS). Sensorimotor neuropathy developed by diabetic patients is the most common peripheral neuropathy affecting in different degrees all types of nerve fibers and causing loss of pain sensation, burst sensation and cutaneous hyperestesia, typically starting at the feet and the lower part of the legs but progressing to hands and arms. In more advanced stages, foot ulcers and neuropathic deformities appear, which could lead to 40% of the non-traumatic limb amputations.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	The pathology of diabetic sensorimotor neuropathy is characterized by axonal atrophy and demyelination, leading to nerve fiber loss followed by abnormal regeneration of these fibers. Despite insulin treatment or pancreas transplantation, progression of diabetic neuropathy is not stopped, indicating the need for a specific treatment at early stages of the diabetes.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	Our team is studying the molecular mechanisms leading to the development of diabetic neuropathy, using primary cell cultures and mouse models of the disease, with the aim to elucidate new therapeutic targets for this complication of the diabetes. In more detail, we are studying the effect of hyperglicemia in the demyelination of the PNS and the role of trophic factors or other molecules implicated in the cellular signaling between sensory neurons and Schwann cells to stimulate the expression of myelin proteins and the regeneration of the PNS.<br />\n	<br />\n	<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>FEATURED PUBLICATIONS</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	&bull; R. Thwaite, G. Pages, M. Chillon, and A. Bosch<br />\n	<em>AAVrh.10 immunogenicity in mice and humans. relevance of antibody cross-reactivity in human gene therapy</em><br />\n	Gene Therapy: 22: 196-201<strong>(2015)<br />\n	<br />\n	&bull; </strong>L. Ariza, L. Gim&eacute;nez-Llort, A. Cubizolle, G. Pag&egrave;s, B. Garc&iacute;a-Lareu, N. Serratrice, D. Cots, M. Chillon, E. Kremer and A. Bosch<br />\n	<em>CNS delivery of helper-dependent canine adenovirus corrects neuropathology and behavior in Mucopolysaccharidosis type VII mice</em><br />\n	Human Gene Therapy: 25(3):199-211<strong> (2014</strong><strong>)</strong></p>\n<p>\n	<strong>&bull; </strong>L. Ariza, G. Pag&egrave;s, B. Garcia-Lareu, PJ Otaegui, J Ruberte, M. Chillon, X Navarro, A.Bosch<br />\n	<em>Experimental diabetes in neonatal mice induces early peripheral sensorimotor neuropathy.</em><br />\n	Neuroscience 274: 250-9; PMID: 24846610.<strong> (2014).</strong></p>\n<p>\n	<strong>&bull; </strong>J. Homs, G. Pag&egrave;s, L. Ariza, C. Casas, M. Chillon, X. Navarro, A. Bosch<br />\n	<em>Intrathecal administration of IGF-I by AAVrh10 improves sensory and motor deficits in a mouse model of diabetic neuropathy.</em><br />\n	Molec Ther-Meth &amp; Clin Dev 1, 7; doi:10.1038/mtm.2013.7.(<strong>2014)</strong>.</p>\n<p>\n	<strong>&bull; </strong>J. Homs, L. Ariza, G. Pag&egrave;s, E. Udina, X. Navarro, M. Chill&oacute;n, A. Bosch .<br />\n	<em>Schwann cell targeting via intrasciatic injection of AAV8 as gene therapy strategy for peripheral nerve regeneration. </em><br />\n	Gene Therapy 18(6):622-30. <strong>(2011)</strong></p>\n<p style=\"margin-left:21.3pt;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	See more publications at&nbsp; PubMed</p>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"http://inc.uab.cat/DocsCKeditor/files/OPol-AltresPublicacions.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><br />\n	</a></p>\n',89,2,2),(739,30,0,'Miguel Chillon- Grup de Recerca per a Malalties Autoimmunes Desmielinitzants','<p>\n	<strong>Coordinador de l&#39;SGR:&nbsp; </strong></p>\n<table height=\"116\" width=\"141\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				Miguel Chill&oacute;n</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				TEL: +34 935 811910</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:Miguel.Chillon@uab.cat\">Miguel.Chillon@uab.cat</a></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<table height=\"36\" width=\"66\">\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-0840-2111\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/orcid.png\" style=\"width: 26px; height: 26px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/miguel-chillon-rodriguez-98496853\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Linkedin.jpg\" style=\"width: 35px; height: 29px;\" /> </a></td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	<br />\n	<strong>GRUPS D&#39;INVESTIGACI&Oacute;</strong><br />\n	<a href=\"http://inc.uab.cat/Catala/index.php#!/Nueva%20P%C3%A1gina_756_1_1\">- Assumpci&oacute; Bosch</a><br />\n	<a href=\"http://inc.uab.cat/Catala/index.php#!/Miguel%20Chill%C3%B3n_753_1\" target=\"_blank\">- Miguel Chill&oacute;n</a><br />\n	<a href=\"http://inc.uab.cat/Catala/index.php#!/Lydia%20GIMENEZ-LLORT_271_1\" target=\"_blank\">- Lydia Gim&eacute;nez</a><br />\n	<a href=\"http://inc.uab.cat/Catala/index.php#!/Ester%20FERN%C3%81NDEZ_268_1\" target=\"_blank\">- Ester Fern&aacute;ndez Gimeno</a></p>\n<p>\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/FotoSGRChillon_.jpg\" style=\"width: 100%;\" /></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>1. Desenvolupament d&#39;estrat&egrave;gies de terapia g&egrave;nica per malalties autoimmunes desmielinitzants.</strong><br />\n	L&#39;objectiu principal d&#39;aquesta l&iacute;nia &eacute;s treballar amb malalites autoimmunes desmielinitzants com l&#39;Esclerosi M&uacute;ltiple (EM) i la neuropatia diab&egrave;tica (ND), abordant-les de forma integral des de diferents angles, tant analitzant el proc&eacute;s autoimmune (paper dels TLR, desregulaci&oacute; de la via Th17,etc) com els mecanismes moleculars implicats en el proc&eacute;s de desmielinitzaci&oacute; (NRG1)</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>2. Desenvolupament d&#39;estrat&egrave;gies de ter&agrave;pia g&egrave;nica per malalties neurodegeneratives.</strong><br />\n	Desenvolupament d&#39; estrat&egrave;gies de ter&agrave;pia g&egrave;nica que permetin estabilitzar i revertir el proc&egrave;s de neurodegeneraci&oacute; observat en diferents malalties, ja siguin d&#39;origen gen&egrave;tic com a mucopolisacaridosis, o no, com l&#39;Alzheimer.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>3. Desenvolupament de vectors virals de ter&agrave;pia g&egrave;nica i optimitzaci&oacute; de la producci&oacute;/purificaci&oacute;. </strong><br />\n	Generaci&oacute; de vectors virals (AAVs,Ads) d&#39;alta qualitat per tal de fer estudis de ter&agrave;pia g&egrave;nica en models animals de malalties humanes. En els darrers anys s&#39;han optimitzat els sistemes d&#39;amplificaci&oacute; i purificaci&oacute; dels vectos cl&agrave;ssics Ad5 i AAV2, a m&eacute;s d&#39;altres serotips d&#39;AAV (AAV1, AAV5,AAV8,AAV9 i AAVrh10). En aquest sentit s&#39;ha creat la Unitat de Producci&oacute; de Vectors (UPV) com a plataforma tecnol&ograve;gica per grups externs.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	Ref. SGR: 2014-13554</p>\n',96,2,0),(740,52,0,'Miguel Chillon- Grupo de Investigación para Enfermedades Autoinmunes Desmielinizantes','<p>\n	<strong>Coordinador del Grupo:&nbsp; </strong></p>\n<table height=\"115\" width=\"153\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				Miguel Chill&oacute;n</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				TEL: +34 935 811910</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:Miguel.Chillon@uab.cat\">Miguel.Chillon@uab.cat</a></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<table height=\"36\" width=\"66\">\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-0840-2111\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/orcid.png\" style=\"width: 26px; height: 26px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/miguel-chillon-rodriguez-98496853\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Linkedin.jpg\" style=\"width: 35px; height: 29px;\" /> </a></td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	<br />\n	<strong>GRUPOS DE INVESTIGACI&Oacute;N</strong><strong>: </strong><br />\n	<a href=\"http://inc.uab.cat/Castellano/index.php#!/Assumpció Bosch_757_1\">- Assumpci&oacute; Bosch</a><br />\n	<a href=\"http://inc.uab.cat/Castellano/index.php#!/Miguel%20Chill%C3%B3n_752_1\" target=\"_blank\">- Miguel Chill&oacute;n</a><br />\n	<a href=\"http://inc.uab.cat/Castellano/index.php#!/Lydia%20Gimenez%20Llort_452_1\" target=\"_blank\">- Lydia Gim&eacute;nez</a><br />\n	<a href=\"http://inc.uab.cat/Castellano/index.php#!/Ester%20Fern%C3%A1ndez_449_1\" target=\"_blank\">- Ester Fern&aacute;ndez Gimeno</a></p>\n<p>\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/FotoSGRChillon_.jpg\" style=\"width: 100%;\" /></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>1. Desarrollo de estrategias de terapia g&eacute;nica para enfermedades autoinmunes desmielinizantes.</strong><br />\n	El objetivo principal de esta l&iacute;nea es trabajar con enfermedades autoinmunes desmielinizantes como la Esclerosis M&uacute;ltiple EM) i la neuropat&iacute;a diab&eacute;tica (ND), abord&aacute;ndolas de forma integral des de diferentes &aacute;ngulos, tanto analizando el proceso autoinmune (papel de los TLR, desregulaci&oacute;n de la v&iacute;a Th17, etc) como los mecanismos moleculares implicados en el proceso de desmielinizaci&oacute;n (NRG1).</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>2. Desarrollo de estrategias de terapia g&eacute;nica para enfermedades neurodegenerativas.</strong><br />\n	Desarrollo de estrategias de terapia g&eacute;nica que permitan estabilizar y revertir el proceso de neurodegeneraci&oacute;n observado en diferentes enfermedades, ya sean de origen gen&eacute;tico como la mucopolisacaridosis, o no, como el Alzheimer.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>3. Desarrollo de vectores virales de terapia g&eacute;nica y optimizaci&oacute;n de la producci&oacute;n/purificaci&oacute;n.</strong><br />\n	Generaci&oacute;n de vectores virales (AAVs, Ads) de alta calidad para hacer estudios de terapia g&eacute;nica de enfermedades humanas en modelos animales . En los &uacute;ltimos a&ntilde;os se han optimizado los sistemas de amplificaci&oacute;n y purificaci&oacute;n de los vectores cl&aacute;sicos Ad5 y AAV2, adem&aacute;s de otros serotipos de AAV (AAV1, AAV5, AAV8, AAV9 i AAVrh10). En este sentido se ha creado la Unidad de Producci&oacute;n de Vectores (UPV como plataforma tecnol&oacute;gica para grupos externos.<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<table align=\"left\" border=\"2\" height=\"48\" width=\"402\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"background-color: rgb(204, 0, 51);\">\n				<span style=\"color:#000000;\"><strong>GRUPO SGR 2014-13554</strong></span></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"background-color: rgb(204, 0, 51);\">\n				<span style=\"color:#000000;\"><strong>Coordinaci&oacute;n: Miguel Chill&oacute;n</strong></span></td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<h2>\n	&nbsp;</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n',92,2,1),(741,45,0,'Miguel Chillon- Research Group in Demyelinating Autoimmune Diseases','<p>\n	<strong>Group coordinator:&nbsp; </strong></p>\n<table height=\"115\" width=\"153\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				Miguel Chill&oacute;n</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				TEL: +34 935 811910</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:Miguel.Chillon@uab.cat\">Miguel.Chillon@uab.cat</a></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<table height=\"36\" width=\"66\">\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-0840-2111\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/orcid.png\" style=\"width: 26px; height: 26px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/miguel-chillon-rodriguez-98496853\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Linkedin.jpg\" style=\"width: 35px; height: 29px;\" /> </a></td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<div>\n	<br />\n	<strong>RESEARCH GROUPS</strong><br />\n	<a href=\"http://inc.uab.cat/English/index.php#!/Miguel%20Chill%C3%B3n_754_1\">- Miguel Chill&oacute;n</a></div>\n<div>\n	<a href=\"http://inc.uab.cat/English/index.php#!/Assumpció Bosch_755_1\">- Assumpci&oacute; Bosch</a><br />\n	<a href=\"http://inc.uab.cat/English/index.php#!/Lydia%20Gimenez%20Llort_419_1\" target=\"_blank\">- Lydia Gim&eacute;nez</a><br />\n	<a href=\"http://inc.uab.cat/English/index.php#!/Ester%20Fern%C3%A1ndez_416_1\" target=\"_blank\">- Ester Fern&aacute;ndez Gimeno</a></div>\n<p>\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/FotoSGRChillon_.jpg\" style=\"width: 100%;\" /></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>1.Development of gene therapy strategies for demyelinating autoimmune diseases. </strong><br />\n	The main objective of this line is to work with autoimmune demyelinating diseases such as multiple sclerosis and diabetic neurophaty, comprehensively addressing them from different angles, both analyzing the autoimmune process (role of TLR, Th17 pathway deregulation, etc.) as well as the molecular mechanisms involved in the demyelination process.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>2. Development of gene therapy strategies for neurodegenerative diseases. </strong><br />\n	Development of gene therapy strategies that allow stabilize and reverse the process of neurodegeneration observed in different diseases, either of genetic origin, such as mucopolisacaridosis, or not, such as Alzheimer&#39;s Disease.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<strong>3. Development of viral vectors for gene therapy and optimization of the production/purification.</strong><br />\n	Generation of high quality viral vectors (AAVs, Ads) for gene therapy studies in animal models of human diseases. In recent years we have optimized amplification and purification processes of AAVs and Adenovirus vectors, which had allowed us to create the Vector Production Unit (UPV) as a service for external groups.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	Ref. SGR: 2014-13554</p>\n',90,2,2),(742,51,0,'Seminarios 2015','<p style=\"margin:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt\">\n	<strong><span style=\"font-size:\n9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;color:dimgray\">23 GENER</span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt;\">\n	<strong><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;color:firebrick\">The neural basis of sexual attraction (or how you knew you liked sex before you tried it)</span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Arial, sans