iguez-122</a></u></span></div>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/44.jpg\" style=\"width: 100%;\" /></p>\n<p>\n	<strong>Membres del Grup:</strong></p>\n<div>\n	&Agrave;ngel Edo Salvador</div>\n<div>\n	Susana Miravet Delgado</div>\n<div>\n	Roberto Notario Manzano</div>\n<div>\n	Mar&iacute;a Ontiveros Gonz&aacute;lez</div>\n<div>\n	Jose Antonio Piedra Bueno</div>\n<div>\n	Meritxell Puig Ferrer</div>\n<div>\n	Marcos Tejero Ambrosio<span id=\"cke_bm_249E\" style=\"display: none;\">&nbsp;</span><span id=\"cke_bm_248E\" style=\"display: none;\">&nbsp;</span></div>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>OBJECTIUS ESTRAT&Egrave;GICS</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	Actualment la medicina encara t&eacute; molts reptes per resoldre, especialmente en malalties complexes, on est&aacute;n implicats un gran nombre de factors tant gen&egrave;tics com ambientals. Entre aquestes malalties hi destaquen les malalties neurodegeneratives i autoinmunes que afecten el Sistema Nervi&oacute;s Central (SCN), no nom&eacute;s perqu&egrave; l&rsquo;SCN &eacute;s de dif&iacute;cil acc&eacute;s pels tractaments farmacol&ograve;gics cl&agrave;ssics, sin&oacute; perqu&egrave; no existeixen tractaments curatius efica&ccedil;os per a aquestes malalties. Per fer front a aquests problemes hem centrat les nostres l&iacute;nies d&rsquo;investigaci&oacute; en estrat&egrave;gies de terapia g&eacute;nica per malalties autoinmunes i trastorns neurodegeneratius especialmente aquelles associades amb l&rsquo;envelliment.<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PRINCIPALS L&Iacute;NIES D&#39;INVESTIGACI&Oacute;</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	1) Mecanismes moleculars implicats en la formaci&oacute; de la memoria: Estudi de l&rsquo;alteraci&oacute; de les vies de senyalitzaci&oacute; en el SCN en envelliment no patol&ograve;gic i la malaltia d&rsquo;Alzheimer.</p>\n<p>\n	2) Estrat&egrave;gies de ter&agrave;pia g&eacute;nica per Esclerosis M&uacute;ltiple: una malaltia autoinmune que afecta el sistema nervi&oacute;s.</p>\n<p>\n	3) Generaci&oacute; i desenvolupament de vectors virals m&eacute;s selectius i menys immunog&egrave;nics</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PUBLICACIONS DESTACADES</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	- R. Thwayte, G. Pages, M. Chillon, and A. Bosch (<strong>2015</strong>)<br />\n	AAVrh.10 immunogenicity in mice and humans. relevance of antibody cross-reactivity in human gene therapy. Gene Therapy: 22: 196-201<br />\n	<br />\n	- J. Piedra, M. Ontiveros, S. Miravet, C. Penalva, M. Monfar, M. Chillon (<strong>2015</strong>) Development of a rapid, robust and universal picogreen-based method to titer adeno-associated vectors. Human Gene Therapy Methods;26(1):35-42<br />\n	<br />\n	- A. Mass&oacute;, A. S&aacute;nchez, L. Gim&eacute;nez-Llort J.M. Lizcano M. Ca&ntilde;ete, B. Garc&iacute;a, V. Torres-Lista, M. Puig, A. Bosch, M. Chillon (<strong>2015</strong>)<br />\n	Secreted and transmembrane alfa-klotho isoforms have different spatio-temporal profiles in brain during aging and Alzheimer&#39;s disease progression. Plos One, 10(11):e0143623<br />\n	<br />\n	- G. N. Condezo, R. Marabini, S. Ayora, J. M. Carazo, M. Chillon, C. San Mart&iacute;n (<strong>2015</strong>). Structures of adenovirus incomplete particles clarify capsid architecture and show maturation changes of packaging protein L1 52/55k. Journal of Virology, 89(18):9653-64<br />\n	<br />\n	- L. Ariza, L. Gim&eacute;nez-Llort, A. Cubizolle, G. Pag&egrave;s, B. Garc&iacute;a-Lareu, N. Serratrice, D. Cots, M. Chillon, E. Kremer and A. Bosch (<strong>2014</strong>)<br />\n	CNS delivery of helper-dependent canine adenovirus corrects neuropathology and behavior in Mucopolysaccharidosis type VII mice<br />\n	Human Gene Therapy: 25(3):199-211</p>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/49708434/public/\" target=\"_blank\"><u>Veure m&eacute;s publicacions de M. Chill&oacute;n en Pubmed</u></a></p>\n',99,2,0),(754,45,0,'Miguel Chillón','<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><a href=\"http://inc.uab.cat/English/index.php#!/Strategic%20research%20areas_351_1\" target=\"_blank\">Neurodegeneration and Ageing</a></span></p>\n<h2>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\">G<b class=\"b5\">ene therapy strategies for Central Nervous Sistem Diseases</b></span></h2>\n<p>\n	<strong>Group leader:</strong></p>\n<table height=\"116\" width=\"141\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				Miguel Chill&oacute;n</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				TEL: +34 935 811910</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:Miguel.Chillon@uab.cat\">Miguel.Chillon@uab.cat</a></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<table height=\"36\" width=\"66\">\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-0840-2111\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/orcid.png\" style=\"width: 26px; height: 26px;\" /></a></td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/miguel-chillon-rodriguez-98496853\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Linkedin.jpg\" style=\"width: 35px; height: 29px;\" /> </a></td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<div>\n	<span style=\"color:#4b0082;\"><u><a href=\"http://sct.uab.cat/upv/\" target=\"_blank\">http://sct.uab.cat/upv/</a></u></span></div>\n<div>\n	<span style=\"color:#4b0082;\"><u><a href=\"https://www.icrea.cat/Web/ScientificStaff/miguel-chillon-rodriguez-122\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.icrea.cat/Web/ScientificStaff/miguel-chillon-rodriguez-122</a></u></span></div>\n<div>\n	&nbsp;</div>\n<p>\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/44.jpg\" style=\"width: 100%;\" /></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong>Group members:</strong></p>\n<div>\n	&Agrave;ngel Edo Salvador</div>\n<div>\n	Susana Miravet Delgado</div>\n<div>\n	Roberto Notario Manzano</div>\n<div>\n	Mar&iacute;a Ontiveros Gonz&aacute;lez</div>\n<div>\n	Jose Antonio Piedra Bueno</div>\n<div>\n	Meritxell Puig Ferrer</div>\n<div>\n	Marcos Tejero Ambrosio</div>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><span style=\"color:#800000;\"><span style=\"color:#800000;\"><span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>STRATEGIC OBJECTIVES</strong></span></span></span></span></p>\n<p>\n	Medicine still has many challenges to solve specially on complex diseases were a large number of both, genetic and environmental factors are involved. Among them, neurodegenerative and autoimmune disorders affecting the central nervous system have attracted attention because CNS is difficult to access and to manipulate with classical pharmacological treatments and, in addition, there are no effective curative treatments for these diseases. To address these problems we have focused our research interests in gene therapy strategies for autoimmune diseases and neurodegenerative disorders specially those associated to aging.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>MAIN RESEARCH LINES</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	1) Molecular mechanisms involved in memory formation: Study of altered signaling pathways in CNS in aging and in Alzheimer&#39;s Disease<br />\n	<br />\n	2) Gene Therapy Strategies for Esclerosis Multiple, an autoimmune disease affecting the nervous system<br />\n	<br />\n	3) Generation and development of more selective and less immunogenic viral vectors</p>\n<p>\n	<br />\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>SELECTED PUBLICATIONS</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	- R. Thwayte, G. Pages, M. Chillon, and A. Bosch (<strong>2015</strong>)<br />\n	AAVrh.10 immunogenicity in mice and humans. relevance of antibody cross-reactivity in human gene therapy. Gene Therapy: 22: 196-201<br />\n	<br />\n	- J. Piedra, M. Ontiveros, S. Miravet, C. Penalva, M. Monfar, M. Chillon (<strong>2015</strong>) Development of a rapid, robust and universal picogreen-based method to titer adeno-associated vectors. Human Gene Therapy Methods;26(1):35-42<br />\n	<br />\n	- A. Mass&oacute;, A. S&aacute;nchez, L. Gim&eacute;nez-Llort J.M. Lizcano M. Ca&ntilde;ete, B. Garc&iacute;a, V. Torres-Lista, M. Puig, A. Bosch, M. Chillon (<strong>2015</strong>)<br />\n	Secreted and transmembrane alfa-klotho isoforms have different spatio-temporal profiles in brain during aging and Alzheimer&#39;s disease progression. Plos One, 10(11):e0143623<br />\n	<br />\n	- G. N. Condezo, R. Marabini, S. Ayora, J. M. Carazo, M. Chillon, C. San Mart&iacute;n (<strong>2015</strong>). Structures of adenovirus incomplete particles clarify capsid architecture and show maturation changes of packaging protein L1 52/55k. Journal of Virology, 89(18):9653-64<br />\n	<br />\n	- L. Ariza, L. Gim&eacute;nez-Llort, A. Cubizolle, G. Pag&egrave;s, B. Garc&iacute;a-Lareu, N. Serratrice, D. Cots, M. Chillon, E. Kremer and A. Bosch (<strong>2014</strong>)<br />\n	CNS delivery of helper-dependent canine adenovirus corrects neuropathology and behavior in Mucopolysaccharidosis type VII mice<br />\n	Human Gene Therapy: 25(3):199-211</p>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/49708434/public/\" target=\"_blank\"><u>M. Chill&oacute;n in Pubmed</u></a></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n',95,2,2),(755,45,0,'Assumpció Bosch','<p>\n	<a href=\"http://inc.uab.cat/Catala/index.php#!/%C3%80rees%20estrat%C3%A8giques%20de%20recerca_223_1\">N</a><a href=\"http://inc.uab.cat/English/index.php#!/Strategic research areas_351_1\">euroregeneration and Repair</a></p>\n<h1>\n	<span style=\"color: rgb(128, 0, 0);\">Gene Therapy Strategies for Neuropathies</span></h1>\n<p>\n	<strong>Group leader:</strong></p>\n<table height=\"116\" width=\"141\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				Assumpci&oacute; Bosch</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				TEL: +34 93 581 4203</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:Assumpcio.Bosch@uab.cat\">Assumpcio.Bosch@uab.cat</a></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<table height=\"36\" width=\"66\">\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								<table height=\"63\" width=\"176\">\n									<tbody>\n										<tr>\n											<td>\n												<a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0002-7205-2796\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/orcid.png\" style=\"width: 26px; height: 26px;\" /></a></td>\n											<td>\n												<a href=\"http://www.researcherid.com/ProfileView.action?SID=P2kuQGYxkyrpJ1tyKI2&amp;returnCode=ROUTER.Success&amp;queryString=KG0UuZjN5WmZlFdP%252FqIpbTkk9zM0TtA40EwYW58wKzg%253D&amp;SrcApp=CR&amp;Init=Yes\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/RID.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n											<td>\n												<a href=\"https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Assumpcio_Bosch\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/researchgate.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n											<td>\n												<a href=\"https://es.linkedin.com/pub/assumpci%C3%B3-bosch/2b/b33/781\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Linkedin.jpg\" style=\"width: 35px; height: 29px;\" /></a></td>\n										</tr>\n									</tbody>\n								</table>\n							</td>\n							<td>\n								&nbsp;</td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/_ABoschgrup2pendent.jpg\" style=\"width: 402px;\" /></p>\n<p>\n	<b>Group members</b></p>\n<div>\n	Bel&eacute;n Garc&iacute;a Lareu</div>\n<div>\n	Marc Leal Juli&agrave;</div>\n<div>\n	Rolando Szilveszter Matos</div>\n<div>\n	Meritxell Puig Ferrer</div>\n<div>\n	&Aacute;ngela S&aacute;nchez Osuna</div>\n<div>\n	&nbsp;</div>\n<p>\n	<font color=\"#800000\"><b>STRATEGIC OBJECTIVES</b></font></p>\n<p>\n	The research activity of our group is focused on the development of gene therapy strategies for diseases affecting the nervous system, both central (lysosomal storage diseases) and peripheral (pain, genetic and acquired neuropathies) and on the elucidation of the molecular mechanisms implicated in the development of these pathologies combining the use of animal models, tissue cell culture and viral vectors.</p>\n<p>\n	Funding: ISCIII; MINECO; EU; Feder-EU; AGAUR, Marat&oacute; TV3; Genzyme</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong style=\"color: rgb(128, 0, 0);\">MAIN RESEARCH LINES</strong></p>\n<p>\n	<strong>1) Study of the tropism of different gene therapy viral vectors in the peripheral nervous system</strong></p>\n<p>\n	Gene transfer to the peripheral nervous system (PNS) is particularly challenging as it involves several cell types, most of them post-mitotic. Efficient gene transfer to certain cell types of the PNS can be of great interest for gene therapy for neurological diseases or for pain treatment. Also important, delivery or inhibition of target molecules with viral vectors can be used as a tool to analyze physiological processes in the PNS, such as interactions between glia and neurons, retrograde or anterograde transport, nerve regeneration, etc. Within the aim to determine the most efficient gene transfer vectors for each cell type in the PNS, we are characterizing the tropism of different pseudotypes of AAV vectors and different human and non-human adenoviral vectors through different routes of administration.</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong>2) Gene therapy for diabetic neurological complications</strong></p>\n<p>\n	Diabetic complications involve both sensorimotor and autonomic components of the peripheral nervous system (PNS). Sensorimotor neuropathy developed by diabetic patients is the most common peripheral neuropathy affecting in different degrees all types of nerve fibers and causing loss of pain sensation, burst sensation and cutaneous hyperestesia, typically starting at the feet and the lower part of the legs but progressing to hands and arms. In more advanced stages, foot ulcers and neuropathic deformities appear, which could lead to 40% of the non-traumatic limb amputations.</p>\n<p>\n	The pathology of diabetic sensorimotor neuropathy is characterized by axonal atrophy and demyelination, leading to nerve fiber loss followed by abnormal regeneration of these fibers. Despite insulin treatment or pancreas transplantation, progression of diabetic neuropathy is not stopped, indicating the need for a specific treatment at early stages of the diabetes.</p>\n<p>\n	Our team is studying the molecular mechanisms leading to the development of diabetic neuropathy, using primary cell cultures and mouse models of the disease, with the aim to elucidate new therapeutic targets for this complication of the diabetes. In more detail, we are studying the effect of hyperglicemia in the demyelination of the PNS and the role of trophic factors or other molecules implicated in the cellular signaling between sensory neurons and Schwann cells to stimulate the expression of myelin proteins and the regeneration of the PNS.</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong>3) Understanding and treating Mucopolysaccharidosis type VII</strong></p>\n<p>\n	Gene therapy is one of the most attractive treatments for diseases affecting the central nervous system (CNS) since blood-brain-barrier impairs delivery of systemically administered drugs to the cerebral parenchyma. Currently, some gene therapy clinical trials are ongoing for the treatment of some lysosomal storage diseases (LSD) with neuronal involvement, which are progressive neurological diseases affecting young children. However, the proper development and evaluation of these therapies requires understanding how cell signaling pathways are affected in these diseases and what is the impact on the viability or function of LSD cells and particulary in neurons. Other organs like bone or heart can be difficult to correct, even with high serum enzyme levels. We are paying particular attention to these tissues in a mouse model of Mucopolysaccahridosis type VII.</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<font color=\"#800000\"><b>FEATURED PUBLICATIONS&nbsp;</b></font></p>\n<p>\n	&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;R. Thwaite, G. Pages, M. Chillon, and A. Bosch (<strong>2015</strong>).</p>\n<p>\n	<em>AAVrh.10 immunogenicity in mice and humans. relevance of antibody cross-reactivity in human gene therapy.</em></p>\n<p>\n	Gene Therapy: 22: 196-201</p>\n<p>\n	&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;L. Ariza, L. Gim&eacute;nez-Llort, A. Cubizolle, G. Pag&egrave;s, B. Garc&iacute;a-Lareu, N. Serratrice, D. Cots, M. Chillon, E. Kremer and A. Bosch (<strong>2014</strong>).</p>\n<p>\n	<em>CNS delivery of helper-dependent canine adenovirus corrects neuropathology and behavior in Mucopolysaccharidosis type VII mice.</em></p>\n<p>\n	Human Gene Therapy: 25(3):199-211</p>\n<p>\n	&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;L. Ariza, G. Pag&egrave;s, B. Garcia-Lareu, PJ Otaegui, J Ruberte, M. Chillon, X Navarro, A. Bosch (<strong>2014</strong>).</p>\n<p>\n	<em>Experimental diabetes in neonatal mice induces early peripheral sensorimotor neuropathy.</em></p>\n<p>\n	Neuroscience 274: 250-9; PMID: 24846610.</p>\n<p>\n	&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;J. Homs, G. Pag&egrave;s, L. Ariza, C. Casas, M. Chillon, X. Navarro, A. Bosch (<strong>2014</strong>).</p>\n<p>\n	<em>Intrathecal administration of IGF-I by AAVrh10 improves sensory and motor deficits in a mouse model of diabetic neuropathy.</em></p>\n<p>\n	Molec Ther-Meth &amp; Clin Dev 1, 7; doi:10.1038/mtm.2013.7.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;J. Homs, L. Ariza, G. Pag&egrave;s, E. Udina, X. Navarro, M. Chill&oacute;n, A. Bosch (<strong>2011</strong>).</p>\n<p>\n	<em>Schwann cell targeting via intrasciatic injection of AAV8 as gene therapy strategy for peripheral nerve regeneration.</em></p>\n<p>\n	Gene Therapy 18(6):622-30.</p>\n<p>\n</p>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/48831039/public/\">See more A. Bosch in PubMed.</a></p>\n',96,2,2),(756,30,810,'Assumpció Bosch','<p>\n	<a href=\"http://inc.uab.cat/Catala/index.php#!/%C3%80rees%20estrat%C3%A8giques%20de%20recerca_223_1\">Neuroregeneraci&oacute; i reparaci&oacute;</a></p>\n<h1>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\">Estrat&egrave;gies de Ter&agrave;pia G&egrave;nica per Neuropaties</span></h1>\n<p>\n	<strong>L&iacute;der del grup:</strong></p>\n<table height=\"116\" width=\"141\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				Assumpci&oacute; Bosch</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				TEL: +34 93 581 4203</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:Assumpcio.Bosch@uab.cat\">Assumpcio.Bosch@uab.cat</a></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<table height=\"36\" width=\"66\">\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								<table height=\"63\" width=\"176\">\n									<tbody>\n										<tr>\n											<td>\n												<a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0002-7205-2796\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/orcid.png\" style=\"width: 26px; height: 26px;\" /></a></td>\n											<td>\n												<a href=\"http://www.researcherid.com/ProfileView.action?SID=P2kuQGYxkyrpJ1tyKI2&amp;returnCode=ROUTER.Success&amp;queryString=KG0UuZjN5WmZlFdP%252FqIpbTkk9zM0TtA40EwYW58wKzg%253D&amp;SrcApp=CR&amp;Init=Yes\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/RID.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n											<td>\n												<a href=\"https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Assumpcio_Bosch\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/researchgate.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n											<td>\n												<a href=\"https://es.linkedin.com/pub/assumpció-bosch/2b/b33/781\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Linkedin.jpg\" style=\"width: 35px; height: 29px;\" /> </a></td>\n										</tr>\n									</tbody>\n								</table>\n							</td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"https://es.linkedin.com/pub/assumpció-bosch/2b/b33/781\" target=\"_blank\"> </a></td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/_ABoschgrup2pendent.jpg\" style=\"width: 100%;\" /></p>\n<p>\n	<strong>Membres</strong></p>\n<div>\n	Bel&eacute;n Garc&iacute;a Lareu</div>\n<div>\n	Marc Leal Juli&agrave;</div>\n<div>\n	Rolando Szilveszter Matos</div>\n<div>\n	Meritxell Puig Ferrer</div>\n<div>\n	&Aacute;ngela S&aacute;nchez Osuna</div>\n<div>\n	&nbsp;</div>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>OBJECTIUS ESTRAT&Egrave;GICS</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	La recerca del nostre grup est&agrave; enfocada en el desenvolupament d&rsquo;estrat&egrave;gies de ter&agrave;pia g&egrave;nica per malalties que afecten el sistema nervi&oacute;s, tant a nivell central, com en el cas de les malalties lisosomals, com perif&egrave;ric, pel tractament del dolor, o de neuropaties tant de causa gen&egrave;tica com adquirides. Tamb&eacute; treballem en la recerca dels mecanismes moleculars implicats en el desenvolupament d&rsquo;aquestes patologies combinant la utilitzaci&oacute; de models animals, cultius cel&middot;lulars i vectors virals.</p>\n<p>\n	Finan&ccedil;ament: ISCIII; MINECO; EU; Feder-EU; AGAUR, Marat&oacute; TV3; Genzyme</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PRINCIPALS L&Iacute;NIES D&rsquo;INVESTIGACI&Oacute;</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	1) Estudi del tropisme de diferents vectors virals de ter&agrave;pia g&egrave;nica en el sistema nervi&oacute;s perif&egrave;ric.</p>\n<p>\n	La transfer&egrave;ncia g&egrave;nica al sistema nervi&oacute;s perif&egrave;ric presenta les seves dificultats degut a que inclou diferents tipus cel&middot;lulars, la majoria dels&nbsp; quals s&oacute;n post-mit&ograve;tics. Tanmateix, aconseguir una transfer&egrave;ncia g&egrave;nica eficient a alguns d&rsquo;aquests tipus cel&middot;lulars t&eacute; un especial inter&egrave;s pel tractament de malalties neurol&ograve;giques o per l&rsquo;alleujament del dolor cr&ograve;nic. A m&eacute;s a m&eacute;s, el suplement o la inhibici&oacute; de certes mol&egrave;cules utilitzant vectors virals poden ser &uacute;tils per analitzar els processos fisiol&ograve;gics en el sistema nervi&oacute;s perif&egrave;ric, per exemple les interaccions entre la glia i les neurones, el transport retr&ograve;grad o anter&ograve;grad , la regeneraci&oacute; nerviosa, etc. Amb aquest objectiu estem caracteritzant el tropisme de diferents pseudotips de vectors AAV i adenovirus humans i d&rsquo;altres esp&egrave;cies a trav&eacute;s de diverses vies d&rsquo;administraci&oacute;.</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	2) Ter&agrave;pia g&egrave;nica per les complicacions neurol&ograve;giques de la diabetis</p>\n<p>\n	Les complicacions de la diabetis impliquen tant components sensorimotors com aut&ograve;noms del sistema nervi&oacute;s perif&egrave;ric. La neuropatia sensoriomotora que desenvolupen els pacients diab&egrave;tics &eacute;s la neuropatia perif&egrave;rica m&eacute;s com&uacute; que afecta en diferents graus a tots els tipus de fibres nervioses i provoca la p&egrave;rdua de la sensaci&oacute; de dolor, sensaci&oacute; de cremor i hiperest&egrave;sia cut&agrave;nia, generalment a partir dels peus i la part inferior de les cames, per&ograve; que progressa a mans i bra&ccedil;os amb el temps. En etapes m&eacute;s avan&ccedil;ades, apareixen &uacute;lceres als peus i deformitats neurop&agrave;tiques, el que podria conduir a amputacions de les extremitats, el que representa un 40% de les amputacions no traum&agrave;tiques. La patologia de la neuropatia sensorimotora diab&egrave;tica es caracteritza per una atr&ograve;fia axonal i desmielinitzaci&oacute;, el que porta a la p&egrave;rdua de fibres nervioses seguit de la regeneraci&oacute; anormal d&#39;aquestes fibres. Tot i el tractament amb insulina o el trasplantament de p&agrave;ncrees, la progressi&oacute; de la neuropatia diab&egrave;tica no s&#39;atura, el que indica la necessitat d&#39;un tractament espec&iacute;fic en les primeres etapes de la diabetis. El nostre equip estudia els mecanismes moleculars que condueixen al desenvolupament de la neuropatia diab&egrave;tica, utilitzant cultius primaris de c&egrave;l&middot;lules i models de ratol&iacute; de la malaltia, amb l&#39;objectiu d&#39;elucidar noves dianes terap&egrave;utiques per a aquesta complicaci&oacute; de la diabetis. En m&eacute;s detall, estem estudiant l&#39;efecte de la hiperglic&egrave;mia en la desmielinitzaci&oacute; del PNS i el paper de factors tr&ograve;fics o d&#39;altres mol&egrave;cules implicades en la senyalitzaci&oacute; cel&middot;lular entre les neurones sensorials i les c&egrave;l&middot;lules de Schwann per estimular l&#39;expressi&oacute; de prote&iuml;nes de la mielina i la regeneraci&oacute; del sistema nervi&oacute;s perif&egrave;ric .</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	3) Tractament i estudi de la Mucopolisacaridosi tipus VII</p>\n<p>\n	La ter&agrave;pia g&egrave;nica &eacute;s un dels tractaments m&eacute;s prometedors per a les malalties que afecten el sistema nervi&oacute;s central ja que la barrera hematoencef&agrave;lica impedeix l&#39;administraci&oacute; de molts f&agrave;rmacs al par&egrave;nquima cerebral per via sist&egrave;mica. Actualment, ja hi ha en curs alguns assaigs cl&iacute;nics de ter&agrave;pia g&egrave;nica per al tractament d&#39;algunes malalties d&#39;emmagatzematge lisosomal amb afectaci&oacute; neuronal, que s&oacute;n malalties neurol&ograve;giques progressives que afecten als nens petits. No obstant aix&ograve;, el bon desenvolupament i l&#39;avaluaci&oacute; d&#39;aquestes ter&agrave;pies requereix la comprensi&oacute; de com les vies de senyalitzaci&oacute; cel&middot;lulars es veuen afectades en aquestes malalties i quin &eacute;s l&#39;impacte sobre la viabilitat o la funci&oacute; de les c&egrave;l&middot;lules dels pacients i particularment en les seves neurones. Altres &ograve;rgans com l&#39;os o el cor poden ser dif&iacute;cils de tractar, fins i tot amb els nivells d&#39;enzims s&egrave;rics elevats. El nostre equip de recerca est&agrave; posant especial atenci&oacute; en aquests teixits utilitzant un model mur&iacute; de Mucopolisacaridosis tipus VII.</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\"><strong>PUBLICACIONS REPRESENTATIVES</strong></span></p>\n<p>\n	&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;R. Thwaite, G. Pages, M. Chillon, and A. Bosch (<strong>2015</strong>).</p>\n<p>\n	<em>AAVrh.10 immunogenicity in mice and humans. relevance of antibody cross-reactivity in human gene therapy.</em></p>\n<p>\n	Gene Therapy: 22: 196-201</p>\n<p>\n	&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;L. Ariza, L. Gim&eacute;nez-Llort, A. Cubizolle, G. Pag&egrave;s, B. Garc&iacute;a-Lareu, N. Serratrice, D. Cots, M. Chillon, E. Kremer and A. Bosch (<strong>2014</strong>).</p>\n<p>\n	<em>CNS delivery of helper-dependent canine adenovirus corrects neuropathology and behavior in Mucopolysaccharidosis type VII mice.</em></p>\n<p>\n	Human Gene Therapy: 25(3):199-211</p>\n<p>\n	&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;L. Ariza, G. Pag&egrave;s, B. Garcia-Lareu, PJ Otaegui, J Ruberte, M. Chillon, X Navarro, A. Bosch (<strong>2014</strong>).</p>\n<p>\n	<em>Experimental diabetes in neonatal mice induces early peripheral sensorimotor neuropathy.</em></p>\n<p>\n	Neuroscience 274: 250-9; PMID: 24846610.</p>\n<p>\n	&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;J. Homs, G. Pag&egrave;s, L. Ariza, C. Casas, M. Chillon, X. Navarro, A. Bosch (<strong>2014</strong>).</p>\n<p>\n	<em>Intrathecal administration of IGF-I by AAVrh10 improves sensory and motor deficits in a mouse model of diabetic neuropathy.</em></p>\n<p>\n	Molec Ther-Meth &amp; Clin Dev 1, 7; doi:10.1038/mtm.2013.7.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;J. Homs, L. Ariza, G. Pag&egrave;s, E. Udina, X. Navarro, M. Chill&oacute;n, A. Bosch (<strong>2011</strong>).</p>\n<p>\n	<em>Schwann cell targeting via intrasciatic injection of AAV8 as gene therapy strategy for peripheral nerve regeneration.</em></p>\n<p>\n	Gene Therapy 18(6):622-30.</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/49708436/public/\">Veure m&eacute;s publicacions d&#39;A. Bosch a Pubmed</a></p>\n',100,2,0),(757,52,0,'Assumpció Bosch','<p>\n	<a href=\"http://inc.uab.cat/Catala/index.php#%21/%C3%80rees%20estrat%C3%A8giques%20de%20recerca_223_1\">N</a><a href=\"http://inc.uab.cat/Castellano/index.php#!/Áreas estrategicas de investigación_348_1\">euroregeneraci&oacute;n y reparaci&oacute;n</a></p>\n<h1>\n	<span style=\"color:#800000;\">Estrategias de Terapia G&eacute;nica para Neuropat&iacute;as</span></h1>\n<p>\n	<strong>L&iacute;der del grupo:</strong></p>\n<table height=\"116\" width=\"141\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				Assumpci&oacute; Bosch</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				TEL: +34 93 581 4203</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<a href=\"mailto:Assumpcio.Bosch@uab.cat\">Assumpcio.Bosch@uab.cat</a></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n				<table height=\"36\" width=\"66\">\n					<tbody>\n						<tr>\n							<td>\n								<table height=\"63\" width=\"176\">\n									<tbody>\n										<tr>\n											<td>\n												<a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0002-7205-2796\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/orcid.png\" style=\"width: 26px; height: 26px;\" /></a></td>\n											<td>\n												<a href=\"http://www.researcherid.com/ProfileView.action?SID=P2kuQGYxkyrpJ1tyKI2&amp;returnCode=ROUTER.Success&amp;queryString=KG0UuZjN5WmZlFdP%252FqIpbTkk9zM0TtA40EwYW58wKzg%253D&amp;SrcApp=CR&amp;Init=Yes\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/RID.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n											<td>\n												<a href=\"https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Assumpcio_Bosch\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/researchgate.jpg\" style=\"width: 25px; height: 25px;\" /></a></td>\n											<td>\n												<a href=\"https://es.linkedin.com/pub/assumpci%C3%B3-bosch/2b/b33/781\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Linkedin.jpg\" style=\"width: 35px; height: 29px;\" /> </a></td>\n										</tr>\n									</tbody>\n								</table>\n							</td>\n							<td>\n								<a href=\"https://es.linkedin.com/pub/assumpci%C3%B3-bosch/2b/b33/781\" target=\"_blank\"> </a></td>\n						</tr>\n					</tbody>\n				</table>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/_ABoschgrup2pendent.jpg\" style=\"width: 100%;\" /></p>\n<p>\n	<strong>Miembros</strong></p>\n<div>\n	Bel&eacute;n Garc&iacute;a Lareu</div>\n<div>\n	Marc Leal Juli&agrave;</div>\n<div>\n	Rolando Szilveszter Matos</div>\n<div>\n	Meritxell Puig Ferrer</div>\n<div>\n	&Aacute;ngela S&aacute;nchez Osuna</div>\n<div>\n	&nbsp;</div>\n<p>\n	OBJETIVOS ESTRAT&Eacute;GICOS</p>\n<p>\n	La investigaci&oacute;n de nuestro grupo est&aacute; enfocada en el desarrollo de estrategias de terapia g&eacute;nica para enfermedades que afectan al sistema nervioso, tanto a nivel central, como en el caso de las enfermedades lisosomales, como perif&eacute;rico, para el tratamiento del dolor, o de neuropat&iacute;as tanto de causa gen&eacute;tica como adquiridas. Tambi&eacute;n trabajamos en la investigaci&oacute;n de los mecanismos moleculares implicados en el desarrollo de estas patolog&iacute;as combinando el uso de modelos animales, cultivos celulares y vectores virales.</p>\n<p>\n	Financiaci&oacute;n: ISCIII; MINECO; EU; Feder-EU; AGAUR, Marat&oacute; TV3; Genzyme.</p>\n<p>\n	PRINCIPALES L&Iacute;NEAS DE INVESTIGACI&Oacute;N</p>\n<p>\n	1) Estudio del tropismo de distintos vectores virales de terapia g&eacute;nica en el sistema nervioso perif&eacute;rico.</p>\n<p>\n	La transferencia g&eacute;nica al sistema nervioso perif&eacute;rico presenta sus dificultades debido a que incluye diferentes tipos celulares, la mayor&iacute;a de los cuales son post-mit&oacute;ticos. Asimismo, conseguir una transferencia g&eacute;nica eficiente en algunos de estos tipos celulares tiene un especial inter&eacute;s para el tratamiento de enfermedades neurol&oacute;gicas o para una mejora del dolor cr&oacute;nico. Adem&aacute;s, el suplemento o la inhibici&oacute;n de ciertas mol&eacute;culas usando vectores virales pueden ser &uacute;tiles para analizar los procesos fisiol&oacute;gicos en el sistema nervioso perif&eacute;rico, por ejemplo las interacciones entre la gl&iacute;a y las neuronas, el transporte retr&oacute;grado o anter&oacute;grado, la regeneraci&oacute;n nerviosa, etc. Con este objetivo estamos caracterizando el tropismo de distintos pseudotipos de vectores AVV y adenovirus humanos y de otras especias a trav&eacute;s de diversas v&iacute;as de administraci&oacute;n.</p>\n<p>\n	2) Terapia g&eacute;nica para las complicaciones neurol&oacute;gicas de la diabetes</p>\n<p>\n	Las complicaciones de la diabetes implican tanto componentes sensorimotores como aut&oacute;nomos del sistema nervioso perif&eacute;rico. La neuropat&iacute;a sensoriomotora que desarrollan los pacientes diab&eacute;ticos es la neuropat&iacute;a perif&eacute;rica m&aacute;s com&uacute;n que afecta en distintos grados a todos los tipos de fibras nerviosas y provoca la p&eacute;rdida de la sensaci&oacute;n de dolor, sensaci&oacute;n de quemaz&oacute;n e hiperestesia cut&aacute;nea, generalmente a partir de los pies y la parte inferior de las piernas, pero que progresa a manos y brazos con el tiempo. En etapas m&aacute;s avanzadas, aparecen &uacute;lceras en los pies y deformidades neurop&aacute;ticas, lo que podr&iacute;a conducir a amputaciones de las extremidades, que representan un 40% de las amputaciones no traum&aacute;ticas. La patolog&iacute;a de la neuropat&iacute;a sensorimotora diab&eacute;tica se caracteriza por una atrofia axonal y desmielinizaci&oacute;n, lo que lleva a la p&eacute;rdida de fibras nerviosas seguido de la regeneraci&oacute;n anormal de estas fibras. Aun con el tratamiento con insulina o el trasplante de p&aacute;ncreas, la progresi&oacute;n de la neuropat&iacute;a diab&eacute;tica no se para, lo que indica la necesidad de un tratamiento espec&iacute;fico en las primeras etapas de la diabetes. Nuestro equipo estudia los mecanismos moleculares que conducen al desarrollo de la neuropat&iacute;a diab&eacute;tica, usando cultivos primarios de c&eacute;lulas y modelos de rat&oacute;n de la enfermedad, con el objetivo de elucidar nuevas dianas terap&eacute;uticas para esta complicaci&oacute;n de la diabetes. En m&aacute;s detalle, estamos estudiando el efecto de la hiperglicemia en la desmielinizaci&oacute;n del PNS y el papel de factores tr&oacute;ficos o de otras mol&eacute;culas implicadas en la se&ntilde;alizaci&oacute;n celular entre las neuronas sensoriales y las c&eacute;lulas de Schwann para estimular la expresi&oacute;n de prote&iacute;nas de la mielina y la regeneraci&oacute;n del sistema nervioso perif&eacute;rico.</p>\n<p>\n	3) Tratamiento y estudio de la Mucopolisacaridosis tipo VII</p>\n<p>\n	La terapia g&eacute;nica es uno de los tratamientos m&aacute;s prometedores para las enfermedades que afectan al sistema nervioso central ya que la barrera hematoencef&aacute;lica impide la administraci&oacute;n de muchos f&aacute;rmacos al par&eacute;nquima cerebral por v&iacute;a sistem&aacute;tica. Actualmente, ya hay en curso algunos ensayos cl&iacute;nicos de terapia g&eacute;nica para el tratamiento de algunas enfermedades de almacenamiento lisosomal con afectaci&oacute;n neuronal, que son enfermedades neurol&oacute;gicas progresivas que afectan a los ni&ntilde;os peque&ntilde;os. No obstante, el buen desarrollo y evaluaci&oacute;n de estas terapias requiere la comprensi&oacute;n de c&oacute;mo las v&iacute;as de se&ntilde;alizaci&oacute;n celulares se ven afectadas en estas enfermedades y cu&aacute;l es el impacto sobre la viabilidad o la funci&oacute;n de las c&eacute;lulas de los pacientes y particularmente en sus neuronas. Otros &oacute;rganos como el hueso o el coraz&oacute;n pueden ser dif&iacute;ciles de tratar, hasta con niveles de enzimas s&eacute;ricos elevados. Nuestro equipo de investigaci&oacute;n est&aacute; poniendo especial atenci&oacute;n en estos tejidos usando un modelo murino de&nbsp; Mucopolisacaridosis tipo VII.</p>\n<p>\n	PUBLICACIONES REPRESENTATIVAS</p>\n<p>\n	&bull; R. Thwaite, G. Pages, M. Chillon, and A. Bosch (2015)</p>\n<p>\n	<em>AAVrh.10 immunogenicity in mice and humans. relevance of antibody cross-reactivity in human gene therapy</em></p>\n<p>\n	Gene Therapy: 22: 196-201</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	&bull; L. Ariza, L. Gim&eacute;nez-Llort, A. Cubizolle, G. Pag&egrave;s, B. Garc&iacute;a-Lareu, N. Serratrice, D. Cots, M. Chillon, E. Kremer and A. Bosch (2014)</p>\n<p>\n	<em>CNS delivery of helper-dependent canine adenovirus corrects neuropathology and behavior in Mucopolysaccharidosis type VII mice</em></p>\n<p>\n	Human Gene Therapy: 25(3):199-211</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	&bull; L. Ariza, G. Pag&egrave;s, B. Garcia-Lareu, PJ Otaegui, J Ruberte, M. Chillon, X Navarro, A. Bosch (2014).</p>\n<p>\n	<em>Experimental diabetes in neonatal mice induces early peripheral sensorimotor neuropathy.</em></p>\n<p>\n	Neuroscience 274: 250-9; PMID: 24846610.</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	&bull; J. Homs, G. Pag&egrave;s, L. Ariza, C. Casas, M. Chillon, X. Navarro, A. Bosch (2014).</p>\n<p>\n	<em>Intrathecal administration of IGF-I by AAVrh10 improves sensory and motor deficits in a mouse model of diabetic neuropathy.</em></p>\n<p>\n	Molec Ther-Meth &amp; Clin Dev 1, 7; doi:10.1038/mtm.2013.7. &nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	&bull; J. Homs, L. Ariza, G. Pag&egrave;s, E. Udina, X. Navarro, M. Chill&oacute;n, A. Bosch (2011).</p>\n<p>\n	<em>Schwann cell targeting via intrasciatic injection of AAV8 as gene therapy strategy for peripheral nerve regeneration.</em></p>\n<p>\n	Gene Therapy 18(6):622-30.</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/myncbi/14Q9ynJ9y7CAT/collections/49708436/public/\" target=\"_blank\">Ver m&aacute;s publicaciones de A. Bosch en Pubmed</a></p>\n',97,2,1),(758,29,0,'Meet the speackers: Núria Sebastián','<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Galles_NuriaSebastina_small.jpg\" style=\"width: 160px;\" /></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	Va rebre el seu doctorat en Psicologia experimental a la UB (Universitat de Barcelona) a l&rsquo;any 1986. Despr&eacute;s de realitzar la formaci&oacute; postdoctoral a l&rsquo;Institut Max Planck (Munich) i al CNRS (Paris), es va incorporar com a professora a la UB. A l&rsquo;any 2009 es va traslladar a la UPF (Universitat Pompeu Fabra) on ara dirigeix el grup d&rsquo;investigaci&oacute; SAP (Speech Acquisition and Processing) a la Unitat de Cognici&oacute; i Cervell. La seva investigaci&oacute; es centra en el proc&eacute;s d&rsquo;aprenentatge de lleng&uuml;es , especialment en les poblacions bilingues.&nbsp; Ha sigut reconeguda a nivell internacional amb el premi de la Fundaci&oacute; James S. McDonell (Bridging Mind, Brain and Behaviour Program) al 2001 i impartint les prestigioses Nijmegen Lectures al 2005. Ha sigut Professora Visitant a varis centres d&rsquo;investigaci&oacute;, incloent el IRCS a la Universitat de Pennsylvania, el ICN al University College (Londres) i a la Universitat de Chicago (2010). Als anys 2009 i 2014 li han atorgat el premi Academia de ICREA. Ha sigut presidenta de la Societat Europea de Psicologia Cognitiva i es vicepresidenta del Consell Europeu d&rsquo;Investigaci&oacute;.</p>\n',101,2,0),(759,51,0,'Meet the speakers: Núria Sebastián','<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Galles_NuriaSebastina_small.jpg\" style=\"width: 160px; height: 213px;\" /></p>\n<p>\n	Recibi&oacute; su doctorado en Psicolog&iacute;a experimental en la UB (Universidad de Barcelona) en el a&ntilde;o 1986. Despu&eacute;s de realizar la formaci&oacute;n postdoctoral en el Instituto Max Planck (M&uacute;nich) y en el CNRS (Paris), se incorpor&oacute; como profesora en la UB. En el a&ntilde;o 2009 se traslad&oacute; a la UPF (Universidad Pompeu Fabra) donde ahora dirige el grupo de investigaci&oacute;n SAP (Speech Acquisition and Processing) en la Unidad de Cognici&oacute;n y Cerebro. Su investigaci&oacute;n se centra en el proceso de aprendizaje de las lenguas, especialmente en las poblaciones biling&uuml;es. Ha sido reconocida a nivel internacional con el premio de la Fundaci&oacute;n James S. McDonell (Bridging Mind, Brain and Behaviour Program) en el 2001 e impartiendo las prestigiosas Nijmegen Lectures en el 2005. Ha sido Profesora Visitante a varios centros de investigaci&oacute;n, incluyendo el IRCS a la Universidad de Pennsylvania, el ICN al University College (Londres) y en la Universidad de Chicago (2010). &nbsp;En los a&ntilde;os 2009 y 2014 se le ha otorgado el premio Academia de ICREA. Ha sido presidenta de la Sociedad Europea de Psicolog&iacute;a Cognitiva y es vicepresidenta del Consejo Europeo de Investigaci&oacute;n.</p>\n',98,2,1),(760,44,0,'Meet the speakers: Núria Sebastián','<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/Galles_NuriaSebastina_small.jpg\" style=\"width: 160px; height: 213px;\" /></p>\n<p>\n	She received her doctorate in Experimental Psychology at the UB (University of Barcelona) in the year 1986. After receiving her postdoctoral training at the Max Planck Institute (Munich) and at the CNRS (Paris), she became a Professor at the UB. In 2009, she transferred to the UPF (University Pompeu Fabra) where she now directs the research group SAP (Speech Acquisition and Processing) in the Cognition and Brain Unit. Her research is centred on the process of learning languages, especially in bilingual populations. She has been recognised on an international level with the James S. McDonell Foundation prize (Bridging Mind, Brain and Behaviour Program) in 2001 and also having given the prestigious Nijmegen Lectures in 2005. She has been a Visiting Scholar at several research Centres, including the IRCS at Univ. of Pennsylvania, the ICN at the Univ. College (London) and the University of Chicago (in 2010).In the years 2009 and 2014 she was granted the Academia award from ICREA. She has been president of the European Society of Cognitive Psychology and is vice-president of the European Research Council. &nbsp;</p>\n',97,2,2),(761,29,0,'Meet the speakers: Ramon Trullàs','<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/903_ImageInvestigator_trullas_118.jpg\" style=\"width: 118px; height: 156px;\" /></p>\n<p>\n	Va obtenir el doctorat en psicologia a la UAB amb una tesis sobre el mecanisme d&rsquo;acci&oacute; dels f&agrave;rmacs antidepressius, que va rebre el premi de doctorat de la UAB amb distinci&oacute; especial. Va realitzar investigaci&oacute; postdoctoral al Laboratori de Qu&iacute;mica Bio-Org&agrave;nica, NIDDK, dels Instituts Nacionals de Salud a Bethesda, MD, EEUU des del 1985 al 1988 i va continuar com a investigador associat al Laboratori de Neuroci&egrave;ncia (NIDDK, NIH) del 1988 al 1991. Ha sigut coordinador de l&rsquo;&agrave;rea de Fisiologia i Farmacologia de l&rsquo;Agencia Nacional d&rsquo;Avaluaci&oacute; i Prospectiva (ANEP) (2005-2009) i membre del Consell Cient&iacute;fic Assessor d&rsquo; ErasysBio ERANET de Biologia de Sistemes de la Comissi&oacute; Europea (2009-2013). Actualment, es Professor d&rsquo;Investigaci&oacute; l&rsquo;Institut d&rsquo;Investigacions Biom&egrave;diques de Barcelona (IIBB/CSIC/IDIBAPS) i L&iacute;der de grup al CIBERNED. Des del 2011 es Editor Acad&egrave;mic de PLoSONE. Els seus interessos cient&iacute;fics inclouen la investigaci&oacute; dels mecanismes moleculars de la neurodegeneraci&oacute; i la plasticitat neuronal; l&rsquo;estudi de la funci&oacute; din&agrave;mica mitocondrial en neurones i l&rsquo;an&agrave;lisi de biomarcadors en la malaltia d&rsquo;Alzheimer amb l&rsquo;objectiu d&rsquo;identificar nous tractaments terap&egrave;utics.</p>\n',102,2,0),(762,29,0,'Meet the speakers: Miquel Vila','<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/vila miquel.jpg\" style=\"width: 150px; height: 179px;\" /></p>\n<p>\n	Va acabar el seu doctorat en medicina a la UB al 1993. Llavors es va traslladar al Laboratori de Neurologia Experimental i Terap&egrave;utica a l&rsquo;Hospital Salp&ecirc;tri&egrave;re a Paris, on va obtenir el seu M&agrave;ster i postdoctorat en neuroci&egrave;ncia de la Universitat de Paris VI (Pierre et Marie Curie). La seva feina postdoctoral es centrava en l&rsquo;estudi de les conseq&uuml;&egrave;ncies funcionals de la degeneraci&oacute; dopamin&egrave;rgica sobre la funcionalitat del gangli basal. Del 1998 al 2001, va treballar com a investigador postdoctoral al Departament de Neurologia, Divisi&oacute; de Trastorns del Moviment a La Universitat de Columbia (Nova York, EEUU), estudiant els mecanismes moleculars de la mort neuronal en la malaltia de Parkinson. Al 2001, va obtenir la posici&oacute; de Professor Ajudant de Neurologia a la Universitat de Columbia. Despr&eacute;s, al desembre 2005, va tornar a Barcelona com a investigador ICREA per desenvolupar un nou laboratori de recerca de Neurodegeneraci&oacute; a la Vall d&rsquo;Hebron Institut de Recerca, gr&agrave;cies al suport del programa de beques d&rsquo;excel&middot;l&egrave;ncia Marie Curie de la Comissi&oacute; Europea. Tamb&eacute; es professor associat de la UAB i Investigador Principal al CIBERNED.</p>\n',103,2,0),(763,51,0,'Meet the speakers: Ramon Trullàs','<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/903_ImageInvestigator_trullas_118.jpg\" style=\"width: 118px; height: 156px;\" /></p>\n<p>\n	Obtuvo el doctorado en Psicolog&iacute;a en la UAB con una tesis sobre el mecanismo de acci&oacute;n de los f&aacute;rmacos antidepresivos que recibi&oacute; el premio de doctorado de la UAB con distinci&oacute;n especial. Realiz&oacute; investigaci&oacute;n postdoctoral en el Laboratorio de Qu&iacute;mica Bio-Org&aacute;nica, NIDDK, de los Institutos Nacionales de la Salud en Bethesda, MD, EE.UU desde el a&ntilde;o 1985 hasta 1988 y continu&oacute; como investigador asociado en el Laboratorio de Neurociencia (NIDDK, NIH) desde 1988 hasta 1991. Ha sido coordinador del &aacute;rea de Fisiolog&iacute;a y Farmacolog&iacute;a de la Agencia Nacional de Evaluaci&oacute;n y Prospectiva (ANEP) (2005-2009) y miembro del Consejo Cient&iacute;fico Asesor de ErasysBio ERANET de Biolog&iacute;a de Sistemas de la Comisi&oacute;n Europea (2009-2013). Actualmente es Profesor de Investigaci&oacute;n en el Instituto de Investigaciones Biom&eacute;dicas de Barcelona (IIBB / CSIC / IDIBAPS) y jefe de grupo en CIBERNED. Desde 2011 es Editor Acad&eacute;mico de PLoSONE. Sus intereses cient&iacute;ficos incluyen la investigaci&oacute;n de los mecanismos moleculares de la neurodegeneraci&oacute;n y la plasticidad neuronal; el estudio de la funci&oacute;n de la din&aacute;mica mitocondrial en neuronas y el an&aacute;lisis de biomarcadores en la enfermedad de Alzheimer con el objetivo de identificar nuevos tratamientos terap&eacute;uticos.</p>\n',99,2,1),(764,51,0,'Meet the speakers: Miquel Vila','<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/vila miquel.jpg\" style=\"width: 150px; height: 179px;\" /></p>\n<p>\n	Acab&oacute; su doctorado en medicina en la UB en el 1993. Luego se traslad&oacute; al Laboratorio de Neurolog&iacute;a Experimental y Terap&eacute;utica en el Hospital Salp&ecirc;tri&egrave;re en Paris, donde obtuvo su M&aacute;ster y postdoctorado en neurociencia de la Universidad de Paris VI (Pierre et Marie Curie). Su trabajo postdoctoral se centraba en el estudio de las consecuencias funcionales de la degeneraci&oacute;n dopamin&eacute;rgica sobre la funcionalidad del ganglio basal. Del 1998 al 2001, trabaj&oacute; como investigador postdoctoral en el Departamento de Neurolog&iacute;a, Divisi&oacute;n de Trastornos del Movimiento en la Universidad de Columbia (Nueva York, EEUU), estudiando los mecanismos moleculares de la muerte neuronal en la enfermedad de Parkinson. En el 2001, obtuvo la posici&oacute;n de Profesor Ayudante de Neurolog&iacute;a en la Universidad de Columbia. Despu&eacute;s, en diciembre 2005, volvi&oacute; a Barcelona como investigador ICREA para desarrollar un nuevo laboratorio de investigaci&oacute;n de Neurodegeneraci&oacute;n en la Vall d&rsquo;Hebron Instituto de Investigaci&oacute;n, gracias al soporte del programa de becas de excelencia Marie Curie de la Comisi&oacute;n Europea. Tambi&eacute;n es profesor asociado de la UAB e Investigador Principal en el CIBERNED.</p>\n',100,2,1),(765,44,0,'Meet the speakers: Ramon Trullàs','<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/903_ImageInvestigator_trullas_118.jpg\" style=\"width: 118px; height: 156px;\" /></p>\n<p>\n	He obtained his Ph.D. degree in Psychology from the UAB with a thesis on the mechanism of action of antidepressant drugs, which merited a doctoral award with special distinction. He served as a Postdoctoral Fellow at the Laboratory of Bio?Organic Chemistry, NIDDK, NIH in Bethesda, MD, USA from 1985 to 1988 and continued as a Visiting Associate at the Laboratory of Neuroscience, NIDDK, NIH from 1988 to 1991. He has been Chairman of the National Physiology and Pharmacology Grant Evaluation Program (ANEP) 2005?2008 and member of the Scientific Advisory Board of EraysBio ERA?NET for Systems Biology of European Commission. Currently, he serves as a Professor of Research and Head of the Neurobiology Unit at the Institute for Biomedical Research of Barcelona (IIBB/CSIC/IDIBAPS) and as Group Leader at CIBERNED (Centre for Research on Neurodegenerative Diseases). From 2011 he has been the Academic Editor of PLoSONE. His scientific interests include researching molecular mechanisms of neurodegeneration and neuronal plasticity; the study of the functions of mitochondrial dynamics in neurones and the analysis of biomarkers in Alzheimer&rsquo;s disease with the objective of identifying new therapeutic treatments.</p>\n',98,2,2),(766,44,0,'Meet the speakers: Miquel Vila','<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/vila miquel.jpg\" style=\"width: 150px; height: 179px;\" /></p>\n<p>\n	He received his M.D. from the University of Barcelona Medical School in 1993. He then moved to the laboratory of Experimental Neurology and Therapeutics, at the Salp&ecirc;tri&egrave;re Hospital in Paris, where he obtained his Master degree and Ph.D. in Neuroscience from the University of Paris VI (Pierre et Marie Curie). His Ph.D. work was devoted to the study of the functional consequences of dopaminergic neurodegeneration on the functioning of the basal ganglia. From 1998 to 2001, he worked as a postdoctoral researcher in the Department of Neurology, Movement Disorders Division, at Columbia University (New York, USA), focusing on the molecular mechanisms of neuronal death in Parkinson&#39;s disease. In 2001 he obtained a position as an Assistant Professor of Neurology at Columbia University. Then, in December 2005, he moved back to Barcelona as an ICREA Research Professor to develop a new research lab on Neurodegeneration at the Vall d&rsquo;Hebron Research Institute, thanks to the support of the European Commission&rsquo;s Marie Curie Excellence Grants program. He also holds positions as Associate Professor at the UAB and as Principal Investigator at the CIBERNED</p>\n',99,2,2),(767,29,0,'Visita del Comitè Científic Extern','<p>\n	Els propers dies 11, 12 i 13 de maig l&rsquo;INc tindr&agrave; l&rsquo;honor de rebre la visita dels membres del seu&nbsp;Comit&egrave; cient&iacute;fic extern. Aquest comit&egrave; est&agrave; format per eminents investigadors en el nostre camp de recerca:</p>\n<table align=\"center\" border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" height=\"849\" width=\"402\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"text-align: center; vertical-align: top; width: 150px;\">\n				<p>\n					<img alt=\"\" src=\"/DocsCKeditor/images/FAWCETT end.jpg\" style=\"wid